description: Amelia Holowaty Krales is a senior photo editor who loves using a toaster oven for its compact size, speed, and versatility in cooking various dishes. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: EMMA ROTH
description: Emma Roth is a news writer who uses a FoodSaver vacuum sealer to keep food fresh and save space in the fridge or freezer. She shops at wholesale clubs and buys meat in bulk. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: FOODSAVER
description: FoodSaver is a brand that produces vacuum sealers, which help keep raw meat and other food fresher for longer in the fridge and save space in the freezer by making packages flatter when all the air is sucked out of them. The FoodSaver vacuum sealer can vacuum up all the air and then close the bag using its heat sealing feature in one fell swoop [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: LUMESNER CARRY-ON BACKPACK
description: The Lumesner carry-on backpack is a travel bag that can carry a laptop, several days' worth of clothes, a 40oz Hydro Flask bottle, and more. It includes some packing cubes, is very comfortable, and the weight is well distributed when it's completely full. It's an inexpensive alternative to many name-brand carry-on bags and has held up in quality after being used on a handful of trips [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: ANKER 321 POWER STRIP
description: The Anker 321 Power Strip is a device that boasts three AC outlets, two USB-A ports, and one USB-C port. It is currently on sale for $15 at Amazon and is recommended by Sarah Jeong as a useful device for travelers staying in older buildings [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: ELECTRICAL SOCKET
description: The only electrical socket in the bedroom is in the corner farthest away from the bed and is already occupied by two lamps. This issue is more prevalent in older buildings due to loose socket syndrome, where modern socket extenders with multiple USB and USB-C charging ports cannot stay in place because they are too heavy.[]

name: LOOSE SOCKET SYNDROME
description: Loose socket syndrome refers to the issue where modern socket extenders with multiple USB and USB-C charging ports cannot stay in place in older buildings because they are too heavy.[]

name: ANKER COMBINATION EXTENSION CORD / POWER STRIP
description: The Anker combination extension cord / power strip is a solution to the loose socket syndrome. It is a cube with a few sockets along with USB and USB-C charging ports at the end of a five-foot cable. It has been used and found effective by the author during their travels.[]

name: BRANDON WIDDER
description: Brandon Widder, a senior commerce editor with a keen interest in technology and its practical applications, recently shared his insights on the Sonos Roam, a portable smart speaker that he has been using. In addition to his audio experiences, Widder also expressed his preference for ambient lighting, particularly highlighting his recent purchase of MPOWERD's string lights. These lights have become an essential addition to his gear for car camping and backcountry trips, enhancing the atmosphere and functionality of his outdoor adventures. As of 2023-11-24, Widder's expertise and personal experiences in the tech and entertainment space continue to inform and enrich his contributions to The Verge, where he shares valuable insights with the community.

name: ULTIMATE EARS ROLL 2
description: The Ultimate Ears Roll 2 was the author's go-to portable speaker for camping and backpacking before purchasing the Sonos Roam. It was small and efficient but did not mesh well with the rest of the author's audio setup.[]

name: EPICKA UNIVERSAL TRAVEL ADAPTER
description: Epicka's universal travel adapter is an all-in-one adapter that includes four different plugs covering over 150 countries, comes with USB ports for charging multiple devices, and includes a spare fuse for voltage issues [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: AMAZON
description:
Amazon, a multinational technology and e-commerce powerhouse, has a vast presence across multiple sectors, including robotics, smart home devices, entertainment, and online retail. The company is significantly invested in robotics, developing advanced systems like Proteus, Sequoia, and bipedal robots from Agility to enhance safety and productivity in its operations. Utilizing generative AI in its robotics lab, Amazon has improved the design and functionality of its robots, making them more adept at handling various tasks such as picking up objects and managing material flow. With over 750,000 mobile robots and thousands of other robotic systems integrated into its operations, Amazon has managed to reduce the recordable injury rate by 15% in 2022 compared to manual buildings. Its fleet of robots, including the Robin fleet, has inducted over 2 billion packages, and the company is now focusing on mobile manipulation, which involves mounting an arm to an autonomous mobile robot (AMR) to manipulate objects.

Amazon hosts several sales events, including Prime Day, Black Friday, and Cyber Monday, offering deals on a wide range of products, from tech gadgets to gaming headsets and video games. Some deals are exclusive to Prime members, and the company's extended return policy for most items purchased between Nov. 1 and Dec. 31 allows returns until Jan. 31, 2024, except for Apple-brand products which can only be returned until Jan. 15, 2024. Amazon Prime members enjoy perks such as free shipping, special prices, and early access to Black Friday deals.

In the smart glasses category, Amazon produces devices like the Echo Frames, Echo Buds, and Echo Show, which were featured in The Verge's 2023 holiday gift guide for kids. The company has introduced a new feature called "Explore with Alexa" for its Echo devices, allowing children under the age of 13 to have interactive conversations with an AI-powered Alexa in a protected and safe manner. This feature is part of the Amazon Kids+ content subscription and uses AI to generate trivia questions and facts based on trusted content, making the experience more interactive and fun for children.

Amazon operates an online marketplace where it sells products and provides a platform for third-party sellers. The company is also an alternative to Discogs, offering a large user base and solid infrastructure for sellers. Amazon is the third largest and fastest growing advertising business in the world, with

name: MPOWERD SOLAR-POWERED LUCI LANTERNS
description: MPOWERD's solar-powered Luci lanterns are a product that Brandon Widder, a senior commerce editor, has long been a proponent of for ambient lighting in remote areas [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: MPOWERD STRING LIGHTS
description: MPOWERD's string lights are a product that Brandon Widder recently picked up for car camping and backcountry trips, featuring 100-lumen LEDs, six color options, and a 2,000mAh battery for emergency charging [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: STRING LIGHTS
description: The 18-foot string lights are a product designed for car camping and backcountry trips, featuring 100-lumen LEDs, six different color options, a 2,000mAh battery, and the ability to charge via USB or solar [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: MEMORY CARD HOLDER AND READER
description: A memory card holder and reader is a gadget that consolidates SD cards and a card reader in one place, includes a carabiner hook, and is priced at $39.95 [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: ATUMTEK 60-INCH SELF-STICK TRIPOD
description: Atumtek’s 60-inch Self-Stick Tripod is a Bluetooth-enabled tripod that can be used as a mobile stand for taking group photographs or as a selfie stick, extending up to 60 inches and featuring a detachable Bluetooth shutter remote [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: CAR-FRIENDLY CHARGER
description: A car-friendly charger is a device that can charge phones in cars, potentially related to Apple's MagSafe charging ecosystem [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: RECENTLY
description: Recently refers to the time when the string lights were picked up for car camping and backcountry trips, and when the memory card holder and reader was gifted [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: BECCA FARSACE
description: Becca Farsace, a prominent figure at The Verge, is recognized for her dual expertise as both a camera expert and a senior producer. In her role as a camera expert, she has provided valuable insights on the quality of photos and videos captured by the innovative Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses, offering readers a professional perspective on the latest technology in wearable cameras. As a senior producer, Becca has demonstrated an appreciation for practical and efficient gear, as evidenced by her enthusiasm for a memory card holder and reader she received as a birthday gift in 2023. This gadget, according to her, serves as an excellent tool for consolidating various memory cards, making it a useful accessory for professionals in the tech and entertainment industry who often deal with multiple devices and storage solutions. Becca's insights at The Verge highlight her deep understanding of both the technical aspects of photography and videography and the practical needs of content creators in the field.

name: VJERAN PAVIC
description: Vjeran Pavic is The Verge’s supervising producer who gifted Becca Farsace a memory card holder and reader [The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: SEAN HOLLISTER
description: Sean Hollister, a senior editor with a keen eye for tech trends, has recommended the iOttie Easy One Touch Qi as a car-friendly charger. This suggestion comes amidst discussions about the evolving charging ecosystem, particularly in relation to Apple's MagSafe technology. Hollister highlights the iOttie charger for its practical design and its ability to provide high-speed charging, making it an ideal choice for tech-savvy individuals who spend a significant amount of time on the road. The recommendation underscores Hollister's expertise in identifying gadgets that not only meet the demands of modern technology but also cater to the specific needs of users in various environments, such as in their cars.

name: IOTTIE EASY ONE TOUCH QI
description: The iOttie Easy One Touch Qi is a car-friendly charger that uses the Qi charging standard, featuring a spring-loaded mechanism to securely hold phones and charge them at high speeds[]

name: BABOON TO THE MOON 3L FANNYPACK
description: The Baboon to the Moon 3L Fannypack is a colorful and durable fanny pack that fits essentials like a wallet, phone, keys, and more, with a quick-release buckle and space for a water bottle[]

name: CHOMCHOM PET HAIR REMOVER
description: The ChomChom PET Hair Remover is a reusable device expertly crafted to tackle the persistent issue of pet hair on various surfaces. This innovative tool is particularly effective in removing cat and dog hair from furniture, making it a must-have for pet owners. During the Black Friday sale, the ChomChom PET Hair Remover was available at a competitive price of $25, making it an affordable solution for managing pet hair. This device can also be purchased at Amazon for the same price, offering convenience and accessibility to customers.

name: BLACK FRIDAY SALES
description: Black Friday sales are an annual event where various products, including devices and accessories, are offered at discounted prices[]

name: MITCHELL CLARK
description: Mitchell Clark, a former news writer at The Verge, leverages his expertise in technology and entertainment to provide insights on various gadgets. One such product he has shared his experience with is the ChomChom pet hair remover, demonstrating his continued engagement with technology even after his tenure at The Verge.

name: ELIZABETH LOPATTO
description: Elizabeth Lopatto is a senior reporter at The Verge who purchased a fuzzy cat bed for her cat, Jeeves[]

name: FUZZY CAT BED
description: The fuzzy cat bed is a cozy pet bed that eventually became the favorite resting place for Elizabeth Lopatto's cat, Jeeves[]

name: PET FIT FOR LIFE PLUSH WAND
description: The Pet Fit For Life Plush Wand is a versatile dog toy designed to offer enrichment and entertainment to pets, even in the absence of their owners' undivided attention. This toy features a plush component attached to a long, chewable rope that is suspended from a sturdy metal pole, facilitating interactive play and chase sessions. It has gained recognition for its ability to effectively distract and engage dogs, as evidenced by its use with Kaitlin Hatton's dog, Trudee. The Pet Fit For Life Plush Wand was notably mentioned in relation to Black Friday sales, indicating its popularity and the potential for savings during this retail event.

name: VERGE DEALS
description: Verge Deals is a service initiated by The Verge, a leading technology and entertainment news source, that operates on X (formerly known as Twitter) and through email newsletters. As of 2023-12-24, Verge Deals has a strong presence on X with over 51,000 followers who receive daily updates on the best tech deals. Additionally, Verge Deals sends out a daily newsletter to its subscribers, featuring deals on products that have been tested and reviewed by The Verge's team. This ensures that subscribers are provided with reliable and high-quality product recommendations. The service has been consistently active, as noted in updates from The Verge on 2023-10-10, 2023-11-24, and 2023-12-24, making it a trusted source for tech enthusiasts seeking great deals.

name: TRUDEE
description: Trudee is a dog who requires undivided attention from her owner to play. With the Pet Fit For Life Plush Wand, Trudee is able to play and chase the toy, even when her owner is not making direct eye contact. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-24]

name: DIANE BAZELLA
description: Diane Bazella, a 64-year-old woman from Minnetonka, Minnesota, was switched at birth and spent nearly four decades searching for her biological family. Originally named Kelly Jean, she was later identified as Dawn Marie. In 2017, Bazella took a home DNA test which set her on the path to discovering her true identity and finding her birth mother, Sherri Nordlie Geerts, in 2021. The reunion brought Diane immense joy and peace, especially during the Christmas holiday, as she was finally able to establish a mother-daughter relationship with Sherri. This heartwarming story was reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on 2023-12-15.

name: SHERRI GEERTS
description: Sherri Geerts, an 81-year-old resident of Sunnyvale, California, is the birth mother of Diane Bazella, also known as Bazella. Geerts and Bazella share a similar sense of humor and mannerisms, indicating a strong connection between them. After a period of separation, Geerts is hopeful to make up for lost time with her daughter. Her aspirations include staying healthy and living long enough to spend more quality time with Bazella. The joy of being able to spend Christmastime with her oldest child and only daughter is particularly significant for Geerts, marking a milestone in her journey to reconnect with her family. This reunion, which has been a long time coming, is a testament to Geerts' resilience and determination to be a part of her daughter's life. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: WALTER AND ILA PETERSON
description: Walter and Ila Peterson are Diane Bazella's adoptive parents who told her she was adopted when she was five years old ["When Bazella was five years old, her parents, Walter and Ila Peterson, told her she was adopted."]

name: FOX NEWS
description:
FOX NEWS, a prominent media organization, actively covers a diverse range of topics through its digital platform, engaging with various aspects of American life and culture. In late 2023, FOX NEWS - Lifestyle featured a series titled "Meet the American Who...", spotlighting compelling stories of Americans, including Diane Bazella's emotional reunion with her birth mother after a decades-long search. The outlet also delved into the significance of Henry Wadsworth Longfellow's poem "I Heard the Bells on Christmas Day" in relation to Christmas traditions, enriching readers' understanding of the holiday's literary heritage.

In the entertainment sector, FOX NEWS conducted interviews with notable figures such as Don McLean, discussing his new album of classic Christmas tunes, and Craig Morgan, who shared insights about his re-enlistment in the U.S. Army Reserve and his music career. These interviews provided fans with exclusive insights into the personal and professional lives of these artists.

Addressing health concerns, FOX NEWS reported on a study by Common Sense Media that examined the use of smartphones by young people during school hours and beyond, highlighting the impact of technology on education and well-being. The outlet also published an article about Miller's personal experience with the flu and her advocacy for flu vaccinations, offering a personal perspective on public health issues.

FOX NEWS further explored the spiritual landscape of America, publishing an article that discussed the nation's relationship with God and included comments by Pastor Jesse Bradley, providing a thought-provoking analysis of religious sentiments in contemporary society. Through these varied reports and interviews, FOX NEWS demonstrates its commitment to covering a wide spectrum of issues, engaging its audience with both heartwarming human interest stories and critical discussions on health, entertainment, and spirituality.

name: BAZELLA
description: Bazella, a woman born in 1960 at Booth Memorial Hospital in St. Paul, Minnesota, to 18-year-old unmarried parents, was unknowingly switched at birth and adopted by the Petersons in Edina, Minnesota. She spent 39 years of her life trying to bond with what she believed were her birth parents and biological family, only to discover in 2023 that she was switched at birth. Upon this revelation, Bazella has recently reconnected with her true birth family, including her birth mother, Sherri Geerts, and her birth father, Victor Rebeck. She shares a liking for garden gnomes and a similar sense of humor with her birth mother, which has helped her feel a sense of peace and unconditional love, a stark contrast to the survival mode and loneliness she felt for many years. This heartwarming story was reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 15, 2023.

name: BIRTH PARENTS
description: Bazella's birth parents were 18-year-old unmarried individuals who gave birth to her at Booth Memorial Hospital in St. Paul, Minnesota, in 1960. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: HALF-SIBLINGS
description: Bazella's half-siblings are individuals she believed to be related to her through her birth parents. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: PETERSONS
description: The Petersons are Bazella's adoptive parents who raised her in Edina, Minnesota. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: BOOTH MEMORIAL HOSPITAL
description: Booth Memorial Hospital, now known as the Booth Brown House Youth Shelter, is a facility in St. Paul, Minnesota, where Bazella was born in 1960. It began as a safe haven for unwed mothers and later became The Salvation Army Booth Memorial Hospital in 1913. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: THE SALVATION ARMY CENTRAL TERRITORY
description: The Salvation Army Central Territory is the organization that owns the Booth Brown House Youth Shelter, which was originally The Salvation Army Women’s Home and Hospital. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: HOME DNA TEST
description: A home DNA test, a technology that Diane Bazella utilized in 2017, is a tool enabling individuals to explore their genetic ancestry and discover potential biological relatives. Initially, Bazella experienced confusion when the test results did not match with any of her known relatives. However, her primary objective was to find her birth father's other children, demonstrating the capability of home DNA tests to uncover unknown familial connections. Despite the initial mismatch, the technology proved instrumental in Bazella's quest for her biological family, highlighting its potential for resolving long-standing questions about personal heritage and lineage.

name: SHERRI NORDLIE GEERTS
description: Sherri Nordlie Geerts, the biological mother of Diane Bazella, gave birth to her in 1960 at a hospital designated for unwed mothers. At the tender age of 18, Sherri had to relinquish her newborn due to the circumstances surrounding her birth. However, fate intervened when the truth about a mix-up at birth was uncovered, leading Sherri and Diane to reconnect. Since then, they have maintained a relationship, meeting several times a year to strengthen their bond. This heartwarming story was reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 15, 2023.

name: BIRTH SWITCH
description: There was a birth switch at a hospital where Diane Bazella was originally named Kelly Jean but was later identified as Dawn Marie, the daughter of Sherri Nordlie Geerts [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: VICTOR REBECK
description: Victor Rebeck is Bazella's birth father, who is 84 years old. He has formed a relationship with Bazella after she was switched at birth. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: GARDEN GNOMES
description: Garden gnomes are a type of decorative object that both Bazella and her birth mother, Sherri Geerts, like and are collecting. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-15]

name: FOX NEWS APP
description: The FOX News App is a comprehensive software platform designed for users to access a wide array of news and information from Fox News. This application serves as a one-stop solution for staying updated on various topics, including health, lifestyle, and entertainment. As of 2023, the app has featured articles discussing relevant issues such as Zoom fatigue and tips for managing it, insights into faith and prayer life, and reports on social awareness, such as the use of blue Halloween buckets for autism awareness. The platform also covers lifestyle advice, as seen in Keeley's guidance on creating a 'wish list' and a 'give list.' Additionally, the app delves into personal stories, like the one about Bazella and her journey with her birth family. In the entertainment sector, the FOX News App has published articles about notable figures, including Robin Williams. With its diverse content, the FOX News App caters to a broad audience seeking news and information across different domains.

name: BEYONCE
description: Beyoncé, a renowned musical artist and performer, has made significant waves in the entertainment industry with her concert film, "Renaissance: A Film by Beyoncé." As reported by Fortune on 2023-12-03, the film enjoyed a spectacular debut, topping the box office with a $21 million opening, a testament to Beyoncé's immense popularity and the appeal of her live performances. Polygon, in their article dated 2023-11-07, highlighted Beyoncé's prowess as a live performer and discussed how "Renaissance" captures the essence of her dynamic stage presence, offering audiences a unique opportunity to experience her performance in a cinematic format.

name: RENAISSANCE
description: 'Renaissance' is a concert film by Beyoncé that debuted with $21 million at the box office [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-03]

name: ANIMAL
description: 'Animal' is a film that earned $6.1 million at the box office [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-03]

name: THE SHIFT
description: 'The Shift' is a film that earned $4.4 million at the box office [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-03]

name: SILENT NIGHT
description: "SILENT NIGHT" is a multi-faceted entity with both musical and cinematic representations. Firstly, it is a cherished Christmas song, famously covered by Don McLean on his album "Christmas Memories: Remixed & Remastered," which holds a special place in his heart as it was his mother's favorite song. Additionally, "Silent Night" is also the title of a film that has made a notable impact in the entertainment industry, grossing $3 million at the box office. Despite the different mediums, both the song and the film share the title "SILENT NIGHT," highlighting the versatility and enduring appeal of this name in popular culture.

name: THANKSGIVING
description: "Thanksgiving is a significant cultural holiday primarily observed in the United States on the fourth Thursday of November, which fell on the 23rd of November in 2023. It is a time for people to come together, commemorate what they are grateful for, and prepare a lavish feast with traditional dishes, including cranberry sauce, which is an essential part of the dinner table for six out of ten Americans. The holiday symbolizes peace, thankfulness, and marks the beginning of the holiday season. It is also celebrated in Canada on the second Monday in October and in Liberia on the first Thursday of November. Despite its traditional connotations, a film titled 'Thanksgiving' was released in 2023, directed by Eli Roth, which is a horror genre movie. Contrary to the general atmosphere of the holiday, this film earned $2.6 million at the box office. Additionally, the holiday has been associated with popular culture through Spider-Man's appearances in the Thanksgiving parade, highlighting the holiday's theme of mutual connection, support, and nurturing."

name: BEST BUY
description:
Best Buy is a major retail company known for its extensive range of technology and entertainment products. As of 2023, the company has been actively participating in various sales events, offering significant discounts on a wide array of items. Best Buy started its Black Friday deals early, contributing to the abundance of sales in the market, and also competes with Amazon by matching deals during Amazon's Prime Day event, ensuring that non-Prime members can also benefit from the discounts.

The retailer has been selling the IdeaPad Flex 5i Chromebook Plus for $379, marking a $120 reduction from its list price. Additionally, Best Buy has discounted the second-generation Amazon Echo Buds with a wired charging case, the base MacBook Air with the M1 chip to $749.99 ($250 off), and the upgraded 15-inch M2 MacBook Air configuration to $1,199, offering a $300 discount. The LG A2 OLED TV, specifically the 48-inch model, has been available at a new low price of $550, and the Google Pixel Tablet was offered at a discounted price of $399 for Black Friday.

Best Buy's product offerings extend to the 2021 iPad, 10th-gen iPad, 2019 Kindle Oasis, and the new Echo Show 5, among others. The company also provides a Price Match Guarantee, allowing for price reductions on new, identical products immediately available at a qualifying competitor's store or online, with some exceptions, such as items for sale the Friday before Thanksgiving Day through the Monday after Thanksgiving.

Best Buy offers early access to Black Friday deals through its My Best Buy Plus and Total memberships, which cost $49.99 and $179.99, respectively. The retailer also provides various shipping options, including free two-day shipping for My Best Buy Plus and Total subscribers with no order minimum, while other customers need to meet a $35 order threshold. Free next-day delivery is available on select items through December 23rd, and free same-day delivery is offered on December 23rd or December 24th if orders are placed by 12PM local time. Customers can order online by 5PM local time on Christmas Eve for an in-store pickup by 7PM. Major appliances may take longer to be delivered.

Furthermore, Best Buy extends its return

name: WALMART
description: Walmart, a multinational retail corporation, is known for offering a wide range of products and deals, particularly during major shopping events such as Black Friday and Cyber Monday. As of 2023, Walmart began its Black Friday deals early, launching the first round on November 8, with an additional round the day before Thanksgiving, contributing to a month-long sales event. Walmart+ members received early access to these deals, a perk that comes with the membership which costs $99 per year (temporarily reduced to $50), and includes benefits like free next-day and two-day shipping with no order minimum for subscribers. The official Cyber Monday sale started on Sunday, November 26, at 7 p.m. ET, exclusive to Walmart.com and the Walmart app, promising up to 80% savings on top gifts in categories such as apparel, beauty, tech, toys, and more. Walmart competes with Amazon by offering deals during Amazon's Prime Day event, providing discounts to non-Prime members. Despite not price-matching competitors' prices, Walmart does offer price-matching on items purchased from Walmart stores if the item is in stock at Walmart.com, with certain exclusions. Walmart's extended holiday return policy, effective between October 1 and December 31, allows items to be returned on or before January 31, 2024. Among the deals offered, Walmart provided discounts on the Lightning version of the second generation AirPods Pro for $169, the Dyson V15 Detect Absolute vacuum, and the 10th-gen iPad and the Google Nest Hub (second-gen). To ensure Christmas delivery, orders must be placed by 2PM local time on December 21st for two-day shipping, with free shipping for orders over $35. Next-day shipping is also available in select areas. Notably, Walmart was closed on Thanksgiving Day before reopening for Black Friday, an annual shopping occasion filled with store deals.

name: COSTCO
description: Costco is a membership-based retailer recognized for its bulk offerings, particularly in food products, which can make the $60 membership fee a worthwhile investment, especially during the holiday season when purchases are typically higher (Polygon, 2023-11-12). It operates as a grocery store and more, with a wide range of products available. However, it does not participate in price matching with competitors (The Verge, 2023-10-25) and is also not included in Lenovo's price matching policy. For online purchases, Costco provides a credit for the difference if the price drops within 30 days of the purchase (The Verge, 2023-10-25). In-store, customers must visit the membership counter at the specific store where the purchase was made to address any price discrepancies. Additionally, all US Costco stores will be closed on Thanksgiving Day, as noted on the retailer's official site, allowing its employees to enjoy the holiday (The Verge, 2023-10-25).

name: AMAZON PRIME
description: Amazon Prime is a multifaceted membership program offered by Amazon, designed to provide a wide array of benefits to its subscribers. Primarily, it offers early access to Black Friday deals, free and expedited shipping options including Same-Day, One-Day, and Two-Day Delivery for eligible products, with specific deadlines for holiday orders. Same-Day Delivery is available through December 24th for certain items, meeting a minimum threshold that varies by location, while One-Day Delivery is accessible through December 23rd, and Two-Day Delivery through December 22nd. Additionally, Prime members in select US cities can enjoy two-hour grocery delivery services up until December 24th. Beyond shopping perks, Amazon Prime is also recognized as a streaming service, providing a diverse selection of shows, although some content may be geoblocked in certain countries. This streaming service has been considered by NASCAR as a potential platform to expand its audience beyond traditional cable viewers, highlighting Amazon Prime's role in the entertainment sector as well. The service invites potential members with a free 30-day trial, making it accessible for a broad range of consumers to experience the full spectrum of benefits it offers.

name: WALMART PLUS
description: Walmart Plus is a membership program offered by Walmart that provides early access to Black Friday deals and other perks. It costs $99 per year ($50 for a limited time) [Polygon, 2023-11-12]

name: MY BEST BUY PLUS
description: My Best Buy Plus is a membership program offered by Best Buy that provides early access to Black Friday deals. It costs $49.99 [Polygon, 2023-11-12]

name: TOTAL MEMBERSHIP
description: Total Membership is a membership program offered by Best Buy that provides early access to Black Friday deals. It costs $179.99 [Polygon, 2023-11-12]

name: TARGET
description:
TARGET, a major retail company, is known for its competitive stance against Amazon, engaging in sales during Prime Day and offering deals on a wide array of products. In 2023, TARGET initiated its Black Friday sales early, providing discounts on notable tech items such as Apple's 9th-gen iPad, the second generation AirPods Pro with USB-C charging for $190, the third generation AirPods with the Lightning charging case for $140, and the Google Pixel Tablet at a reduced price of $399. The company also sells educational toys, as evidenced by a third-party seller listing Brain Flakes at a lower price on TARGET than on Amazon in September 2022. TARGET's product range extends to the LG DualUp monitor and includes digital gifts like gift cards and subscriptions, catering to diverse customer needs.

The retailer implements a price-matching policy for online purchases, with certain exclusions such as doorbusters, competitors' lightning sales, products requiring login to see the price, "Marketplace" items from third-party sellers, and lower-priced items from other TARGET stores. This policy, along with TARGET's price adjustment guarantee for purchases made between Oct. 22 and Dec. 24, ensures that customers receive the best value for their money. TARGET accepts most unopened items in new condition for returns within 90 days of purchase, further enhancing customer satisfaction.

In response to the COVID-19 pandemic, TARGET announced permanent store closures on Thanksgiving Day in 2020, a policy that has been upheld since then, prioritizing the health and well-being of its employees and customers. Despite this, TARGET continues to thrive as a go-to destination for tech and entertainment products, offering competitive pricing and a broad selection to meet the demands of the holiday shopping season.

name: DECEMBER DEALS
description: Deals often extend through much of December, providing additional opportunities for savings beyond Black Friday and Cyber Monday [Polygon, 2023-11-12]

name: POLYGON
description: Polygon is a comprehensive media organization that specializes in providing recommendations and highlights for a wide array of entertainment and gaming products. They cover movies, TV shows, video games, tabletop games, comics, merch, toys, and other entertainment experiences, ensuring that their audience is well-informed about the best, funniest, scariest, and most exciting content available. Polygon's team of experts tests and reviews products, including gaming hardware, to help consumers find the best value and experience. They have been curating and reviewing games across every platform, saving gamers time by guiding them to the most innovative and intriguing games. Polygon has endorsed products like the Steam Deck OLED as an improvement over its predecessor and has provided detailed reviews of games such as Baldur's Gate 3, Super Mario Bros. Wonder, Warhammer 40,000: Rogue Trader, and Spider-Man 2, often using pre-release download codes provided by the respective game developers. Additionally, Polygon offers insights into the world of tabletop gaming, with contributions from nearly two dozen writers, designers, presenters, actors, and personalities sharing the TTRPGs that made a significant impact on them and their players. They also discuss the restrictions and opportunities for VTubers in different agencies, and provide reviews of the best controllers for PC gaming and portable chargers for gear, focusing on charging speeds and device compatibility. Polygon's coverage extends to gadgets and streaming services, making it a one-stop destination for all things entertainment and gaming. They adhere to an ethics policy related to affiliate partnerships, ensuring transparency in their recommendations.

name: GEORGIA
description: Georgia, a prominent college football team, has solidified its status as the two-time reigning national champions, maintaining an undefeated record throughout the 2023 season. As of October 1, 2023, they were ranked No. 1, with a record of 5-0, having showcased their resilience in comeback victories against SEC opponents South Carolina and Auburn, as reported by CBSSports.com. Their Week 6 game against Kentucky marked their first ranked matchup of the season. By November 11, 2023, Georgia had clinched the SEC East title for the third consecutive year and the sixth time in seven seasons, a testament to their consistent dominance. Notable figures associated with the team include Bubba Watson, AJ Minter, Kelee Ringo, and Stetson Bennett, who have been spotted on the sidelines, adding to the team's prestige as mentioned by Sporting News. Despite their impressive talent, The New York Times on December 3, 2023, noted that Georgia, alongside powerhouses Alabama and Ohio State, has experienced losses in the past that had significant consequences. As the season progressed, Georgia faced a critical challenge in the SEC championship game on December 1, 2023, against No. 8 Alabama, a game that was broadcast on CBS at 4 p.m. A victory for Alabama against Georgia would serve as a signature win, highlighting the high stakes and intense rivalry between these two top-tier teams.

name: KENTUCKY
description: In 2023, the Kentucky Wildcats, a college football team, have been making waves with their exceptional performance, securing a spot as the No. 20 ranked team with an undefeated record of 5-0. As the season progresses, they are set to face a significant challenge in Week 6 against the formidable Georgia Bulldogs, who are considered heavy favorites in the upcoming match. Despite the odds, Kentucky's chances of an upset victory are bolstered by the outstanding skills of their running back, Ray Davis. In a recent game against Florida in Week 5, Davis showcased his prowess by rushing for an impressive 280 yards and scoring three touchdowns, a performance that has undoubtedly raised the team's morale and attracted attention to their potential for a strong showing against Georgia. [CBSSports.com, 2023-10-01]

name: MISSOURI
description: In the realm of college football, the Missouri Tigers, ranked No. 21, are gearing up for a significant challenge in Week 6 of the 2023 season. As they face off against LSU, the team is aiming to maintain their undefeated status, a feat that has garnered them considerable attention and respect within the sports community. This match-up promises to be a pivotal moment for the Missouri Tigers, potentially solidifying their position in the rankings or presenting an opportunity for growth and strategy adjustment. The team's performance against LSU will be closely watched by fans and analysts alike, as it could influence the trajectory of their season.

name: LSU
description: LSU, a college football team, has experienced a notable shift in its season's trajectory, transitioning from a popular choice for the College Football Playoff (CFP) to a team with two losses already under its belt as of 2023-10-01. Ranked No. 23, LSU is set to play against Missouri in Week 6 amidst efforts to strengthen their defense, which has been criticized for poor performances in recent games against Arkansas and Ole Miss. The team's current standing and upcoming match reflect the dynamic nature of college football, where any team's fortunes can change rapidly based on their on-field results.

description: Louisville, a college football team, has made significant strides in the 2023 season under the leadership of coach Jeff Brohm. Initially, the team was ranked No. 25 with an impressive 5-0 record a month into the season, marking their first time facing ranked competition when they played against Notre Dame in Week 6. By December, Louisville's performance had elevated them to the No. 14 spot in the rankings. In a notable achievement, Louisville defeated No. 4 Florida State in the ACC championship game, which took place on Saturday, December 1, 2023, at 8 p.m. on ABC. This victory not only showcased the team's strength but also freed up one of the four spots in the College Football Playoff (CFP), highlighting Louisville's competitive edge and success in the 2023 college football season.

name: NOTRE DAME
description: Notre Dame, a prominent college football team, has been actively engaged in competitive matches during the 2023 season. On October 14, 2023, in a Week 7 game against the USC Trojans, Notre Dame demonstrated a strong performance, leading with a score of 24 to USC's 3 at 1:30 left in the first half, as reported by Sporting News. Despite being penalized for defensive holding and offensive pass interference, the team managed to score with a 4-yard touchdown pass from Sam Hartman to Gi'Bran Payne. In the same game, Sporting News noted that Notre Dame won with a 5-0 turnover margin, even though they were held to 251 total yards of offense. Earlier in the season, on October 1, 2023, CBSSports.com highlighted Notre Dame's involvement in close games over the past two weeks, and their upcoming challenge against Louisville, an unbeaten team a month into the Jeff Brohm era. These summaries provide a snapshot of Notre Dame's football team's performance and challenges during the 2023 season.

name: ALABAMA
description: Alabama, also known as the Crimson Tide, is a prominent college football team that, despite a rocky 2-1 start in the season, managed to find its stride and secure an 11-1 record by the end of the regular season. Notably, they defeated Ole Miss and Mississippi State in consecutive games, showcasing a strong comeback. As the one-loss SEC champion, Alabama made headlines by ending Georgia's 29-game winning streak, a significant achievement that contributed to their inclusion in the College Football Playoff (CFP) discussions. Ranked at No. 8, the team's fate in the CFP was uncertain, especially considering they were positioned behind No. 6 Ohio State. However, a crucial victory against the then-No. 1 Georgia in the SEC championship game could potentially elevate their standing and secure a spot in the College Football Playoff, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-12-01. The New York Times on 2023-12-03 highlighted the implications of regular season losses on CFP eligibility, with Alabama's single loss at home serving as a case study. Despite the early setbacks, Alabama's season was marked by resilience and high-stakes victories, positioning them as a formidable contender in the college football landscape.

name: TEXAS A&M

name: CUBIC TELECOM
description: Cubic Telecom, a swiftly expanding Dublin-based startup, specializes in offering software-driven networking solutions that facilitate global mobile network connectivity for vehicles and various devices. With a robust ecosystem of 90 national and multinational mobile network operator partnerships, the company ensures seamless connectivity to more than 17 million vehicles across 190 countries and regions. Notably, Cubic Telecom adds approximately 450,000 new vehicles to its network every month, projecting an exponential growth trajectory over the next five years. Beyond mere connectivity, Cubic Telecom is also recognized for its IoT asset connectivity solutions, which significantly cut down the expenses associated with constructing and overseeing vehicle connectivity, making it a pivotal player in the technology and automotive sectors. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-05]

name: SOFTBANK CORP
description: SoftBank Corp, a prominent Japanese telecoms and IT division, has made a strategic investment of \u20ac473 million ($513 million) in Cubic Telecom, a move that has granted them a controlling 51% stake in the company. As a result of this acquisition, Cubic Telecom now operates as a consolidated subsidiary of SoftBank Corp. This significant investment, reported by TechCrunch on 2023-12-05, underscores SoftBank's expansion into the connected car market, leveraging Cubic Telecom's expertise to strengthen its position in the evolving technology landscape.

name: BARRY NAPIER
description: Barry Napier is the CEO of Cubic Telecom and will retain his position and have a seat on the board of the company after SoftBank's investment. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-05]

name: DAICHI NOZAKI
description: Daichi Nozaki is the SVP of global business at SoftBank and will join the board of Cubic Telecom along with two other SoftBank-appointed people. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-05]

name: CARIAD

This chipset represents QUALCOMM's commitment to innovation and advancement in wearable technology. Additionally, QUALCOMM maintains a strategic investment in Cubic Telecom, a company specializing in connectivity solutions for the Internet of Things (IoT). As an existing investor, QUALCOMM holds a seat on Cubic Telecom's board, demonstrating its interest in shaping the future of IoT and connectivity services. This dual involvement in both wearable technology and IoT investment underscores QUALCOMM's broad reach and influence in the tech sector.

However, Ratajkowski has recently faced backlash for a photo shoot that some have deemed distasteful and contradictory to her previous stance on body positivity. The controversy has sparked fury among some of her followers and the public, leading The Independent to contact her representatives for a comment on the matter. Despite the criticism, Ratajkowski's efforts to challenge societal norms and advocate for women's rights remain a significant part of her public persona.

name: THE INDEPENDENT
description:
The Independent is a comprehensive news organization that covers a wide array of topics, catering to diverse interests within its audience. Known for its Life and Style section, The Independent provides insightful articles on lifestyle, fashion trends, and cultural events, enriching readers' understanding of the world around them. The publication has been a source of information on significant cultural moments, such as the debate on Daylight Saving Time, the dynamics of long-term relationships, and the controversy sparked by Calla's choice to have her mother walk her down the aisle instead of her stepfather.

In the realm of entertainment, The Independent has closely followed the personal lives of celebrities, including Jada Pinkett Smith and Will Smith's separation, and Britney Spears' relationships and her memoir, "The Woman in Me." The outlet has also reported on the evolving relationship between Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce, from the secret start of their relationship to Swift's attendance at a Kansas City Chiefs game and Kelce's comments on the NFL's coverage of Swift during a game against the New York Jets. The Independent further delved into Kelce's personal life, discussing his reaction to media scrutiny and his confession about attempting to delete his tweets amidst rumors of dating Swift.

The Independent's coverage extends to social issues, such as the lack of plus-size representation in the fashion industry, and highlights the latest in fashion with features on Emily Ratajkowski's photo shoots. Additionally, the publication offers a Thanksgiving store closures update, providing practical information for its readers.

For sports enthusiasts, The Independent publishes Miguel Delaney’s Reading the Game newsletter, focusing on football events, including Manchester United’s performance in the Champions League. Travel enthusiasts can also find enriching content in The Independent, with travel articles and the opportunity to sign up for Simon Calder's travel email.

The Independent's Life and Style section has also provided guidance on personal matters, such as whether to introduce a partner to family during the holidays, featuring expert insights to navigate the complexities of relationships. Through its various sections and newsletters, The Independent remains a trusted source for news, analysis, and commentary on a multitude of subjects, engaging its audience with relevant and timely information.

name: BELGIUM
description: Belgium, a country known for its national football team, experienced a setback when an unspecified player missed games due to a hamstring issue, as reported by Sky Sports on 2023-10-20. However, the Belgium national soccer team, which can be considered a part of the broader football community, demonstrated resilience and prowess in a UEFA Women's Nations League match against England on 2023-10-31.
