description: Charles Schwab Foundation is an organization that provides support for educational and explanatory reporting to improve financial literacy. The Associated Press receives support from this foundation. [Fortune, 2023-12-23]

name: ASSOCIATED PRESS
description: The Associated Press, a renowned news agency, has been actively involved in various reporting endeavors, contributing significantly to the dissemination of information across different domains. In 1959, the Associated Press published a story that highlighted the pivotal role of Marcus Urann in making cranberries an integral part of the Thanksgiving tradition, as reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on November 23, 2023. Demonstrating its commitment to enhancing public knowledge, the agency also receives support from the Charles Schwab Foundation, which aids in educational and explanatory reporting aimed at improving financial literacy, as noted by Fortune on December 23, 2023. The Associated Press's extensive coverage is further enriched by the contributions of its dedicated writers, such as Kevin Freking and Mary Clare Jalonick, who have significantly contributed to reports that the organization has produced.

name: SONY WH-1000XM5
description: The Sony WH-1000XM5, recognized as the best pair of noise-canceling headphones by The Verge and a top pick in Engadget's guide to the best wireless headphones, are Sony's highest-end model in this category. They build upon the features of the WH-1000XM4, boasting improved active noise cancellation (ANC) that effectively blocks out external sounds, enhanced voice call quality, and a warm yet customizable sound. The headphones are designed for comfort, with a snug fit that naturally isolates a significant amount of outside noise, and they offer an impressive battery life of approximately 30 hours per charge. Engadget has reviewed the WH-1000XM5 twice, initially giving it a score of 87 and later updating the score to 95. The headphones also feature a "Speak to Chat" function and allow for EQ adjustments through Sony's app. As of 2023-12-07, they are available for $328 at B&H Photo, Best Buy, and Target, which represents a $72 drop from the original price and matches the lowest price seen, according to Engadget's update on 2023-11-24.

name: SONY WF-1000XM5
description: The Sony WF-1000XM5 are flagship wireless earbuds, considered the best on the market by Engadget, which praised them as the top pick in their guide to the best wireless earbuds. These earbuds improve upon their predecessors with richer sound quality, more powerful active noise cancellation (ANC), and a vastly improved comfort level due to their reduced size and weight. They deliver a warm sound that is enjoyable out of the box but can be customized if needed. The WF-1000XM5 offer numerous helpful features, including adaptive sound and Speak-to-Chat. Battery life is decent, lasting around seven to eight hours per charge with ANC, and up to 12 hours without it. As of late 2023, the Sony WF-1000XM5 earbuds are available at a discount, with prices ranging from $248 to $278, depending on the source. Engadget gave the WF-1000XM5 a score of 87 in their review, highlighting their excellent ANC, customizable sound, and comfortably snug fit. The design is lighter, smaller, and more comfortable than past Sony earbuds, making them a superior choice for those seeking high-quality wireless earbuds.

name: SONY WH-1000XM4
description: The Sony WH-1000XM4 are over-ear, noise-canceling headphones, recognized as an older model in Sony's lineup yet still considered terrific for their performance. They offer excellent noise cancellation, good sound quality, and the convenience of pairing with two devices simultaneously. Designed for comfort during long periods of wear, the headphones feature plush ear pads and can fold up more compactly than their newer model, the XM5, making them easier to store. With a battery life of up to 30 hours on a single charge, they provide ample listening time and can be recharged via USB-C. The WH-1000XM4 received a review score of 94 in 2020, highlighting its strong feature set that is nearly identical to its successor, albeit with slightly less clear microphones for calls and a bit more bulk. During the anti-Prime Day deals in 2023, the Sony WH-1000XM4 were available at a discount, offering consumers a great opportunity to purchase a high-quality audio product.

name: BOSE
description: Bose, a super premium and reputable brand in the technology industry, is renowned for its high-quality audio products. The company, which has a strong focus on headphones and earbuds, recently entered the smart glasses market, showcasing its innovation and adaptability. Bose's QuietComfort Earbuds II and the newly released QuietComfort Ultra headphones, along with the QuietComfort Ultra Earbuds, have received positive reviews for their exceptional noise cancellation capabilities and sleek design. These products are particularly recommended for office use due to their advanced signal processing and four microphones that effectively limit surrounding sound. During the Black Friday sales event, Bose offers discounts on its products, making it an opportune time for consumers to purchase their highly regarded headphones and earbuds.

name: BEATS
description: BEATS is a renowned company in the electronics industry, specializing in the production of various high-quality audio products. Among its offerings are the Fit Pro and Studio Pro headphones, both praised for their design, sound quality, and features. The Studio Pro, a recent release by BEATS, boasts impressive noise canceling capabilities, although some reviews from WIRED in October 2023 suggest that the battery life could be improved and that more robust controls and EQ options would enhance the user experience. BEATS products, including headphones and earbuds, are popular choices during Black Friday sales, as noted by Engadget on November 24, 2023, offering consumers the opportunity to purchase premium audio equipment at discounted prices.

name: APPLE AIRPODS PRO
description: Apple AirPods Pro, the wireless earbuds designed specifically for the Apple ecosystem, have been recognized as the best earbuds for iPhone users. As of Prime Day, the second-generation models are available at a reduced price of $189. These earbuds boast improved sound quality, noise cancelation, and Transparency Mode, making them a top choice for dedicated Apple fans. The AirPods Pro offer a sound profile that is pleasantly warm and noise cancelation that is as effective as the Powerbeats Pro. They also come with a suite of Apple-specific features, including hands-free access to Siri, quick pairing with iPhones, and device tracking through Apple's Find My network. With an average six-hour battery life, the AirPods Pro received a review score of 88 last year, solidifying their position as a leading product in the wireless earbud market.

name: APPLE AIRPODS (3RD-GEN)
description: The third-generation Apple AirPods are wireless earbuds that sound noticeably richer than their predecessor and feature haptic feedback. They received a review score of 88 in 2021. [Source: Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: SONY
description:
Sony is a renowned technology and entertainment company, celebrated for its innovative OLED screens and other electronic products. In the realm of televisions, Sony offers the X90L LED TV, a 65-inch model that boasts excellent picture processing, good brightness, and great local dimming for rich contrast, which was noted to be at its lowest price of the year in a Wired article dated 2023-11-27. The company is also a significant player in the audio market, manufacturing the WH-1000XM5 headphones and the WF-1000XM5 earbuds, as highlighted by Engadget on 2023-11-19. These products, along with the standard LinkBuds, which feature an open-ear design allowing wearers to hear their surroundings, are part of Sony's diverse electronics portfolio, as recommended by WIRED Recommends on 2023-10-10 and Engadget on 2023-11-24. Sony's XM5 headphones are particularly noted for their wider feature set and ability to be used passively, making them a preferred choice over Bose products, according to Engadget on 2023-11-24.

In the gaming industry, Sony is a major force, with a revenue surpassing that of Microsoft. The company owns 21 development teams, including notable studios such as Bungie, Guerrilla Games, Haven Studios, Housemarque, Insomniac Games, Media Molecule, Naughty Dog, and Sucker Punch Productions, as reported by Engadget on 2023-12-19. Sony's contributions to the gaming world also include the co-development of CD technology with Philips, although the exact date of this collaboration is not specified. Additionally, Sony is the producer of the PlayStation gaming console and receives approximately a 30% cut of in-game purchases made on the platform, as mentioned in the text.

Sony's extensive involvement in various sectors, from visual technology to audio and gaming, showcases its commitment to delivering high-quality products and experiences to consumers worldwide.

name: QUIETCOMFORT ULTRA HEADPHONES
description: The QuietComfort Ultra headphones are a product from Bose that offers outstanding noise cancellation, above-average call quality, and a bassy default sound [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: QUIETCOMFORT ULTRA EARBUDS
description: The QuietComfort Ultra Earbuds are a product from Bose that received a review score of 88 for their noise cancellation performance and spatial audio tech, but have larger earpieces, average call quality and battery life, and lack multi-device pairing [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: BEATS FIT PRO
description: The Beats Fit Pro, a product from Beats by Dr. Dre, are highly recommended wireless earbuds for workouts due to their sporty design, physical control buttons, and punchy yet refined sound quality. These earbuds, which are currently on sale for $160, offer a secure and comfortable fit during physical activities, thanks to their wing tips. They deliver great sound and work seamlessly with iPhones, providing full conveniences due to Apple's proprietary H1 chip and deeper OS integration, much like the first-gen AirPods Pro. However, their functionality with Android phones is limited, although an app is available for customization of controls and a fit test. Despite their sportier design and superior sound, the Beats Fit Pro lacks multi-device pairing and wireless charging, and its ANC (Active Noise Cancellation) is less capable than that of the AirPods Pro. The product received a review score of 87 in 2021, highlighting its overall performance and value.

name: BEATS STUDIO PRO
description:
The Beats Studio Pro, an over-ear headphone model from Apple-owned Beats, was released earlier this year as a successor to the Beats Studio 3. These headphones have garnered attention for their improved sound quality, support for lossless audio over USB-C, and enhanced active noise cancellation (ANC) capabilities. As of December 7, 2023, the Beats Studio Pro is available in blue for $271.15 at Amazon, while other colors are priced at $299.99 at Best Buy and Verizon. However, for Black Friday, the price dropped to an unprecedented low of $170 at Amazon, Target, and Best Buy, marking a $10 decrease from the previous lowest price and a $130 discount from its average street price in recent months.

The product has received mixed reviews, with a 7/10 rating from WIRED in October 2023 and an 81 review score in July 2023, highlighting its largely pleasant and even-handed sound quality. The ANC feature is noted to be strong enough for practical use, and the headphones perform well with both iOS and Android devices, although multi-device pairing is not supported on iOS. Despite lacking auto-pausing functionality when removed and featuring a mostly plastic design, the Beats Studio Pro may still appeal to buyers due to its compatibility with Android and the Beats brand aesthetic.

At the sale price of $180, the Beats Studio Pro presents a compelling option for consumers looking for wireless over-ear headphones with good sound quality, ANC, and the ability to stream higher-quality audio over a USB-C connection. The lack of top-tier features and conveniences, such as wear detection and multi-device pairing on iOS, is offset by the attractive price point and the brand's design appeal.

name: AIRPODS
description: AirPods, a product by Apple, are widely recognized wireless earphones that many people use for listening to audio in public settings, such as during commutes, where ambient noise or the use of AirPods by others makes audio leakage from alternative devices, like Meta smart glasses, inconspicuous. AirPods are noted for their superior bass quality compared to the Amazon Echo Frames, making them a preferred choice for audio enthusiasts. They are also a point of comparison for the price of the Samsung Galaxy Buds2, indicating their competitive positioning in the market. AirPods can be conveniently charged using various accessories, including the Courant Catch:2, Satechi Duo Wireless Charger Stand and Power Bank, and ESR Travel Kit, offering users flexibility and convenience in their charging options.

name: AMAZON ECHO BUDS (2023)
description: The Amazon Echo Buds (2023) are wireless earbuds designed for individuals who prefer a semi-open design, allowing for a more natural listening experience by letting in outside noise, as opposed to the isolating nature of traditional in-ear headphones. These earbuds, which have an average battery life of around five hours per charge, are equipped with wear detection, multipoint connectivity, and hands-free Alexa integration, making them a versatile choice for daily use. Despite their IPX2 sweat-resistance rating, which is not robust enough for intense workouts, the Echo Buds can deliver decent sound quality with some EQ tweaking. As of Black Friday 2023, they are available at a budget-friendly price of $35, marking a $15 drop from their usual cost and matching an all-time low. Although the Amazon companion app is somewhat bloated and the earbuds lack wireless charging, these drawbacks are less significant considering the reduced price point. The Echo Buds received a review score of 77 in July 2023, indicating they are a solid choice for those who value an open design and Alexa features over deep bass and gym-ready durability.

name: ANKER SOUNDCORE SPACE A40
description: The Anker Soundcore Space A40, a wireless earbud model, is currently on sale for $54, a price that matches its all-time low and is available for Black Friday. This product is highlighted as the top pick in the guide to the best budget wireless earbuds, offering a range of features typically found in more expensive models. The Space A40 boasts adaptive ANC (active noise cancellation), which is notably effective for a pair under $100, multi-device pairing for seamless switching between devices, and wireless charging, all while fitting comfortably in the ear. Its battery life is impressive, lasting up to 10 hours per charge. The audio quality, while not as powerful as higher-end models, is warm and pleasing to most listeners, and can be customized through a clean companion app. However, the Space A40 does not have wear detection, meaning it won't automatically pause when an earbud is removed, and its call quality is described as mediocre or middling, which could be a downside for those prioritizing clear phone conversations. Despite these limitations, the Anker Soundcore Space A40 remains one of the best values in wireless earphones, especially at its sale price.

name: ANKER SOUNDCORE LIBERTY 4 NC
description: The Anker Soundcore Liberty 4 NC is a budget-friendly wireless earbud model, recognized as the runner-up in Engadget's guide to the best wireless earbuds as of November 24, 2023. This product boasts a "stem" design reminiscent of Apple's AirPods, offering a bass-forward sound profile by default, which can be customized using EQ tools available in Anker's app. The Liberty 4 NC supports wear detection, enhancing user experience with its extensive touch controls. As of the latest update on November 24, 2023, the Anker Soundcore Liberty 4 NC is on sale for $70, marking a $10 decrease from its previous low and a significant $30 below Anker's list price, providing an excellent value for consumers seeking high-quality audio at a reduced cost.

name: ANKER
description: Anker, a prominent player in the tech and entertainment accessory market, offers a wide array of electronic devices and audio products designed to enhance the user experience. The company's product lineup includes power banks, chargers such as the Anker MagGo 637 for iPhones and other devices, and audio devices like the Soundcore Liberty 4 NC earbuds, Space Q45, and Life Q30. Anker's Liberty 4 NC earbuds, known for their excellent noise canceling capabilities, were recently on sale for $80, a $20 discount. Additionally, Anker produces the Anker Nano, the Backbone One, and the Anker 3-in-1 MagSafe wireless charging dock. In anticipation of the holiday season, Anker launched an early Black Friday sale in 2023, providing customers with discounts and promotions on their sought-after tech products. These details were reported by Wired and Engadget, highlighting Anker's commitment to delivering high-quality, feature-packed devices to its customers.

name: ANKER SOUNDCORE SPACE Q45
description:
The ANKER SOUNDCORE SPACE Q45 is a pair of noise-canceling over-ear headphones, known for their adaptive ANC (Active Noise Cancellation) technology that surpasses average performance, providing users with a superior sound isolation experience. These headphones are designed with comfort in mind, featuring a softly padded construction that ensures long hours of listening without discomfort. The multi-device pairing capability allows for seamless switching between different audio sources, enhancing the versatility of the headphones for various use cases.

The sound profile of the ANKER SOUNDCORE SPACE Q45 is V-shaped, which typically emphasizes the bass and treble frequencies, making it ideal for genres like rock and electronic music. However, users have noted uneven treble quality, a minor drawback that can be mitigated by customizing the sound settings through Anker's Soundcore app. This app offers a range of equalization options, enabling users to tailor the audio experience to their preferences.

Despite the generally positive features, call quality is reported to be mediocre, which might be a consideration for those who frequently use their headphones for phone calls. As of 2023, the ANKER SOUNDCORE SPACE Q45 has been available at a Black Friday price of $100, a significant $50 discount from its usual retail price. This price point matches the lowest price tracked for these headphones, making it an attractive deal for potential buyers. The discounted price is accessible at both Amazon and Anker's online store, providing multiple purchasing options for consumers.

name: AUDIO-TECHNICA ATH-M20XBT
description: The Audio-Technica ATH-M20XBT is a budget wireless headphone with a comfortable fit, 60-hour battery life, multi-device connectivity, and relatively detailed audio quality. It lacks ANC and has a less sturdy design, but it is a no-frills wireless headphone option for a low price. The product is currently $10 off for Black Friday, priced at $69 [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: EARFUN FREE 2S
description: The EarFun Free 2S is a budget wireless earbud that is currently priced at an all-time low of $24.59 at Amazon with a Prime-only discount and the checkout code FREE2SPD1. The earbuds have a bass-forward sound and are the "best under $50" pick in the budget wireless earbuds guide [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: JLAB GO AIR POP
description: The JLab Go Air Pop is a pair of budget wireless earbuds, priced at an affordable $17 on Amazon, designed for individuals seeking a compact and functional audio solution without breaking the bank. These earbuds boast an IPX4 water resistance rating, making them suitable for workouts and outdoor activities, as they can withstand splashes and light rain. With a battery life of approximately eight to nine hours per charge, the JLab Go Air Pop offers extended listening sessions, ideal for long commutes or travel. The touch controls provide a modern and intuitive way to manage playback, and the inclusion of three EQ presets directly in the earbuds allows users to customize their sound experience. Despite its low price point, the sound quality is described as boomy but well beyond serviceable, making the JLab Go Air Pop a compelling choice for those prioritizing value and performance in their wireless earbud selection.

name: GOOGLE PIXEL BUDS PRO
description: The Google Pixel Buds Pro, Google's top-tier wireless earbuds, are currently available at a discounted price of $120, marking a significant $80 off the list price, as noted by Engadget on 2023-10-10. These earbuds are particularly well-suited for Android users, boasting tight integration with the Android OS and Google's Pixel phones. They have received high praise for their comfort and wide array of color options, earning a 9/10 rating from WIRED on 2023-10-10. The Pixel Buds Pro feature solid Active Noise Cancellation (ANC) and a V-shaped sound profile, delivering punchy bass and a well-rounded audio experience. Depending on ANC usage, they offer up to 11 hours of battery life. Engadget awarded them a score of 87 in a review conducted last year, highlighting their good ANC, reliable touch controls, and wireless charging capabilities. An upcoming firmware update is anticipated to further enhance call quality and introduce an automatic music pause feature when the user starts speaking. This makes the Google Pixel Buds Pro an excellent choice for Android users seeking high-quality wireless earbuds with advanced features and a competitive price point.

name: BEYERDYNAMIC DT 900 PRO X
description: Beyerdynamic's DT 900 Pro X headphones are down to $249 at Amazon and Target from a trusted third-party seller. They are a wired pair of open-back headphones designed for critical listening at home. The DT 900 Pro X is the top pick in our guide to the best headphones for gaming due to its wonderfully spacious sound. The headphones deliver enough low-end to give in-game explosions a powerful sense of impact and feature soft velour earpads for comfort [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: SENHEISER HD 560S
description: The Sennheiser HD 560S is another open-back pair of wired headphones highlighted in our gaming headset guide. It is down to $150 at an unspecified retailer. The HD 560S is designed for critical listening and gaming, with a spacious sound profile and soft velour earpads for comfort [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: SENNHEISER HD 560S
description: The Sennheiser HD 560S is an open-back pair of wired headphones highlighted in Engadget's gaming headset guide. It offers a balanced, spacious, and detailed sound profile and a comfortable frame for extended use. The product is currently on sale for $150, which is $30 less than the street price since summer 2023. However, it can sound a little piercing in the treble and is not as sturdily built as the DT 900 Pro X. It won't block much external noise due to its open design. [Source: Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: DROP X SENNHEISER HD 6XX
description: The Drop X Sennheiser HD 6XX is on sale for $169 at Drop, a $50 discount. Engadget's audio expert Billy Steele gave positive impressions of this pair in a hands-on review back in 2016. It is based on the Sennheiser HD 650, a favorite among audiophiles. The headphones are open-back with a little more bass warmth, making them a good option for those looking for audio-centric headphones for less than $200. [Source: Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: ASTRO A40 TR
description: The Astro A40 TR is Engadget's favorite dedicated gaming headset for most people. It is currently on sale for $100 at Amazon, a $30 discount. The deal includes Astro's MixAmp M80, an optional amp that connects to Xbox controllers and provides various audio controls. The A40 TR provides a wider soundstage than most gaming headsets, with a slight bass boost that gives in-game effects extra boom. It is comfortable, but its built-in mic isn't the clearest tested. [Source: Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: HYPERX CLOUD STINGER 2
description: The HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 is a budget gaming headset, recognized as the top pick in its category for gamers seeking affordability without compromising on quality. As of the latest update, it is on sale for $35, matching the lowest price ever recorded. This headset boasts a V-shaped sound signature, delivering a bass-heavy profile that enhances the impact of action scenes, making it particularly appealing for immersive gaming experiences. The built-in microphone is noted for its decent to impressive quality, especially considering the headset's price point. Despite being mostly constructed from plastic, which may give a cheap impression, the design ensures comfort during extended gaming sessions. The sale price represents a modest discount over its original cost, making the HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 an even more attractive option for budget-conscious gamers. [Sources: Engadget, 2023-10-10, 2023-10-12, 2023-11-24]

name: ASTRO A40
description: The Astro A40 is a gaming headset that provides a wider and more balanced sound than the HyperX Cloud Stinger 2. [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: LOGITECH G535
description: The Logitech G535 is a wireless gaming headset, recognized as an honorable mention in the gaming headsets guide, currently priced at $80, which is $25 below its average street price. This headset is lightweight and offers Bluetooth support, making it a suitable choice for gamers seeking a wireless option under $100. It provides relatively well-balanced sound, although users may need to crank up the volume to achieve a listenable level. The microphone, while functional, tends to make voices sound thin. Additionally, it's important to note that the Logitech G535 does not work with Xbox consoles. Despite these drawbacks, the headset boasts a decent battery life, lasting between 30 to 35 hours per charge, enhancing its appeal for extended gaming sessions.

name: SHOKZ OPENRUN PRO
description: The SHOKZ OPENRUN PRO is a sophisticated model of bone conduction headphones, designed to provide an enhanced listening experience without compromising situational awareness. This innovative device gently wraps around the sides of the head, transmitting sound through vibrations that travel along the skull, ensuring that the ear canals remain completely open. As noted by Engadget on 2023-10-10 and 2023-10-12, the OpenRun Pro stands out from its competitors by delivering a richer audio experience with more pronounced low-end depth, making it particularly appealing for music and podcast enthusiasts. The headphones are not only comfortable for extended wear but also boast an impressive battery life of up to 10 hours. During Prime Big Deal Days, the SHOKZ OPENRUN PRO is available at a special price of $125, offering potential buyers an excellent opportunity to acquire a high-quality audio accessory that seamlessly integrates into their active lifestyle.

name: HEADPHONES
description: Headphones are a product category that includes in-ear devices, some of which may not perform as well in noisy environments and may not sound as full as traditional models [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: JON TURI
description: Jon Turi is an Engadget Editor who found a specific pair of headphones to deliver more low-end depth than most of its peers [Engadget, 2023-11-24]

name: MICHIGAN
description:
Michigan, or the University of Michigan, is a prominent college football team within the Big Ten conference, currently coached by Jim Harbaugh. As of December 2023, the Wolverines are ranked No. 2 and have experienced a historic season on the field, although they recently suffered a loss to Iowa in the Big Ten championship game, potentially impacting their standing in the CFP rankings. Off the field, Michigan has been embroiled in a sign-stealing scandal, with allegations that the team has been illegally recording signals and stealing signs for two-and-a-half years, potentially giving them an unfair advantage. The scandal involves now-fired staffer Connor Stalions and has led to an investigation by the NCAA into alleged illegal in-person scouting, where the team is accused of purchasing tickets to opponents' games to spy on them.

The university has responded to these allegations, arguing that any punishment before the completion of a full NCAA investigation would be premature and that the use of electronic recordings is limited to field equipment used for the current game, questioning the material effect of the alleged observations on the competition's integrity. Despite initial resistance, Michigan has dropped its litigation against the Big Ten over Harbaugh's three-game suspension and will accept the punishment. The university has also filed a temporary restraining order against the Big Ten to delay the suspension, expressing frustration with the conference's process.

Big Ten coaches have expressed frustration over the new Big Ten commissioner's perceived lack of action against Michigan, feeling that the commissioner is not motivated to address the Wolverines' alleged misconduct. Michigan has alleged that in-person scouting and sign-stealing are common practices across the NCAA, suggesting that the issue is not unique to their program. The team is facing potential punishment from the Big Ten conference for the sign-stealing scheme and is awaiting word on a potential suspension due to a violation of the Big Ten Sportsmanship Policy.

Notably, Michigan's football program has produced standout players, such as Kris Jenkins, who is projected to be picked by Kansas City in the 2024 NFL Draft. The team's performance and the ongoing investigations have been significant news in the college football landscape, with updates and developments being closely followed by major sports outlets including The New York Times, Sporting News, and CBSSports.com.

name: CONNOR STALIONS
description: Connor Stalions, a now-fired and suspended former Michigan football analyst and staffer, is central to an ongoing NCAA investigation regarding an alleged sign-stealing scheme. The controversy escalated when it was revealed that Stalions had purchased tickets to over 35 games involving Big Ten and potential College Football Playoff (CFP) opponents, a move that included games in at least seven Big Ten stadiums before those teams faced the Wolverines over the past three seasons. His actions have raised questions about ethical boundaries in scouting and competitive intelligence, with implications for the integrity of collegiate sports. Stalions' resignation came amid the investigation, which also includes allegations of his appearance on Central Michigan's sideline, further complicating the narrative around his role and the extent of the scheme. [Sources: Sporting News, 2023-11-06; The Sporting News, 2023-11-11; The New York Times, 2023-11-03]

name: JIM HARBAUGH
description: Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of the University of Michigan Wolverines football team, is embroiled in a sign-stealing scandal that has led to significant repercussions within the Big Ten conference and the NCAA. Despite initial denials of knowledge regarding the alleged impermissible, in-person scouting operation that spanned multiple years, Harbaugh has been suspended for the remaining three regular season games by the Big Ten, a decision that came while the team was en route to Penn State for a game. This suspension was confirmed on November 11, 2023, and Sherrone Moore has temporarily taken over coaching duties in Harbaugh's absence. The team has warned against "premature" disciplinary action against Harbaugh, indicating support amidst the controversy. Harbaugh is scheduled to state his case at a hearing on November 17, 2023, as he requests the opportunity to prove his innocence. The NCAA investigation into the sign-decoding allegations could result in further punishment for Harbaugh, as he is facing potential suspension or additional penalties. The Athletic's Pete Thamel reported on ESPN's "College GameDay" that Harbaugh is "likely" to face suspension, adding to the speculation surrounding the coach's future. Harbaugh's suspension and the ongoing investigation have caused frustration among Big Ten coaches, as evidenced by their reactions following a video call with commissioner Tony Petitti. The scandal has cast a shadow over Harbaugh's return to coaching on Monday, November 25, 2023, as reported by Sporting News, and the involvement of Connor Stalions in the sign-stealing scheme has further complicated the situation.

name: THE BIG TEN
description: The Big Ten, a prominent collegiate athletic conference, has recently been involved in a situation concerning Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of one of its member institutions. As of November 6, 2023, reports from Sporting News indicated that the conference was considering a suspension for Harbaugh. Later that day, the Big Ten confirmed the decision, officially suspending Jim Harbaugh for three games. This action taken by the organization highlights its commitment to maintaining standards and discipline within the conference.

name: PENN STATE
description: Penn State, an esteemed educational institution renowned for its football team, was scheduled to engage in a competitive football game against the University of Michigan Wolverines. This match-up was highly anticipated, as evidenced by the attention it garnered from notable sports sources such as Chris Vannini and Pete Thamel's Twitter, both reporting on the event on 2023-11-10 and 2023-11-11, respectively. However, the dynamics of the game were influenced by recent events within the Big Ten conference, where Michigan's head coach, Jim Harbaugh, faced a suspension, as reported by The Sporting News on 2023-11-06. Despite Harbaugh's absence, Michigan managed to secure a victory over Penn State, with Sherrone Moore taking the reins as the coach for that game, according to The Sporting News on 2023-11-11. This outcome highlights the competitive nature of collegiate football and the strategic challenges teams face when key personnel are unavailable.

name: CHRIS PARTRIDGE
description: Chris Partridge is the linebackers coach from Michigan who was fired on Friday and is alleged to have destroyed evidence on a computer pertaining to the sign-stealing allegations [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: UNCLE T
description: Uncle T is a Michigan booster who is named as having at least partially funded Connor Stalions in the NCAA's investigation into the sign-stealing and advanced scouting operation [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: NCAA
description: The NCAA, the governing body for college sports in the United States, is conducting an ongoing investigation into the University of Michigan's football program, specifically focusing on the alleged sign-stealing and advanced scouting operation. The scandal involves the Michigan Wolverines and centers around claims that the team violated NCAA rules by engaging in prohibited in-person, on-campus scouting and the audio or video recording of signals. The investigation has revealed that football analyst Connor Stalions was at least partially funded by a Michigan booster and is accused of buying tickets to scout future opponents in-person and possibly appearing on Central Michigan's sideline in Chippewas gear for a game against Michigan State. The University of Michigan is cooperating fully with the NCAA's probe. The NCAA is also considering further punishment for head coach Jim Harbaugh. As of the last update, no final decision has been made regarding potential punishment for the alleged violations. The investigation is moving slowly, as is typical for such cases.

name: BIFF POGGI
description: Biff Poggi, a former assistant coach for the Wolverines and a trusted confidant of Jim Harbaugh, currently holds the position of head coach for the Charlotte 49ers football team. In a recent development, Poggi has made headlines by extending an open invitation to Harbaugh to join him on the sidelines for the next two Charlotte football games, showcasing a strong bond and mutual respect between the two coaches. This gesture not only highlights Poggi's leadership style but also underscores the potential for a collaborative and supportive relationship within the coaching community. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: CHARLOTTE
description: Charlotte is an organization whose head coach, Biff Poggi, has offered Jim Harbaugh an invitation to join him on the sidelines for the next two Charlotte football games [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: SOUTH FLORIDA
description: South Florida, known for its vibrant community and diverse activities, is highlighted in two distinct contexts. Firstly, it is identified as an organization in the realm of sports, set to compete against Charlotte on November 25, as reported by Sporting News on November 6, 2023. Secondly, South Florida is also recognized as a location that hosted a notable event for digital marketers. This gathering, covered by The Verge on November 1, 2023, featured an impressive 10-foot alligator as a unique gimmick, reflecting the area's penchant for unconventional and engaging entertainment options. Despite the dual nature of the entity in these descriptions, both underscore the dynamic and active nature of South Florida's community and events.

name: CHARLOTTE 49ERS
description: The Charlotte 49ers are a football team coached by Biff Poggi. They have upcoming games against Rice on Saturday, November 18, 2023, and at South Florida on November 25, 2023. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: BIG TEN
description: The Big Ten is a collegiate athletic conference, prominently featuring Michigan, that has been grappling with a sign-stealing scandal involving the University of Michigan's football team. Coaches within the conference have expressed frustration over the situation, which they believe has been inadequately addressed by the new Big Ten commissioner, Tony Petitti. The Big Ten has taken several actions in response to the allegations, including issuing a notice of discipline to Michigan and suspending its head coach, Jim Harbaugh, for three games amidst claims of his involvement in the impermissible, in-person scouting operation that violated the conference's Sportsmanship Policy. However, the league has also stated that it is not aware of any evidence suggesting Harbaugh's direct knowledge of the illegal sign-stealing scheme. The Big Ten is currently reviewing Michigan's official response to the sign-decoding allegations and is considering a range of punishments, such as a suspension or a significant fine, while awaiting the NCAA's investigation results. The Compliance and Reinstatement Committee will play a role in recommending penalties for this rules violation. Amidst these developments, Jonathan Smith has joined the Big Ten as the new football coach at Michigan State University. The conference's actions demonstrate its commitment to upholding integrity and fair play within its member institutions.

name: UNIVERSITY OF MICHIGAN
description:
The University of Michigan, a renowned educational institution, has recently made headlines in multiple arenas. In the field of health, the university conducted a study that compiled data from various sources, suggesting a striking similarity between addiction to ultra-processed foods and that to substances like alcohol, tobacco, and even drugs, due to the presence of 'feel-good chemicals' in these foods. This research, reported by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-19, highlights the potential for food addiction to have serious health implications akin to those of substance abuse.

Meanwhile, in the realm of computer science and engineering, the University of Michigan is home to Roya Ensafi, an assistant professor recognized for her expertise and contributions to the field. This information was shared by Engadget on 2023-10-16, showcasing the university's commitment to academic excellence and its role in shaping the future of technology.

On the sports front, the university's football team, the Wolverines, has been embroiled in a sign-stealing scandal, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-11-06. This controversy has brought attention to the competitive nature of collegiate sports and the ethical standards expected of athletes and teams.

Despite the diverse nature of these events, they collectively paint a picture of the University of Michigan as a multifaceted institution, engaged in significant research, fostering technological innovation, and navigating the challenges of competitive sports.

name: SANTA ONO
description: Santa Ono is the president of the University of Michigan, who praised the Wolverines for handling challenges and adversity, including the current controversy. [Source: Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: WARDE MANUEL
description: Warde Manuel is the athletic director of the University of Michigan, who issued a strong statement against the Big Ten conference's suspension of Jim Harbaugh, describing it as "completely unethical" and an "assault on the rights of everyone (especially in the Big Ten) to be judged by a fair and complete investigation." [Source: Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: PETE THAMEL
description: Pete Thamel, a prominent sports journalist, is known for his in-depth coverage of college sports, particularly focusing on significant developments within the realm of football. As of 2023, Thamel has been reporting on multiple high-profile stories involving Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of the University of Michigan's football team. Thamel first broke the news regarding Harbaugh's expected travel to State College amidst the ongoing Michigan sign-stealing scandal, a story that Thamel has been closely following. He then reported on the suspension of Jim Harbaugh, detailing the legal actions taken by the University of Michigan against the Big Ten conference in response to the controversy. It is noteworthy that Thamel has contributed to both ESPN and The Athletic, showcasing his versatility and reach within the sports journalism industry. His reporting on these events has been instrumental in keeping the public informed about the complex dynamics and legal implications within college football.

name: SHERRONE MOORE
description: Sherrone Moore, a significant figure in the University of Michigan football team, stepped up as the acting head coach in place of Jim Harbaugh during a critical game against Penn State. This occurred on November 11, 2023, as confirmed by Adam Rittenberg's Twitter and a report by The Sporting News. Moore's performance was not only commendable but also emotionally charged. After securing a victory against Penn State, Moore was visibly moved and expressed his deep affection and respect for Coach Harbaugh in a post-game interview. This event highlights Moore's capability to lead the team effectively in Harbaugh's absence and his strong bond with the head coach, showcasing his dedication to the Michigan football program.

name: CAROL KUNHKE
description: Carol Kunhke is the judge handling the case of Jim Harbaugh's suspension, and she is a Michigan alumnus [source: Pete Thamel's Twitter, 2023-11-11]

name: TIMOTHY P. CONNORS
description: Timothy P. Connors, a prominent figure in both academia and the judicial system, serves as the judicial officer for Michigan's temporary restraining order request as of November 2023. In addition to his judicial responsibilities, Connors enriches the educational landscape as a lecturer at the University of Michigan (U-M) and an adjunct professor at Wayne State University and the University of Vermont. His dual roles in law and education demonstrate his commitment to public service and the dissemination of knowledge.

name: U-M REGENTS
description: U-M regents are part of the plaintiffs in the temporary restraining order request against the Big Ten and Tony Petitti [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: TONY PETITTI
description: Tony Petitti, the commissioner of the Big Ten conference, found himself at the center of a controversy involving the University of Michigan (U-M) in November 2023. Initially, he was mentioned as one of the defendants in a temporary restraining order request filed by Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of the Michigan Wolverines, and U-M regents, as reported by Sporting News on November 6, 2023. This legal action was presumably related to allegations of a sign-stealing scheme by Michigan, which had caused significant frustration among Big Ten coaches. The New York Times, on November 3, 2023, detailed that Petitti, in his role as the new Big Ten commissioner, was on a video call with the conference's coaches where these concerns were voiced. Despite the mounting pressure, Petitti, as confirmed by Heather Dinich on November 9, 2023, was not attending the College Football Playoff (CFB) meeting. Instead, he was tasked with deciding how to proceed with potential discipline against Michigan, indicating his pivotal role in resolving the dispute within the conference.

name: J.J. MCCARTHY
description: J.J. McCarthy, a prominent Michigan player, is recognized as one of the leaders of the Wolverines, a distinguished and talented sports team. In a display of loyalty and support, McCarthy responded to Jim Harbaugh's suspension by tweeting the succinct yet powerful message "Bet" on November 6, 2023, as reported by Sporting News. Adding to this demonstration, McCarthy was also seen wearing a "Free Harbaugh" shirt when Harbaugh was serving a separate suspension at the beginning of the season, further highlighting his commitment to his coach and team. This incident underscores McCarthy's role not only as a player but also as a vocal and influential figure within the Wolverines community. As of November 11, 2023, according to Sporting News, McCarthy continues to be a key leader for the team, contributing significantly to its dynamics and success.

name: MICHIGAN PLAYERS
description: Michigan players, including J.J. McCarthy, responded to Jim Harbaugh's suspension by tweeting "Bet" at the same time on Friday night [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: MICHIGAN WOLVERINES
description:
The Michigan Wolverines, the football team representing the University of Michigan, have been a dynamic force in the realm of collegiate sports. Under the guidance of head coach Jim Harbaugh, the team has showcased impressive performances, securing victories in the Big Ten championship game for the past two consecutive years. However, their journey has not been without challenges, as they have faced subsequent losses in the College Football Playoff (CFP) semifinals. Adding to their trials, the Wolverines are currently entangled in an ongoing NCAA investigation, which has brought additional scrutiny and pressure upon the team, including the potential for punishment from the Big Ten conference.

Despite these hurdles, the Michigan Wolverines have demonstrated remarkable resilience and unity, maintaining a strong team spirit and commitment to playing for each other. The story of the 2023 season for the Wolverines is still unfolding, with Harbaugh returning to the sidelines on Monday after serving a suspension that affected the team's performance for the remainder of the regular season. The team's ability to persevere through adversity and their coach's return signal that the Wolverines are poised to continue their competitive drive, with the hope of overcoming the current investigations and achieving further success on the field.

name: STATE COLLEGE
description: State College is the location where Michigan's football team is heading for a game against Penn State [source: Chris Vannini, 2023-11-10]

name: CHRIS VANNINI
description: Chris Vannini is a journalist who reported on the Big Ten's statement regarding Michigan's violation of the Sportsmanship Policy and Jim Harbaugh's suspension [source: Chris Vannini, 2023-11-10]

name: ADAM RITTENBERG
description: Adam Rittenberg, a seasoned journalist working for ESPN, has been closely following the developments within the Big Ten conference. In a report dated November 6, 2023, Rittenberg informed the public about the Big Ten's contemplation of various penalties for Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of the Michigan Wolverines, which could potentially include a substantial financial fine. Four days later, on November 10, 2023, Rittenberg updated the story, noting that Michigan was still awaiting official communication from the Big Ten regarding the impending punishment, even as the team prepared for an upcoming flight scheduled for 1 p.m. ET. Rittenberg's coverage highlights his expertise in sports journalism and his commitment to providing timely updates on critical issues affecting the Big Ten and its member institutions.

name: ESPN
description: ESPN is a comprehensive sports media organization, part of the ESPN family of networks carried by Fubo, that offers a wide range of services and coverage in the world of sports. The ESPN app provides live streaming options for various football games, including the Colorado vs. UCLA match, as reported by Sporting News on October 28, 2023. ESPN is also known for its authoritative rankings for the College Football Playoff (CFP), featuring the Football Power Index and strength of record, as noted by Sporting News on December 1, 2023. Beyond football, ESPN extends its coverage to international baseball, reporting on the Giants' meeting with Japanese ace Yoshinobu Yamamoto, as mentioned in an ESPN article on December 23, 2023. Additionally, the network has been involved in reporting on Shohei Ohtani's free agency and his potential interest in the Boston Red Sox. ESPN's investigative journalism is exemplified by its coverage of the Michigan sign-stealing scandal, with Adam Rittenberg and Pete Thamel associated with the network, as reported by Adam Rittenberg on November 10, 2023. ESPN is the go-to broadcaster for major football games, including the Ole Miss vs. Georgia game on November 11, 2023, with Chris Fowler, Kirk Herbstreit, and Holly Rowe on the call, and the Chicago Bears vs. Minnesota Vikings game on November 27, 2023, featuring Joe Buck as the play-by-play announcer, Troy Aikman as the color analyst, and Lisa Salters providing updates from the sidelines.

name: TOM MARS
description: Tom Mars is an attorney representing Jim Harbaugh, who reportedly told ESPN that the coach will be headed to State College regardless of the punishment [source: Pete Thamel, 2023-11-10]

name: HEATHER DINICH
description: Heather Dinich is a journalist for ESPN who reported on the Big Ten's potential punishment for Michigan and Jim Harbaugh. She noted that any punishment beyond two games or a $10,000 fine would require special permission from an executive board. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: DAN WETZEL
description: Dan Wetzel is a journalist for Yahoo Sports who posted Michigan's full 10-page letter to the Big Ten on X (formerly Twitter). [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

description: Penn State is a university that is scheduled to play against Michigan in a football game. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]
