description: Tony Pettiti is the commissioner of the Big Ten who is not attending the College Football Playoff meeting on Thursday, leading to speculation about imminent punishment in Michigan's sign-stealing scandal. [Source: Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: OHIO STATE
description:
Ohio State, formally known as Ohio State University, is a prominent educational institution and a member of the Big Ten conference, actively participating in the realm of college sports. The university's football team, also referred to as Ohio State, is renowned for its roster filled with raw talent, a factor that has placed them in the spotlight alongside other top teams like Georgia and Alabama. Despite their high ranking, the team has experienced significant setbacks, including a notable loss to the Michigan Wolverines, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-11-25. This defeat has left them with a single loss on their record, a status that could potentially be overtaken by Alabama in the College Football Playoff (CFP) rankings, according to Sporting News on 2023-12-01. At the time of the report, Ohio State was ranked No. 6 in the CFP, ahead of Alabama.

The team has also been embroiled in controversy, facing accusations of sharing Michigan's play signals with Purdue before a crucial Big Ten championship game in 2022. These allegations, as mentioned by Sporting News on 2023-11-06, have been vehemently denied by Ohio State's head coach, Ryan Day. The incident has added to the complex dynamics within the Big Ten conference, highlighting the competitive nature and the importance of fair play in collegiate sports.

name: RYAN DAY
description: Ryan Day is the coach of Ohio State. He was asked about the allegations that Ohio State had given information about Michigan's signs to Purdue before the Big Ten championship game in 2022. He denied the allegations [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: PURDUE
description: Purdue, formally known as Purdue University, is a prominent educational institution and a member of the Big Ten conference in the realm of college sports. The university's football team, also referred to as Purdue, has been at the center of a controversy involving allegations of sign-stealing and scouting. In 2022, prior to the Big Ten championship game, it was alleged that Purdue was given information about Michigan's play signals by Ohio State, as reported by Sporting News on November 6, 2023. The team's coach, Ryan Walters, further fueled the controversy by publicly commenting on the allegations against Michigan, asserting that the accusations were based on attending their games, as detailed in The New York Times on November 3, 2023. Additionally, Purdue University has faced accusations of compiling documents based on information provided not only by Ohio State but also by Rutgers, contributing to the complex dynamics within the Big Ten conference.

name: RUTGERS
description: RUTGERS, or Rutgers University, is a university and a member of the Big Ten conference, accused of sharing intelligence on Michigan's signals

name: RYAN WALTERS
description: Ryan Walters, the head coach of the Purdue football team, confirmed Michigan's alleged sign-stealing and scouting activities in November 2023. He stated that there is substantial evidence supporting these claims, including video footage and ticket purchase records, which he discussed on his radio show. Walters went further, publicly calling for action against Michigan and asserting that the allegations have evolved beyond mere speculation, according to reports by The New York Times on November 3, 2023, and Sporting News on November 6, 2023.

name: THE QUIET YEAR
description:
"The Quiet Year is a modern classic and elegantly designed tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG) that has gained recognition for its unique mechanics and portable nature. It was a standout game of the year for the author, who successfully ran it for their niece, aged 4 at the time, and nephew, aged 8. The game ensures that every player gets a turn, ritualizes dissent and discussion, and incorporates a sheet of blank paper for drawing, enhancing the creative and interactive experience. Its versatility is further highlighted by its use as a prologue in other popular TTRPGs like Friends at the Table and The Adventure Zone. The Quiet Year's appeal is evident from the nephew's request to have the entire [Polygon, 2023-12-13] group play the game, affectionately referred to as 'the skulls game,' indicating its memorable and engaging qualities." 

Note: The reference to "[Polygon, 2023-12-13]" seems out of place in the context of the description. It might be a citation or a placeholder for additional information. If it's meant to be part of the description, it could be referring to a group or an event related to Polygon, possibly a gaming community or a gaming event. However, without further context, it's unclear what specific information this date and source are meant to convey. In the summary, I've kept it in brackets to indicate that it might be a citation or additional detail that requires clarification.

name: THE ONE RING
description: The One Ring is a modern classic tabletop role-playing game that has made a second appearance on Polygon's list of impactful TTRPGs

name: CITY OF WINTER
description: City of Winter is a tabletop role-playing game that focuses on themes of assimilation, diaspora, and baggage, with a cloth map illustrating a landscape and lightweight rules

name: LINDA CODEGA
description: Linda Codega is an Ennie Award-winning entertainment journalist who shared her experience playing City of Winter with friends

name: DEAD AFTER DINNER
description: "Dead After Dinner is a pick-up-and-play tabletop role-playing game that masterfully blends procedural revelation with a murder mystery theme, akin to the engaging and humorous style found in the movie 'Knives Out.' The game offers two distinct scenarios for players to explore: a struggling Kansas town on the brink of starvation and a cursed fishing boat. Unique to Dead After Dinner are the spoken text cards that players assign to their characters, adding depth and personality to the gameplay. The game's tone is further enhanced by the artistic touch of faux woodcuts by Jabari Weathers and Brennen Reece, which complement the flavorful card text, creating an immersive and entertaining experience for all participants. As of 2023-12-13, Dead After Dinner has been recognized by Polygon for its innovative approach to gaming and its ability to provide a hilarious and engaging experience for players."

name: JASON MORNINGSTAR
description: Jason Morningstar, a prominent figure in the tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG) community, is recognized for his multifaceted role at Bully Pulpit Games, where he serves as the owner, creative director, and lead designer. In 2023, Morningstar gained attention for designing Desperation, a card-driven TTRPG that was notably played and enjoyed by Tim Hutchings, as reported by Polygon on December 13, 2023. Additionally, Morningstar's expertise extends to murder mystery games, as evidenced by his recommendation of Dead After Dinner, a pick-up-and-play title that exemplifies his knack for creating engaging and accessible gaming experiences.

name: TIM HUTCHINGS
description: Tim Hutchings, a renowned game designer and academic, had a remarkable year in 2023, during which he played several games. Among these, he identified two games as the best he played that year: Desperation, designed by Jason Morningstar, and Orestes' Choice, created by Susanne Vejdemo. His appreciation for these games was highlighted in an article by Polygon on December 13, 2023. Hutchings' expertise in the gaming industry and academia lends significant weight to his opinion, making these recommendations particularly noteworthy for both casual gamers and industry professionals.

name: DESPERATION
description: "Desperation, a card-driven Tabletop Role-Playing Game (TTRPG) masterminded by Jason Morningstar, stands out with its innovative gameplay mechanics. In this game, players draw cards inscribed with spoken text, which they then assign to their characters, facilitating an immersive and tightly woven narrative experience. Desperation offers two scenarios steeped in the dark ambiance of American Gothic, enhancing the game's thematic richness. The game's visual appeal is further bolstered by the artistic talents of Jabari Weathers and Brennen Reece, whose artwork graces its pages. This information was reported by Polygon on December 13, 2023."

name: ORESTES’ CHOICE
description: Orestes’ Choice is a LARP (Live Action Role-Playing Game) designed by Susanne Vejdemo. It is a chamber LARP with a heavy-duty theme, where players swap roles and play through a queer Greek myth involving young Orestes returning home to decide whether to kill his mother and father-in-law. The game includes erotically charged practice stabbing. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DUNGEON CRAWL CLASSICS
description: Dungeon Crawl Classics is an RPG system by Goodman Games. It has aesthetics influenced by greats like Leiber and Moorcock, volatile magic, a relatively flat power curve, and an emphasis on player skill over effective builds. DCC is not a heroic power fantasy like D&D 5e or Pathfinder, nor is it minimalist like many old-school games. It feels like playing through a Bal-Sagoth or Eternal Champion song. It is easy to pick up for groups with experience in D&D’s third edition or Pathfinder. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: SUSANNE VEJDEMO
description: Susanne Vejdemo is the designer of Orestes’ Choice, a LARP that Tim Hutchings played and enjoyed in 2023. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: THILO GRAF
description: Thilo Graf of AAW Games played and enjoyed Dungeon Crawl Classics by Goodman Games in 2023. He also wrote the Survivalist’s Guide to Spelunking for 5e, a book inspired by DCC's simple and impactful rules. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DCC
description: DCC is a tabletop role-playing game that feels like playing through a Bal-Sagoth or Eternal Champion song. It has simple, impactful rules and was a core design inspiration for the Survivalist’s Guide to Spelunking for 5e, a book written by the author with Douglas Niles and Stephen Yeardley. DCC authors, judges, and players use the book as well![]

name: SURVIVALIST’S GUIDE TO SPUELUNKING FOR 5E
description: The Survivalist’s Guide to Spelunking for 5e is a book that was written with a focus on simple, impactful rules, inspired by DCC. It was written by the author with Douglas Niles and Stephen Yeardley.[]

name: DOUGLAS NILES
description: Douglas Niles is one of the co-authors of the Survivalist’s Guide to Spelunking for 5e, a book inspired by DCC.[]

name: STEPHEN YEARDLEY
description: Stephen Yeardley is one of the co-authors of the Survivalist’s Guide to Spelunking for 5e, a book inspired by DCC.[]

name: HEROES’ FEAST
description: Heroes’ Feast is a game hosted by Mike Haracz, a corporate R&D chef.[]

name: MIKE HARACZ
description: Mike Haracz is a corporate R&D chef and host of Heroes’ Feast. He is in the seventh year of a homebrew Dungeons & Dragons campaign.[]

name: THE HEARTSGUARD SAGA
description: The Heartsguard Saga is a homebrew Dungeons & Dragons campaign played by Mike Haracz and his friends in the Chicagoland area.[]

name: DEVEN RUE
description: Deven Rue is the creator of the map of Euphoros, which is the basis for Mike Haracz’s homebrew Dungeons & Dragons campaign, The Heartsguard Saga.[]

name: EUPHOROS
description: Euphoros is a place on a map created by Deven Rue, which is the basis for Mike Haracz’s homebrew Dungeons & Dragons campaign, The Heartsguard Saga.[]

name: PETRANA RADULOVIC
description: Petrana Radulovic is an entertainment reporter who started playing Dungeons & Dragons in 2020. She has two separate D&D groups in 2023, both with enthusiastic members who are committed to at least trying to meet regularly.[]

name: D&D
description: Dungeons & Dragons, commonly abbreviated as D&D, is a renowned tabletop role-playing game that has captured the imagination of players across North America and beyond. The game is characterized by its rich class system, which, although sharing some similarities with the video game Baldur's Gate 3, does not fully align with the distinctions found in that digital adaptation. As a community analyst, it is noted that the author has been actively engaged in playing D&D with various groups spread out across North America, highlighting the game's enduring appeal and its ability to foster connections among players despite geographical distances. This engagement underscores the game's versatility and the passion it inspires among its community, who often find creative ways to come together and enjoy the collaborative storytelling experience that D&D offers.

name: SAM DUNNEWOLD
description: Sam Dunnewold is a person associated with the Dice Exploder podcast who has been thinking about the game Eating Oranges in the Shower [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DICE EXPLODER PODCAST
description: Dice Exploder podcast is a media source that Sam Dunnewold is associated with [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: EATING ORANGES IN THE SHOWER
description: Eating Oranges in the Shower is a game about members of a group chat who discover the /r/ShowerOrange subreddit and decide to try eating an orange in the shower for themselves [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: /R/SHOWERORANGE
description: /r/ShowerOrange is a real online community dedicated to the act of eating an orange while taking a shower [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: HAZEL ANNEKE DIXON
description: Hazel Anneke Dixon is the game designer who created Eating Oranges in the Shower [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: EXQUISITE BIOME
description: Exquisite Biome is a tabletop role-playing game in the world-building tradition that focuses on ecological biomes and the creatures that populate them [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: CARO ASERCION
description: Caro Asercion, a talented game designer, is recognized for co-creating the innovative game "Exquisite Biome," as well as being the sole creator of "I’m Sorry Did You Say Street Magic," a unique GM-less city-building game. Both achievements were highlighted in Polygon on the same day, 2023-12-13, showcasing Asercion's diverse skills and contributions to the gaming community.

name: SI SWEETMAN
description: Si Sweetman is an illustrator who contributed to Exquisite Biome [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: FETCH MY BLADE
description: "Fetch My Blade is a captivating solo journaling role-playing game, masterminded by the creative duo Kelly Tran and Ethan Yen. This game offers players the flexibility to engage in the narrative without the constraints of scheduling or time commitments, making it accessible for busy individuals who still crave immersive storytelling experiences. In Fetch My Blade, players take on the persona of a loyal dog belonging to a retired legendary sword master. The central quest involves the retrieval of the master's fabled weapon, a journey that is fraught with challenges and revelations. The game mechanics are driven by three six-sided dice, which players use to navigate the passage of time, confront and overcome treacherous encounters, and gradually uncover the hidden truths of their master's illustrious past. The dice-based system adds an element of unpredictability and excitement, ensuring that no two gaming sessions are alike. Fetch My Blade is not just a game; it's a narrative adventure that allows players to explore the world through the eyes of a faithful companion, all while unraveling the mysteries of a retired hero's life."

name: KELLY TRAN
description: Kelly Tran, a talented game creator, is recognized for co-creating Fetch My Blade, a captivating solo journaling role-playing game. This innovative game, designed for individual players to immerse themselves in a narrative-driven experience, was developed under Tran's creative vision, showcasing her expertise in the realm of entertainment and technology. The game's release and Kelly Tran's involvement were highlighted by Polygon on December 13, 2023, solidifying her status as a significant figure in the gaming community.

name: ETHAN YEN
description: Ethan Yen, a notable figure in the gaming community, is recognized for his significant role as a co-creator of Fetch My Blade, a solo journaling role-playing game that was highlighted by Polygon on December 13, 2023. This game, which blends elements of traditional role-playing with the introspective practice of journaling, has garnered attention for its unique approach to solo gameplay, positioning Ethan Yen as an innovative game creator in the technology and entertainment space.

name: HOME
description: Home is a tabletop role-playing game that can be played with a full table of players or alone as a solo journaling experience. It is a haunted house exploration simulator that uses custom tarot cards and a whiteboard to track your character’s progress as they dare to shine a light on the chilling danger of a variety of potential scenarios full of ghosts and other dark entities. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: WESLEY “NOX” CROWE
description: Wesley “Nox” Crowe, also known as Noxweiler Berf, is the creative director for Hunters Entertainment and a fan of the tabletop role-playing game Home. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: HUNTERS ENTERTAINMENT
description: Hunters Entertainment is the company for which Wesley “Nox” Crowe serves as creative director. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DOUG LEVANDOWSKI
description: Doug Levandowski is one of the creators of the tabletop role-playing game Home. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: YEONSOO JULIAN KIM
description: Yeonsoo Julian Kim is one of the creators of the tabletop role-playing game Home. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: THE LUMINANT AGE
description: The Luminant Age is a tabletop role-playing game set in a unique world with ancestries named Blood, Clay, Silk, and Horn. The game features a city called Ourichor, built on giant oil-rig-like platforms in the open ocean, with three moons and a predominant religion, the Angelites, who memorialize their dead by preserving their eyeballs. The game is compatible with Pathfinder 2nd edition and has been enchantingly addictive, with supplements on creatures and equipment available. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: OURICHOR
description: Ourichor is a city in The Luminant Age, built on giant oil-rig-like platforms in the open ocean. There are no sun nor stars, but three moons. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: ANGELITES
description: The Angelites are a predominant religion in The Luminant Age, memorializing their dead by preserving their eyeballs, which can be worn as mourning jewelry. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: PATHFINDER 2ND EDITION
description: Pathfinder 2nd edition is a tabletop role-playing game that The Luminant Age is compatible with. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MARVEL MULTIVERSE ROLE-PLAYING GAME
description: Marvel Multiverse Role-playing Game is a tabletop role-playing game that gives players the feeling of playing a hero in the Marvel universe. The game features a system that is easy, streamlined, and carries the four-color comic book flavor. It includes an exhaustive list of Marvel heroes and villains, and allows players to create their own heroes with unique power sets. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MARVEL UNIVERSE
description: The Marvel Universe is a vibrant, fictional universe that serves as the setting for an extensive array of superheroes and villains, known for their captivating stories and iconic characters such as Spider-Man and the Hulk. In 2023, Polygon highlighted a game system inspired by this universe, which offers players an engaging and streamlined experience to create their own heroes. The game system is designed to capture the essence of the four-color comic book style, immersing players in the classic Marvel aesthetic and allowing them to explore their creativity within the rich lore of the Marvel Universe.

name: SPIDER-MAN
description: Spider-Man, a fictional superhero and a key Marvel character, has been a significant figure in popular culture since his first comic book appearance. He is well-known for embodying the struggles and ordinary frustrations that are part of life, even amidst his superhero persona. Spider-Man's presence has extended beyond comics and animated series to become a part of Thanksgiving celebrations, where he has notably appeared on floats and been inflated to an impressive 80 feet. However, his parade appearances have not been without incident; he is the only Marvel character to have had his head torn open by a tree branch during a parade, an event that further underscores the theme of setbacks and challenges that his character often represents. Additionally, Spider-Man's powers and characteristics have been utilized in a game system, providing a template for players to create their own heroes, highlighting his influence and versatility in the realm of entertainment.

name: THE HULK
description: The Hulk is another key Marvel hero whose powers and characteristics can be used as a basis for creating a player's own hero in the game system. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MASKS OF THE MASKS
description: Masks of the Masks is a tabletop role-playing game (RPG) created by Hazel Amber Goswick. It is presented as a fully illustrated comic book, an homage to Bronze Age superhero stories, and critically explores and examines the violence inherent in its medium. The game has brilliant mechanics that blend Belonging Outside Belonging and Powered by the Apocalypse systems, and it includes wicked advancement mechanics that heighten the sense of dread and tragedy essential to comics of that time period. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: HAZEL AMBER GOSWICK
description: Hazel Amber Goswick is the creator of Masks of the Masks, a tabletop RPG that is presented as a fully illustrated comic book and critically explores and examines the violence inherent in superhero stories. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: THE MONSTER OVERHAUL
description: The Monster Overhaul, a groundbreaking tabletop RPG supplement authored by Skerples, is celebrated for its innovative approach to monster design and bestiary creation. This comprehensive guide, described as a monstrous achievement by Polygon on 2023-12-13, not only reimagines traditional monsters but also challenges the very concept of what a bestiary should embody. The book is meticulously organized into 20 unique categories, each featuring 10 creatures that adhere to a specific theme, ranging from the conventional "Dragons" to the more abstract "Summer" and "A Wizard Did It." Its purpose is to equip game masters (GMs) with the tools and inspiration to think about monsters in fresh, unexpected ways, providing answers to questions on how to make these creatures feel new, how to recontextualize them within their game worlds, and how to subvert player expectations, thereby enhancing the gaming experience. The Monster Overhaul is highly recommended for every GM's shelf, offering a wealth of creative content and guidance for those looking to enrich their role-playing games with imaginative and engaging monster encounters.

name: SKERPLES
description: Skerples is the creator of The Monster Overhaul, a tabletop RPG supplement that reimagines monsters and the notion of a bestiary. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: REACH OF THE ROACH GOD
description: Reach of the Roach God is a hardcover book that is the high-watermark of A Thousand Thousand Islands (ATTI), a series of zines presenting a system-agnostic setting inspired by the folklore of Southeast Asia. It features Odoyoq, the roach god, and three schemes that can insinuate itself into the lives of non-roachkind, presented as traditional adventures and collections of facts. The book includes two gazetteers, a sourcebook on roaches, and Munkao’s fantastically disgusting artwork. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MONSTERHEARTS
description: Monsterhearts is a tabletop RPG game that the author played for the first time in three years. It was one of the first games the author ever played, and they played a one-shot with friends, mostly group game mastering. The game involved a gang of messy screw-ups who didn’t hugely get along, with the author's character having traded her old gender to the fae over the summer, and they tried to investigate a potential monster hunter, an NPC most of their characters found too cool to talk to. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MUNKAO
description: Munkao is an artist whose work is featured in Reach of the Roach God. His artwork is described as fantastically disgusting, with a focus on feelers, chitin, and filth, creating revolting visuals in the best possible way. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: ODOYOQ
description: Odoyoq is the roach god featured in Reach of the Roach God. It senses new ways to insinuate itself into the lives of non-roachkind, presenting three schemes that can lead to chaos in a small village, a monastery, and a necropolis. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MÖRK BORG
description: Mörk Borg is a TTRPG with a distinct art style that transports players into a doom metal fantasy setting. It was released in 2020 but gained popularity in 2023, offering a beginner-friendly experience with easy-to-run gameplay and a variety of classes for unsavory characters. The game provides hints at nefarious deeds in item descriptions and offers tools for dungeon and NPC character sheet generation [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: JASMINE BHULLAR
description: Jasmine Bhullar is a writer, content creator, and executive producer of DesiQuest. She played Mörk Borg in 2023 and appreciated its art style, easy-to-run gameplay, and the variety of unsavory character classes [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DESIQUEST
description: DesiQuest is a podcast where Jasmine Bhullar serves as an executive producer. The podcast is likely related to tabletop gaming and role-playing games [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: I'M SORRY DID YOU SAY STREET MAGIC
description: I’m Sorry Did You Say Street Magic is a TTRPG that emphasizes creative collaboration among players. It is mentioned alongside Mörk Borg as one of the best tabletop RPGs played in 2023 [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MADISON DURHAM
description: Madison Durham, a talented writer and journalist, serves as a staff writer at Reviewed, where she covers a variety of topics. In 2023, she shared her insights and experiences with tabletop games, specifically highlighting her appreciation for "I'm Sorry Did You Say Street Magic," a game that emphasizes creative collaboration among players. Madison's expertise in the realm of technology and entertainment allows her to engage with communities and provide valuable perspectives on gaming trends and dynamics. Her work at Reviewed and contributions to Polygon demonstrate her passion for exploring and sharing the intricacies of tabletop gaming culture.

name: REVIEWED
description: Reviewed is a media outlet recognized for its comprehensive coverage of diverse topics, prominently featuring reviews and articles. Madison Durham, a talented writer, is part of the Reviewed team, serving as a staff writer and contributing to the outlet's content, which notably includes insights on tabletop gaming. This publication is a valuable source of information for enthusiasts and consumers alike, providing in-depth analysis and updates on the latest trends and products in the tech and entertainment sectors. As of 2023-12-13, Reviewed continues to be a significant platform where Durham shares her expertise and perspectives, as reported by Polygon.

name: ORK BORG
description: Örk Borg is a tabletop game that has inspired other games like Pirate Borg and Abyss of Hallucinations. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: PIRATE BORG
description: Pirate Borg is a game that has sprung up this year, inspired by Örk Borg. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: ABYSS OF HALLUCINATIONS
description: Abyss of Hallucinations is an upcoming game by Chris Lockey, also inspired by Örk Borg. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: I’M SORRY DID YOU SAY STREET MAGIC
description: I’m Sorry Did You Say Street Magic is a GM-less city-building game played between a group of two to six people with a stack of index cards and writing utensils. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: TRIANGLE AGENCY
description: Triangle Agency is a recently launched tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG) that masterfully blends elements from The X-Files, Annihilation, and Control, with a distinct nod to the imaginative and mind-bending concepts of Robert Anton Wilson. The game is centered around a group of super-abled agents whose mission is to investigate and prevent ontological anomalies from unraveling the fabric of reality. Players have the exciting opportunity to craft supernaturally powered characters, each with unique abilities and backstories, to tackle these mysterious and dangerous phenomena. Triangle Agency has garnered significant praise for its innovative mechanics, captivating art, and thoughtful design, making it a standout addition to the TTRPG genre. This critical acclaim was highlighted in a Polygon article dated 2023-12-13, which recognized the game's potential to engage and captivate players with its intriguing premise and high-quality production values.

name: BRENNAN LEE MULLIGAN
description: Brennan Lee Mulligan, a game designer known for his innovative contributions to the gaming community, made a significant mark in 2023 by releasing the first official 5e homebrew. This milestone was widely recognized and reported by Polygon on December 13, 2023. Mulligan, not only a designer but also a multifaceted personality in the entertainment industry, is the host of Dimension 20, a popular show on Dropout. In an interview with Polygon on September 26, 2023, Mulligan expressed his view that the brand under his stewardship is in the most healthy and sustainable state it has ever been, reflecting his positive impact on both the gaming and entertainment communities.

name: STARTPLAYING.GAMES
description: StartPlaying.Games, as reported by Polygon on 2023-12-13, is a comprehensive tabletop gaming community that serves as both a meetup hub for players and a marketplace for hiring game masters. This platform facilitates the connection between players seeking engaging weekly gaming sessions and experienced game masters who can lead them, making it an essential destination for tabletop enthusiasts looking to enhance their gaming experiences.

name: TWILIGHT: 2000
description: "Twilight: 2000 is a tabletop role-playing game that immerses players in the challenging task of survival in the aftermath of a fictional nuclear conflict, set in the heart of Europe. This game is unique in that it is based in an alternate history where the Cold War escalated to a full-blown military confrontation, resulting in the involvement of an entire United States Marine division. The gameplay is driven by dice for gunplay and a playing-card-style system for encounter creation, providing a realistic simulation of a military career. It has gained significant popularity among a group of middle-aged men who found a new way to reconnect after years spent in isolation during the pandemic. The game's mechanics and setting have made it an instant hit, offering a compelling and engaging experience for those interested in post-apocalyptic scenarios and military role-playing."

name: AS YOU ’WICH
description: As You ’Wich is a party game that involves building hands and convincing others to eat disgusting sandwiches. It was played by the author and became a new favorite. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: CHARLIE HALL
description: Charlie Hall is a senior editor at Polygon who focuses on tabletop games. He believes that tabletop role-play should always take into account the audience that sits down to play. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: DISCORD
description: Discord, a versatile communication platform, is actively working on enhancing user experiences and prioritizing teen safety by integrating content filters and automated warnings, as reported by Engadget on 2023-10-19. The company is also exploring solutions for app portability, aiming to provide a seamless experience across various devices over the next few quarters. Discord's wide appeal is evident, as it is used by individuals like Moni, mentioned in TechCrunch on 2023-10-26, to share insights and experiences from events such as the 2023 TwitchCon in Las Vegas. Additionally, as noted by Polygon on 2023-12-13, Discord serves as a tool for organizing friendly gaming sessions, specifically Call of Duty's DMZ mode, and facilitates community building, enabling users to reconnect with others in their neighborhood, such as a group of dads. These diverse use cases highlight Discord's adaptability and its role as a central hub for communication and community engagement in the technology and entertainment sectors.

name: PROJECT ECCO
description: Project ECCO is a solo TTRPG that found a balance between narrative and mechanics. It's a story of time travel and cosmic horror, easy to get into and relatively quick to play (three to 10 hours per game). The game uses hundreds of narrative prompts, various time travel “devices” (coins, dice, tarot cards, etc.), and has an absolutely stunning layout [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: MY FIRST DUNGEON
description: My First Dungeon is a podcast that featured a Project ECCO miniseason with game designer Elliot Davis. The podcast provides an example of gameplay and a masterfully produced actual play [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: ELLIOT DAVIS
description: Elliot Davis is a game designer who was featured in the Project ECCO miniseason of My First Dungeon podcast [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: EM FRIEDMAN
description: Em Friedman is an associate professor of English at Auburn University and a Polygon contributor. They noted The Quiet Year as the standout game of this year [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: AUBURN UNIVERSITY
description: Auburn University is an institution where Em Friedman, an associate professor of English, teaches and contributes to Polygon [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: THE BEST TABLETOP RPGS WE PLAYED IN 2023
JAY DRAGON
description: Jay Dragon is a person who praised the elegance of The Quiet Year, a tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG)

name: KEERTHI SRIDHARAN
description: Keerthi Sridharan noted the way their game group used The Quiet Year as a prologue, similar to how Friends at the Table and The Adventure Zone have popularized this approach

name: DANNY QUACH
description: Danny Quach is a Digital Thiccness, TTRPG writer, designer, and performer who loves exploring themes of melancholy and loss in games

name: WHAT DUST REMAINS
description: What Dust Remains is a TTRPG designed by Bianca Canoza (aka Momatoes) that explores themes of despair, desperation, and sacrifice to leave a legacy. The game uses card-prompted questions and dice rolls to move the story along

name: BIANCA CANOZA
description: Bianca Canoza, aka Momatoes, is the 2022 Diana Jones Emerging Designer award winner and the designer of What Dust Remains

name: BIG BAD CON 2023
description: Big Bad Con 2023 is an event where Danny Quach played What Dust Remains with two other strangers who quickly became co-collaborators in the tragic world they built

name: THE WILDSSEA
description: The Wildsea, a captivating tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG) co-created by Felix Isaacs and Mythworks, is set in a vivid world dominated by fantastical vegetation. This game uniquely encourages players to embrace the roles of wildsailors, swashbuckling adventurers, and to develop rich, delightfully bizarre character concepts. The mechanics of The Wildsea are driven by a d6 dice pool system, adding an element of unpredictability and excitement to gameplay. Notably, The Wildsea was recognized for its excellence in the gaming community, winning an Ennie award in 2023, as reported by Polygon on December 13, 2023.

name: FELIX ISAACS
description: Felix Isaacs is a talented game designer known for creating The Wildsea, a captivating tabletop role-playing game (TTRPG). Discovered by the author earlier this year, The Wildsea has since gained a dedicated following, including the author and their players, who have come to love it for its richly imaginative world and innovative mechanics. As of December 13, 2023, Polygon has also recognized and praised The Wildsea, further solidifying Felix Isaacs' reputation as a skilled and creative force in the realm of TTRPGs.

name: MYTHWORKS
description: MYTHWORKS, a company operating in the realm of tabletop role-playing games (TTRPGs), is recognized for its collaborative efforts with Felix Isaacs in the creation of The Wildsea. This game, developed under the joint expertise of MYTHWORKS and Isaacs, has made a significant impact in the TTRPG community, as noted by Polygon on December 13, 2023. The Wildsea, a product of this collaboration, showcases the innovative and creative capabilities of MYTHWORKS, positioning the company as a notable player in the technology and entertainment sector, specifically within the TTRPG landscape.

name: ENNIE AWARDS
description: The Ennie Awards are an accolade given to tabletop role-playing games. The Wildsea won an Ennie award in 2023 [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: PRIME DAY
description: Prime Day, also known as Prime Big Deal Days, is an annual shopping event organized by Amazon, occurring twice in 2023, in July and again in October. This event offers steep discounts on a wide variety of products, including video games, TVs, soundbars, smart home devices, and headphones. Some of the deals are exclusive to Amazon Prime members, providing them with additional benefits. For instance, Aqara's smart home devices are currently on sale during the October Prime Day, as reported by The Verge on 2023-10-10. Engadget and Wired also covered the event, highlighting the discounts available on various products. The Verge confirmed that Prime Day is specifically designed to offer deals to Amazon's Prime members, making it a significant event for them to take advantage of savings.

name: GOD OF WAR RAGNAROK
description: God of War Ragnarök is a PlayStation 5 video game that is available at a discounted price of $62 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a 11% off its original price

name: DEMON'S SOULS
description: Demon's Souls is a 2020 video game, a remake of the 2009 game by FromSoftware, rebuilt by Bluepoint Games, available at a discounted price of $30 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a 57% off its original price

name: MARIO + RABBIDS SPARKS OF HOPE
description: Mario + Rabbids Sparks of Hope is a turn-based strategy video game that pairs classic Mario characters with the chaotic Rabbids, available at a discounted price of $30 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a 50% off its original price

name: MARIO GOLF: SUPER RUSH
description: Mario Golf: Super Rush is a video game for the Nintendo Switch, selling for $39.99 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a $20 off its original price

name: SUPER MARIO MAKER 2
description: Super Mario Maker 2 is a Nintendo Switch video game that is also $39.99 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a $20 off its original price

name: METROID DREAD
description: Metroid Dread is the fifth mainline entry in Nintendo’s Metroid franchise, a 2D side-scroller and direct sequel to Metroid Fusion, available at a discounted price of $40 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a 33% off its original price

name: PLAYSTATION GIFT CARD
description: PlayStation gift cards are sold in $10, $25, $50, and $100 values and can be used to purchase titles, add-ons, and downloadable content for PlayStation consoles

name: STREETS OF RAGE 4
description: Streets of Rage 4 is a game for PlayStation 4 that is currently on sale for $19.29 ($15 off) at Amazon

name: HALLMARK
description: Hallmark is a company that produces ornaments, including a Nintendo Entertainment System Console Ornament on sale for $16.16 (about $4 off) at Amazon

name: NINTENDO ENTERTAINMENT SYSTEM
description: The Nintendo Entertainment System is a classic video game console that is featured in a Hallmark ornament

name: MICROSOFT XBOX SERIES X
description: The Xbox Series X is Microsoft’s flagship console, serving as its most powerful (and biggest) option, focused on fast 4K gameplay and available for $400 (refurbished) at Amazon

name: JSAUX MOD CASE FOR STEAM DECK
description: Jsaux Mod Case for Steam Deck is a protective modular case system for Valve’s Steam Deck, consisting of a base case with grippy texture, a built-in kickstand, a removable lid, and a rear mounting system, available for $24 at Amazon

name: 45W USB-C CHARGER
description: Jsaux’s 45W USB-C charger with a five-foot cable and included right-angle adapter is designed for the Steam Deck but can also charge a Nintendo Switch or any USB-C phone or tablet, currently on sale for $15.19 ($3 off) at Amazon

name: RAZER WIRELESS WOLVERINE V2 CHROMA
description: Razer’s wired Wolverine V2 Chroma is an Xbox controller with six remappable buttons, clicky buttons, and RGB lighting on the grips, available for $87.99 ($62 off) at Amazon

name: RAZER WOLVERINE V2 CHROMA
description: Razer’s wired Wolverine V2 Chroma is an Xbox controller featuring six remappable buttons, clicky buttons, and RGB lighting on the grips. It is on sale at Amazon for $87.99, which is $62 off its original price [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: RAZER WOLVERINE V2
description: The cheaper Razer Wolverine V2 controller in white, with a built-in USB cable and no RGB lighting, is also on sale at Amazon for $45.99, which is $54 off its original price [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: GAMESIR G7
description: The GameSir G7 is a wired controller for Xbox and PC, on sale for $35.99 at Amazon. It is a third-party gamepad with two programmable rear buttons, clicky face buttons, and a paintable front shell attached with magnets [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: GAMESIR T4 KALEID
description: The GameSir T4 Kaleid is a transparent wired controller with RGB lighting, on sale for $33.59 at Amazon. It is the first time this controller has gone on sale and features drift-free Hall effect sticks, compatible with PC, Nintendo Switch, and Android [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: 8BITDO ULTIMATE BLUETOOTH CONTROLLER
description: The 8BitDo Ultimate Bluetooth Controller comes with a charging dock, remappable controls, and is compatible with the Nintendo Switch, Steam Deck, and Windows PCs. It features drift-free Hall effect sticks and is on sale at Amazon for $56 [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: POWERA SPECTRA INFINITY ENHANCED WIRED CONTROLLER
description: The PowerA Spectra Infinity Enhanced Wired Controller for Xbox and PC is on sale at Amazon for $29.99, which is $15 off its original price. It is one of the cheapest controllers with hair trigger lockouts and colorful lights [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: PDP VICTRIX BFG WIRELESS CONTROLLER
description: The PDP Victrix BFG Wireless Controller, a high-performance gaming accessory designed for PlayStation 5, PS4, and PC, is currently featured in a special Call of Duty: Modern Warfare II-branded black-and-gold edition. As of October 10, 2023, The Verge reported that this controller is available at Amazon with a notable discount, priced at $169.99, which is $30 off its regular price. The controller boasts multi-stage hair triggers for enhanced gaming responsiveness and a versatile button layout to cater to various gaming preferences, making it a sought-after choice for gamers looking to upgrade their gaming experience. Despite the initial lack of price or discount information in one of the descriptions, the consolidated information confirms the availability and special pricing at Amazon.

name: RA INFINITY ENHANCED WIRED CONTROLLER
description: The RA Infinity Enhanced Wired Controller for Xbox and PC is on sale at Amazon for $29.99 ($15 off), featuring colorful lights and hair trigger lockouts [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: ASUS ROG FLOW Z13
description: The Asus ROG Flow Z13 is a gaming tablet with a detachable keyboard, kickstand, and high performance for QHD gaming, currently on sale for $893 ($407 off) at Amazon [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: SONY INZONE H3
description: The Sony InZone H3 is a wired gaming headset compatible with both PlayStation and PC, featuring customizable audio profiles through the InZone companion app and Sony’s Spatial Sound Personalizer, on sale for $58 ($42 off) at Amazon and Best Buy [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: ELGATO STREAM DECK MINI
description: Elgato’s Stream Deck Mini is a smaller, six-key version of its popular macro pads, offering customizable LCD keys for quick one-button macros during livestreams or controlling shortcuts on computers, currently on sale for $59 ($21 off) at Amazon [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: 1TB SANDISK EXTREME MICROSD CARD
description: A 1TB SanDisk Extreme microSD card is now $79.99 ($10 off) at Amazon, capable of storing a large number of games on devices like the Steam Deck or Nintendo Switch [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: SAMSUNG EVO SELECT MICROSD CARD
description: The Samsung Evo Select microSD card offers 512GB of extra storage for Nintendo devices, currently on sale for $30 ($10 off) [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: X (FORMERLY KNOWN AS TWITTER)
description: X, formerly known as Twitter, serves as a prominent social media platform that facilitates the exchange of ideas and opinions among its vast user base. Recently, the platform has been the stage for fans to voice their disapproval and criticism towards Travis Kelce, a well-known sports personality, for making remarks that were perceived as sexist. This incident highlights the role of X in amplifying public discourse and holding influential figures accountable for their statements in the public sphere.

name: BRUISED FOREARMS
description: Bruised forearms can occur as a result of physical activities or impacts, such as those experienced in certain games or sports. The context suggests that this might be a consequence of playing a game, but no specific game is mentioned.[]

name: SPLENDOR
description: Splendor is a resource management game set in Renaissance Europe where players compete to build the best jewelry business. It is a modern tabletop classic. [The Verge, 2023-10-10]

name: TWITCHCON 2023
description: TwitchCon 2023 was a convention for Twitch streamers and attendees, which was better than the previous year's event but was criticized for being held in Las Vegas [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: LAS VEGAS
description: Las Vegas, a city renowned for its emphasis on drinking, gambling, and a frenetic pace, served as the host for TwitchCon 2023. However, the city's characteristics and size were met with significant disapproval from a large portion of Twitch's usership. Attendees at the convention expressed frustration over the high costs associated with the location, the lack of walkability, and the scarcity of spaces for casual hangouts with other streamers. These issues, coupled with complaints about the absence of accessible third places and the inconvenience of traveling to venues outside the convention center, highlighted the challenges faced by many at the event. The overall sentiment from the attendees was that Las Vegas was not an ideal choice for TwitchCon due to its expense, poor walkability, and the dearth of areas conducive to the community-building that is a hallmark of such conventions.

name: LOWCO
description: LOWCO, a prominent Twitch streamer, shared a mixed bag of experiences and opinions regarding TwitchCon 2023. LOWCO posted positive feedback about the event on X (formerly known as Twitter), acknowledging improvements in Twitch's communication and transparency, which were highlighted during the opening ceremony where LOWCO proposed to her girlfriend on stage, making for a memorable and emotional moment. However, LOWCO also expressed dissatisfaction with the social spaces at TwitchCon 2023, which was held in Las Vegas, and suggested that San Diego would be a better location for future events. This sentiment was echoed by others in the community, indicating a collective desire for a change in venue. LOWCO's comments on Moni’s UserVoice post further emphasized the preference for San Diego, where TwitchCon had previously taken place, suggesting a more favorable environment for the gathering.

name: DAN CLANCY
description: Dan Clancy, a pivotal figure in the technology and entertainment community, currently holds the position of CEO and President at Twitch, a leading live streaming platform for gamers and creators. Taking the helm earlier this year, Clancy has made it a priority to foster a closer relationship with Twitch streamers, actively involving their perspectives in policy changes to ensure their voices are heard and considered. His commitment to improving communication and transparency within the platform was evident during TwitchCon 2023, where he engaged directly with the streamer community. This interaction was met with praise, as Clancy demonstrated a deep understanding of the streamer culture and the challenges they face. In a significant move, he addressed the revenue split controversy, outlining Twitch's long-term monetization strategy in a clear and concise manner, as reported by TechCrunch on October 26, 2023. Through these efforts, Dan Clancy has positioned himself as a leader who values community input and strives to create a more equitable and supportive environment for Twitch's content creators.

name: EMMETT SHEAR
description: Emmett Shear, a prominent figure in the tech industry, is best known as the co-founder of Twitch, a leading video streaming platform for gamers. Shear served as the CEO of Twitch for an impressive 16 years, steering the company through significant growth and transformation, until Dan Clancy took over the role earlier this year, as reported by TechCrunch on October 26, 2023. In a surprising turn of events, Shear has also been appointed as the interim CEO of OpenAI, a cutting-edge artificial intelligence research laboratory, stepping in to replace Murati. This dual role highlights Shear's versatility and expertise in both the entertainment and technology sectors.

name: REDCLAWDRAW
description: RedclawDraw is a Twitch streamer who agreed with the positive vibes at TwitchCon 2023 but strongly opposed the event being held in Las Vegas again [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: RACHEL DELPHIN
description: Rachel Delphin is the chief marketing officer at Twitch who confirmed that the next year's convention will not be in Las Vegas, but did not disclose the location [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: TWITCHCON
description: TwitchCon, an annual convention organized by Twitch for its streamers and viewers, held its 2023 edition in Las Vegas, Nevada. The event, which is a significant gathering for the Twitch community, featured diverse programming and meetups, allowing streamers and fans to celebrate the platform and its community. However, attendees at the 2023 TwitchCon felt that organic interactions were somewhat restricted to Twitch-sponsored events due to a lack of casual social spaces. Moreover, the location in Las Vegas presented significant challenges, including navigating the bustling Las Vegas Strip, dealing with the intense heat, and addressing accessibility issues, which collectively contributed to negative feedback about the choice of venue. Despite these drawbacks, TwitchCon continues to be a key event for those interested in engaging with the Twitch community and exploring the latest trends in technology and entertainment.

name: DELPHIN
description: Delphin is a representative of Twitch who credits the company's quick learning for mitigating crowding issues during this year's convention. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: SAN DIEGO CONVENTION CENTER
description: The San Diego Convention Center is a venue that hosted last year's Twitch convention. Its tight hallways couldn't accommodate the large number of attendees, leading to overcrowding and poor traffic flow. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: THIRD PLACES
description: Third places are sociological terms referring to physical spaces that are neither work nor home, where people can socialize without obligations of productivity. Attendees of TwitchCon suggested the need for more accessible third places at next year's convention. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: MONI
description: MONI, also recognized by the username Monistreams, is a dedicated Twitch user and games tech streamer who voiced significant concerns regarding the 2023 TwitchCon event held in Las Vegas. In a detailed UserVoice post, MONI critiqued the choice of Las Vegas as the venue, highlighting that the city's design and infrastructure posed challenges for attendees in connecting with their favorite streamers and communities. MONI's feedback emphasized the need for improvements in future TwitchCon events, particularly focusing on the accessibility of third places, which are crucial for fostering community engagement and interaction. This critique, published on TechCrunch on October 26, 2023, reflects MONI's commitment to enhancing the TwitchCon experience for all participants.

name: LAS VEGAS STRIP
description: The Las Vegas Strip is a tourist-heavy area in Las Vegas, Nevada, known for its casinos, restaurants, and entertainment venues. However, it is difficult to navigate on foot due to its size and the oppressive October heat, and it lacks adequate accommodations for disabled attendees [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: USERVOICE
description: UserVoice is a comprehensive platform serving as a feedback forum where users, particularly those from the Twitch community, can share their experiences, opinions, and innovative ideas for enhancing the Twitch service and its events. Moni, a Twitch user, utilized UserVoice to provide feedback on the 2023 TwitchCon experience in Las Vegas, highlighting the platform's role in facilitating user engagement and communication with Twitch. Through UserVoice, Twitch users have the opportunity to post, discuss, and vote on suggestions, contributing to the continuous improvement of the Twitch platform and ensuring that the community's voice is heard and considered in decision-making processes. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: UBER
description:
Uber, a prominent ride-sharing and delivery company, has recently reported its third-quarter earnings, showcasing a profitable business amidst slowing growth in certain sectors. In Q3 2023, Uber's revenue reached $9.3 billion, marking an 11% increase year-over-year, albeit below the anticipated $9.5 billion. The company reported a net income of $221 million, a significant improvement from the net loss of $1.2 billion in the same quarter last year. Gross bookings are forecasted to be between $36.5 billion to $37.5 billion, a modest 6% increase at the upper end from Q3 results. However, Uber's financial landscape has been affected by business model changes in some countries, which led to classifying certain sales and marketing costs as contra revenue, impacting its 2023 revenue and delivery business outcomes.

Despite its financial strides, Uber continues to grapple with the issue of sexual assaults, an ongoing problem since 2014. The company has been sued multiple times over the past few years by passengers alleging sexual assault during rides. Uber's terms of use prevent class action lawsuits in such cases, necessitating individual hearings for each case, which has hindered collective advocacy for survivors. Although Uber claims a 38% decrease in the rate of sexual assault reported on the app between its first and second safety reports covering 2017-2018 and 2019-2020, the total number of reports across five categories fell from 5,981 to 3,824, potentially due to a decrease in trips. However, the number of incidents in categories such as nonconsensual kissing, touching, and penetration or rape increased between 2017 and 2019. The total number of rape incidents also rose during this period, and while the reported cases dropped in 2020, the rate has remained unchanged since 2017.

In response to safety concerns, Uber has introduced several safety features over the last five years, including a 911 button, location sharing, audio recording during trips, and live help from ADT safety agents. However, the company has faced criticism for not implementing in-car cameras and further tech upgrades to enhance passenger safety. Uber has attempted to dismiss motions to consolidate sexual assault cases, arguing that it did not owe a duty to protect

name: STEVE SAYLOR
description: Steve Saylor is a blind gamer and disability advocate who attended the 2023 TwitchCon in Las Vegas. He struggled to get around the city, even with rideshares, and highlighted the difficulties faced by those with motor disabilities due to the lack of adequate accommodations in the city's infrastructure [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: CES
description: CES is a technology conference that also takes place in Las Vegas. Attendees of CES are familiar with the traffic and accessibility issues of the Las Vegas Strip [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: SAN DIEGO
description: San Diego, a city known for its smaller size and walkable nature, has been highlighted by multiple Twitch users, such as Lowco and Moni, as a preferred location for hosting TwitchCon. The city's layout facilitates organic interactions among creators and viewers, enhancing the potential for better social connections at the event. Previously, San Diego served as the host for TwitchCon, garnering positive feedback for its intimate environment that promotes engagement within the technology and entertainment community.

name: HEROKERREY
description: Herokerrey is a Twitch streamer who commented on Moni's UserVoice post, expressing concerns about the overstimulation in Las Vegas and its compatibility with the Twitch demographic. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: DINOMITETWINS
description: DinomiteTwins are Twitch streamers who are identical twins and share a channel. They commented on the difficulty of meeting fellow creators in Las Vegas due to the city's size and lack of casual social spaces. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: VIDCON
description: VidCon, a prominent convention for online video creators and fans, initially established in Anaheim, California, has expanded its reach by launching a second convention in Baltimore, Maryland. This move could potentially serve as a model for TwitchCon to host multiple events in various locations. Known for its focus on the creator economy, VidCon hosted an industry leadership summit for the first time, providing a unique platform for creators and experts to convene, discuss, and share ideas about the evolving landscape of online content creation. The event, celebrated for its vibrant community engagement, continues to grow and adapt, reflecting the dynamic nature of the digital entertainment industry. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-26]

name: CREATIVE INDUSTRIES
description: Creative industries, which include music, photography, and writing, are grappling with the explosion of AI into every artistic medium, raising questions about the technology's role and potential harm. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

name: FIGHT FOR THE FUTURE
description: Fight for the Future is a digital rights organization that has partnered with United Musicians and Allied Workers to launch the #AIdayofaction campaign, calling on Congress to block corporations from obtaining copyrights on AI-made art. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

name: UNITED MUSICIANS AND ALLIED WORKERS
description: United Musicians and Allied Workers is a music industry labor group that has partnered with Fight for the Future to address concerns about AI's impact on the creative process and copyright issues. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

name: LIA HOLLAND
description: Lia Holland is the Campaigns and Communications director at Fight for the Future, who spoke to TechCrunch about the siloed nature of creative fields and the common concerns shared across artistic mediums regarding AI. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

name: SPOTIFY
description:
Spotify, a prominent music and podcast streaming company, has been making headlines in 2023 for various reasons. The company, known for its digital music service, was among the initial testers for Google's User Choice Billing program, demonstrating its commitment to exploring new revenue models. Spotify played a key role in the marketing and promotion of Iñigo Quintero's song "Si No Estás," which topped the Global Top 50 chart and was featured on Today's Top Hits, Viral 50, and Top 50 playlists worldwide, highlighting its influence in the music industry. The platform has also been instrumental in the success of independent artists such as Nadhif Basalamah and Grupo Frontera, whose music has charted on Spotify in 2023.

In terms of financial performance, Spotify reported an operating profit for the first time in a year, partly due to a $1 price increase and the downsizing of its podcast operation. The company is focusing on leaner operations and more scale in its podcasting business, rather than producing original content. Spotify is exploring new ways to scale its podcasting business by creating personalized ads for each user, potentially in different languages, using the same voice actor. This could significantly contribute to podcasting if its translation technology is successful.

Spotify has integrated its music streaming service with Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses, enabling users to play automatic recommendations based on their favorites by simply tapping and holding the gesture control area. As of February 2023, the company had 44.4 million paying subscribers in the United States, showcasing its substantial user base.

However, Spotify has not been immune to challenges. The company has faced issues with AI-crafted songs on its platform and recently launched an AI-powered DJ that curates music, illustrating the complex relationship between AI and the music industry. In an effort to become "both productive and efficient" amidst slow economic growth and rising capital costs, Spotify has undergone significant restructuring, including three rounds of layoffs this year, with the latest round eliminating about 1,500 jobs, or roughly 17% of its workforce, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-12-09. These job cuts follow previous reports of downsizing, indicating a strategic shift in the company's operations.

name: REBECCA SLAUGHTER
description: Rebecca Slaughter is a commissioner at the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) who spoke about the role of technology in art and the importance of human creativity. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

name: TECHNOLOGY
description: Technology, a broad concept that includes tools, methods, and processes for the creation, development, and enhancement of products and services, plays a significant role in various aspects of life. As highlighted by TechCrunch on 2023-10-06, it can assist in the creation of art, yet it cannot replace the human creativity that is essential to artistic expression. However, as noted by The Guardian on 2023-10-10, the rapid pace of technological advancement has introduced complexities, particularly affecting older individuals who may find it challenging to adapt to new devices and software. These difficulties encompass a range of issues, including navigating online banking systems, dealing with fridge alarms, managing software updates, understanding apps, and operating modern phones. Despite its limitations in replicating human creativity, technology's pervasive influence necessitates efforts to ensure accessibility and ease of use for all age groups.

name: ART
description: Art is a fundamental human concept that involves creativity and expression. It can be assisted by technology but requires human input to exist. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-10-06]

description: Chinese President Xi Jinping met with five U.S. senators for 80 minutes to discuss China-U.S. relations, as reported by CNBC [2023-11-13]
