One of the notable features of the Mac Mini is its expanded port selection, offering a comprehensive connectivity suite that includes four Thunderbolt 4 USB-C ports, USB-A ports, HDMI, 10-gigabit Ethernet, and a 3.5-mm headphone jack, as detailed by Wired on November 25, 2023. Users are required to provide their own mouse, keyboard, and monitor to complete the setup, making it a customizable option for those looking to tailor their computing environment.

name: B&H PHOTO
description: B&H Photo, a renowned retailer in the technology space, is offering significant discounts on a wide range of Apple products as of 2023-10-26. Customers can find the 14-inch MacBook Pro model equipped with 1TB storage, a 12-core M2 Pro CPU, and 19 GPU cores for $1,999, marking a $500 reduction from its original price. Additionally, the 16-inch 2021 MacBook Pro with 16GB of RAM and 1TB of storage is available for $1,799, a $900 discount. B&H Photo also has a souped-up M1 Max model with 64GB of RAM and 2TB of storage on sale for $2,499, a $1,800 off deal. Contrary to the M3 Pro chips and 18GB of RAM mentioned in another description, the focus is on M2 and M1 Max chipsets. The retailer is further extending its savings to MacBook Air models, with the 13-inch M2 MacBook Air priced at $899, a $200 discount, and $300 off on the 512GB SSD and 10-core GPU configuration of the 15-inch M2 MacBook Air. Lastly, B&H Photo is selling both the base M2 Mac Mini and the M2 Pro version at discounted prices of $479 and $1,149, respectively. These deals make B&H Photo an attractive destination for tech enthusiasts looking to purchase Apple products at reduced prices.

name: M1 MACBOOK AIR
description: The M1 MacBook Air is a laptop model that is a few years old but still offers great value in terms of everyday performance and battery life. It is currently being discounted by Amazon and Best Buy to $749.99. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: M2 MACBOOK AIR
description: The M2 MacBook Air is a newer, super slim and light laptop model with a 1080p webcam, a handy magnetic charger, and an M2 processor. Its base model with 256GB of storage and an eight-core GPU is currently selling for $899 at B&H Photo, and the upgraded configuration with 512GB SSD and 10-core GPU is being offered at $1,199 by Best Buy and B&H Photo. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: 15-INCH M2 MACBOOK AIR
description: The 15-inch M2 MacBook Air is a larger model with a 15.3-inch notched screen, six speakers, a 10-core GPU, and a higher starting price of $1,299. The base model comes with a 256GB SSD and 8GB of RAM. It is currently being sold for $999 with a $300 discount at Amazon and Best Buy. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: M3 PRO
description: M3 Pro is a computer chip used in the 2023 MacBook Pro models. It comes in different configurations, including 11-core CPU / 14-core GPU and 12-core CPU / 18-core GPU. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: M2 PRO
description: M2 Pro is a high-performance computer chip developed by Apple, prominently featured in their 2023 MacBook Pro models, specifically the 14-inch variant equipped with a 12-core CPU and 19 GPU cores. This advanced chip is also utilized in the Mac Mini and Mac Studio, significantly boosting their computational capabilities and overall performance. The Verge, in its coverage dated 2023-10-26, highlights the M2 Pro as a key component in these devices, underscoring its role in delivering superior processing power and graphics handling to users in the technology and entertainment sectors.

name: M2 PRO CPU
description: M2 Pro CPU is a processor used in MacBook Pro models, offering superior performance. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: M1 MAX
description: M1 Max is a processor used in MacBook Pro models, featuring a 10-core CPU and 32-core GPU. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: MACBOOK PRO 14
description: MacBook Pro 14 is a laptop model from Apple, which the Mac Mini is likened to in terms of performance and features, but in a desktop form. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: MAC STUDIO
description: Mac Studio is a high-performance desktop computer from Apple, with the M2 Pro version of the Mac Mini being compared to it as a more affordable option. [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: THE GOOD FIGHT
description: The Good Fight is a TV show created by Robert and Michelle King, starring Christine Baranski, Audra McDonald, and a rotating cast of actors. It premiered in 2017 and follows the story of Diane Lockhart, a character from The Good Wife, who joins Chicago’s largest Black law firm after losing her savings in a Ponzi scheme [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: ROBERT AND MICHELLE KING
description: Robert and Michelle King are the creators of The Good Fight, a TV show that explores Trump-era America through the lens of a law firm [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: CHRISTINE BARANSKI
description: Christine Baranski is an actress who stars in The Good Fight as Diane Lockhart, a character originally from The Good Wife, who becomes a partner at a Black law firm in Chicago [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: AUDRA MCDONALD
description: Audra McDonald is an actress who is part of the rotating cast of The Good Fight, contributing to the show's rich narrative [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: STAR TREK: STRANGE NEW WORLDS
description: Star Trek: Strange New Worlds is a TV show that is considered one of the best new Star Trek series, part of a crop of stellar new shows in the franchise [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: APPLE TV PLUS
description: Apple TV Plus is a streaming service that offers Hijack, a TV show about a hijacking incident [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: HIJACK
description: "Hijack" is a captivating TV series streaming on Apple TV Plus, masterminded by creators George Kay and Jim Field Smith. The show stars the talented Idris Elba, Neil Maskell, and Archie Panjabi, weaving a narrative centered around a high-stakes hijacking scenario. Idris Elba portrays Sam Nelson, one of the passengers who finds himself thrust into the heart of the crisis. The plot thickens as the passengers, including Nelson, are faced with the daunting task of securing the plane and ensuring the safety of everyone on board after terrorists take control. The series is notable for its taut and twisty nature, utilizing every moment to its advantage, even incorporating unexpected details to keep the audience on the edge of their seats. It unfolds in close to real time, providing an immersive experience as decisions are made both on the plane and on the ground, where British law enforcement springs into action to assist. In a world where watchlists are growing, "Hijack" stands out as a breezy blockbuster thriller, offering a breath of fresh air with its easy, competent, and purely pleasurable viewing experience.

name: GEORGE KAY
description: George Kay is a creator of Hijack, a TV show on Apple TV Plus that tells the story of a hijacking [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: JIM FIELD SMITH
description: Jim Field Smith is a creator of Hijack, a TV show on Apple TV Plus that focuses on a hijacking incident [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: IDRIS ELBA
description: Idris Elba, a renowned British actor, stars in the series Hijack as Sam Nelson, a passenger entangled in a harrowing hijacking situation. Elba, known for his impressive height, shared that he had to maneuver carefully during filming, as the scenes were shot aboard an actual plane, which presented unique challenges due to the aircraft's confined spaces. This commitment to authenticity in the production adds an extra layer of realism to Elba's performance, making Hijack a gripping watch for audiences. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: NEIL MASKELL
description: Neil Maskell is an actor who is part of the cast of Hijack, a TV show on Apple TV Plus about a hijacking [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: ARCHIE PANJABI
description: Archie Panjabi is an actress who is part of the cast of Hijack, a TV show on Apple TV Plus that centers around a hijacking incident [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: SAM NELSON
description: Sam Nelson is one of the main characters in Hijack, portrayed by Idris Elba. He is a passenger trying to make it home when his plane is hijacked. Sam and his fellow travelers have to figure out how to secure the plane and get everyone home safely. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: THE CONTINENTAL
description: "The Continental is a TV series that serves as a prequel to the John Wick film franchise, delving into the origins of the Continental hotel and the establishment of its distinctive rules. Set in a different era, the show successfully avoids mimicking the movies' visual style, opting instead for action sequences that are fitting for its time period. Larnell Stovall, a renowned fight choreographer, leads the action design, ensuring that the series delivers reliable and engaging fight scenes throughout its three-episode run. The Continental is praised for its ability to build strong characters and relationships within the brief time frame it is set, providing viewers with a compelling narrative that enriches the understanding of the hotel's history and its role in the John Wick universe."

name: LARNELL STOVALL
description: Larnell Stovall is an action director who was hired to lead the fight sequences in The Continental. Stovall and his team delivered impressive action scenes, from the opening heist sequence to the incredible rooftop fight in the third episode. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: JOHN WICK
description: John Wick is a movie series that The Continental is based on. The series explores the world of assassins and the Continental hotel, which serves as a central location in the movies. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: RIAN JOHNSON
description: Rian Johnson is the creator of the inverted detective series Poker Face, which stars Natasha Lyonne. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: POKER FACE
description: Poker Face is an inverted detective series created by Rian Johnson and starring Natasha Lyonne. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: GRAND CREW
description: Grand Crew is a sitcom about Black wine aficionados. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: GIRLS5EVA
description: Girls5Eva is a hilarious comedy about a girl group getting back together. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: THE RESORT
description: The Resort is a dark mystery-comedy starring William Jackson Harper and Cristin Milioti as a couple on vacation who stumble across a deadly mystery. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: WILLIAM JACKSON HARPER
description: William Jackson Harper is an actor known for his role in The Good Place and stars in The Resort alongside Cristin Milioti. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: CRISTIN MILIOTI
description: Cristin Milioti is an actress known for her role in Made for Love and stars in The Resort alongside William Jackson Harper. [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: ASOS
description: ASOS, a globally recognized online fast fashion retailer, was launched in 2000 and quickly gained popularity for its extensive range of affordable dresses and its convenient next day delivery and easy returns service. Initially, the company specialized in imitations of celebrity clothing, but over time, ASOS expanded its offerings to include 850 affordable to mid-range high-street brands, catering to a busy demographic of 20-somethings in 196 countries. However, ASOS is currently experiencing significant economic challenges, as evidenced by the pre-tax losses of nearly £300m reported in the year to 3 September 2023, a stark contrast to the £31m profit in the previous year. The company's struggles are attributed to increased competition, a maturing clientele possibly seeking more personalized experiences, and the costly business model that supports free returns, leading to substantial financial losses. In response, ASOS plans to invest an additional £30m in marketing, focusing on fashion and excitement in its products, while also considering raising quick cash, potentially through the sale of its Topshop brand, to address its debt issues and adapt to the evolving consumer buying habits.

name: RICK SMITH
description: Rick Smith is the Managing Director of Forbes Burton, a business recovery firm. He explains that ASOS's business model of allowing large numbers of free returns makes the company susceptible to financial losses during challenging economic conditions [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: FORBES BURTON
description: Forbes Burton is a business recovery firm that provides insights into ASOS's business model and its susceptibility to financial losses [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: SMITH
description: Smith is an analyst who discusses the challenges faced by ASOS, including the shift in consumer buying habits and the potential need for the company to raise quick cash. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: JOSE ANTONIO RAMOS CALAMONTE
description: José Antonio Ramos Calamonte is the chief executive of ASOS who stated that the company has made good progress in a very challenging environment and would continue to invest in its brand and stock more fashionable lines of clothing. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: TOPSHOP
description: Topshop is a brand that ASOS acquired when the Arcadia Group went bust in 2021. ASOS may need to raise quick cash soon, potentially through the sale of Topshop. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: ARCADIA GROUP
description: The Arcadia Group is a company that went bust in 2021, leading to ASOS acquiring Topshop. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: SHEIN
description: SHEIN, a Chinese-founded global retail giant, has made significant strides in the fashion industry, acquiring the UK-based company Missguided among other rival brands. As of 2023, SHEIN is valued at approximately £53bn, reflecting its expansive growth and market influence. In 2022, the company reached a notable milestone, becoming the most-googled fashion brand worldwide, and reported a substantial revenue of £18.9bn. This success underscores SHEIN's strategic acquisitions and global expansion efforts, solidifying its position as a leading player in the international fashion retail sector.

name: MISSGUIDED
description: Missguided, a once-struggling UK-based online fashion retailer, has experienced a significant change in ownership over the past year and a half. Initially, the company was bought out of administration by Mike Ashley's Frasers Group. However, in a recent development, Shein, a global e-commerce giant known for its fast fashion, has acquired Missguided with ambitious plans to reignite the brand and leverage its market presence. This acquisition signals Shein's commitment to expanding its portfolio and influence in the fashion industry, particularly in the UK market.

name: MIKE ASHLEY
description: Mike Ashley, the owner of Frasers Group, successfully acquired Missguided from administration approximately a year and a half ago, as reported by The Independent - Life and Style on November 1, 2023. This strategic move by Ashley and his company highlights their interest in expanding their presence in the retail sector, particularly in the fashion industry, by rescuing and integrating brands that are facing financial difficulties. The acquisition of Missguided demonstrates Ashley's expertise in identifying potential within struggling businesses and leveraging Frasers Group's resources to stabilize and grow them.

name: FRASERS GROUP
description: Frasers Group is a company owned by Mike Ashley that bought Missguided out of administration a year and a half ago. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: ANTI-FASHION CAMPAIGNERS
description: Anti-fashion campaigners are a group that has called for boycotts against Shein, despite the company's global expansion and high valuation. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: FAST FASHION
description: Fast fashion is a concept that refers to the production of inexpensive clothing in response to the latest trends. Despite calls for boycotts, fast fashion remains popular among consumers who want to find entire outfits on a budget. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-01]

name: ALYSSA HEALY
description: Alyssa Healy, the captain of the Australian women's cricket team, expressed her disappointment over the recent Test match loss against India, emphasizing that the points system for the trophy was not utilized, which could have provided a more balanced competition between the two teams. Despite this setback, Healy rejected the idea that Australia's dominance in international women's cricket is fading, asserting that the loss should not be overemphasized when considering the team's extensive and successful record. She advocated for three-Test tours of India, suggesting that such a format would offer a better match-up and that incorporating the Test into a multi-format series would have been more appropriate. Healy's comments reflect her realistic perspective on the dominance of white-ball cricket in the female game and her commitment to maintaining Australia's strong position in the sport.

name: MEG LANNING
description: Meg Lanning is a retired Australian cricketer who was part of the team's leadership. Her retirement, along with Rachael Haynes', has been noted as a significant change for the Australian team. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-24]

name: RACHAEL HAYNES
description: Rachael Haynes is a retired Australian cricketer. Her retirement, along with Meg Lanning's, has been noted as a significant change for the Australian team. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-24]

name: ICC
description: The International Cricket Council (ICC) is the global governing body for cricket. Australia has won four consecutive global ICC events, including the 50-over World Cup earlier this year. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-24]

name: BANGLADESH
description: Bangladesh, a country in South Asia, has made notable contributions to the world of cricket, co-hosting the 2011 ODI Cricket World Cup alongside India and Sri Lanka, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-10-01. This cricket-loving nation is also set to host the upcoming T20 World Cup, an event that holds significant importance for the Australian women's cricket team, according to The Roar | Sports Writers Blog on 2023-12-24. Despite its sporting achievements, Bangladesh's educational system faces substantial challenges, as highlighted by TechCrunch on 2023-10-12. The country struggles with providing quality education to a large portion of its 42 million K12 students, indicating a need for improvement and investment in the education sector.

name: WORLD CUP
description: The World Cup, a significant event in the realm of sports, serves as a major international tournament for both cricket and football. In cricket, England is the defending champion from the 2019 edition but is encountering challenges in the 2023 tournament, while Australia is actively preparing and building towards this cricket World Cup. In the context of football, England has been an active participant in the post-pandemic international cycle, indicating their continued involvement in this sport's World Cup as well. The diverse participation of nations in these tournaments highlights the global appeal and competitive nature of the World Cup in both cricket and football.

name: TROPHY
description: The trophy was supposed to be contested in the multi-format 2021-22 series between Australia and India, but the system for awarding points was not used. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-24]

name: MULTI-FORMAT SERIES
description: The multi-format series is a cricket event that took place between Australia and India in 2021-22. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-24]

name: DIAMONDBACKS
description:
The Diamondbacks, a resilient and competitive baseball team, have been making significant strides in the 2023 postseason. After a successful sweep of two games in Milwaukee against the Brewers, they advanced to the division series where they faced the Dodgers. Despite splitting six games against the Dodgers at Chase Field earlier in the season, the Diamondbacks demonstrated their tenacity and refusal to back down. Key players Christian Walker and Alek Thomas have been pivotal in their journey.

In the World Series 2023, the Diamondbacks have faced both the Phillies and the Rangers, showcasing their adaptability and strength against varying opponents. As of the top of the 8th inning on October 28th, the Diamondbacks were leading the Rangers 4-1. However, the series has seen its ups and downs, with the Diamondbacks winning games on October 24th and 28th, but suffering a loss on October 27th against the Rangers, where they scored six runs over the final two innings but ultimately lost with a score of 7-11. In a more recent game, they struggled, trailing 7-0, with their bullpen being overwhelmed.

The Diamondbacks' journey to the World Series also included a challenging Wild Card series against the Phillies and Brewers, followed by a hard-fought Championship Series against the Phillies. Despite facing elimination in Game 5 for the third time in this postseason, the Diamondbacks remain determined to make a strong showing and compete for the championship title.

name: DODGERS
description: The Dodgers, a professional baseball team, had a remarkable 2020 postseason, playing all 16 games at Globe Life Field during the expanded playoffs as reported by The New York Times on 2023-10-08. They swept the Padres in the National League Division Series (NLDS), engaged in a thrilling seven-game series with the Braves in the National League Championship Series (NLCS), and ultimately clinched the World Series title. Fast forward to 2023, the Dodgers have been active in strengthening their roster, as noted on 2023-12-23. They met with Japanese pitcher Yoshinobu Yamamoto on December 12, 2023, and made a significant move by signing the versatile Shohei Ohtani to a 10-year contract, further solidifying their position as a competitive force in the league.

name: CHASE FIELD
description: Chase Field, a state-of-the-art stadium equipped with a unique feature of a pool and a retractable roof, serves as the home ballpark for the Arizona Diamondbacks. Throughout the 2023 season, the Diamondbacks had a mixed performance at this venue, splitting six games against the Dodgers, as reported by The New York Times on October 8, 2023. Additionally, Chase Field is set to witness a significant event in the baseball calendar, as the Rangers have the potential to clinch the championship title there as early as the night of October 31, 2023, according to Sporting News. This highlights the stadium's role as a pivotal location for major baseball events, hosting both regular season games and potential championship deciders.

name: GLOBE LIFE FIELD
description: Globe Life Field, the home ballpark of the Texas Rangers, is a state-of-the-art venue that opened its doors in 2020. With a seating capacity of 40,300, it has become a significant hub for baseball enthusiasts, averaging an attendance of 31,272 in 2023. The stadium is equipped with a closed roof, which not only contains the noise but also transforms the atmosphere into a vibrant, real ballpark environment, especially during late-inning rallies in October. Despite its hosting of 16 postseason games in its history, it is noteworthy that the Texas Rangers have yet to play a playoff game at Globe Life Field as of The New York Times report on October 8, 2023.

name: TEXAS RANGERS
description: The Texas Rangers, a professional baseball team, have made a significant mark in the 2023 baseball season by advancing to the World Series, where they are facing off against the Arizona Diamondbacks. Despite having experienced losing seasons in 2021 and 2022, the Rangers have shown remarkable resilience and improvement, leading them to compete in one of the most prestigious events in baseball. It is noteworthy that Game 2 of the 2023 World Series, which took place on October 29, 2023, was the first playoff game ever played at their home ballpark, Globe Life Field, although the team suffered a loss in that particular match. This milestone in the team's history signifies a turning point and a new era for the Texas Rangers as they strive for excellence on the global stage of baseball.

name: RANGERS
description:
The Rangers, a professional baseball team, have been making significant strides in the 2023 World Series, showcasing their prowess against formidable opponents such as the Diamondbacks and the Astros. As of October 28, 2023, they were trailing 4-1 against the Diamondbacks in a particular game, as reported by The Guardian. However, the team's performance has been dynamic throughout the series, with varying results across different games, as noted by Sporting News on October 31, 2023. In a standout game, the Rangers scored an impressive ten runs in the first two innings, taking a commanding 10-0 lead against the Diamondbacks. They secured a victory in that game with a final score of 11-7, bringing them one win closer to clinching their first championship in franchise history.

Key players contributing to the Rangers' success include Corey Seager, Marcus Semien, and Travis Jankowski, who have been instrumental in their dominating performance against the Diamondbacks, leading 7-0 in another game. The team's recent victories have been significant, with a win on October 27, 2023, and a loss on October 28, 2023, as reported by Sporting News on October 30, 2023. Notably, the Rangers also competed against the Astros in the 2023 World Series, overcoming a tie to secure a win, further solidifying their position in the championship race.

Prior to the World Series, the Rangers had a successful run in Arlington, winning their last five games and effectively keeping the Mariners out of the postseason. Since September 24, 2023, the team has not played a home game, indicating a strong performance in away games leading up to and during the World Series. The Rangers' journey in the 2023 World Series has been marked by resilience and high-scoring games, positioning them as a team to watch as they vie for their first championship title.

name: MARINERS
description: The Mariners, a sports team, faced a significant setback as they were excluded from the postseason due to the Rangers' triumphant last three wins in Arlington. As of November 13, 2023, Yardbarker reported that the Mariners are unlikely to trade George Kirby, a valuable asset to the team. It would take an extraordinary offer to convince them to part ways with Logan Gilbert. The team's front office, however, is exploring strategic options to enhance long-term offensive capabilities, which might involve the potential movement of players such as Bryan Woo, Bryce Miller, or Emerson Hancock. These decisions reflect the Mariners' commitment to building a competitive and balanced team for future seasons.

name: MINNESOTA TWINS
description: The Minnesota Twins, a professional baseball team based in Minneapolis, Minnesota, play their home games at Target Field. As of November 13, 2023, the team might be considering salary adjustments, potentially including moves to offload part of Vázquez's contract. On a more celebratory note, the Twins recently ended an 18-game postseason losing streak, achieving their first playoff victory since October 5, 2004. This historic win was secured against the Blue Jays, thanks to two impressive home runs by rookie Royce Lewis, which also marked the team's first postseason series win since 2002, completing a Wild Card sweep.

name: TARGET FIELD
description: Target Field, the proud home of the Minnesota Twins, is a stadium that has earned a reputation as an awesome place to play since its opening in 2010. Despite not being known for intimidating its opponents, it has a seating capacity of 38,544 and has hosted significant postseason moments, notably marking the Twins' first playoff victory in almost two decades. This venue, celebrated by The New York Times in 2023, continues to be a cornerstone for baseball in Minnesota, offering a memorable experience for both players and fans alike.

name: ROYCE LEWIS
description: Royce Lewis is a rookie player for the Minnesota Twins who hit two home runs, contributing to the team's first playoff win since 2004.[]

name: ROCCO BALDELLI
description: Rocco Baldelli is the manager of the Minnesota Twins who commented on the incredible noise and support from the fans at Target Field during the postseason games.[]

name: CORREA
description: Correa is a person who told Sonny Gray that the crowd noise at Target Field was so loud that the Blue Jays' baserunners couldn't hear their third-base coach.[]

name: SONNY GRAY
description: Sonny Gray is a person who commented on the incredible crowd noise at Target Field after the game against the Blue Jays.[]

name: MINUTE MAID PARK
description: Minute Maid Park, a colossal and resonant stadium, is renowned for being the home ground of the Houston Astros, a professional baseball team. Opened in 2000, this impressive venue boasts a seating capacity of 41,168 spectators, making it a significant hub for sports enthusiasts. The New York Times, in a 2023 article, dubbed Minute Maid Park "the loudest stadium," highlighting its vibrant and energetic atmosphere that amplifies the excitement of every game.

name: TRUIST PARK
description: Truist Park is a stadium that is the home of the Atlanta Braves. [The New York Times, 2023-10-08]

name: ORIOLE PARK AT CAMDEN YARDS
description: Oriole Park at Camden Yards is the home stadium of the Baltimore Orioles, opened in 1992 with a capacity of 44,970. The ballpark is described as beautiful and unmistakable, but can be taken over by opposing fans when the team is not performing well. [The New York Times, 2023-10-08]

name: DODGER STADIUM
description: Dodger Stadium, an iconic baseball venue, serves as the home field for the Los Angeles Dodgers since its opening in 1962. With a seating capacity of 56,000, it is recognized for its vast size and has been ranked as the second most daunting home field in the list of intimidating venues for the 2023 MLB playoffs, as reported by The New York Times on October 8, 2023. The stadium leverages its unique atmosphere to create an imposing environment for opposing teams, enhancing the Dodgers' home-field advantage.

name: DELMON YOUNG
description: Delmon Young is a baseball player who had a memorable three-run double in the eighth inning of Game 2 of the 2014 ALDS, helping the Baltimore Orioles complete a comeback against the Tigers. [The New York Times, 2023-10-08]

name: ZACK BRITTON
description: Zack Britton is a baseball player who pitched a perfect ninth inning in Game 2 of the 2014 ALDS, contributing to the Baltimore Orioles' victory over the Tigers. [The New York Times, 2023-10-08]

name: BRANDON HYDE
description: Brandon Hyde is the manager of the Baltimore Orioles. There is a concern about his decision-making on the road, specifically about using his best reliever in a must-win game. [The New York Times, 2023-10-08]

name: OSHA
description: OSHA is a regulatory body that sets and enforces standards for workplace safety and health

name: CITIZENS BANK PARK
description: Citizens Bank Park is the home venue of the Philadelphia Phillies, opened in 2004, with a capacity of 42,792 and an attendance of 38,157 in 2023

name: ROY HALLADAY
description: Roy Halladay was a baseball player who pitched a no-hitter in Game 1 of the 2010 NLDS against the Reds in his first postseason start

name: JAY BRUCE
description: Jay Bruce is a baseball player who walked with two outs in the fifth inning during Roy Halladay's no-hitter in Game 1 of the 2010 NLDS

name: BRYSON STOTT
description: Bryson Stott is a baseball player who hit a grand slam at Citizens Bank Park during the 2023 postseason, creating a memorable moment

name: M.L.B. PLAYOFF TEAMS
description: M.L.B. Playoff teams are the baseball teams competing in the Major League Baseball playoffs, which are ranked based on their home field advantage

name: TECHCRUNCH+
description: TechCrunch+, a subscription service by TechCrunch, serves dual roles within the technology and legal arenas. On one hand, it functions as a media organization dedicated to comprehending the market for startups that utilize large language models (LLMs) in the artificial intelligence (AI) sector, keeping its subscribers informed about the latest trends and innovations as of 2023-10-13. On the other hand, TechCrunch+ provides additional expertise and commentary on the high-profile SBF trial, offering detailed analysis of the case and potential outcomes, as noted on 2023-10-06. This service ensures that its audience remains well-informed on both the technological advancements and legal implications affecting the tech community.

name: LLMS
description: LLMs, or Large Language Models, are a recent and impactful method of creating AI software that startups are exploring for various applications. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: RICK GRINNELL
description: Rick Grinnell is the founder and managing partner at Glasswing Ventures, a venture capital firm active in the AI investing space. He believes that most opportunities for startups in the AI tech stack lie in the application layer. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: GLASSWING VENTURES
description: Glasswing Ventures is a venture capital firm that invests in AI-focused startups. According to Rick Grinnell, the best applications in the AI tech stack will harness in-house expertise to build specialized middle-layer tooling. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: ALUMNI VENTURES
description: Alumni Ventures is a venture capital firm that invests in startups. Edward Tsai suggests that focusing on speed to market and delivering value could be a viable strategy for startups in the AI space. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: WING VENTURES
description: Wing Ventures is a venture capital firm that invests in startups, particularly in the AI sector, as mentioned in a TechCrunch article published on 2023-10-13

name: FOUNDATION MODEL PROVIDERS
description: Foundation model providers are companies that create the base models for AI, which are essential for the development of specialized applications, as categorized in Wing Ventures' proprietary view of the GenAI tech stack

name: MIDDLE-TIER COMPANIES
description: Middle-tier companies are entities that focus on model fine-tuning, prompt engineering, and agile model orchestration, connecting the foundational aspects of AI with the application layer

name: END-MARKET APPLICATIONS
description: End-market or top-layer applications are specialized AI solutions that harness in-house expertise to blend with appropriate foundational models, as identified by Wing Ventures as the layer with the most opportunity for startups

name: FULL STACK VERTICAL COMPANIES
description: Full stack or end-to-end vertical companies are entities that cover all aspects of the AI tech stack, from foundational models to specialized applications, as part of Wing Ventures' categorization of the GenAI landscape

name: DATADOG
description: Datadog is a company that has built products to support the expanding AI market, including an LLM observability tool, as mentioned in the TechCrunch article published on 2023-10-13

name: NEW RELIC
description: New Relic is an incumbent tech company that has produced LLM observability tools, as part of the middle layer category in the AI tech stack, as noted in the TechCrunch article published on 2023-10-13

name: SPLUNK
description:
"SPLUNK is an esteemed technology company, recognized for its significant contributions to the AI tech stack. Specifically, Splunk has developed Limited Liability Model (LLM) observability tools, which play a crucial role in the middle layer of the AI technology ecosystem. This innovative development was highlighted in a TechCrunch article published on October 13, 2023, shedding light on Splunk's pivotal position in advancing AI capabilities and monitoring systems." 

However, it seems there might be a slight misunderstanding in the abbreviation "LLM" as it is typically not associated with technology but rather with legal or academic contexts (Master of Laws). In this tech context, it might refer to "Limited Liability Model," but this is not a common term in the AI tech stack. The term "observability" in AI usually refers to the ability to understand the internal states of a machine learning model based on its external behavior, which is a critical aspect of model monitoring and maintenance. Splunk's tools in this area would thus be essential for ensuring the reliability and performance of AI systems.

name: DATABRICKS
description: Databricks is an entity that Wing Ventures anticipates will rise in the middle layer of the AI tech stack, focusing on model fine-tuning and other cutting-edge capabilities

name: REAL ENTERPRISE PAIN POINTS
description: Real enterprise pain points are prioritized by executives as critical areas needing improvement. These pain points can be addressed by AI applications tailored to specific needs, which can provide long-term differentiation and tangible benefits. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: PROPRIETARY DATA
description: Proprietary data is necessary for AI applications to provide specific and relevant insights. It ensures that others cannot replicate the final product, giving a competitive edge to companies with in-house middle-layer capabilities. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: ENTERPRISE SECTOR
description: The enterprise sector recognizes the value of AI but often lacks the internal capabilities to develop AI solutions. This gap presents an opportunity for startups specializing in AI to engage with enterprise clients. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: STARTUPS
description: Startups are businesses that can specialize in AI to address the needs of the enterprise sector. They should consider the technical competence of their future enterprise AI customers and the presumed expertise guiding product selection and go-to-market motion. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: MCKINSEY
description: McKinsey is a consulting firm that reports on the potential value of generative AI across industries and the increasing importance of AI in businesses' success. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: AI BUDGETS
description: AI budgets are now more than double that of cloud computing, indicating the growing investment in AI technology. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: USAGE-BASED PRICING
description: Usage-based pricing has seen a slowdown in growth for tech products in recent quarters. This fact may lead startups building modern AI tools to consider more traditional SaaS pricing models. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: AI APPLICATIONS
description: AI Applications, as referenced in the EU's AI Act, are technologies that fall under a regulatory framework established by the European Union. This framework includes specific provisions for certain applications that are banned due to ethical or safety concerns, and it outlines penalties for any violations of these regulations. The AI Act, discussed in a TechCrunch article on 2023-12-09, aims to govern the use of AI technologies within the EU to ensure they are developed and deployed responsibly.

name: CLOUD COMPUTING
description: Cloud computing, an innovative technology in the realm of digital services, operates under a distinct cost metric when compared to AI tools. Unlike AI tools that frequently charge based on the number of tokens used, cloud computing services typically bill their users according to the amount of computing power, storage, and bandwidth they consume. This cost model allows for greater flexibility and scalability, making cloud computing a popular choice for businesses and individuals seeking to manage their digital resources efficiently [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13].

name: ADOG
description: ADOG is a company that aims to assist in the acceptance of AI tools by monitoring AI performance bottlenecks [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC STARTUPS
description: Industry-specific startups are organizations that specialize in tuning generative AI models for specific niches [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: GENERATIVE AI MODELS
description: Generative AI models are AI technologies that can create new content or data based on input parameters [TechCrunch, 2023-10-13]

name: SUNDAR PICHAI
description: Sundar Pichai, the CEO of Google, has been at the center of significant legal and business scrutiny in late 2023. Pichai provided testimony in an antitrust lawsuit involving Epic Games, as reported by TechCrunch on November 6, 2023. This follows his earlier defense of Google's business practices during the U.S. government's antitrust trial against the company, as detailed in a TechCrunch article on October 31, 2023. In the midst of these legal challenges, a report by The Verge on November 5, 2023, revealed that Pichai and other Google employees were implicated in setting potentially incriminating messages to auto-delete, adding a layer of controversy to the ongoing antitrust issues. Despite these challenges, Pichai has also been vocal about defending specific Google services, such as agreements with smartphone makers and wireless carriers, as well as the company's travel listings, which he asserts are among the most popular experiences Google has created.

name: DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE
description:
The Department of Justice, a key entity in the United States' legal and regulatory landscape, has been actively engaged in antitrust litigation against Google, a tech giant, in late 2023. On October 31, 2023, the Department of Justice, in conjunction with eight states, initiated a significant legal action against Google, alleging that the company has been executing an anticompetitive scheme that stifles competition in the digital advertising sector. This lawsuit, as reported by TechCrunch, is aimed at halting Google's monopolistic practices and restoring a fair competitive environment in the digital advertising industry.

Furthermore, the Department of Justice's involvement with Google extends beyond the digital advertising lawsuit. As of November 6, 2023, TechCrunch also reported that the Department of Justice is embroiled in another antitrust lawsuit against Google, this time concerning the company's alleged monopoly in the search market. This dual-front legal challenge underscores the Department of Justice's commitment to ensuring fair competition and preventing monopolistic practices in the technology sector.

name: PRABHAKAR RAGHAVAN
description: Prabhakar Raghavan is Google’s search head who testified in court on October 28, revealing that Google spent $26.3 billion in 2021 to be the default search engine across various platforms [The Verge, TechCrunch, 2023-10-31]

name: NITIN
description: Nitin is an individual who argued in a 2007 Google product strategy meeting that focusing on homepage market share is one of the most effective things Google can do to make gains in search market share [The Verge, TechCrunch, 2023-10-31]

name: DUCKDUCKGO
description: DuckDuckGo, a privacy-centric search engine company, has been making waves in the tech industry as an alternative to giants like Google. Its commitment to user privacy is evident in its policy of not collecting extensive user data, which sets it apart by prioritizing confidentiality over personalized search results. This approach has garnered a loyal user base that values privacy over the potentially superior search capabilities and readability of competitors. Recently, the company's CEO took a stand in the Google antitrust case, testifying earlier this month, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-31. Megan Gray, a significant figure in the tech community, is a former vice-president at DuckDuckGo, further highlighting the company's influence and the expertise it attracts. Despite the challenges in competing with Google's search performance, DuckDuckGo remains a favored choice for those seeking a more secure online search experience, as noted by The Age on 2023-10-22.

name: ANTITRUST CASE
description: Google is involved in an antitrust case, which is a legal proceeding that examines whether a company has engaged in unfair business practices or has a monopoly that restricts competition

name: HANH BADGER
description: Hanh Badger is a pharmacist and mother of Brooke Badger, who found her daughter pale and motionless in bed on 17 June 2021, believing she had not died of a drug overdose [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: BROOKE BADGER
description: Brooke Badger, 17, died of an overdose at her California home after purchasing what she believed to be Roxicet, a prescription medication, from a drug dealer through Snapchat [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: NALOXONE
description: Naloxone is a nasal spray that reverses the effects of an opioid overdose, administered by the sheriff upon arrival at Brooke Badger's home [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: SNAPCHAT
description: Snapchat, a social media platform owned by Snap Inc., is widely recognized for its unique disappearing messages feature. It has become a staple in the daily lives of young people, with some users spending up to three hours daily on the app and checking their phones over 100 times a day. However, the platform has been embroiled in controversy due to its use in facilitating the purchase of counterfeit pills, some of which contained fentanyl, leading to tragic outcomes including the deaths of Alexander Neville and other children. Brooke Badger and Alexander Neville are among the victims who purchased these dangerous substances through Snapchat, highlighting the platform's role in a drug crisis that has sparked criticism for its perceived lack of action against drug dealers and for creating a false sense of safety around drug transactions. In response to these issues, Snapchat has taken measures to limit the visibility of its Snap Map feature, particularly the heat map, in regions experiencing conflict, such as Ukraine and now in the context of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, to prevent misuse and ensure user safety. These actions reflect the company's efforts to address safety concerns and improve its platform. Despite the legal challenges and safety concerns, some parents have collaborated with Snapchat to promote awareness campaigns and advocate for enhanced safety measures, aiming to protect future users from similar tragedies.

name: FENTANYL
description: Fentanyl, a potent and dangerous opioid, has been linked to a tragic increase in overdose deaths among young people, particularly in California. This surge in fatalities is often associated with the procurement of counterfeit pills containing Fentanyl, which are frequently bought through social media platforms like Snapchat. The Guardian, in a report dated 2023-10-18, highlights the severity of the situation and the urgent need for awareness and intervention to prevent further loss of life.

name: CALIFORNIA
description: California, a state in the United States, is emerging as a potential global leader in the regulation of artificial intelligence (AI), with a strong emphasis on safeguarding the rights and privacy of its residents. This technological focus is driven by the state's innovative spirit and its desire to set standards that could influence AI policies worldwide. However, California also faces significant public health challenges, particularly concerning the sharp rise in fentanyl-related overdose deaths among teenagers. Between 2018 and 2021, the number of such deaths increased by nearly 800%, a trend that has deeply impacted communities and prompted urgent calls for action. Despite these health crises, California continues to be a hub for technological advancement and policy-making, demonstrating the complex dynamics that define the state.

name: SOCIAL MEDIA VICTIMS LAW CENTER
description: The Social Media Victims Law Center, a dedicated law firm, represents the families of over 65 victims in legal actions against Snap, the parent company of Snapchat, as reported by The Guardian on October 18, 2023. The firm contends that Snapchat's design inadvertently supports illegal drug sales by offering users a level of anonymity that hinders law enforcement's ability to monitor and track the activities of drug dealers on the platform. Among the victims represented by the Social Media Victims Law Center is Brooke Badger, whose case is part of the broader litigation against Snap. The firm's efforts are aimed at holding the social media giant accountable for the consequences of its platform design and seeking justice for the affected families.

name: SNAP
description: Snap, the parent company of Snapchat, a social media platform renowned for its disappearing messages feature, has been at the center of legal controversies in 2023. The company is facing lawsuits from the parents of Alexander Neville and the relatives of over 65 other victims, including Brooke Badger, who claim that Snapchat's platform facilitated drug sales, leading to the tragic deaths of their loved ones. The lawsuits argue that Snapchat's anonymity features enable drug dealers to operate undetected, hindering law enforcement efforts to track and prevent illegal activities. Despite these challenges, Snap continues to innovate, recently investing $2 million in StarNews Mobile through its Yellow Accelerator program and launching an AI startup called ZML. ZML is focused on enhancing machine learning inference and other foundational tools in the tech industry. Additionally, Snap has joined the smart glasses trend, further expanding its technology portfolio. However, the ongoing legal battles highlight the complex dynamics and potential risks associated with the intersection of technology, social media, and public safety.

name: MATTHEW BERGMAN
description: Matthew Bergman is the lead attorney on the case against Snap. He claims that Snapchat's features were designed with the intention of allowing and encouraging illegal activity, making it a platform for drug sales ["The Guardian", 2023-10-18].

name: SECTION 230 OF THE COMMUNICATIONS DECENCY ACT
description: Section 230 of the Communications Decency Act protects online platforms from being held responsible for the illegal actions of their users. Snap has cited this section in its motion to dismiss the complaint ["The Guardian", 2023-10-18].

name: PERLA MENDOZA
description: Perla Mendoza is a parent involved in the lawsuit against Snap. She found that the company did little to prevent illegal drug sales on Snapchat after her son, Daniel (Elijah) Figueroa, died from fentanyl-laced pills purchased on the platform. Mendoza's reports to the help center went unanswered for eight months ["The Guardian", 2023-10-18].

name: DANIEL (ELIJAH) FIGUEROA
description: Daniel (Elijah) Figueroa is the son of Perla Mendoza who died from fentanyl-laced pills purchased from a dealer on Snapchat. His death is one of the cases included in the lawsuits against Snap ["The Guardian", 2023-10-18].

name: BADGER
description: Badger is a parent who believes that removing a dealer's account on Snapchat is insufficient and emphasizes the need for structural reforms that warn young users of dealers' predatory practices or prevent drugs from being peddled to kids on the platform. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: AMY NEVILLE
description: Amy Neville is a parent who is part of a lawsuit against Snapchat. She lost her 14-year-old son Alexander, who died after taking a counterfeit Oxycontin tablet he procured through the app. She believes that Snapchat creates a false sense of safety around drug transactions, allowing her son to avoid in-person meetups and have the pills delivered to his door. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: ALEXANDER
description: Alexander is Amy Neville's 14-year-old son who died after taking a counterfeit Oxycontin tablet he procured through Snapchat. He was described as sensitive, impulsive, and curious about many things, including drugs, but hesitant about putting himself in dangerous situations. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: ED TERNAN
description: Ed Ternan is a parent who did not join the lawsuit against Snapchat. He lost his 21-year-old son Charlie in April 2020 after taking a counterfeit Percocet he bought on Snapchat. Ternan sees suing the platform as counterproductive and has worked with Snap to promote awareness campaigns and find ways to make the app safer. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: CHARLIE
description: Charlie is Ed Ternan's 21-year-old son who died in April 2020 after taking a counterfeit Percocet he bought on Snapchat. He was described as energetic and fun-loving, weeks away from graduating from UC Santa Cruz. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: ALEXANDER NEVILLE
description: Alexander Neville is the son of Liza Neville, who died after taking counterfeit pills he purchased on Snapchat. His story is being shared by his mother to raise awareness about the risks of fentanyl. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: LIZA NEVILLE
description: Liza Neville is the mother of Alexander Neville, who died after taking counterfeit pills he purchased on Snapchat. She travels to schools to share her son's story and hosts monthly online meetings to empower young people for peer-to-peer youth outreach. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: MENDOZA
description: Mendoza is a parent who, like Liza Neville, is suing Snap. She works to spread awareness of the risks of fentanyl to Spanish-speaking families. [The Guardian, 2023-10-18]

name: BIDEN ADMINISTRATION
description: The Biden Administration, a significant player in the realm of policy and governance, is actively engaged in the multifaceted task of regulating artificial intelligence (AI) development. In a move to safeguard the public, enhance federal agency practices, and foster an environment of innovation and competition, while simultaneously managing the inherent risks associated with AI, the Administration has recently unveiled an executive order. This order, carrying the weight of law, is set to be implemented over the course of the next year, introducing a series of safety and security measures. However, the Administration's stance on climate issues has been criticized by Peter Kalmus, who perceives them as lacking understanding and direction in this critical area. Despite this critique, the Administration continues to push forward with its AI regulatory agenda, aiming to balance technological advancement with responsible governance.

name: BRUCE REED
description: Bruce Reed is the White House Deputy Chief of Staff who will chair the "AI council" created by the Biden Administration to oversee the execution of actions related to AI regulation and ensure federal agencies are on schedule. [Engadget, 2023-10-30]

name: DEFENSE PRODUCTION ACT
description: The Defense Production Act is being leveraged by the Biden Administration's executive order to require companies developing foundation AI models that pose a serious risk to national security, economic security, or public health and safety to notify the federal government and share red-team safety test results before making the model available to the public. [Engadget, 2023-10-30]

name: 15 MAJOR AMERICAN TECHNOLOGY COMPANIES
description: 15 major American technology companies have begun voluntary commitments to ensure that AI technology is safe, secure, and trustworthy before releasing it to the public, in response to the President's leadership on AI regulation. [Engadget, 2023-10-30]

name: UNITED
description: "UNITED, officially recognized as Manchester United, is a renowned football club that has been navigating a season filled with unexpected challenges and a decade marked by disappointments in European competition, a period punctuated by both emotional highs and lows. Despite these struggles, the club, often referred to by its nickname 'Man United', recently secured a victory in a Premier League match against Chelsea with a final score of 2-1. The hero of the match was Scott McTominay, who scored both goals, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-12-06. However, the club's primary signing, Ten Hag, has been a subject of scrutiny amidst a strange season, and issues extend beyond the goalkeeper position, as highlighted by The Independent - Sports on 2023-12-12. In a recent encounter with Bayern Munich, Manchester United failed to make any significant impact, resulting in a non-event of a match."

name: SCOTT MCTOMINAY
description: Scott McTominay is a prominent midfielder for Manchester United, showcasing his exceptional skills and versatility on the field. Initially sidelined from Erik Ten Hag's plans, McTominay's dedication and hard work led to his successful reintegration into the team's strategy, as reported by The Independent - Sports on December 12, 2023. His resurgence has been marked by a significant contribution to the team's offensive capabilities, with McTominay becoming United's top scorer this season, as highlighted by Sporting News on December 6, 2023. In a standout performance against Chelsea, he scored two goals, including the opening goal in the 19th minute, and nearly secured a second goal in the 32nd minute, only to head directly at Sanchez, as detailed by Sporting News on the same date. McTominay's goal-scoring prowess is not limited to domestic matches; he also scored a crucial goal against Galatasaray in the Champions League, as noted by TalkSport on November 29, 2023. His fifth and sixth goals of the season, which helped solidify his position as the team's top scorer, were celebrated by The Guardian on December 6, 2023, further emphasizing his pivotal role in Manchester United's midfield and overall team tactics.

name: TEN HAG
description: Erik Ten Hag, the coach of Manchester United, has been a significant figure in the current season, which has been marked by unusual circumstances and challenges, as reported by The Independent - Sports on 2023-12-12. Despite the issues, Ten Hag has managed to enhance the attacking capabilities of midfielder Scott McTominay, as explained in a Sporting News article published on 2023-12-06. This strategic move has allowed McTominay to play a more prominent role in the team's offensive plays, showcasing Ten Hag's tactical acumen amidst a season fraught with difficulties. It is noteworthy that while Ten Hag is not explicitly the primary signing of Manchester United for the season, his role as the coach and the impact he has had on the team's performance and player development is highlighted, indicating his importance to the club's current roster.

name: $1/YR FEE
description: X is charging users a nominal $1 per year fee as part of its strategy to combat bots and spam on the platform [TechCrunch, 2023-10-18]

name: VERIFICATION PROGRAM
description: X's verification program includes a $1 'Not a Bot' feature and other methods to identify and stop bots, such as payment, phone, and ID verification [TechCrunch, 2023-10-18]

name: ERIC FARRARO
description: Eric Farraro is the director of engineering at X and has explained the company's broader plan to stop bots, acknowledging that AI will soon be able to mimic human interactions and that current bot-catching methods will need to evolve [TechCrunch, 2023-10-18]

name: MULLENWEG
description: Mullenweg is a person who wrote on his blog about the cost of creating bot accounts and the effectiveness of fees as a deterrent. [Source: TechCrunch, Time: 2023-10-18]

name: BENJAMIN NETANYAHU
description:
Benjamin Netanyahu, the Prime Minister of Israel, has been at the forefront of significant national and technological developments in October 2023. On the morning of October 7, 2023, Netanyahu announced that Israel had entered a state of war, emphasizing the country's first objective as the removal of hostile forces that had infiltrated Israeli territory, with the ultimate goal of restoring security and peace to the affected communities. This declaration was made amidst escalating tensions and direct threats to Israel's safety.

In addition to managing the country's military response, Netanyahu engaged in a conversation with Elon Musk, the renowned entrepreneur and CEO of Tesla and SpaceX, on October 18, 2023. The discussion centered around the implications of AI technology, its regulation, and the challenges posed by hate speech in the digital age. This meeting highlighted Netanyahu's interest in technology and its impact on society, demonstrating his commitment to addressing contemporary issues that affect both Israel and the global community.

Throughout these events, Netanyahu has maintained a strong leadership role, balancing the immediate needs of national defense with the long-term considerations of technological advancement and social harmony. His actions and statements reflect the complex responsibilities of a modern head of state, navigating through military conflicts while also engaging in dialogue about the future of technology and its ethical use.

name: ANTI-DEFAMATION LEAGUE
description: The Anti-Defamation League is an organization that accused both Elon Musk and X of being antisemitic. [Source: TechCrunch, Time: 2023-10-18]

name: SIMILARWEB

He argues that a fee for using X could exclude genuine users and increase the digital divide, using the example of the cost of living differences between the Philippines and New Zealand [TechCrunch, 2023-10-18]

name: LINE SHOPPING
description: Line Shopping is a strategic approach employed in the realm of sports betting, where bettors meticulously compare betting lines and odds offered by various sportsbooks. This practice is not limited to a specific type of bet but can be applied to moneylines, point spreads, totals, prop bets, and futures. By engaging in line shopping, bettors are able to identify and capitalize on the differences in odds and lines, which can significantly enhance their betting outcomes. This strategy involves checking the available options at multiple online sports betting sites to ensure that the bettor secures the most favorable terms for their wager. According to Sporting News (2023-11-06), line shopping is a time-worthy activity that can lead to improved betting results, making it an essential tool for bettors looking to maximize their profits in the competitive world of sports betting.

name: ODDSMAKING SERVICES
description: Oddsmaking services are companies that provide odds and lines for sports betting. They use sophisticated methods to set the odds, including computer models and algorithms that consider various factors such as analytics, statistics, and news. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: BETTING PUBLIC
description: The betting public refers to the collective group of bettors who place wagers on sports events. Their betting patterns can influence the lines and odds set by sportsbooks. [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: LIVE ODDS FEED
description: A live odds feed is a tool that provides real-time updates on the odds and lines for various sporting events, allowing bettors to compare and make informed decisions.[]

name: VEGAS LINE
description: The Vegas line is a reference point for betting lines and odds, often considered the standard in the sports betting industry. Sportsbooks may stray from this line due to increased betting on one side [Sporting News, 2023-11-06]

name: FLORIDA STATE
description: Florida State, a prominent college football team, experienced a controversial exclusion from the College Football Playoff (CFP) in 2023 despite being a one-loss champion, as highlighted by The New York Times on December 3, 2023. This exclusion came amidst their anticipation of having second-string quarterback Tate Rodemaker return, providing them a month to prepare for a potential semifinal game in the CFP. Ranked No. 4, Florida State was set to face No. 14 Louisville in the ACC championship game on Saturday at 8 p.m., as reported by Sporting News on December 1, 2023. However, they suffered a loss to Louisville in this championship game, which could have implications for Alabama's CFP standing, given Florida State's status as a one-loss team. Despite the setback, Florida State's performance and potential impact on the CFP landscape underscore their competitive presence in college football.

Despite leading his team with dedication and strategic prowess, Norvell found the committee's choice disheartening, emphasizing the hard work and commitment displayed by his players throughout the season. This sentiment reflects the competitive spirit and high expectations within the Florida State football community, where Norvell's leadership plays a crucial role in shaping the team's performance and aspirations.

name: QUENTIN TARANTINO
description: Quentin Tarantino is a renowned filmmaker, celebrated for his unique directorial style and contributions to the world of cinema, including the acclaimed 2009 film "Inglourious Basterds," which featured Eli Roth in a notable role. Despite his belief that directors do not necessarily improve with age, leading him to announce his intention to retire after making just 10 movies, Tarantino's perspective has been challenged by the late-stage career success of Martin Scorsese. This turn of events suggests that the creative spark does not have an expiration date, a notion that invites Tarantino, as well as other artists and critics, to reconsider their views on the relationship between age and artistic prowess.

name: MARTIN SCORSESE
description:
Martin Scorsese, a legendary and renowned film director, has an illustrious career spanning over 30 years, during which he has directed more than 27 feature-length narrative films. His 27th film, "Killers of the Flower Moon," is a significant addition to his body of work, serving as an act of lamentation and a powerful cinematic critique of one of the foundational horrors of the United States. The film, an adaptation of a major literary work of historical true crime, is described as a classic Scorsese Catholic reckoning, delving into themes of white supremacy and systemic racism. In a poignant moment, Scorsese appears in the movie's closing minutes, expressing a sense of guilt and culpability as a beneficiary of inequality.

In recent years, Scorsese has achieved the autonomy he longed for during the earlier stages of his career. This newfound control has allowed him to tell challenging stories, set his own budgets, and determine the run time of his films. He has been revisiting and revising his past work, creating great new films, and adding crucial addendums to his previous projects. This period in his career has been marked by a remarkable level of collaboration and creativity, with his films displaying a fluidity and vitality that was sometimes constrained before the 2000s. Scorsese's late career phase has only added to his legend, solidifying his status as a master filmmaker.

On a lighter note, Scorsese was quizzed on internet slang by his daughter, Francesca Scorsese, in a TikTok challenge. The video, posted on October 5, 2023, showed the director engaging with modern internet culture, demonstrating his willingness to connect with younger generations. While he initially misunderstood some terms, he was quick to correct himself or was helped by his daughter. Despite his age and the prestige of his career, Scorsese's participation in the quiz revealed a playful side and a curiosity about contemporary language and trends.

Among his notable works are "The Wolf of Wall Street," "King of Comedy," and "Taxi Driver," which have contributed to his reputation as a director who can create groundbreaking films even late in his career. Scorsese's ability to blend serious themes with engaging storytelling, combined with his openness to new experiences, makes him a unique figure in the world of cinema.

name: KILLERS OF THE FLOWER MOON
description: "Killers of the Flower Moon" is Martin Scorsese's 27th feature-length narrative film, marking his first foray into the Western genre. The movie, which has sparked significant public interest and conversation, is an adaptation of David Grann's 2017 historical true crime book of the same name. It serves as a poignant reflection of the dark undercurrents in American history, focusing on the reign of terror that targeted the Osage Native American tribe in the 1920s. The film stars notable actors Leonardo DiCaprio, Lily Gladstone, and Robert De Niro, and is centered around the characters of Ernest Burkhart, William Hale, and Mollie Kyle. "Killers of the Flower Moon" is described as an act of lamentation and a cinematic wail against one of the many foundational horrors of the United States, a crime that remains vividly in living memory. The movie's release has been highly anticipated, with many viewing it as a testament to Scorsese's continued capability for groundbreaking greatness. [Polygon, 2023-10-26; The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-10; Polygon, 2023-10-07]

name: DAVID GRANN
description: David Grann is a distinguished writer known for his compelling narratives, particularly his 2017 book "Killers of the Flower Moon." This book delves into the harrowing true story of the reign of terror that targeted the Osage Nation in the 1920s, a period marred by murder and deceit. Grann's meticulous research and gripping storytelling have not only earned critical acclaim but also caught the attention of renowned filmmaker Martin Scorsese. Scorsese adapted Grann's book into a major motion picture, also titled "Killers of the Flower Moon," further cementing Grann's work as a significant contribution to both literature and cinema. The book serves as the historical foundation and narrative backbone for the film, providing a rich and detailed account of the events that shocked the nation and changed the course of the Osage's history.

name: WHITE SUPREMACY AND SYSTEMIC RACISM
description: White supremacy and systemic racism are themes explored in Martin Scorsese's film "Killers of the Flower Moon." The film is full of unsparing and punishing conclusions and self-recriminations in the wake of George Floyd's death and the 2020 protests. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-26]

name: THE DEPARTED
description: "The Departed" is a film by Martin Scorsese that is referenced for its nervy energy incorporated into "Killers of the Flower Moon." [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-26]

name: THE WOLF OF WALL STREET
description: "The Wolf of Wall Street" is a film directed by the renowned filmmaker Martin Scorsese. This movie has been discussed in various contexts, one of which is in relation to the term "slept on," as mentioned in an article by The Independent - Life and Style on 2023-10-10. The term "slept on" typically refers to something that has been overlooked or underestimated, suggesting that the film may have aspects that are not immediately recognized by the audience but are worth exploring. Additionally, "The Wolf of Wall Street" is noted for its nervy energy, which has been referenced in the context of Scorsese's later work, "Killers of the Flower Moon," as reported by Polygon on 2023-10-26. This indicates that Scorsese's style and energy in "The Wolf of Wall Street" have left a lasting impact and have been influential in his subsequent projects.

name: EUROPA LEAGUE
description: The Europa League is a prominent football competition where teams can qualify through their performance in various domestic leagues and, notably, third-place finishers from each Champions League group are dropped into the playoff round, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-12-12. Liverpool, a participating team, has been demonstrating exceptional prowess by cruising through the group stage, as indicated by The Guardian on 2023-10-20. However, Manchester United will not be a part of the Europa League due to their recent defeat, as mentioned by The Independent - Sports on 2023-12-12. This football tournament is a significant platform for teams to showcase their skills and compete at an international level, offering a second chance to those who just missed out on the Champions League's knockout stages.

name: ANDY ROBERTSON
description: Andy Robertson, a Liverpool player, is out for up to three months due to a shoulder injury, which has heightened defensive concerns for the team. [The Guardian, 2023-10-20]

name: EVERTON
description:
Everton, a football club with a rich history, has been at the center of significant developments both on and off the pitch in 2023. The club, which has been a mainstay in the Premier League, faced a substantial challenge when it was penalized with a 10-point deduction for breaching financial rules, a penalty that has had a profound impact on their survival prospects amidst a relegation battle. Despite this setback, Everton demonstrated resilience, winning six out of nine recent games, including a notable 3-0 victory over Newcastle, which helped them move clear of the relegation zone. The team's performance has shown overall improvement, with three wins in the past four games, although they have scored more than once in only eight Premier League matches over the past 12 months.

In a poignant moment for the club, Bill Kenwright, who had served as chairman since 2004, passed away, leading Everton to announce that it was "in mourning." Kenwright was recognized as the club's longest-serving chairman in more than a century, a testament to his dedication and influence on the team. These events have underscored the dynamic nature of Everton's journey, highlighting both the challenges and the spirit that defines the club.

name: SEAN DYCHE
description: Sean Dyche is the manager of Everton Football Club, a position he holds with unwavering confidence in his own abilities, those of his staff, and the potential of his players, as noted by The Guardian on 2023-11-24. Despite the club facing a significant 10-point penalty for breaching Premier League financial rules, Dyche remains optimistic, believing that this challenge will only serve to galvanize the team and its supporters. He chose not to speculate on the broader implications of Everton's punishment for other clubs, such as Manchester City and Chelsea, who are also under investigation for financial breaches. As reported by The Guardian on 2023-10-20, Dyche is a strategic thinker, hoping to take advantage of any post-international fatigue in Liverpool's team when facing them. The Roar | Sports Writers Blog on 2023-12-07 highlighted Dyche's assertion that, absent the ten-point penalty, Everton would be in a more favorable position in the league. Throughout these tough times, Dyche's leadership and belief in Everton's resilience are evident, showcasing his commitment to the club and its success amidst adversity.

name: BURNLEY
description: Burnley, a football team known for their robust defensive strategies under the management of Sean Dyche, has presented a formidable challenge to opponents this season. As evidenced in a match against Manchester United, Burnley's defensive strength made them a "super-difficult" team to crack, a testament to their tactical discipline and organization on the pitch. Despite this, Manchester United's Bruno Fernandes managed to score a goal against Burnley, highlighting a significant moment in their encounter. These insights into Burnley's performance and tactics are drawn from reports by The Guardian on October 20 and October 28, 2023.

name: THE GUARDIAN
description:
The Guardian, a prominent news organization, actively covers a wide range of topics in the realm of entertainment and sports. In recent months, The Guardian has published various articles and live reports, showcasing its diverse editorial focus. On December 13, 2023, The Guardian provided a live report of the T20 international cricket match between the West Indies and England, keeping cricket enthusiasts updated in real-time. The outlet also delved into the personal life of Britney Spears, releasing an article on October 24, 2023, that discussed her memoir, which candidly addressed issues of body shaming, her experiences under a conservatorship, and her sexuality, offering readers a deeper understanding of the pop icon's journey.

In the world of football, The Guardian has been a reliable source of information, with Jonathan Liew contributing insightful pieces. On December 6, 2023, Liew wrote about the intense football game between Manchester United and Chelsea, capturing the excitement and nuances of the match. Earlier, on December 1, 2023, he discussed England's national team and their participation in the post-pandemic international cycle, providing analysis on the team's performance and the challenges they faced in the changing landscape of international football. Additionally, The Guardian covered Liverpool FC and the anticipation surrounding the upcoming Merseyside derby on October 20, 2023, offering insights into the team's strategies and the significance of the event for fans.

Overall, The Guardian demonstrates a commitment to comprehensive coverage, engaging with both sports enthusiasts and those interested in the personal narratives of entertainment figures, making it a go-to source for diverse content.

name: GOGORO
description:
Gogoro, a pioneering company in battery-swapping technology for electric vehicles, has experienced a complex year in terms of financial performance and strategic expansion. Originating from Taiwan, Gogoro's battery-swapping service has seen a significant growth in revenue, reaching $33.6 million, marking a 10.4% increase year-on-year. This success is attributed to the widespread adoption of its battery-swapping system in Taiwan, where it captures 93% of all electric vehicles, with about 80% using Gogoro's own branded vehicles. However, the company's overall revenue has dropped, with a 10.2% year-on-year decrease, leading to a net loss of $3.1 million. Gogoro attributes this decline to lobbying efforts against electric vehicle adoption and the lingering effects of the COVID-19 pandemic.

Despite these challenges, Gogoro is looking to diversify and expand its operations, particularly by entering the Indian market. The company is optimistic about replicating its Taiwan model in India, planning to launch 30 battery-swapping stations in Delhi by Q1 2024. Gogoro's technology is not only limited to passenger vehicles but also extends to auto-rickshaws, a popular mode of transportation in India. By collaborating with vehicle manufacturers in India, Gogoro aims to tap into the growing demand for efficient alternatives to Internal Combustion Engine (ICE) vehicles, aligning with the Indian government's ambitious target of achieving 30% EV adoption by 2030. The company's expansion into India could potentially serve as a manufacturing hub, further solidifying its position in the global electric vehicle market. Despite the stagnation and decline in growth observed in Taiwan, Gogoro's battery-swapping service remains a key driver of its business, and the company is hopeful that its India venture will contribute to a turnaround in its financial fortunes.
