description: Shen Yun, a dance troupe renowned for its heavily advertised performances, is an integral part of a nonprofit network that includes The Epoch Times and a digital production company. This network is referred to as "our media" by the leader of the Falun Gong religious movement, indicating a close association between these entities. In 2021, Shen Yun received a significant financial contribution of $10.4 million from The Epoch Times, highlighting the financial interdependence within this network.

name: LI
description:
Li, the founder and leader of Falun Gong—a personal development movement blending Buddhism and Taoism—holds a significant influence over the group's beliefs and actions. Falun Gong, often regarded by its followers as a path to salvation amidst the approaching end of the world, has teachings that reject modern science, art, and medicine, and denounce aspects of worldliness such as homosexuality and feminism. Li is venerated as a God-like figure by his followers, who believe he possesses extraordinary abilities including levitation, walking through walls, and precognition.

In 1999, Li fled to the United States following China's ban on Falun Gong, which was labeled a cult and faced a severe crackdown. Despite his earlier teachings that encouraged followers to avoid involvement in U.S. politics, Li's stance appeared to evolve. At a Falun Gong conference in 2018, he indicated a shift towards explicit support of Republicans, suggesting that Falun Gong's media outlets should present news in a "constructive" light to further the group's objectives. He justified this by stating that it was not wrong to cover a politician whose values and goals align with Falun Gong's conservative principles. These developments were reported in a Hacker News article published on 2023-10-16, providing insights into the complex dynamics of Falun Gong and its leader's evolving political stance.

name: CHINESE COMMUNIST PARTY
description: The Chinese Communist Party banned Falun Gong in 1999, labeling it a cult and conducting a brutal crackdown on its followers, which included confiscation of books, blocking of websites, closure of teaching centers, and arrests. Human rights groups reported that some adherents were sent to labor camps, while others were tortured and killed. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: JOHN TANG
description: John Tang is a Falun Gong practitioner who founded The Epoch Times in Georgia in 2000 and remains its CEO. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: NEW TANG DYNASTY TELEVISION
description: New Tang Dynasty Television is a TV production company associated with The Epoch Times, which has a home base in New York. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: ROMAN BALMAKOV
description: Roman Balmakov is a former Epoch Times delivery person who now hosts the online show Facts Matter. The Epoch Times spent millions on internet-infamous ads featuring him railing against the mainstream media, communism, and the persecution of Trump. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: NBC NEWS
description: NBC NEWS is a prominent media organization known for its comprehensive coverage of various topics. In one instance, NBC News published an article under the byline of Evan Bush, highlighting the views of Peter Kalmus and the Possibility Alliance on climate change and the necessary lifestyle adjustments to combat it. This piece reflects the organization's commitment to addressing environmental issues and the perspectives of activists in the field. On another front, NBC News reported on The Epoch Times' aggressive pro-Trump ad campaigns, noting the use of foreign actors posing as Americans to disseminate political content. This coverage, which was significant enough to lead to a ban from Facebook advertising in 2019, demonstrates NBC News' role in scrutinizing and exposing manipulative practices in media and politics, as acknowledged by Hacker News on October 16, 2023. Through these reports, NBC News showcases its dedication to investigative journalism and its impact on public discourse.

name: DATA BROKERS
description: Data brokers are companies that collect and sell personal data, including addresses, specifically for conservatives aged 60 and over.[]

name: A.J. BAUER
description: A.J. Bauer is an assistant journalism professor at the University of Alabama who studies conservative media. He noted that The Epoch Times' dynamic changed in 2020, partly because of their criticism of China around Covid.[]

name: STEVE BANNON
description: Steve Bannon is a political figure whose glowing testimonial was hosted on The Epoch Times' subscription page.[]

name: GLENN BECK
description: Glenn Beck is a media personality whose glowing testimonial was hosted on The Epoch Times' subscription page.[]

name: PAUL GOSAR
description: Paul Gosar is a far-right Arizona congressman whose glowing testimonial was hosted on The Epoch Times' subscription page.[]

name: ELECTION INTEGRITY PARTNERSHIP
description: The Election Integrity Partnership is a coalition of researchers that documented misinformation and the 2020 vote. The group cited The Epoch Times as a "repeat spreader" of false and misleading voter fraud stories as well as a major promoter of debunked conspiracy theories around Dominion voting machines and the "Stop the Steal" movement.[]

name: NATIONAL CHRISTIAN CHARITABLE FOUNDATION
description: The National Christian Charitable Foundation is a foundation that connects anonymous donors with Christian causes. It gave $55,750 to The Epoch Times in 2021. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: DONORS TRUST
description: Donors Trust is a fund for conservative and libertarian donors. It gave $31,000 to The Epoch Times in 2021. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: DATA MANAGING CORPORATION
description: Data Managing Corporation is a company that received $2.7 million from The Epoch Times for advertising services in 2021. Its listed address is a single-family home in New Jersey owned by a reporter for The Epoch Times. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: NEW TANG DYNASTY
description: New Tang Dynasty is a media organization that produces videos. It received $8.3 million from The Epoch Times in 2021. [Hacker News, 2023-10-16]

name: EPOCH TIMES
description: The Epoch Times is a media outlet that has gone mainstream and made millions, often associated with Falun Gong and promoting conspiracy theories. The details are from a Hacker News article published on 2023-10-16

name: HACKER NEWS
description: Hacker News is a news source that published an article on 2023-10-16 about the mainstream success and financial gains of The Epoch Times, which is linked to Falun Gong

name: CHINESE FIRM
description: A Chinese firm, linked to the repression of Uyghurs, is aiding Israeli surveillance in the West Bank [The Guardian, 2023-11-11]

name: ISRAELI SURVEILLANCE
description: Israeli surveillance in the West Bank is being assisted by a Chinese firm linked to the repression of Uyghurs [The Guardian, 2023-11-11]

name: UYGHURS
description: Uyghurs are a group that has been repressed by a Chinese firm, which is now aiding Israeli surveillance in the West Bank [The Guardian, 2023-11-11]

name: HUMAN RIGHTS
description: Human rights are being profoundly impacted in problematic ways by the use of technologies by a Chinese firm and Israeli surveillance in the West Bank [The Guardian, 2023-11-11]

name: IROBOT
description: iRobot, a prominent company in the technology and home automation sector, specializes in the production of robotic vacuum cleaners (RVCs). The entity has recently garnered significant attention due to Amazon's acquisition plans, which have raised formal competition concerns within the European Union. As of November 27, 2023, the EU bloc remains vigilant over the potential influence Amazon may exert on competitive outcomes in its marketplace, specifically in relation to iRobot versus rival robot vacuum brands. This scrutiny highlights the intense competition iRobot faces from other vacuum cleaner suppliers in the market. Additionally, iRobot has been navigating challenges, including increased debt, as the deal with Amazon has been delayed due to the ongoing regulatory examination. Despite these hurdles, iRobot continues to innovate and maintain its position as a leading robot vacuum maker.

name: ROBOT VACUUM CLEANERS (RVCS)
description: Robot vacuum cleaners (RVCs) are a product category that the European Union regulators are concerned about in relation to Amazon's proposed acquisition of iRobot. The transaction could potentially restrict competition in this market, leading to higher prices and reduced innovation.

name: RVCS
description: RVCs (Robotic Vacuum Cleaners) are a type of product offered by iRobot and other companies. The EU is concerned that Amazon's acquisition of iRobot could restrict competition in the RVC market, leading to higher prices, lower quality, and less innovation for consumers [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: DIGITAL MARKETS ACT
description: The Digital Markets Act is a new ex ante competition regulation in the EU that designates certain large online platforms as gatekeepers. It lists Amazon's marketplace as a core platform service and imposes a series of up-front obligations on the company, including restrictions on self-preferencing [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: WIRE
description: WIRE, known more widely as Wired, is a distinguished media organization that specializes in publishing insightful articles and comprehensive guides on technology, products, and entertainment. As of 2023, Wired has been actively providing its readers with valuable information, such as the Best Portable Chargers guide, released on 2023-10-10. Additionally, the outlet has featured exclusive deals on popular tech items like the Apple Watch SE, Apple Watch Ultra 2, and the Silver Milanese Loop band in their Best Prime Day Apple Deals guide for 2023, published on the same date. Not stopping there, Wired also covers post-holiday sales, offering a guide to Walmart's Cyber Monday deals on 2023-11-27, ensuring that their audience stays informed and engaged with the latest in technology and product trends.

name: NINTENDO SWITCH OLED
description: The Nintendo Switch OLED, a gaming device renowned for its vibrant display and versatile gaming capabilities, is currently making waves in the market. As of 2023-11-27, a noteworthy Cyber Monday deal has been reported by Wired, highlighting that Walmart is offering the Nintendo Switch OLED at a special price. Typically retailing for $349, this deal presents an excellent opportunity for gamers to acquire the console at a potentially discounted rate, making it an attractive choice for those looking to enhance their gaming experience with the latest technology from Nintendo.

name: LAPTOP
description: Wired recommends a 14-inch laptop with an AMD Ryzen 7 (7730U) processor, 16 gigabytes of RAM, and 512 gigabytes of storage, which is part of Walmart's Cyber Monday deals on 2023-11-27[]

name: DUALSENSE CONTROLLER
description: The DualSense controller, a gaming accessory renowned for its exceptional haptic feedback technology, offers users a directional and immersive experience akin to surround sound within a controller. This innovative feature has been widely praised for enhancing the gaming experience by providing a more realistic and engaging interaction with the game environment. As of 2023-11-27, according to Wired, the DualSense controller is available at a discounted price during Walmart's Cyber Monday deals, making it an attractive purchase for gamers looking to upgrade their gaming experience.

name: LG DUALUP
description: The LG DualUp is a technologically advanced monitor, specifically engineered for vertical usage, boasting a unique 16:18 aspect ratio that complements its upright design. This feature ensures a wider viewing angle and minimizes content cut-off, making it an ideal choice for tasks that require a vertical orientation, such as coding, graphic design, or reading long documents. The monitor is praised for its excellent color accuracy, which is crucial for professionals in the creative fields. Additionally, it comes equipped with an arm mount, facilitating a quick and easy setup process. As of 2023-11-27, the LG DualUp is featured in Walmart's Cyber Monday deals, offering potential buyers an attractive opportunity to acquire this innovative monitor at a discounted price, as reported by Wired.

name: KITCHEN APPLIANCES
description: Kitchen appliances are a category of products that include blenders, juicers, and chef's knives, which are covered in the Best Blenders, Best Juicers, and Best Chef's Knives guides. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: DYSON V12 DETECT SLIM
description: The Dyson V12 Detect Slim, a mid-level model in Dyson's lineup, is designed with a focus on versatility and ease of use. It offers slightly less suction power and a smaller dust bin compared to the V15 Detect Absolute, making it suitable for a variety of cleaning tasks without the bulk. This vacuum cleaner is equipped with an LCD screen that allows users to select power levels and monitor essential information such as battery status, filter conditions, and blockage alerts. Its lightweight construction and maneuverability are key features, ensuring that cleaning is efficient and effortless. As of 2023, the Dyson V12 Detect Slim continues to be a popular choice for those seeking a balance between performance and convenience.

name: DYSON
description: Dyson, a renowned company in the realm of technology and design, is celebrated for its innovative stick vacuums, with the V12 Detect Slim being a notable model. The company has a unique approach to product development, seamlessly blending functionality with aesthetic appeal, as evidenced by the Pure Hot + Cool, a versatile device that combines air purification, heating, and cooling capabilities. Dyson's commitment to integrating cutting-edge technology with beautiful form has solidified its position as a leader in the industry, as recognized by Wired on 2023-11-27.

name: BISSELL
description: BISSELL is a renowned company specializing in the production of cleaning machines. Among their offerings is a model that has gained significant recognition, earning spots on both the Best Carpet Cleaners and the Best Viral TikTok Gadgets lists. This particular model boasts an impressive filtration size of 0.3 microns, ensuring that it can effectively remove even the tiniest particles from carpets. Additionally, BISSELL has been innovative in integrating an air quality monitor into their product line, further enhancing the cleaning experience and contributing to a healthier living environment. The company is also celebrated for its Green Machine, a portable and cordless carpet cleaner that is particularly handy for dealing with spills and pet-related accidents. Its ease of use and efficient cleaning capabilities make it a popular choice among consumers looking for a quick and effective solution to maintain the cleanliness of their carpets. [Sources: Wired, 2023-11-27; Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: K-EXPRESS
description: The K-Express is a compact coffee machine with a width of 6.5 inches and a depth of 12 inches. It has a 36-fluid-ounce, removable reservoir that can make a round of coffee for multiple people without needing constant refills. It is recommended to use Keurig Reusable Pods to reduce plastic waste. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: KEURIG REUSABLE PODS
description: Keurig Reusable Pods are a product that can be used with the K-Express coffee machine to cut down on single-use plastic waste. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: STILOSA
description: The Stilosa is a budget-friendly espresso machine that is compact and reliable. It comes with a solid portafilter, a reliable steam pump, and a steaming wand. Unlike other cheap machines, the Stilosa did not show signs of slowing down. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: NINJA CREAMI
description: The Ninja Creami is a kitchen gadget that makes ice cream. It is not essential but is a fun tool for experimenting with sorbets and ice cream recipes. Ninja also offers a $17 recipe book for the Ninja Creami. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: NINJA CREAMI RECIPE BOOK
description: The Ninja Creami recipe book is a $17 guide that provides ideas for recipes to use with the Ninja Creami kitchen gadget. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SAMSUNG QN900C
description: The Samsung QN900C is a newly released TV that is on sale. It has "brilliantly clear and detailed video," rich color shading, deep blacks, and butter-smooth motion processing. It can display up to 8K resolution. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: LG C3<||LG C3
description: The LG C3 is a TV with stunningly fast response times of 9.2 milliseconds and support for 4K display. It is described by WIRED associate reviews editor Parker Hall as having vivid, high-contrast images. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: LG C3
description: The LG C3, a highly recommended choice for gamers, boasts LG's OLED panels which deliver exceptional visual experiences with perfect black levels. This model features a 120-Hz refresh rate, ensuring smooth gameplay and a 9.2 millisecond response time, significantly reducing input lag. As noted by Wired on 2023-10-19, the LG C3 is a top contender in the gaming TV market, combining cutting-edge technology with performance that meets the demands of avid gamers.

name: JBL
description: JBL, a renowned company in the audio equipment industry, specializes in manufacturing high-quality soundbars and speakers. As highlighted in Wired on 2023-10-10, JBL's Bar 1300X soundbar was featured in Prime Day deals, offering consumers an excellent opportunity to purchase this top-tier product at a discounted price. The Bar 1300X is part of a versatile multi-piece soundbar system, noted for its superior Dolby Atmos immersion, providing an immersive audio experience. This system boasts fully wireless surround sound speakers that can be conveniently placed behind the listener for a more enveloping sound or used as portable Bluetooth speakers. A unique feature is the ability to connect these speakers back to the main bar for charging and playback, ensuring they remain charged and ready for use. JBL's product range, as listed on their website, includes various audio equipment, solidifying their position as a comprehensive audio solutions provider.

name: KLIPSCH
description: Klipsch is a company that has a talent for crafting soundbars that prioritize sound quality over frills. The Cinema 600 is an excellent example, built from a speaker-like MDF cabinet and paired with a massive 10-inch subwoofer driver, offering clear and powerful sound suitable for music and cinematic experiences [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: POLK AUDIO
description: Polk Audio is a company that produces the Signa 4, one of the most affordable Dolby Atmos soundbars of its kind. It offers true up-firing drivers, a wireless subwoofer for beefy bass, and generally pleasing performance, making it a great deal at its current price [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONY HT-A5000
description: Sony’s HT-A5000 is a soundbar with engulfing surround sound expansion and a wide range of features, including next-gen HDMI with VRR support for gaming consoles, multiple ways to stream over Wi-Fi, support for both Dolby Atmos and DTS:X, hi-res audio, and more [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONOS ARC
description: The Sonos Arc is a soundbar favored for big home theaters, equipped with three tweeters and eight mid-woofers to deliver deep bass and full Dolby Atmos support. It can bounce sound off walls and ceilings to mimic a surround sound setup and was on sale for the same price during holiday sales last year [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONOS BEAM GEN 2
description: The SONOS BEAM GEN 2 is a technologically advanced soundbar designed to elevate audio experiences with its support for Dolby Atmos, ensuring immersive and enhanced sound quality. It features a fast processor for seamless operation and an HDMI eARC port, enabling high-definition audio connectivity. This versatile device is compatible with popular voice assistants such as Alexa and Google Assistant, and also supports AirPlay 2 for convenient streaming from Apple devices. The SONOS BEAM GEN 2 can be integrated with other Sonos speakers to create a comprehensive surround sound system, making it an ideal choice for home entertainment setups. As of 2023-11-27, the soundbar is available at the lowest price tracked, as reported by Wired, presenting an excellent opportunity for potential buyers to invest in superior audio technology.

name: BOSE SMART 900
description: The Bose Smart 900 soundbar has been updated to include better bass extension and true up-firing drivers for expansive Dolby Atmos and virtual surround sound. This is the first time the price has dropped. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SENNHEISER
description: Sennheiser is a company known for its luxury soundbar model that provides high-flying virtual surround sound and Dolby Atmos. The model has a hefty unit without a separate subwoofer but offers punchy grooves, musicality, and convenience features like Wi-Fi streaming and an analog input at a price that has finally dropped below the stratosphere. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SAMSUNG HW-Q800C
description: Samsung’s HW-Q800C is a two-piece sound system that includes upfiring Dolby Atmos speakers and side-firing drivers for an engaging cinematic experience. Its wireless subwoofer adds a punch to effects and streaming music. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: ULTRAHUMAN RING AIR
description: The Ultrahuman Ring Air is a fitness and sleep-tracking accessory, expertly crafted from titanium, which offers durability and a sleek design. This ring is available in various colors, allowing users to choose a style that best suits their preferences. It is designed to monitor physical activities and sleep patterns throughout the day and night, delivering comprehensive data to a companion app. Despite its four-day battery life, which is a commendable feature for a wearable device, the Ultrahuman Ring Air's fitness tracking capabilities have been noted to be less reliable than expected. Additionally, the black version of the ring is prone to scuffing easily, which might be a concern for those who value aesthetics. A noteworthy aspect is that the Ultrahuman Ring Air does not require a subscription for its services, making it a cost-effective choice for individuals interested in tracking their health and wellness without ongoing financial commitments.

name: WHOOP 4
description: The WHOOP 4 is a sophisticated fitness tracker designed to promote a healthier lifestyle and enhance fitness levels. Unlike traditional wearables, it doesn't feature a screen but instead, seamlessly transfers data to a companion app, providing users with comprehensive insights into their health and wellness. The device is known for its accurate tracking capabilities, although specific features are not detailed in the source. It's important to note that the WHOOP 4 comes with a significant financial commitment, requiring a subscription that costs $30 per month. However, the subscription includes a year's deal, offering some relief to the overall cost. As reported by Wired on 2023-11-27, the WHOOP 4 is a notable addition to the wearable technology market, catering to health-conscious individuals seeking detailed health metrics without the need for a screen on the device.

name: VERSA 4
description: The Versa 4 is the best Fitbit smartwatch available, with a six-day battery life in testing (if the display is not left on the entire time). It features a vibrant 1.5-inch AMOLED touchscreen, easy and snappy use, and a rich list of features including Google apps like Maps[2023-11-27, Wired]

name: POWERBEATS PRO WIRELESS EARBUDS
description: The Powerbeats Pro Wireless Earbuds, released in 2019, are recommended for their secure fit, making them suitable for intensive workouts. They have an IPX4 water-resistance rating, protecting them from sweat, and offer excellent sound quality[2023-11-27, Wired]

name: SONY WH-1000XM5 HEADPHONES
description: Sony’s WH-1000XM5 headphones, the priciest wireless headphones from Sony, deliver upgraded noise canceling, a new design, and a more refined sound signature, making them a great package especially on sale[2023-11-27, Wired]

name: BOSE QUIETCOMFORT ULTRA HEADPHONES
description: Bose’s QuietComfort Ultra headphones, released in October, have class-leading noise canceling, great sound, and a luxuriously comfy design loaded with modern features. They are pricey but have already received a discount[2023-11-27, Wired]

name: SONY WH-1000XM4 HEADPHONES
description: Sony's WH-1000XM4 headphones have been a popular pair of wireless headphones for years, offering reliable performance and features[2023-11-27, Wired]

name: TECHNICS EAH-AZ80
description: The Technics EAH-AZ80 are top-shelf earbuds with fantastic sound, great features, noise canceling, and the ability to connect to up to three devices at once. They are currently on sale, making their very high asking price more palatable. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SOUNDCORE LIFE Q30
description: Soundcore's Life Q30 are earbuds with impressive noise canceling that exceeds its class. They offer accessible and adjustable sound quality, good features, and great battery life. The current deal makes them a great value. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: AURA FRAMES
description: Aura makes the best digital picture frames, with photos that look great and not too bright. They have a mat look and are discounted regularly. The newest 15-inch Walden frame is currently $249 ($50 off). [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: NANOLEAF LINES
description: The Nanoleaf Lines are modular smart lighting bars that can be installed on walls and arranged into any design. They are great for subtle ambient light and can sync to music or mirror screens for gaming immersion. The starter kit is at its cheapest price. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: EUFYCAM 3
description: The EufyCam 3 is a sophisticated smart security camera system designed to capture high-quality footage in up to 4K resolution. It offers 16 GB of local storage on a connected home base, which can be expanded to an impressive 16 TB, catering to extensive recording needs. A notable feature is its integrated solar panels, enabling the system to recharge its batteries, promoting sustainable and continuous operation. The EufyCam 3 is equipped with onboard AI technology, capable of detecting people, pets, vehicles, and recognizing faces, enhancing its surveillance capabilities. However, it is acknowledged that the system comes with a premium price tag and has previously encountered security incidents, which attracted criticism. In response, the company has taken proactive measures to address these concerns and improve the system's security, demonstrating a commitment to customer safety and privacy.

name: WALMART CYBER MONDAY DEALS
description: Walmart's Cyber Monday Deals offer some of the best value in their class from one of the top names in the business. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: GOOGLE NEST CAM
description: Google's Nest Cam (Wired) is a smart indoor security camera that blends in easily and accurately detects people, animals, and vehicles. It offers 1080p footage with HDR and a high frame rate. However, access to more than three hours of history requires a subscription to Nest Aware, starting at $6 per month, which includes familiar face recognition. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: TP-LINK DECO X20
description: The Deco X20 is a solid Wi-Fi 6 mesh system from TP-Link, appearing as the budget pick in our Best Mesh Routers guide. It is a dual-band (2.4-GHz and 5-GHz) system with parental controls and basic security, performing dependably well. The system is frequently discounted, usually priced between $160 and $180. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: GOOGLE NEST WIFI PRO
description: The Google Nest Wi-Fi Pro is one of our favorite mesh systems, recommended for its ability to bring Wi-Fi to every corner of a home. It employs the 6-GHz band for backhaul, covers 2,200 square feet per unit, and can connect up to 100 devices. However, it is not backward compatible with older Nest routers. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONOS SUB SPEAKER GEN 3
description: The Sonos Sub (Gen 3) is a speaker recommended in our guides to the best speakers, best Bluetooth speaker, and the best gear for audiophiles. Details about its features and pricing are not provided in the text. [Source: Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: NEST ROUTERS
description: Nest routers are devices used for home networking, but the newer models are not backward compatible with older Nest routers

name: SONOS SUB (GEN 3)
description: The Sonos Sub (Gen 3) is a speaker designed to upgrade bass in a sound system. It has better processing power and more memory than previous models and is meant to be paired with Sonos' non-portable options like soundbars, speakers, and amplifiers. It is expensive but top-notch and is currently at the lowest price tracked so far [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONOS AMP
description: The Sonos Amp is an amplifier option for those looking to power their turntable, TV, outdoor speakers, and more at higher volumes. It has a touch-sensitive front control panel for pausing music and adjusting volume and connects via the Sonos app with support for AirPlay 2. It does not have built-in mics but allows voice control when paired with another Sonos voice-enabled speaker [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: SONOS PORT
description: The Sonos Port is a device that streams to an external amp, which then sends a signal to the speakers. Unlike the Sonos Amp, it does not come with a control panel but can be controlled through the Sonos app for adjusting treble, bass, and volume. It also supports AirPlay 2 and can be paired with other Sonos speakers for voice control [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: BOSE SOUNDLINK REVOLVE+
description: Bose's Soundlink Revolve+ is a portable speaker that offers excellent sound in a neat and water-resistant design with up to 17 hours of battery life. It is currently on sale at a price lower than its usual $300+ price point [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: JBL FLIP SPEAKERS
description: JBL's Flip speakers are portable and waterproof devices that provide great sound quality, more detailed and powerful than expected for their size. The newest model includes a separate tweeter for better detail and is currently on sale [Wired, 2023-11-27]

name: WIRELESS SPEAKERS
description: Wireless speakers are a category of audio devices that can connect to other devices without wires, often used for home entertainment systems or portable music listening

name: WIRELESS AMPLIFIERS
description: Wireless amplifiers are devices that can boost the signal of wireless speakers and are often used for powering audio systems in larger spaces or for specific devices like turntables or TVs

name: ADAM D’ANGELO
description: Adam D’Angelo, the CEO of Quora, is a significant figure in the technology industry. Not only is he the founder of Quora, a platform known for its extensive question-and-answer format that fosters knowledge sharing and community engagement, but he is also a current member of the OpenAI board. As of November 18, 2023, Adam is reported to be involved in discussions with Sam Altman, the CEO of OpenAI, indicating his active participation in shaping the future of artificial intelligence. Moreover, it is confirmed that Adam will be part of the new initial board of directors at OpenAI, a role that underscores his influence and expertise in the tech sector. His dual involvement with Quora and OpenAI highlights his commitment to advancing both human knowledge and AI capabilities.

name: HELEN TONER
description: Helen Toner is a board member of OpenAI who was pushed out by Sam Altman due to a critical paper she co-wrote, contributing to the current predicament of the company [The New York Times, 2023-11-18]

name: DARIO AMODEI
description: Dario Amodei, a prominent figure in the field of artificial intelligence, is recognized as the co-founder and CEO of Anthropic, a leading competitor in the large-language model development sector. In a significant move that garnered industry attention, Amodei was approached by the board of OpenAI, a major player in AI, with a proposal for a merger between the two companies. Additionally, the offer included the possibility of Amodei taking over as the CEO of OpenAI, replacing Sam Altman. However, demonstrating a commitment to Anthropic's independent trajectory and vision, Amodei declined the high-profile opportunity, a decision reported by The Information on November 18, 2023. This strategic choice reflects Amodei's dedication to shaping Anthropic's future in the AI landscape on its own terms.

name: ANTHROPIC
description: Anthropic, a prominent rival to OpenAI in the development of large-language models, has recently been approached by OpenAI's board for a potential merger, as reported by The Information on 2023-11-18. Under the leadership of CEO Dario Amodei, the company has been actively engaging in the AI industry's discourse on copyright issues. According to Music Business Worldwide on 2023-11-30, Anthropic submitted its perspective to the US Copyright Office, arguing that the use of copyrighted works for training AI models falls under fair use, as the copying is merely an intermediate step for generating new outputs. This stance positions Anthropic as a proponent of a more open ethos in AI development, potentially attracting businesses seeking multi-modal strategies amidst recent industry turmoil, as noted by TechCrunch on 2023-11-21. As a key player in the AI sector, Anthropic's actions and viewpoints are closely watched, especially in relation to its competitive dynamics with OpenAI.

name: BRAD LIGHTCAP
description: Brad Lightcap is the COO of OpenAI. He sent an internal memo explaining that the board's decision to fire Sam Altman was not due to malfeasance or issues with the company's practices

name: THRIVE CAPITAL
description: Thrive Capital, a prominent investment firm, is currently spearheading the planned sale of OpenAI employee shares. This significant transaction, however, is facing potential challenges and uncertainties. The recent dismissal of Sam Altman, a key figure at OpenAI, has cast a shadow over the proceedings, possibly jeopardizing the sale. As reported by TechCrunch on November 18, 2023, the situation is evolving and the outcome remains uncertain, with the investment community closely monitoring the developments.

name: BROCKMAN
description: Greg Brockman, known as "BROCKMAN" in certain contexts, is a significant figure in the technology industry who recently announced his resignation from OpenAI, a leading artificial intelligence research laboratory, on November 18, 2023, as reported by TechCrunch. His departure was linked to "today's news," suggesting a connection to events or decisions that were unfolding at the time. Brockman is also recognized for his role in testing the capabilities of GPT-4, an advanced AI model, by administering a multiple-choice biology test, as noted by The Age on December 9, 2023. Additionally, Brockman has been involved in allegations concerning the firing of Sam Altman, a prominent figure in the AI community and a co-founder of OpenAI. Despite the tension, Brockman is expected to join Sam Altman's new venture, having been invited to a meeting at OpenAI's headquarters, although his attendance at this meeting remains uncertain.

name: THE INFORMATION
description: The Information is a news source that reported on the sale of OpenAI and Sam Altman's plans for a new venture. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-18]

name: SATYA NADELLA
description: Satya Nadella, the CEO of Microsoft, made a significant statement in response to Sam Altman's dismissal from OpenAI, as reported by TechCrunch on November 18, 2023. Nadella, a key figure in the tech industry, addressed the situation with clarity and authority, providing insight into the dynamics between Microsoft and OpenAI, two prominent entities in the technology landscape. Despite the redundancy in the descriptions, the summary consolidates the information, emphasizing Nadella's role and the event's context within the tech community.

name: SUTSKEVER
description: Ilya Sutskever is the chief scientist at OpenAI and a co-founder, who defended the ouster of Sam Altman during an all-hands meeting. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-18]

name: ALTMAN
description: Sam Altman is the former CEO of OpenAI, who was ousted from the company. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-18]

name: JAKUB PACHOCKI
description: Jakub Pachocki is the director of research at OpenAI, who resigned after Brockman. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-18]

name: ALEKSANDER MADRY
description: Aleksander Madry is the head of preparedness at OpenAI, who resigned after Brockman. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-18]

name: DILLON DANIS
description: Dillon Danis, a Bellator MMA fighter, has been deeply involved in a feud with the Paul family, specifically Jake and Logan Paul. Initially, Danis was rumored to have been in a relationship with Savannah Montano, which might have contributed to the tension between him and Jake Paul. However, Danis has remained silent about the details of his relationship with Montano, dismissing Jake Paul's claims regarding their connection. Despite the initial plans, Danis never ended up fighting Jake Paul. Instead, he is now scheduled to face Logan Paul on October 14th in a Misfits contest. In preparation for this fight, Danis has been intensifying his efforts, not only physically but also psychologically. He has attempted to unsettle Logan Paul by delving into the past relationships of Logan's fiancée, Nina Agdal, aiming to create turmoil in Paul's mindset as a strategic move before their bout. This psychological warfare is part of Danis's broader strategy to gain an edge in the upcoming fight.

name: LOGAN PAUL
description: Logan Paul, a multi-faceted personality known for transitioning from a YouTuber to a professional boxer, is set to engage in a highly anticipated boxing match against Dillon Danis on October 14th. This bout has been fueled by a feud that initially began when Logan's younger brother, Jake Paul, challenged Danis on Instagram in 2020. In the realm of professional wrestling, Logan has also made a name for himself as a WWE talent. During his time in WWE, Seth Rollins compared Logan to CM Punk, both in terms of their wrestling skills and their perceived level of selfishness. Adding to the drama surrounding the Danis fight, Logan strategically brought up Danis's ex-girlfriend, Savannah Montano, during their confrontation, intensifying the rivalry. Despite his controversial persona, Logan Paul continues to captivate audiences across various platforms, from YouTube to the boxing ring and the WWE stage.

name: JAKE PAUL
description: Jake Paul, the younger brother of Logan Paul, is a multifaceted personality known for his transition from a popular YouTuber to a professional boxer. In 2020, he initiated a feud with Dillon Danis by calling him out on Instagram, using Danis's ex-girlfriend, Savannah Montano, as a taunt. This move was part of Paul's strategy to engage in the competitive world of boxing, where he has participated in notable fights, including a bout against Ben Askren in 2021 and a rematch against Tyron Woodley the same year. Amid these events, Paul was also embroiled in controversy when he was accused of having an affair with Montano, a detail he brought up in his public challenge to Danis, further fueling the tension between the two. Despite the accusations, Paul continues to make headlines in the boxing world, demonstrating his commitment to the sport and his ability to attract attention through his bold actions and statements.

name: SAVANNAH MONTANO
description: Savannah Montano, a successful Instagram model boasting approximately 1.6 million followers, is known for her past relationship with Dillon Danis, which ended amidst controversy. Following their breakup, rumors circulated that Montano was dating real athletes, adding to her public persona. During the press conference for the Logan Paul fight, Montano was mentioned by Danis, highlighting the significance of their past relationship in the context of the entertainment and combat sports community. Additionally, Montano found herself at the center of speculation regarding a rumored affair with Jake Paul. She firmly denied any such relationship, addressing the claims in a video where she expressed her feelings of confusion and disgust towards the speculations, thereby clarifying her stance amidst the swirling rumors. Despite the controversies, Montano maintains a strong presence on social media, where she shares her life and career with her substantial following.

name: MISFITS
description: Misfits is the organization hosting the contest in which Dillon Danis is preparing to fight Logan Paul. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: NINA AGDAL
description: Nina Agdal is Logan Paul’s fiancée. Her past relationships were brought up by Dillon Danis as a way to create turmoil in Paul’s mindset during the fight. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: BEN ASKREN
description: Ben Askren is a former Olympic MMA artist who fought Jake Paul in 2021. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: TYRON WOODLEY
description: Tyron Woodley is a person who had a rematch with Jake Paul in 2021. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: TMZ
description: TMZ, a prominent media organization known for its coverage of celebrity news and entertainment, has been at the forefront of reporting various high-profile stories in 2023. On October 7th, TMZ was the platform where Jake Paul, the controversial internet personality, shared details about his alleged relationship with Savannah Montano, a move that garnered significant public interest. Later, on October 25th, the outlet highlighted the surge in popularity for NFL star Travis Kelce, noting a substantial increase in his jersey sales and Instagram followers, which was attributed to the public's fascination with his rumored romance with pop icon Taylor Swift. In between these events, on October 18th, TMZ covered a tense situation involving Sam Asghari, Britney Spears' partner, who confronted her over cheating allegations that had surfaced in the media, showcasing the outlet's ability to capture and report on the dynamics within celebrity relationships. These instances demonstrate TMZ's role as a key source of information in the entertainment and celebrity news sphere, providing updates on the personal lives of public figures and the impact of these stories on their public image and fan engagement.

name: DANIS
description: Dillon Danis is a person involved in a boxing fight with Logan Paul. He is also known for his relationship with Savannah Montano and his comments about her during the press conference for the fight. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: AO ARENA
description: AO Arena in Manchester is the location where Danis's first-ever boxing debut is scheduled to take place on October 14. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: ESSENTIALLY SPORTS
description: Essentially Sports is a media outlet that published an article about the Dillon Danis and Logan Paul fight, including details about Danis's relationship with Savannah Montano. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: PIPPIN
description: Pippin is a fictional character from J.R.R. Tolkien's "The Lord of the Rings," used here as a metaphor to describe the anticipation of deals before the holiday season. [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: SAMSUNG S95C
description: The Samsung S95C is a TV with a quantum dot OLED panel, perfect black levels, and a ridiculously bright image. It comes with an excellent centered pedestal mount. [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: POLK SOUNDBAR
description: This soundbar from Polk comes with a subwoofer that boosts deep, booming notes and has several audio presets to tune the sound based on the type of media being watched. [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: NZXT FUNCTION
description: The NZXT Function is a mechanical keyboard with a stylish design, configurable switches and keycaps, and tools for modification. [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: ROCCAT VULCAN 121
description: The Roccat Vulcan 121 is a mechanical keyboard with illuminated switches and semi-clear, clicky switches that are loud. [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: LOGITECH G915
description: The Logitech G915 is a high-performance keyboard specifically designed with gamers in mind, yet its versatility extends to users of creative tools as well. This keyboard is celebrated for its sleek design and seamless integration with Logitech's G Hub software, which streamlines task automation, making it an ideal choice for both gaming and media production. The G Hub software enables users to customize and automate various functions, enhancing the experience for gamers and facilitating workflow for those utilizing software such as DaVinci Resolve, Adobe Premiere, Blender, Cinema 4D, and other media-production applications. The Logitech G915, therefore, serves as a bridge between the gaming and creative communities, offering a solution that caters to the needs of both groups effectively.

name: LOGITECH
description: Logitech is a company known for its powerful G Hub software that enhances the functionality of its products, such as the Logitech G915 keyboard [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: ROCCAT VULCAN II MINI
description: The Roccat Vulcan II Mini is a keyboard with twice the number of LEDs per switch, offering smoother color animations and functional benefits like indicating when a mute toggle is enabled [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: ANKER PRIME
description: The Anker Prime is a power bank included in Anker's early Black Friday sale, featuring discounts and a buy-one-get-another-50-percent-off promotion. Anker gear is generally well-liked, with the Anker Prime power bank and Anker Nano Power Bank being standouts [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: GOOGLE PIXEL BUDS A-SERIES
description: The Google Pixel Buds A-Series are highly recommended earbuds, suitable for nearly everyone, including some iPhone users. They offer up to five hours of battery life, IPX4 water resistance, and nearly instant pairing with Android devices [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY BUDS2 PRO
description: The Samsung Galaxy Buds2 Pro, specifically tailored for Samsung owners, are high-end earbuds that have been praised for their excellent sound quality, comfortable fit, and robust IPX7 water resistance. As highlighted by Wired on 2023-10-19, these earbuds not only offer a superior audio experience but also cater to the active lifestyle of users by ensuring they remain secure and functional even in wet conditions. With a design that prioritizes the Samsung ecosystem, the Galaxy Buds2 Pro provide an enhanced experience for users of Samsung devices, making them a top recommendation from Wired for those seeking a seamless integration between their earbuds and Samsung gadgets.

name: IPHONE USERS
description: iPhone users are mentioned as a potential audience for earbuds that are compatible with Android devices [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: SAMSUNG
description: Samsung is a renowned technology company that specializes in the production of various electronics. The company is celebrated for its foldable phones and The Frame QLED TV, which has been featured in both Prime Day deals and Black Friday sales. The Frame TV, known for its unique design that mimics framed artwork when not in use, boasts a matte, anti-reflective display, supports 4K content, and utilizes Quantum Dot technology. It operates on Samsung's Tizen TV operating system. Additionally, Samsung manufactures earbuds, such as the Galaxy Buds2 Pro and Galaxy Buds2, which are compatible with Android devices. The company also produces a stick vacuum, noted for its design and functionality, particularly suitable for midcentury modern homes, although it does not incorporate AI technology.

name: ANDROID DEVICES
description: Android devices are mentioned as being nearly instantly paired with the earbuds discussed in the text [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: PIXEL BUDS A-SERIES
description: The Pixel Buds A-Series are earbuds with multi-device connectivity, which is not a feature of the Samsung Galaxy Buds2 Pro [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY BUDS2
description: The Samsung Galaxy Buds2 are a slightly more affordable version of the Galaxy Buds2 Pro, with five hours of battery life with active noise canceling turned on and 7.5 hours with it turned off [Wired, 2023-10-19]

name: RIDESHARING
description: Ride-sharing is a business segment of Uber that saw total bookings rise from $29.1 billion to $35.3 billion, a gain of around 21%. In the third quarter, Uber generated $17.9 billion in ride-hailing bookings (+31% year over year). [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: DELIVERY
description: Delivery is a business segment of Uber that saw total bookings rise from $29.1 billion to $35.3 billion, a gain of around 21%. In the third quarter, Uber generated $16.1 billion worth of delivery bookings (+18%). [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: INVESTORS
description: Investors had expected Uber to report revenues of around $9.5 billion (FactSet, Refinitiv), meaning that despite the company’s growth, it fell short of estimates. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: FACTSET
description: FactSet is an organization that provides financial data and analytics, and had expected Uber to report revenues of around $9.5 billion. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: REFINITIV
description: Refinitiv is an organization that provides financial data and analytics, and had expected Uber to report revenues of around $9.5 billion. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: UBER FREIGHT
description: Uber Freight, a business unit of Uber that specializes in logistics and freight services, encountered a significant 27% decline in revenue during the third quarter of 2023 when compared to the same quarter the previous year, as reported by TechCrunch on November 7, 2023. This drop in revenue was accompanied by a decrease in profitability, with the unit recording a $13 million loss in adjusted net income for Q3 2023, a stark contrast to the $1 million profit in the same quarter of the previous year. Despite these year-over-year losses, Uber Freight managed a 1% revenue increase on a quarter-over-quarter basis. The challenging freight market cycle is identified as the primary cause for the lower revenue per load and reduced volume, impacting the overall financial performance of the business unit.

name: SEGMENT ADJUSTED EBITDA
description: Segment adjusted EBITDA is a financial metric used by Uber to measure profitability, showing significant increases in the ride-hailing and delivery segments in Q3 2023 [TechCrunch, 2023-11-07]

name: ACTIVISION BLIZZARD
description: Activision Blizzard, a prominent video game company with studios in London, Guildford, and Warrington, is known for developing iconic games such as Crash Bandicoot, Spyro the Dragon, and Candy Crush Saga. The company has also been the creator of the immensely popular Call of Duty series. Over the past few years, Activision Blizzard has been involved in internal unionization efforts, which it has attempted to stall. Despite this, QA employees at Raven Software, one of its subsidiaries, managed to successfully unionize in May 2022. In January 2020, Activision Blizzard entered into a significant three-year agreement with Google, valued at approximately $360 million, to remain on Google Play, showcasing the company's strategic partnerships in the tech industry. More recently, Activision Blizzard was acquired by Microsoft, a deal that has far-reaching implications for its games. Microsoft's acquisition ensures that games like Call of Duty will potentially be included in Game Pass and will continue to be available on PlayStation until 2038, addressing concerns about the future of streaming rights for Activision Blizzard's titles. This acquisition highlights the evolving landscape of the gaming industry and the increasing influence of major tech companies in shaping its future.

name: PLAYSTATION
description:
PlayStation, a gaming console developed by Sony, has been making waves in the technology and entertainment sectors. As per BBC News - Technology (2023-10-13), PlayStation users can rest assured that they will continue to have access to the popular game Call of Duty until 2038, as Microsoft has agreed not to make the game an Xbox exclusive until then. This decision ensures that the gaming community remains inclusive and diverse.

Polygon (2023-10-16) highlighted PlayStation's capabilities in rendering detailed textures and ray-traced graphics, which are fully utilized in the game Spider-Man 2. The console's advanced graphics processing creates a realistic and immersive game environment, enhancing the overall gaming experience for users.

In a significant move, PlayStation recently received support from Roblox, as reported by The Verge (2023-10-12). This allows PlayStation users to access the platform and play existing creations, expanding the console's gaming library and providing a new avenue for social interaction. The announcement was made at Roblox's annual developer conference in San Francisco, further solidifying PlayStation's position as a gaming platform that caters to creators and their existing works.

PlayStation is known for its thoughtful approach to social cross-platform features, making it a popular choice among creators. The platform's compatibility with existing creations ensures that the gaming community remains connected and engaged, fostering a vibrant ecosystem of games and players.

Additionally, PlayStation offers subscription services that grant users access to free digital titles, online multiplayer, and cloud-based saves, as mentioned by The Verge (2023-12-24). These features enhance the gaming experience by providing a range of benefits, including the ability to play with friends across different platforms and the convenience of accessing saved games from any device.

In summary, PlayStation is a gaming console by Sony that boasts advanced graphics capabilities, a diverse gaming library, and a thoughtful approach to social cross-platform features. The platform's recent agreement with Microsoft regarding Call of Duty, support from Roblox, and subscription services offering free digital titles, online multiplayer, and cloud-based saves, make it a popular choice among gamers and creators alike.

name: UBISOFT
description: Ubisoft, a renowned video game company, has secured a significant 15-year deal with Microsoft, granting it the cloud gaming and streaming rights for all Activision Blizzard games, encompassing both past and future titles. This strategic partnership ensures that popular games, such as Call of Duty, will not become exclusive to Xbox until 2038, as reported by BBC News - Technology on 2023-10-13. However, the agreement might potentially impact Ubisoft's revenue from in-game purchases and microtransactions, introducing a new dimension to the financial dynamics of this collaboration.

name: CLOUD GAMING
description: Cloud gaming is a technology that allows people to stream games over the internet, similar to a "Netflix for games," and is a concern for UK regulators due to Microsoft's potential dominance in the industry. [Source: BBC News - Technology, Publish Time: 2023-10-13]

name: UK REGULATORS
description: UK regulators were worried about Microsoft dominating the cloud gaming industry and made sure Activision Blizzard games couldn't be streamed exclusively on Xbox for 15 years. [Source: BBC News - Technology, Publish Time: 2023-10-13]

name: GAME PASS
description: Game Pass is a subscription service by Microsoft that offers access to a library of games, including big blockbuster titles on the first day of release, such as Starfield and potentially new Call of Duty games. [Source: BBC News - Technology, Publish Time: 2023-10-13]

name: UK REGULATOR
description: The UK regulator is a government agency that oversees business practices and competition in the UK, including the gaming industry

name: MICROTRANSACTIONS
description: Microtransactions are in-game purchases that are increasingly becoming a major source of revenue for game companies, including Activision Blizzard, which made $5.89bn in 2022 from microtransactions, downloadable content, and royalties

name: EGX
description: EGX is a gaming convention where BBC Newsbeat spoke to fans about the Microsoft-Activision deal

name: OLIVER
description:
In the context provided, there are two distinct entities named "OLIVER." The first entity is a 16-year-old gaming enthusiast who holds an optimistic view about the Microsoft-Activision deal, believing it could potentially expand the gaming market and bring good news for the Call of Duty franchise. This OLIVER is a real-world individual with an interest in the technology and entertainment sectors.

The second entity, also named OLIVER, is a character within the game Baldur's Gate 3. He is described as Thaniel's other half, and players must find him to progress in the game and lift a curse. According to Polygon's report on December 19, 2023, OLIVER can be persuaded or threatened to rejoin with Thaniel. Once reunited, he gains the ability to teleport the player to the Moonrise Towers town square and can also command undead minions to attack. This OLIVER is a fictional character within the Baldur's Gate 3 universe, adding depth and complexity to the game's narrative and gameplay mechanics.

name: SOPHIE
description: Sophie is Ubisoft's content creator of the year who told the BBC she "just wants the games to win" and wants everyone to be able to play video games they want to play

name: CRASH BANDICOOT
description: Crash Bandicoot is a game that was once a PlayStation exclusive and is now under the ownership of Activision Blizzard.[]

name: SPYRO THE DRAGON
description: Spyro the Dragon is a game that was once a PlayStation exclusive and is now under the ownership of Activision Blizzard.[]

name: CANDY CRUSH SAGA
description: "Candy Crush Saga, a globally renowned mobile game, is developed and operated by King, a company with headquarters in Stockholm and London. King, which is the mobile division of the larger entity Activision Blizzard, has seen tremendous success through this game. As of December 19, 2023, Candy Crush Saga boasts an impressive 238 million monthly active users, a testament to its widespread popularity. Moreover, the game has generated over $20 billion in lifetime revenue, highlighting its significant commercial success and impact on the mobile gaming industry."

name: GOLDENEYE 007
description: GoldenEye 007 is a game developed by Rare, which was acquired by Microsoft in 2002.[]

name: RARE
description: Rare is a game developer that specialized in Nintendo games until it was acquired by Microsoft for $375m in 2002.[]

name: MOJANG
description: Mojang is the developer of Minecraft, which was acquired by Microsoft for $2.5bn in 2014.[]

name: MINECRAFT
description: Minecraft, a best-selling game of all time, was originally developed by Mojang and was later acquired by Microsoft in 2014. The game offers players an expansive sandbox world where they can engage in a variety of activities such as mining, building, digging, fishing, planting crops, and surviving against monsters. This versatile gameplay, as highlighted by Polygon on 2023-10-20, has contributed to its massive popularity and enduring appeal in the gaming community.

name: UKIE
description: Ukie is the body that represents games companies in the UK. It stated that international investment, such as Microsoft's acquisition of Activision Blizzard, is a crucial part of the UK games industry.[]

name: POWER MINISTRY
description: The Power Ministry is responsible for scheduling tenders for renewable energy projects, aiming for 50 GW annually over the next five years to achieve 500 GW of non-fossil fuel capacity [Business Line, 2023-11-11]

name: NTPC
description:
NTPC, a Public Sector Undertaking (PSU) and a major player in the thermal power generation sector, is strategically poised to capitalize on both energy transition and energy security trends. Since August 13, 2023, the company has experienced a significant 48% gain in its stock value, attributed to robust earnings growth and a re-rating of its stock. In the fiscal year 2023, NTPC reported a 32% increase in revenue, and in the first half of FY24, its Profit After Tax (PAT) grew nearly 30% year-over-year. As of the first half of FY24, NTPC is trading at a one-year forward P/E ratio of approximately 11 times, marking a 35% increase from its historical five-year average P/E of around 8.2 times.

NTPC is diversifying its energy portfolio, aiming to add 15-16 GW of renewable energy and 10-11 GW of thermal-based capacity by FY26. The company, with a Debt-to-Equity (D/E) ratio of around 1.24 times as of H1FY24, has the advantage of accessing debt at a lower rate compared to private power generation companies. NTPC is shifting its strategy for its renewable energy arm, NTPC Green Energy Ltd (NGEL), now focusing on an Initial Public Offering (IPO) to unlock value rather than onboarding a strategic investor.

The company's operations are supported by long-term fuel supply agreements with Coal India Limited (CIL) and Singareni Collieries Company Limited (SCCL), as well as captive coal mining capacity. NTPC's operational efficiency is evident in its Plant Availability Factor (PAF) of 93.32% and Plant Load Factor (PLF) of 76.62% in H1FY24. Despite a slight flattening in revenue growth, reaching approximately \u20b988,058.44 crore in H1FY24, NTPC's EBITDA grew by 18% to \u20b925,091 crore, with EBITDA margins expanding to 29%. The company's power generation increased by 4% in H1FY24, reaching 212 billion

name: RENEWABLE ENERGY
description: Renewable energy is a critical focus area for both the Power Ministry and NTPC, as they aim to significantly increase non-fossil fuel capacity in the coming years. The Power Ministry has set an ambitious target to boost renewable energy capacity to 500 GW over the next five years, as reported by Business Line on November 11, 2023. In line with this, NTPC, a leading power generation company, plans to expand its renewable energy portfolio, targeting 60 GW of capacity by 2026. Currently, NTPC has approximately 7.7 GW of renewable energy capacity under construction, and an additional 11 GW in various stages of development, contributing to its near-term plan to add 15-16 GW of capacity by the end of FY26. This strategic expansion is part of NTPC's long-term goal to achieve 3.3 GW of renewable energy capacity, showcasing the company's commitment to sustainable energy solutions.

name: THERMAL ENERGY
description: Thermal energy is a source of power for NTPC, with more than 90% of its revenue tied to long-term power purchase agreements under a cost-plus based tariff regime [Business Line, 2023-11-11]

name: COAL INDIA LIMITED (CIL)
description: Coal India Limited (CIL), a prominent entity in the energy sector, has established a significant long-term partnership with NTPC through a fuel supply agreement inked in 2023. This agreement spans over a period of 20 years, during which CIL is committed to supplying coal to NTPC's thermal-based generating stations. This strategic alliance ensures a steady and reliable source of fuel for NTPC's power plants, supporting the continuous generation of electricity and contributing to the stability of the energy supply in the region. CIL's role in this agreement underscores its importance as a major supplier of coal in the Indian market, reinforcing its position as a key player in the country's energy landscape.

name: SINGARENI COLLIERIES COMPANY LIMITED (SCCL)
description: Singareni Collieries Company Limited (SCCL), a distinguished entity in the coal industry, has established a significant long-term partnership with NTPC, one of India's leading power generation companies. Under the terms of their agreement, SCCL is committed to supplying coal for a duration of 20 years, specifically to fuel NTPC's thermal-based generating stations. This strategic alliance ensures a steady and reliable source of coal for NTPC's energy production, reflecting SCCL's capability to meet the demands of large-scale power generation over an extended period. The agreement underscores the importance of coal in India's energy mix and highlights SCCL's role as a key supplier in supporting the nation's energy needs.

name: THERMAL-BASED CAPACITY
description: Thermal-based capacity, a technology focused on bolstering energy security, is a key component of NTPC's strategic plan. NTPC intends to expand its thermal-based capacity by 10-11 GW by the end of FY26. This increase is aimed at meeting peak power demand and enhancing the nation's energy security. Originally, the target for this expansion was set at 7 GW, but it has been revised upwards to the current 10-11 GW range, reflecting NTPC's commitment to addressing growing energy needs. These plans were reported by Business Line on November 11, 2023.

name: NTPC GREEN ENERGY LTD (NGEL)
description: NTPC Green Energy Ltd (NGEL) is NTPC's renewable energy arm. NTPC is now looking to unlock value by way of IPO rather than onboarding strategic investor for NGEL. [Source: Business Line, 2023-11-11]

name: PETER KALMUS
description: Peter Kalmus, a 49-year-old climate scientist working at NASA, has dedicated his life to studying and combating climate change since leaving his career in astrophysics. Kalmus, who is fixated on the worst-case scenarios of climate change, has been on a 15-year quest to halt its progression. He prioritizes the needs of the planet and has made significant lifestyle changes, such as becoming a vegetarian, ceasing to fly, and driving an electric car, to reduce his personal carbon footprint. In July and August 2023, Kalmus visited the Possibility Alliance homestead in Belfast, Maine, where he found a slower, richer, and more connected life, which helped him manage his climate anxiety. He meditates for two hours a day to cope with the grief that often feels inescapable for those who reckon with global warming daily. Kalmus has been involved in climate activism, including chaining himself to a bank in Los Angeles, leading to his arrest, and has expressed frustration that more scientists are not engaging in similar activism. Despite his efforts, Kalmus feels he is letting the planet down due to his psychological limitations, and is working on research related to climate change while living and working at an eco-village near the Possibility Alliance.

name: NASA
description: NASA, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration, is a federal government agency dedicated to the exploration of space and the advancement of aerospace research. Peter Kalmus, a climate scientist, is employed by NASA, where he contributes to the agency's scientific endeavors. However, Kalmus' activism against the use of fossil fuels has led to concerns within NASA. He has been arrested twice for his involvement in climate protests, and there is a possibility that a third arrest could jeopardize his position at the agency, as NASA has expressed unease over these incidents. Additionally, NASA is known for providing grants to support research, such as grant 80NSSC21K1042, which was awarded to aid M.R.'s scientific investigations.

name: POSSIBILITY ALLIANCE
description: The Possibility Alliance is an 11-acre homestead community situated in Belfast, Maine, where its residents have embraced a life largely devoid of electricity, modern technology, and the trappings of capitalism. This group, led by Peter Kalmus, has constructed a "gift economy," fostering an environment where resources are shared and skills are traded among neighbors. They are committed to self-sufficiency, growing a significant portion of their own food and living in harmony with the natural world. The community is dedicated to climate activism, offering trainings for climate protesters and preparing to host refugees displaced by climate disasters. Their lifestyle is a conscious effort to live simply, richly, and in a manner that anticipates and mitigates the impacts of ecological breakdown. Despite the lack of running water and a sewer system, the Possibility Alliance has discovered a slower, more connected, and fulfilling existence, demonstrating an alternative way of living in a world facing environmental challenges.

name: EVAN BUSH
description: Evan Bush is a photographer who took pictures for the NBC News article about the Possibility Alliance and climate scientist Peter Kalmus. [Evan Bush / NBC News]

name: ETHAN HUGHES
description: Ethan Hughes, a prominent figure in the realm of alternative lifestyles, is recognized as the charismatic and folksy co-founder of the Possibility Alliance. A staunch critic of globalization and capitalism, Hughes champions a gift economy and leads by example, embracing a post-petrol lifestyle. His days are not only filled with visionary discussions but also practical tasks, as evidenced by his involvement in daily chores such as chopping wood, building a new deck, and tending to goats, all of which underscore his commitment to sustainable living. This blend of philosophical leadership and hands-on engagement makes Ethan Hughes a compelling and influential personality in the movement towards self-sufficiency and community resilience.

name: CHASE BANK

Sharon's professional pursuits necessitated the move, impacting not just her career but also the lives of her family members, including her husband Almus, who is also referred to as Peter Kalmus. The family's adjustment to their new life in North Carolina is a testament to Sharon's influence and the sacrifices made for her career.

He daydreams of a simpler life, closer to the land, where he can keep bees, grow vegetables, and press cider. [Evan Bush / NBC News, 2023-12-24]

This sentiment is shared with Peter Kalmus, with whom Sarah feels a profound connection due to their mutual prioritization of addressing environmental needs. Their shared commitment to environmental causes highlights the community's focus on tackling global challenges, as reported by Evan Bush of NBC News on December 24, 2023.

name: INOSTRANCEVIA
description: Inostrancevia is a genus from the extinct group Theriodontia that appeared during the Middle Permian. [Stocktrek Images/Getty Images, 2023]

name: THERIODONTIA
description: Theriodontia, an extinct subgroup of Therapsids, is notably recognized for its evolutionary innovations that significantly distinguished it from other groups. Inostrancevia, a specific species, is identified as a member of this intriguing lineage. Theriodontia's advancements included a unique shift in jaw bones, enabling a wider mouth opening, which likely facilitated more efficient feeding habits. Additionally, these creatures showcased potential enhancements in hearing capabilities, a larger skull, and an expansion in the size of their teeth. The development of more specialized teeth and a more powerful jaw further contributed to their adaptability and survival strategies in their prehistoric environment. These features collectively suggest that Theriodontia played a crucial role in the evolutionary history of jawed vertebrates, leaving a lasting impact on the diversity of life that followed. [Stocktrek Images/Getty Images, 2023; Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: MICHAEL MANN
description: Michael Mann is the author of "Our Fragile Moment: How Lessons from Earth's Past Can Help Us Survive the Climate Crisis" published by Hachette Book Group in 2023. [Hachette Book Group, 2023]

name: HACHETTE BOOK GROUP
description: Hachette Book Group is the publisher of Michael Mann's book "Our Fragile Moment: How Lessons from Earth's Past Can Help Us Survive the Climate Crisis" in 2023. [Hachette Book Group, 2023]

name: SNOWBALL EARTH
description: Snowball Earth refers to a series of major glaciations that occurred in the late Proterozoic eon, around 550 million years ago. [Mark Garlick/Science Photo Library/Getty Images, 2023]

name: GREAT DYING
description: The Great Dying is the greatest extinction event of all time, which occurred 250 million years ago, possibly due to a massive heat-inducing release of carbon into the atmosphere. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: CAMBRIAN EXPLOSION
description: The Cambrian explosion is a remarkable diversification of life that occurred during the first period of the Paleozoic era, around 540 million years ago. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: PALEOZOIC ERA
description: The Paleozoic era extended from around 540 million to 251 million years ago, marking the beginning of a brand new era after the end of the Proterozoic eon. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: GONDWANA
description: Gondwana is the ancient supercontinent that formed around 600 million years ago. [Mark Garlick/Science Photo Library/Getty Images, 2023]

name: NEOPROTEROZOIC ERA
description: The Neoproterozoic era lasted from 1 billion to 538 million years ago, during which the stratospheric ozone layer developed, protecting animals from the sun's damaging ultraviolet rays. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: THERAPSIDS
description: Therapsids were a group of proto-mammals that emerged during the mid-Permian period, possibly warm-blooded and somewhat rodent-like, and became dominant species. They may have developed fur by the late Permian [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: PERMIAN-TRIASSIC BOUNDARY
description: At the Permian-Triassic boundary, levels of CO2 spiked, leading to massive warming and a significant drop in atmospheric oxygen levels, which reached as low as 15% [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: PANGEA
description: Pangea was a single giant continent formed by the convergence of all continents due to plate tectonics by the late Permian, making it difficult for maritime moisture to penetrate deep into the continent, contributing to its hot and dry conditions [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: SYNAPSIDS
description: Synapsids were a group of proto-mammals that thrived during the Permian period, benefiting from high oxygen levels. They were poorly suited to survive when oxygen concentrations dropped at the Permian-Triassic boundary [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: DIAPSIADS
description: Diapsids are a wide-ranging group of tetrapod vertebrates that first emerged during the Carboniferous period around 300 million years ago. They include reptiles, birds, and now-extinct dinosaurs, distinguished by the presence of two holes on each side of their skull [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: ARCHOSAURS
description: Archosaurs, a subgroup of Diapsids, include crocodilians and the earliest dinosaurs. They exploited the innovation of two skull holes to develop a more efficient respiratory system, making better use of available oxygen, which gave them an advantage when oxygen levels dropped at the Permian-Triassic boundary [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-10-01]

name: SMART GLASSES
description: Smart glasses, a wearable technology merging fashion and functionality, have evolved to incorporate AI and voice assistant features, enabling hands-free photo and video capture, as well as audio listening capabilities. The Verge, in a 2023-10-20 report, highlights the practicality and potential appeal of this technology to gadget enthusiasts and content creators, specifically mentioning the Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses. These glasses, reminiscent of spy movie style, are designed to be discreet and stylish, making them suitable for outdoor events like weddings. However, the technology is not yet on par with the advanced capabilities seen in science fiction, facing limitations in processing commands and interacting with non-native apps. Privacy concerns have been a significant issue with smart glasses, as evidenced by the term "glassholes," but Meta has addressed this by adding an LED capture light to indicate when recording is in progress. The effectiveness of this measure is a topic of debate, and users must be mindful of social etiquette and privacy guidelines when using smart glasses in public settings. The author of the report has personally tested various models and even produced a mini-documentary on the category, providing a first-hand account of the technology's capabilities and limitations. Future developments may include audio AI bots and augmented reality features, such as object identification through the camera, further enhancing the smart glasses' utility.

name: RAY-BAN META SMART GLASSES
description:
The Ray-Ban Meta Smart Glasses, developed by Meta in collaboration with Ray-Ban, are a wearable technology product that starts at $299, making them $30 more expensive than the cheapest Echo Frames. These smart glasses offer a multitude of features, including a hands-free camera for capturing photos and videos, the ability to livestream content, and open-ear audio with Bluetooth connectivity. The audio quality is suitable for music and podcasts, though not as effective for thumping bass as closed-ear headphones. The device contains five microphones, one of which is situated in the nose pad, ensuring clear calls even in noisy environments. Spatial audio is also provided, allowing users to hear the direction from which sounds originated when a video was recorded.

The build quality of the Ray-Ban Meta Smart Glasses is superior to that of other smart glasses, and they come in various frame and lens options. Transition lenses are available for an additional $80, making them the best choice for use in diverse scenarios. Users can order the glasses with prescriptions directly from Ray-Ban or a participating LensCrafters for those with vision in the -6 to +4 range. For those with more severe vision issues, using contact lenses alongside the glasses is recommended.

The Ray-Ban Meta Smart Glasses can function as a camera and a pair of headphones, offering a battery life of six hours on a single charge, which can reduce to three or four hours with heavy use. The glasses can be charged quickly, and the charging case is slim and easy to carry. The camera's quality is good enough to match that of a phone from a few years ago, making the captured moments shareable on social media and in group chats. However, the device has some quirks, such as a delay in taking photos and the camera's perspective not being aligned with the user's eye, leading to off-center shots and unintentional angles. Despite these limitations, the Ray-Ban Meta Smart Glasses have impressed with their stylish design, multiple frame and lens options, and the ability to livestream to Instagram. They are not as effective at noise-canceling as dedicated headphones and do not possess the advanced AI capabilities seen in sci-fi movies. The chosen lenses can impact the usability of the glasses as a headphone alternative, with Transition lenses being the most versatile.

The smart glasses, although details are scarce, are expected to integrate Razer's signature design and performance elements, appealing to tech enthusiasts and gamers alike.
