description: The U.K. (United Kingdom) is a country that is not part of the EU (European Union), and its relationship with the EU is described as potentially more collaborative in the future

name: SPILL
description: Spill is an app that focuses on engagement around community and culture. It has not paid for a single acquisition to date, indicating the influence and respect of its leadership in the entertainment and tech industries. Spill has attracted advertising partners like Netflix, Lionsgate, VH1, Showtime, and Sony Pictures. The app is set to exit beta and open to the public next year, with plans to pay creators for their cultural contributions, especially important for Black creators in the creator economy.

name: KERRY WASHINGTON
description: Kerry Washington is a celebrity who joined the Spill platform organically. She is involved with Spill and has been a part of its growth and success.

name: TERRELL
description: Terrell is a leader at Spill who previously led marketing teams at HBO and Showtime. He discussed with TechCrunch the app's plans to pay creators for their cultural contributions, emphasizing the importance of recognizing Black artists in the space.

name: PARHAM
description: Parham is a leader at Spill who ran her own strategic communications consultancy, working with major production studios. She is part of the team that has established Spill's influence and respect in the entertainment and tech industries.

name: LIONSGATE
description: Lionsgate is one of the advertising partners that has been attracted to Spill, indicating the app's influence and respect in the entertainment industry.

description: VH1 is one of the advertising partners that has been attracted to Spill, indicating the app's influence and respect in the entertainment industry.

name: SONY PICTURES
description: Sony Pictures is one of the advertising partners that has been attracted to Spill, indicating the app's influence and respect in the entertainment industry.

name: BAHAMIAN CUSTOMERS
description: Bahamian customers are a group of people who were allowed to fully withdraw their assets from FTX, as per Bankman-Fried's decision [The Verge, 2023-10-31]

name: BAHAMIAN GOVERNMENT
description: The Bahamian government is the governing body of the Bahamas, which had a cozy relationship with Bankman-Fried, as suggested by the testimony [The Verge, 2023-10-31]

name: SASSOON
description: Sassoon, a prominent figure in the legal proceedings against Sam Bankman-Fried, has been actively engaged in establishing the defendant's history of dishonesty. As the prosecutor in the case, she has meticulously questioned Bankman-Fried on direct examination, challenging the narrative he presented. Additionally, Sassoon inquired about an Alameda all-hands meeting with Elison, further demonstrating her thorough approach to uncovering the truth and holding Bankman-Fried accountable for his actions. These efforts were reported by The Verge on two separate occasions, on October 12 and October 31, 2023, highlighting the significance of her role in the case.

name: CRANBERRIES
description: Cranberries, a fruit native to North America, have thrived in the northern United States, particularly in southeastern Massachusetts and Cape Cod, where they have grown for millennia in sandy soils and adapted to short summers. Despite being potentially overlooked at the first Thanksgiving, they have since become a staple in U.S. households during the holiday. Domesticated around 200 years ago, cranberries have a brief autumn harvest season from late September to early November, and due to their short shelf life, fresh cranberries were historically available only in select areas of the nation that could provide the ideal conditions of sandy soil, long summer days, and long winter dormancy. Marcus Urann recognized the potential for a global industry in cranberries and initiated processing methods to extend their selling season, thereby expanding the reach of this once regionally confined fruit to a worldwide market. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23; Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: THE PILGRIMS
description: The Pilgrims explored and settled in the same area where cranberries grow in 1620, and celebrated the first Thanksgiving the following year. However, it seems doubtful that they even noticed the cranberries [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23]

name: RICHARD S. COX AND JACOB WALKER
description: Richard S. Cox and Jacob Walker are the authors of the book "Massachusetts Cranberry Culture: A History from Bog to Table," which is a romantic ode to the quirks of New England history, geography, and culture, and of its low-growing fruit [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23]

name: MASSACHUSETTS CRANBERRY CULTURE: A HISTORY FROM BOG TO TABLE
description: This book, written by Richard S. Cox and Jacob Walker, explores the history of cranberry culture in Massachusetts, from the bog to the dinner table [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23]

name: MARCUS URANN
description: Marcus Urann, born on October 3, 1873, in Sullivan, Maine, was an American farmer, attorney, and entrepreneur who significantly impacted the cranberry industry and the Thanksgiving tradition in the United States. Known as the "Cranberry King," Urann was a bookish individual who attended the University of Maine before founding Phi Kappa Phi, an honor society for elite students, with the motto "Let the love of learning rule humanity." In 1906, he purchased his first cranberry bog on Cape Cod, marking the beginning of his journey in the cranberry farming business. By 1912, Urann had innovated the process of canning cranberry jelly, which transformed the hyper-local fruit into an international industry. His commercial canned cranberry sauce became central to Thanksgiving celebrations nationwide, making cranberries a Turkey Day tradition. Over the next 30 years, Urann significantly expanded the cranberry market, turning the fruit into a global sensation and changing the flavor of gratitude in the United States.

name: BRIAN WICK
description: Brian Wick, the executive director of Massachusetts Cranberries, is a key figure in the cranberry industry. In an interview with Fox News Digital on 2023-11-23, Wick clarified that there is no historical evidence to support the common belief that cranberries were present at the first Thanksgiving, debunking a popular myth. He also highlighted the significant impact of Marcus Urann on the expansion of the cranberry market, emphasizing that Urann's influence continues to be felt in the industry today. Wick's insights provide a deeper understanding of the cranberry sector's historical and contemporary dynamics.

name: MASSACHUSETTS CRANBERRIES
description: Massachusetts Cranberries is an organization that represents and supports the cranberry industry within the state of Massachusetts. The entity acknowledges the significant role of Marcus Urann in broadening the cranberry market across the United States. Brian Wick, serving as the executive director of Massachusetts Cranberries, has provided insights on the industry, notably stating that there is no historical evidence to support the notion that cranberries were present at the first Thanksgiving, as commonly believed. This information was shared during a FOX News - Lifestyle segment on November 23, 2023, shedding light on the history and modern influence of the cranberry sector in Massachusetts.

name: PHI KAPPA PHI
description: Phi Kappa Phi, a prestigious nationwide honor society, was founded by Marcus Urann at the University of Maine. It boasts a vast network of over 325 chapters spread across campuses in the United States and internationally. True to its founding mission, Phi Kappa Phi is dedicated to engaging the community of scholars in service to others, fostering a spirit of academic excellence and community involvement among the nation's best students. This commitment to service and scholarship is a cornerstone of the society's values, as highlighted by both FOX News - Lifestyle and the University.

name: UNIVERSITY OF MAINE
description: The University of Maine is where Marcus Urann attended and became an undergraduate scholar of great renown and vision. He founded Phi Kappa Phi, an honor society, while studying there. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23]

name: ABRAM HARRIS
description: Abram Harris, the president of the University of Maine, promoted the society founded by Marcus Urann, leading the way for its growth after Urann's graduation. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-11-23]

name: UNIVERSITY OF TENNESSEE
description: The University of Tennessee is one of the campuses where Phi Kappa Phi has a chapter [University]

name: SMITHSONIAN MAGAZINE
description: Smithsonian Magazine reported on the history of cranberries and Marcus Urann's processing methods in a 2013 article [Smithsonian Magazine, 2013]

name: CRANBERRY INDUSTRY
description: The cranberry industry, once limited to fresh autumn produce, has grown exponentially due to the innovations of Marcus Urann, with fresh cranberries now accounting for only 5% of the fruit's production [Ocean Spray, 2023-11-23]

name: OCEAN SPRAY
description: Ocean Spray is a company that reports on the cranberry industry, noting the transformation of the industry from selling only fresh cranberries to distributing them internationally as sauce and juice [Ocean Spray, 2023-11-23]

name: CRANBERRY INSTITUTE
description: The Cranberry Institute, located in Carver, Massachusetts, provides data on cranberry production, indicating that the United States is the world's largest grower of cranberries, with American farmers producing twice as many as Canada and 20 times more than Chile [Cranberry Institute, 2023-11-23]

name: WISCONSIN
description: Wisconsin, a state renowned for its agricultural prowess, significantly contributes to the American cranberry industry. According to Scitechdaily, a source for science, space, and technology news, as of 2023, Wisconsin is responsible for approximately 60% of the U.S. cranberry harvest. This statistic highlights the state's dominance in cranberry production, a position it secured decades ago, as reported by FOX News - Lifestyle. Wisconsin surpassed Massachusetts, a former leading cranberry grower, to become the nation's top producer. This transition not only reflects Wisconsin's agricultural advancements but also underscores the cranberry's growing significance in American culture. The state's commitment to cranberry cultivation has played a pivotal role in shaping the industry and its impact on the nation's culinary traditions.

name: WARHAMMER 40,000
description: Warhammer 40,000 is a game set in a brutal and over-the-top sci-fi universe where war is the only constant. The game features a dystopian setting that grinds its people into dust, but some characters get to enjoy being at the top of the food chain. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: ROGUE TRADER
description: Rogue Trader, developed by Owlcat Games and inspired by the Warhammer 40K RPGs from Fantasy Flight Games, is a comprehensive video game that delves into the expansive universe of Warhammer 40K. The game, set for release on December 7, 2023, for Windows PC, centers around the political machinations, a rich cast of characters, and morally ambiguous decisions that define the 40K universe. In this game, players take on the role of Rogue Traders, a group of daring freelance explorers who venture into the uncharted territories at the edges of the Imperium of Man. Despite the inherent dangers of their profession, Rogue Traders are driven by the allure of agency, freedom, power, and the command of a massive flagship, all rewards for their bold expeditions into the unknown. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: IMPERIUM OF MAN
description: The Imperium of Man is a vast organization in the Warhammer 40,000 universe. Rogue Traders explore systems of the Imperium with a loyal crew of companions, making impactful choices and determining the fate of those around them. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: CRPG
description: CRPG (Computer Role-Playing Game) is a genre of games that includes features such as companions with their own narrative paths, top-down strategic combat, and branching choices that impact the world. Rogue Trader is a CRPG in the vein of Baldur’s Gate 3 or Pillars of Eternity. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: VOIDSHIP
description: Voidship is a massive ship in the Warhammer 40,000 universe, the size of a modern city. As a Rogue Trader, the player has to manage the ship, its cargo, and its many occupants. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: KORONUS EXPANSE
description: Koronus Expanse is a location in the Warhammer 40,000 universe where the Rogue Trader has to trek around various planets to get a new Navigator, fix the ship, and avoid any major diplomatic incidents with the locals. [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: WARHAMMER 40K
description: Warhammer 40K is a science fiction universe created by Games Workshop, featuring a dystopian future where humanity is locked in a constant struggle for survival. The universe is explored in various media, including RPGs from Fantasy Flight Games and the video game Rogue Trader, which pays homage to the detailed lore of the 40K canon [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: OWLCAT GAMES
description: Owlcat Games, a renowned developer in the realm of video games, has made significant strides in the gaming community by releasing Rogue Trader, a game that immerses players in the captivating universe of Warhammer 40K. The company, demonstrating its commitment to the franchise, has meticulously crafted the game as an homage to the Warhammer 40K RPGs from Fantasy Flight Games, paying close attention to every detail of the Koronus Expanse to ensure an authentic and engaging experience. In a recent development, Owlcat Games provided a pre-release download code for the review of Rogue Trader, highlighting their confidence in the game's quality and their eagerness to share it with the gaming community. This move by Owlcat Games underscores their dedication to creating content that resonates with fans of the Warhammer 40K universe, solidifying their position as a leading developer in the genre.

name: FANTASY FLIGHT GAMES
description: Fantasy Flight Games is a company that has created Warhammer 40K RPGs, including Rogue Trader and Dark Heresy. These games have been a source of inspiration for the video game Rogue Trader, developed by Owlcat Games [Polygon, 2023-12-06]

name: ADAM YEDIDIA
description: Adam Yedidia, a pivotal figure in the FTX saga, is notably recognized as Sam Bankman-Fried's college roommate from their days at MIT, where they first met and developed a close friendship. Yedidia's professional journey with FTX began in January 2021, working out of the company's Hong Kong office until October of the same year, and subsequently relocated to the Bahamas, remaining an employee until the firm's dramatic collapse. His role within the organization was significant, particularly in addressing a critical bug in the code that inadvertently bestowed preferential treatment upon Alameda Research, a related entity. This discovery led to a realization that FTX had been misusing customer funds, a revelation that prompted Yedidia's resignation. Despite his involvement, Yedidia testified with immunity in the high-profile FTX trial, expressing concerns that his work on the code might have unknowingly facilitated the fraudulent activities that ultimately led to the downfall of the once-prominent crypto exchange. His testimony, given under the protection of immunity, shed light on the intricate technical aspects and the internal dynamics of FTX, contributing to the broader understanding of the events that transpired.

name: JOE BANKMAN
description: Joe Bankman is Sam Bankman-Fried's father. He is mentioned in the "small group chat" and is potentially involved in the case [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: NATHANIEL WANG
description: Nathaniel Wang is a former employee of FTX who oversaw the code "allow_negative" that allowed Alameda Research to avoid liquidation. He testified that Alameda first had a negative balance in late 2019 and that he heard Bankman-Fried tell another trader it was okay to continue withdrawing money from the account as long as the amount was less than FTX’s total trading revenue [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: CARGO SHORTS
description: Cargo shorts are a type of clothing that Sam Bankman-Fried was wearing in a photograph. The defense counsel tried to use this as evidence of Bankman-Fried’s humility, but it seemed to signify his importance and lack of need to dress up, even to meet former world leaders [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: FTT TOKEN
description: FTT token is a cryptocurrency token that Bankman-Fried and Wang had launched. It was not accounted for in the negative balance of Alameda Research [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: CREDIT LINE
description: Credit line refers to the financial privilege given to Alameda Research by FTX. It was unmatched by anyone else on FTX and ultimately reached $65 billion [The Verge, 2023-10-26]

name: CYBERTRUCK
description: The Cybertruck is an electric pickup truck model produced by Tesla, first unveiled in 2019. Known for its distinctive and starkly geometric design, the vehicle features an inflexible stainless steel exterior that resists rust but is hard to shape, contributing to its unique aesthetic and launch delays. Measuring fewer than 19 feet long with a bed longer than six feet, the Cybertruck has four doors and can accommodate six adults. It comes in all-wheel drive and Cyberbeast versions, with a claimed towing capacity of 11,000 pounds. The Cybertruck has been much-hyped and is expected to be compared to other Tesla models and electric pickups from competitors. However, the vehicle has also been the focus of media stories regarding safety concerns due to its design and lack of crumple zones, as noted by The Verge on 2023-12-12 and TechCrunch on 2023-11-30.

name: GIGAFACTORY
description: The Gigafactory is a Tesla facility in Austin where the first deliveries of the Cybertruck occurred on November 30, 2023. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: CYBERBEAST
description: The Cyberbeast is the third variant of the Cybertruck, featuring three motors, 845 horsepower, a 2.6-second 0 to 60 mph acceleration rate, a top speed of 130 mph, and an estimated 320-mile range. It is priced at $99,990. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: RANGE EXTENDER
description: The RANGE EXTENDER is an optional accessory designed by Tesla specifically for the Cybertruck model. This innovative pack is intended to significantly boost the vehicle's range, making it particularly suitable for very long trips or when towing heavy loads up mountains. The Range Extender fits neatly into approximately one-third of the truck bed, ensuring it doesn't compromise too much of the cargo space. When installed, it can extend the range of the all-wheel drive version of the Cybertruck to an estimated 470 miles and the Cyberbeast variant to over 440 miles. This enhancement is aimed at addressing the range anxiety often associated with electric vehicles, especially in demanding conditions, and was announced by Tesla on November 30, 2023, as reported by TechCrunch.

name: EBAY
description:
eBay, a renowned online marketplace, is known for its generous price-matching policy, except during the weeks of Thanksgiving and Cyber Monday. For items bought before or after these periods, if a lower price is found from a qualifying competitor on an eBay Deal item or a product with the "Best Price Guarantee" symbol, eBay offers 110 percent of the price difference as a coupon, as reported by The Verge on 2023-10-25. Compared to Discogs, eBay provides a much broader base of potential buyers and a more solid infrastructure and support system, although its fees are approximately 1 percent higher than Discogs', as noted in an unspecified source.

In a unique and controversial listing, Cybertruck reservations have appeared on eBay for $10,000, as mentioned by TechCrunch on 2023-11-30. However, the legitimacy of these offers is uncertain, and potential buyers should proceed with caution. Elon Musk, the CEO of Tesla, has previously threatened to punish resellers, indicating that such listings might not be authorized or endorsed by the manufacturer.

name: FEDERAL TAX CREDIT
description: The federal tax credit for electric vehicles (EVs) has a number of eligibility requirements, including price. Under current rules, trucks and SUVs priced above $80,000 don’t qualify for the $7,500 credit. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: GMC
description: GMC is a competitor to Tesla in the electric vehicle market, specifically mentioned in relation to its electric pickups [source: TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE
description: Alzheimer's disease, a specific type of dementia, is a neurodegenerative condition characterized by the buildup of a protein called amyloid in the brain, leading to cognitive deterioration. Symptoms may not manifest for decades after the protein buildup has begun. This disease affects more than six million Americans of all ages, with a new diagnosis occurring every 67 seconds, as reported by the Alzheimer's Association. Over the past several decades, there has been a steady increase in Alzheimer's disease diagnoses. However, early detection and positive steps can slow the process and mitigate any major side effects of the disorder. Recent studies suggest that fasting-mimicking diets and intermittent fasting could help control blood sugar, which in turn can slow down the progression of Alzheimer's disease. New drugs are being developed to target this condition, bringing hope for patients in the UK and potentially worldwide.

name: INTERMITTENT FASTING
description: Intermittent fasting, particularly time-restricted feeding, has been shown in a recent study to potentially reduce the risk of cognitive deterioration associated with Alzheimer's disease [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA SAN DIEGO SCHOOL OF MEDICINE
description: Researchers at the University of California San Diego School of Medicine conducted a study on mice to investigate the effects of time-restricted feeding on Alzheimer's disease pathology [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: PAULA DESPLATS
description: Paula Desplats, PhD, is a professor in the Department of Neurosciences at UC San Diego School of Medicine and the senior author of the study on intermittent fasting and Alzheimer's disease [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: AMYLOID PROTEINS
description: Amyloid proteins are substances that accumulate in the brain and are a hallmark of Alzheimer's disease. The study found that mice on a time-restricted feeding schedule had less buildup of these proteins [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: FASTING-MIMICKING DIETS
description: Fasting-mimicking diets are a type of diet that can make drugs more effective and have the potential to drastically reduce many aging and disease risk factors by reducing neuroinflammation or superoxide production in the brain. They can be done in longer periods, helping the body go into higher levels of ketosis, which is beneficial for the brain. They can also help with leaky gut and aid in controlling blood sugar, which can slow down the progression of Alzheimer's [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: DR. VALTER LONGO
description: Dr. Valter Longo is a researcher whose studies demonstrate the connection between metabolism, fasting, and brain health. His work is on a similar track to the UC San Diego study [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: UC SAN DIEGO STUDY
description: The UC San Diego study tested an approach to fasting-mimicking diets that does not require calorie reduction, which may be more sustainable and safer for older people whose metabolisms are already impacted by aging changes [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: L-NUTRA
description: L-Nutra is a nutritech company in California. Dr. Joseph Antoun, CEO and chairman of L-Nutra, was involved in the USC study that showed mice fed the fasting-mimicking diet had improved cognitive performance, motor learning, and both short- and long-term memory [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: DR. JOSEPH ANTOUN
description: Dr. Joseph Antoun is the CEO and chairman of L-Nutra, a nutritech company in California. He was involved in the USC study and explained that fasting-mimicking diets can help the brain function in a myriad of ways, including decreasing pro-aging factors, improving sleep quality, and promoting ketosis [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: NEURODEGENERATIVE CONDITIONS
description: Neurodegenerative conditions are health disorders that affect the brain and nervous system, potentially leading to cognitive decline and other symptoms. Early detection of these conditions allows for positive steps that may slow the process and mitigate any major side effects of the disorder []

name: FASTING
description: Fasting is an activity where an individual abstains from food or drink for a prolonged period. During fasting, cells undergo a process called autophagy, which involves removing and recycling damaged cellular components, helping to maintain proper cellular function and protect the brain from neurodegenerative diseases such as Alzheimer’s [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: AUTOPHAGY
description: Autophagy is a biological process that occurs during prolonged periods of fasting, involving the removal and recycling of damaged cellular components. This process is essential for maintaining proper cellular function and can help protect the brain from neurodegenerative diseases such as Alzheimer’s [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: ALZHEIMER'S ASSOCIATION
description: The Alzheimer’s Association is an organization that provides information and support for individuals with Alzheimer’s disease and their families. According to the association, more than six million Americans of all ages have Alzheimer's, and every 67 seconds, someone in America develops the disease [FOX News - Health, 2023-12-06]

name: DAK PRESCOTT
description: Dak Prescott, a professional football player, serves as the quarterback for the Dallas Cowboys in the National Football League (NFL). As of December 5, 2023, he is considered one of the top contenders for the MVP award, highlighting his significant contributions to the sport. However, his recent performance has been critiqued for its shortcomings, including missed downfield throws and two interceptions that were deemed sloppy. These lapses in performance have affected his ADOT (average depth of target), which currently stands at a low ranking of 28th among 33 qualifying quarterbacks. Despite these challenges, Prescott's overall standing and potential for the MVP award indicate his skill and impact on the team and the league.

name: JARED GOFF
description: Jared Goff is a quarterback for the Detroit Lions, a professional American football team in the NFL. As of December 5, 2023, Goff is considered a longshot for the MVP award, despite his team having a good record and an easy schedule to finish the season. Earlier in the season, on September 26, 2023, he was expected to have success against the Green Bay Packers' pass defense in a Thursday Night Football game, showcasing his potential for strong performances. However, Goff also had a less successful moment on October 30, 2023, when he threw a pick-six that kept the Raiders in the game during the second half. Throughout the season, Goff has connected with receivers like Jameson Williams for a 22-yard gain and Amon-Ra St. Brown for a 44-yard catch, demonstrating his ability to make significant plays.

name: TYREEK HILL
description: Tyreek Hill, a wide receiver for the Miami Dolphins, is making significant waves in the NFL as of 2023-12-05. Notably, he is on track to etch his name in the record books by potentially becoming the first player in history to accumulate 2,000-plus receiving yards in a single season, a feat highlighted by Sporting News. Adding to his impressive season, Hill is also the current frontrunner for the Offensive Player of the Year (OPOY) award, further solidifying his exceptional performance and impact on the field.

name: SEAN PAYTON
description: Sean Payton, the head coach of the Denver Broncos as of 2023, has been instrumental in turning the team's fortunes around after a disastrous start to the season. Payton's coaching prowess has been particularly evident in his handling of quarterback Russell Wilson, whose career has seen a significant resurgence under Payton's guidance. Despite this success, Payton has not shied away from expressing his frustrations with Wilson, as seen in his suggestion to use a wristband to expedite communication in the huddle. Although Payton's efforts have garnered attention, with some even considering him a longshot for Coach of the Year, his relationship with Wilson and innovative communication strategies have been central to the Broncos' recovery.

name: DEMAR HAMLIN
description: Demar Hamlin is a professional football player who is the current favorite for the Comeback Player of the Year award. He is coming back from a life-threatening injury, a cardiac arrest, which makes him a great candidate to win the award.[]

name: NFL AWARDS
description: The NFL awards are an event where various awards are given to professional football players and coaches. The awards include the Comeback Player of the Year, which is currently favored to be won by Demar Hamlin.[]

name: NICKI MINAJ
description: Nicki Minaj, a rapper and recording artist also recognized under the alias Onika, released her fifth studio album, "Pink Friday 2," on December 7, 2023, an event that sparked significant excitement and anticipation among her fan community, the Barbz. This fan group, known for their loyalty and enthusiasm, has created a fictional place called Gag City, which is closely associated with Minaj and symbolizes the fervor surrounding her album releases. The term Gag City has been widely used in tweets and images posted on X (formerly Twitter) on December 7-8, 2023, demonstrating the strength and reach of Minaj's pop star status and her influence over her fanbase. Despite facing controversies in her career, including comments related to the COVID vaccine and defending her husband Kenneth Petty, a convicted sex offender, Minaj has skillfully utilized the Gag City meme for free promotion, showcasing her ability to navigate through public scrutiny while maintaining her relevance and popularity in the entertainment industry.

name: PINK FRIDAY 2
description: "Pink Friday 2" is a multifaceted release by the renowned artist Nicki Minaj, which exists both as her fifth studio album and a song within that album. Released on December 7, 2023, the album marks the sequel to her groundbreaking debut record, "Pink Friday." The anticipation for "Pink Friday 2" was met with a creative celebration, as AI-generated images of a vibrant pink city, dubbed "Gag City," were created and shared, enhancing the album's visibility and appeal. This digital art movement has not only captured the attention of fans but has also contributed to a surge in streaming numbers for the song "Pink Friday 2," demonstrating the powerful impact of community engagement and technology on modern music consumption. Nicki Minaj's latest offering, "Pink Friday 2," thus stands as a testament to her enduring influence in the music industry and her ability to harness digital trends to connect with her audience.

name: GAG CITY
description: "Gag City" is a term coined by Nicki Minaj and her fanbase, known as the Barbz, which has evolved into a viral meme and a promotional tool for her music. Initially, it was used to express the excitement and anticipation surrounding the release of her album "Pink Friday 2." The meme took off on X (formerly Twitter) in December 2023, with AI-generated images of a pink cityscape being widely shared. These images and tweets also featured elaborate narratives about the city's fictional inhabitants and government, showcasing the creativity and engagement of the Barbz community. The meme has since become synonymous with the promotion of Nicki Minaj's music, particularly the song "Pink Friday 2," as reported by TechCrunch on December 9, 2023.

name: BARBZ
description: The Barbz, a dedicated and creative fan community centered around the multi-talented artist Nicki Minaj, has been actively engaging in the digital sphere to amplify anticipation for the release of her upcoming album, "Pink Friday 2." In a display of their unwavering support and innovative spirit, the Barbz have been instrumental in the creation and dissemination of AI-generated images of a fictional place known as "Gag City." This virtual city has become a focal point for the community, where they craft intricate narratives surrounding its governance and societal structure. The enthusiasm and involvement of the Barbz were prominently showcased on X (formerly Twitter) during the dates of December 7-8, 2023, as they shared their imaginative content, contributing to a vibrant and interactive online buzz. Their collective efforts not only highlight the strong bond between Nicki Minaj and her fans but also demonstrate the community's adeptness at leveraging technology to engage with and shape cultural narratives.

description: Atletico Madrid is a sports team that qualified for the Round of 16 in Group E of the Champions League, winning 4 games, drawing 2, and losing 0, with a goal difference of +11 and 14 points. They won the top spot in Group E after defeating Lazio 2-0 on December 13, 2023.[]

name: NOYB
description: NOYB, a European privacy rights advocacy group, has been actively engaged in strategic litigation against Meta's tracking and profiling practices since 2021. The organization has also been challenging the 'pay or okay' approach to General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) consent, a model that it argues forces newspaper readers to essentially "buy back their own data at exorbitant prices." NOYB's efforts have been directed at various data protection authorities across Europe, filing complaints to ensure compliance with privacy laws and protect individuals' data rights.

name: MAX SCHREMS
description: Max Schrems is the founder and honorary chairman of NOYB, who has criticized Meta's proposed subscription fee for privacy as not being 'necessary' or 'appropriate' [TechCrunch, 2023-10-30]

name: IRISH DATA PROTECTION COMMISSION (DPC)
description: The Irish Data Protection Commission (DPC) serves as Meta's primary regulator within the European Union under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), a role that typically entails leading any enforcement actions related to GDPR compliance. Since July 2023, the DPC has been evaluating Meta's consent-based model, a process that is ongoing as of October 30, 2023. However, an unusual development has occurred where the Norwegian Data Protection Authority (DPA) took emergency action, bypassing the GDPR's "one-stop-shop" mechanism, which usually consolidates regulatory actions under the jurisdiction of the lead regulator. This indicates that while the DPC holds the lead role in regulating Meta's GDPR compliance, other EU DPAs can take independent actions under certain circumstances, such as in cases of emergency.

name: COURT OF JUSTICE OF THE EUROPEAN UNION (CJEU)
description: The Court of Justice of the European Union (CJEU) delivered a judgment on July 4, 2023, examining the legal bases for Meta's processing of user data for behavioral advertising [TechCrunch, 2023-10-30]

name: EUROPEAN SUPERVISORY AUTHORITIES
description: European supervisory authorities have been involved in the regulatory assessment of Meta's consent-based model, led by the Irish DPC [TechCrunch, 2023-10-30]

name: DPC
description: The Data Protection Commission (DPC), serving as the lead regulator for Meta in the European Union, has been actively involved in overseeing the company's data processing activities and ensuring compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). In a recent decision, the DPC rejected Meta's assertion that contractual necessity justified the processing of user data for personalized advertisements. This move highlights the regulatory body's commitment to scrutinizing the legal basis Meta uses for tracking and profiling its users. Additionally, the DPC is in ongoing discussions with Meta regarding the company's transition to a lawful basis for these activities. As part of its supervisory role, the DPC is also conducting an assessment to determine if Meta's new user offerings align with the GDPR obligations. The outcome of this exercise is yet to be determined, and the DPC will officially inform Meta if the new services meet the GDPR compliance standards. The DPC's actions underscore its pivotal role as the Lead Supervisory Authority for Facebook and Instagram in Europe, maintaining a watchful eye over Meta's operations to safeguard user data and privacy rights.

name: GDPR
description: GDPR, or the General Data Protection Regulation, is a comprehensive legal framework established by the European Union to govern data protection and privacy. This regulation sets strict guidelines for the processing of personal data, emphasizing that consent must be specific, informed, and freely given for it to be considered legal. Meta, a major technology company, has encountered challenges in aligning its 'pay or okay' model with GDPR's stringent requirements, as this model was found to be incompatible with the regulation. GDPR serves as a critical balancing check on the scope of possible CSAM (Child Sexual Abuse Material) scanning, ensuring that measures taken for protection comply with data protection standards. The enforcement speed of GDPR is often compared to the CPC alert and mobilization process, highlighting its swift and effective implementation. Johansson referenced GDPR in a TechCrunch article dated 2023-10-25, underlining its role in maintaining data protection compliance amidst technological advancements.

name: DMA
description: DMA (Digital Markets Act) is a regulation that puts some limits on the use of people's data for ads. Meta has been designated as a gatekeeper under the DMA, and the Commission is the sole enforcer of the DMA.

name: EUROPEAN COMMISSION
description: The European Commission, a significant organization within the European Union, plays a multifaceted role in facilitating dialogue, assessing issues, and addressing unfair practices. Specifically, it exerts oversight and enforcement on Meta, a major technology company, ensuring compliance with the Digital Markets Act (DMA) and the Digital Services Act (DSA). As the sole enforcer of the DSA on Very Large Online Platforms (VLOPs), the Commission has requested additional information from Meta concerning its handling of content threats stemming from the Israel-Hamas conflict and election security matters. The Commission's scrutiny of Meta's ad tracking offer remains uncertain, leaving open the question of whether the EU will apply the same rigorous examination to this aspect of the company's operations. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: NORWAY'S DPA
description: Norway's DPA (Data Protection Authority) has a local ban order on Meta's tracking ads. It is concerned about the subscription plan and has doubts about whether it would constitute valid consent under GDPR.

name: AD TARGETING
description: Ad targeting is a technology and business practice used by companies like Meta to deliver personalized advertisements to users [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-10-30]

name: TEENS
description: Teens, a demographic group of significant interest, are at the heart of Meta's strategy to deliver a responsible and useful advertising experience, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-30. This focus comes amidst the reality that teens are avid users of social media platforms, dedicating substantial time to these apps, as highlighted by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-01. Among the various social media apps, TikTok emerges as the most popular choice for this demographic, capturing a significant portion of their online engagement. Meta's efforts to tailor its ad experience for teens not only reflect the company's commitment to addressing the unique needs and behaviors of this group but also underscore the importance of understanding and responsibly engaging with the younger generation in the digital space.

name: EUROPE
description:
In the region of EUROPE, there are notable developments in both political and technological spheres. Politically, EUROPE has designated Hamas as a terrorist group, reflecting a stance on international security and peace efforts. The region has also been engaging with Egypt, seeking its assistance to alleviate the humanitarian crisis in Gaza, demonstrating a proactive approach to regional issues and a willingness to collaborate with neighboring countries for solutions.

On the technology front, Meta, a leading social media company, is considering a strategic move in EUROPE by offering an ad-free subscription option. This decision, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-30, is part of Meta's efforts to maintain user tracking capabilities amidst growing privacy concerns and regulatory pressures. The ad-free subscription model could potentially provide users with a more streamlined and private social media experience, while allowing Meta to continue collecting data for targeted advertising outside of the subscription service. This move highlights the complex dynamics between technology companies, user preferences, and regulatory environments in EUROPE.

The film centers around Miles Morales as he confronts a dimension-hopping adversary, while interacting with a diverse multiverse of Spider-People. An intriguing addition to the cast is Miguel O'Hara, also known as Spider-Man 2099, who brings a unique twist to the storyline with his hinted vampiric traits. Despite being mentioned alongside Sound of Freedom as a new movie to watch, it is important to note that Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse is not available on Netflix, as no specific streaming platform is provided for its release."

name: HARRY KANE
description: Harry Kane, an English footballer and the captain of the England national team, made a significant impact in 2023. In 2023 alone, he scored a remarkable 52 goals for Bayern Munich, Tottenham, and England, setting a new Bundesliga record with 17 goals in his opening 11 outings. His performance against Manchester United in the Champions League was particularly noteworthy, where he played a crucial role in the victory, including a sneaky round-the-corner pass that led to a goal. Interestingly, Manchester United had considered signing Kane but did not bid for him in the summer. Kane has outscored their forward Hojlund in domestic competitions, further highlighting his exceptional skills on the field.

name: EPIC GAMES
description: Epic Games, a renowned video game developer and publisher, is best known for creating the wildly popular game Fortnite. The company, which operates the Epic Games Store, has been embroiled in a legal dispute with Google, alleging that Google's high fees for transactions in its app store and its tying of the Google Play payments platform to the app store are illegal, unjustly enriching Google while driving up app prices. Epic Games originally involved Match and several U.S. attorneys general in its antitrust lawsuit against Google, claiming that Google's process for sideloading apps is overly difficult for end users and that Google hid items from discovery by allowing execs and employees to have "off the record" chats. Despite losing its antitrust battle with Apple, Epic Games is now seeking the Supreme Court's intervention. The legal saga continued as Epic Games was set to go to trial with Google on November 6, 2023, over allegations of anticompetitive behavior regarding Google Play and its commission structure. In gaming news, Epic Games announced that Fortnite's next season would return to its original map from the very earliest days of the game, while retaining some modern in-game mobility perks like sprinting. The company has introduced several quality of life improvements in the game over the years and is considering retaining some of these modern conveniences in the new-old version of Fortnite. Epic Games keeps its game metrics confidential but has been proactive in introducing various content updates since the game's launch in 2017. The decision to revert Fortnite to an older save state in 2023 reflects the growing trend in gaming where nostalgia and retro visuals are increasingly popular. The company's head, Steve Allison, and Yoga Buddhi CEO Benjamin Simon, who also appeared in the earlier Epic v. Apple trial, were the first two witnesses in the Epic v. Google trial, highlighting the ongoing legal challenges Epic Games faces in the tech industry.

name: EPIC
description: EPIC, the developer of the popular game Fortnite, is currently embroiled in a legal dispute with Google over antitrust claims related to app store policies. The company has sued Google over issues concerning alternative payment systems in the "User Choice Billing" program, which Google had expected EPIC to join if it wanted to implement an alternative payment method. EPIC's CEO, Tim Sweeney, has publicly expressed skepticism about Google's intentions, suggesting that the tech giant might circumvent any settlement it offers. EPIC is determined to fight the so-called "Google tax" and is willing to push these cases through multiple appeals, standing alone in its lawsuit against Google. Amidst this legal battle, EPIC is also considering retaining some modern features, like sprinting and mantling, in the new-old version of Fortnite, demonstrating the company's commitment to both innovation and legal challenges in the tech and entertainment sectors.

name: TIM SWEENEY
description: Tim Sweeney, the CEO of Epic Games, is deeply involved in the ongoing legal battle against Google. According to TechCrunch (2023-11-06), Sweeney is set to provide testimony in the antitrust lawsuit that his company has brought against the tech giant. The Verge (2023-11-05) adds that Sweeney has expressed concerns that Google might not honor any settlement it agrees to, suggesting that the company could find ways to circumvent the terms. This skepticism has fueled Sweeney's determination to see the cases against Google through multiple appeals, demonstrating his commitment to holding the company accountable and ensuring fair competition in the technology and entertainment sectors.

name: MATCH GROUP
description: Match Group is the company behind Tinder, Match.com, OkCupid, and other dating apps. It reached a surprise last-minute settlement with Google over app store antitrust claims, making it sound like Match effectively gave up. [The Verge, 2023-11-05]

name: US V. GOOGLE ANTITRUST TRIAL
description: The US v. Google antitrust trial is an ongoing legal case in Washington, DC, where Google's anticompetitive practices are being scrutinized. The issue of deleted potentially incriminating messages has come up in this trial as well. [The Verge, 2023-11-05]

name: USER CHOICE BILLING
description: "User Choice Billing" is a program initiated by Google in 2022, designed to offer app developers an alternative payment system. This initiative enables developers to opt for their own payment processing solutions, thereby reducing Google's standard commission by 4 percentage points. By providing this flexibility, Google aims to foster a more competitive and diverse app ecosystem, allowing companies to retain a larger share of their revenue. This move was reported by The Verge on November 5, 2023, highlighting the program's significance in the app development and digital payment landscape.

name: JUDGE DONATO
description: Judge Donato is presiding over the Epic v. Google case. He has set the trial schedule, which is expected to last roughly five weeks starting November 6th and extending through early December. Judge Donato expects a verdict well before the December holiday period. [The Verge, 2023-11-05]

name: BELIEVE
description: Believe, a Paris-headquartered independent music company led by CEO Denis Ladegallerie, has carved a unique niche in the global music industry by specializing in artist development and music distribution. With a presence in 50 countries, Believe focuses on identifying and partnering with local artists and labels to maximize their momentum and growth. The company has developed an innovative, AI and data-driven expertise, which is unique in the music industry, and tools to manage AI-generated content are almost ready for use, as expressed by Ladegallerie. Believe has global partnerships with TikTok and Spotify, which have been instrumental in promoting the track "Si No Estás" by Iñigo Quintero, achieving its first-ever chart-topper on Spotify's Global Top 50. In the week of June 16th, 2023, Believe experienced significant success with their artists, as all the Top 5 albums were by artists signed to Believe directly or through their labels. This highlights Believe's ability to leverage technology and strategic partnerships to drive the success of its artists on a global scale.

name: DAVID BOWIE

name: MAURICIO POCHETTINO
description: Mauricio Pochettino, often referred to as Pochettino, is the manager of Chelsea Football Club. He has been lauded for his leadership, particularly after praising his team's performance and approach in a game against Manchester City, as reported by The Roar | Sports Writers Blog on 2023-11-12. Pochettino appointed Reece James as captain, a decision influenced by James's personality, leadership qualities, and the respect he commands within the club, as detailed by The Guardian on 2023-10-20. Beyond his role at Chelsea, Pochettino shares a close bond with Mikel Arteta, the manager of Arsenal. Their relationship, which Sky Sports described on 2023-10-20, extends beyond friendship to a familial level, rooted in their shared history as players at Paris Saint-Germain. Pochettino holds Arteta in high esteem, believing he has the potential to become one of the greatest coaches in the world.

name: MIKEL ARTETA
description: Mikel Arteta, the head coach of Arsenal FC, holds a significant connection with Mauricio Pochettino, a fellow figure in the football world. This relationship roots back to Arteta's formative years as a teenager at Paris Saint-Germain, where Pochettino's influence was profound, to the point that Arteta considers him part of his family. Their bond has been further solidified over time, extending from their shared experiences as players at Paris Saint-Germain to Arteta's current role as manager of Arsenal, as reported by both Sky Sports and The Guardian on October 20, 2023. This deep-seated relationship underscores the personal and professional dynamics that shape Arteta's approach to coaching and his place within the football community.

name: ARSENAL
description: Arsenal, a prominent European football club, is currently managed by Mikel Arteta, who serves as the head coach. The team, known for its high ticket prices akin to Inter Miami's 2024 season ticket costs, recently dominated a game against Sevilla, creating numerous opportunities but conceded a goal from a corner, leaving them at the top of Group B. In an upcoming derby match against Chelsea, Arsenal will assess the fitness of key players Bukayo Saka, William Saliba, and Leandro Trossard at the last minute. Interestingly, Arsenal's squad includes former Chelsea players Kai Havertz and Jorginho, adding an intriguing subplot to the upcoming fixture.

name: PARIS SAINT-GERMAIN
description:
Paris Saint-Germain, commonly known as PSG, is a prominent football club in the world of sports, boasting a rich history and significant contributions to the game. As of 2023, the club is notably associated with Kylian Mbappe, a prolific goal scorer who has been making significant impacts on the field, including scoring ten goals for the French national team. Mbappe's talent and success have further elevated the club's reputation.

Additionally, Paris Saint-Germain holds a special place in the careers of two former players, Mauricio Pochettino and Mikel Arteta. The Guardian reported on October 20, 2023, that Pochettino and Arteta played together at PSG, where they developed a close relationship. This bond was further detailed by Sky Sports on the same day, highlighting that PSG was where the two first met, and Pochettino took Arteta under his wing, mentoring him and likely influencing his future career in football. These connections underscore the club's role in nurturing talent and fostering camaraderie among its players.

name: ARTETA
description: Arteta, the coach of Arsenal Football Club, has a deeply rooted connection with Pochettino, a fellow football coach. According to Arteta, Pochettino's influence on his career has been profound, with the relationship between the two extending beyond friendship to a familial bond. This sentiment was expressed by Arteta in an interview with Sky Sports on 2023-10-20. Additionally, Arteta, as reported by The Guardian on 2023-10-24, emphasized the significance of resilience under pressure and the ability to adapt, finding various strategies to secure victories for his team. These qualities, it can be inferred, might also be a testament to the lessons he learned under Pochettino's mentorship.

name: KAI HAVERTZ
description: Kai Havertz, a talented attacking midfielder, has transitioned from Chelsea to Arsenal, as noted by Sky Sports on 2023-10-20 and The Independent - Sports on 2023-11-15. His move has reshaped the dynamics of both clubs, particularly in the attacking midfield positions, leaving behind a void at Chelsea while he faces the challenge of proving himself at Arsenal. Despite his potential, Havertz has encountered early difficulties in his Arsenal career, managing only one goal in his first 12 appearances, a fact highlighted by Sky Sports. This performance is under scrutiny as he prepares to confront his former team, Chelsea, adding an intriguing layer to the upcoming match.

However, Portugal's national pride in sports is not limited to rugby. The country's soccer team, bolstered by the exceptional skills of Cristiano Ronaldo, has been making headlines. In 2023, Ronaldo scored an impressive 10 goals, contributing significantly to Portugal's success. This performance helped the Euro 2016 winners secure victories in all ten of their Euro 2024 qualifying matches, showcasing the team's strength and determination to defend their European title.

name: EU LAWMAKERS
description: EU lawmakers, comprising representatives from the European Parliament, Council, and Commission, have made significant strides in the realm of artificial intelligence regulation. They clinched a political deal over the EU AI Act, marking it as the world's first comprehensive law aimed at regulating AI, a global first in AI governance. In a forward-thinking move, EU lawmakers opted for the term "general purpose" AI models and systems over industry-specific terms like "foundational" or "frontier" models, ensuring the law's adaptability to future AI advancements. The agreed-upon legislation includes a phased approach to compliance, granting a 24-month grace period before the high-risk rules will be enforced for general purpose AI systems. This decision reflects a balanced consideration of the need for regulation and the practical challenges faced by AI developers and users in adapting to new legal frameworks.

name: URSULA VON DER LEYEN
description: Ursula von der Leyen is the president of the European Union who made delivering a regulation to promote "trustworthy" AI a key priority of her term when she took up the post in late 2019. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
description: Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a technology that has been the subject of a risk-based regulatory framework proposed by the European Union in April 2021. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: THE COUNCIL
description: The Council is an organization that has established a provisional agreement on sanctions for AI Act violations, with higher penalties for banned AI applications and lower penalties for SMEs and start-ups. The Council also negotiated the phased entry into force of the AI Act, allowing for a gradual implementation of the law's requirements over 24 months. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: CARMEL ARTIGAS
description: Carmel Artigas is Spain’s secretary of state for digital and AI issues, who led the Council’s negotiations on the AI Act as the country held the rotating Council presidency. She hailed the agreement as a significant milestone for the digital information in Europe and the world. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT
description: The European Parliament, a pivotal legislative body within the European Union, is tasked with shaping the final form of laws that govern the region. In a significant move highlighted by TechCrunch on December 9, 2023, the Parliament demonstrated its commitment to technology and ethics by aiming to deliver AI legislation through the guidance of co-rapporteurs Dragoș Tudorache and Brando Benifei. This legislation is designed with a human-centric approach, ensuring that it respects fundamental rights and aligns with European values, reflecting the Parliament's role in balancing innovation with societal welfare.

name: DRAGOȘ TUDORACHE
description: Dragoș Tudorache is a co-rapporteur for the European Parliament who, along with Brando Benifei, aimed to deliver AI legislation that would ensure the ecosystem developed with a human-centric approach. He believes the balance of protection and innovation is present in the text. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: BRANDO BENIFEI
description: Brando Benifei is a co-rapporteur for the European Parliament who, along with Dragoș Tudorache, aimed to deliver AI legislation that would ensure the ecosystem developed with a human-centric approach. He is pleased with the outcome, citing the inclusion of a total ban on the use of AI for predictive policing and for biometric categorization as major wins. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: TUDORACHE
description: Tudorache is a person involved in the development of AI rules within the EU. They have been questioned about the adequacy of protection and stimulation for innovation in the AI rules text, but they assert that the balance is there, with safeguards and provisions needed to give trust to citizens in their interaction with AI [source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: THIERRY BRETTON
description: Thierry Breton is the EU's internal market commissioner. He described the agreement on AI rules as 'historic', emphasizing that it is a full package and a complete deal, which took a lot of time to balance user safety, innovation for startups, and respect for fundamental rights and European values [source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: AI OFFICE
description: The AI Office, established within the European Union's executive Commission, serves as a pivotal expert oversight body tasked with the comprehensive supervision of AI systems, particularly those with systemic risk, such as General Purpose AI (GPAI) models. This entity is responsible for developing guidelines and rules for AI systems, playing a crucial role in setting risk classification thresholds for GPAIs under the EU's risk-based framework. The AI Office will coordinate with Member State oversight bodies, ensuring the enforcement of AI regulations and contributing to the advancement of standards and testing practices for the most sophisticated AI models. To enhance its decision-making process, a scientific panel of independent experts will be appointed to advise the AI Office on matters concerning GPAI models. As of December 2023, the Commission has not yet determined the budget or headcount for the AI Office, indicating that these details are still under consideration.

name: MISTRAL
description: Mistral is a French AI startup that has been lobbying for a total exemption from obligations for foundational models/GPAIs in the EU's AI package. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: SPANISH PRESIDENCY
description: The Spanish presidency agreed to a deal that includes some obligations for GPAIs and foundation models, not a total carve out as Mistral and its lobbyists have been pushing for. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: JEAN-NOËL BARROT
description: Jean-Noël Barrot is France’s digital minister who responded to the political deal on the AI package, stating that France will analyze the compromise and ensure that the text preserves Europe’s ability to develop its own AI technologies and safeguards strategic autonomy. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: ARTIGAS
description: Artigas is a person who suggested during a press conference that Mistral, once commercialized, would likely fit in the “low tier” for GPAIs, meaning it would have only limited transparency obligations. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: THE LIONS
description: The Lions, a sports team, needed to win after a significant loss in Baltimore. They achieved a 26-14 victory over the Raiders in a game that felt more one-sided than the score suggests. The Lions' defense dominated the game, and rookie Jahmyr Gibbs had a breakout performance with 189 scrimmage yards and a touchdown. Amon-Ra St. Brown also had a 100-yard game despite being questionable due to illness. The Lions enter their bye week in sole possession of the No. 2 seed in the NFC [The Sporting News, 2023-10-30]

name: THE RAIDERS
description: The Raiders, a sports team, were outplayed by the Lions, with abysmal offensive performance except for a second-quarter touchdown drive led by Josh Jacobs. They lost the game 26-14 and dropped their second consecutive game against an NFC North opponent. The Raiders have a must-win game against the Giants in Week 9 if they want any chance to linger in the AFC playoff race [The Sporting News, 2023-10-30]

name: DAVANTE ADAMS
description: Davante Adams, a star receiver for the Raiders, had an 11-yard performance against the Lions on October 30, 2023. Despite not having a single catch during the game, his presence on the field was notable. Frustrated with the play of the game, particularly the quarterback's performance, Adams was seen slamming his helmet down on the sideline in the fourth quarter, as reported by The Sporting News. It is suggested that his performance could have been significantly better under different circumstances.

name: JIMMY GAROPPOLO

Recently, in a game against the Lions, Jacobs showcased his exceptional skills by leading a crucial second-quarter touchdown drive, as reported by The Sporting News on October 30, 2023. His ability to make nice gains consistently contributes to the Raiders' offensive capabilities, solidifying his reputation as a key player in the team's lineup.

name: RAIDERS
description: The Raiders, a professional American football team in the NFL, have been actively participating in high-profile night games, showcasing their skills and resilience amidst challenging circumstances. On October 30, 2023, the Raiders faced off against the Lions in a 'Monday Night Football' game, with standout performances by players such as Jacobs, tight end Austin Hooper, and defensive end Maxx Crosby, who contributed significantly to the team's key plays, first downs, and penalties. However, the team's fortunes seemed to shift in their subsequent 'Sunday Night Football' game on November 12, 2023, against the Jets. The Raiders experienced a series of setbacks, including a three-and-out situation, and their corner, Amik Robertson, was forced to leave the field due to a possible concussion. Moreover, their quarterback, O'Connell, narrowly avoided a fumble and threw an interception to Jordan Whitehead, highlighting the intense pressure and competition they faced during the game. Despite these challenges, the Raiders continue to be a significant force in the NFL, with their performances closely followed by fans and analysts alike.
