name: VIRTUAL PRIVATE NETWORKS (VPNS)
description: Virtual private networks (VPNs) are a technology that masks the IP address and the identity of a user's device on the network, creating an encrypted "tunnel" to prevent the internet service provider (ISP) from accessing data about the user's browsing history. However, they do not protect against all security threats and are just one part of a robust online security routine. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: ROYA ENSAFI
description: Roya Ensafi is an assistant professor of computer science and engineering at the University of Michigan. She explained to Engadget that using a poorly designed or unprotected network can still undermine security, even with a VPN. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: YAELE GRAUER
description: Yael Grauer is the program manager of Consumer Reports’ online security guide. She recommends looking for security features like open-source software with reproducible builds, up-to-date support for industry-standard protocols, and the ability to defend against attack vectors. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: CONSUMER REPORTS
description: Consumer Reports is a well-respected organization that serves as a comprehensive resource for consumers seeking reviews and information on a wide array of products and services. They are known for their in-depth analysis and for utilizing pre-existing academic work to test and evaluate the security specifications of different Virtual Private Networks (VPNs). In their guides, they highlight the importance of online security and warn against the use of the Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol (PPTP), citing serious security flaws associated with this protocol. Additionally, Consumer Reports demonstrates a commitment to safety by waiting for more data and independent testing from the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) and the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IIHS) before drawing conclusions about the safety of emerging vehicles, such as the Cybertruck. This approach ensures that their assessments are based on thorough and reliable information, making Consumer Reports a trusted source for consumers making informed decisions.

name: JED CRANDALL
description: Jed Crandall, an associate professor at Arizona State University, is recognized for his expertise in cybersecurity and privacy technologies. In an interview with Engadget on 2023-10-16, Crandall offered valuable insights on the use of Virtual Private Networks (VPNs), emphasizing their effectiveness in safeguarding against passive data snooping. However, he also noted that the use of a VPN is not always necessary, suggesting that individuals should consider their specific needs and circumstances when deciding to employ such services. Crandall's commentary provides a balanced perspective on the role of VPNs in enhancing online security, reflecting his deep understanding of the subject matter.

name: ARIZONA STATE UNIVERSITY
description: Arizona State University, a renowned educational institution, is home to Jed Crandall, who serves as an associate professor. However, the university has recently been embroiled in controversy following false sexual harassment allegations made against Sarah Viren and her wife, which were reported by The Verge on October 25, 2023. These accusations were filed with the university's Title IX Office, highlighting the complexities and challenges that can arise within academic environments. Despite this, Arizona State University continues to be a hub for learning and research, with faculty members like Crandall contributing to its academic community.

name: WIREGUARD
description: WireGuard is an industry-standard protocol for virtual private networks (VPNs) that is preferred by Consumer Reports. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: IPSEC
description: IPsec is an industry-standard protocol for virtual private networks (VPNs). [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: MULTIFACTOR AUTHENTICATION
description: Multifactor authentication methods are security measures that can be used in conjunction with a VPN to protect data

name: VPN
description: A Virtual Private Network (VPN) is a technology that offers private internet access by encrypting and protecting data, enabling users to access geoblocked services and hide information from Internet Service Providers (ISPs). However, it's important to note that a VPN does not guarantee total anonymity, as the provider may still have access to certain user data. To enhance security, users are advised to implement strong passwords and multi-factor authentication to safeguard against phishing attacks, hacking, and other cyber threats. The safety features of a VPN can vary significantly among different providers. To make informed decisions, potential users should consult third-party audits, Consumer Reports reviews, transparency reports, and privacy policies, as suggested by Engadget on 2023-10-16. This due diligence will help in understanding the specific safety measures and privacy guarantees offered by a chosen provider.

name: PUBLIC WIFI NETWORKS
description: Public WiFi networks are wireless internet connections available in public places, which can be less secure than private networks

name: ISP
description: Internet Service Providers (ISPs) are companies that provide internet access to users and can potentially see their online activities

name: GEOBLOCKING
description: Geoblocking is a technology that restricts access to certain online services based on the user's geographic location

name: TOR BROWSER
description: The Tor browser is a free tool that can provide anonymity and privacy online, and is suggested as an alternative to VPNs for certain professions

name: PROTONVPN
description: ProtonVPN, a Virtual Private Network service offered by Proton Technologies, is recognized for its robust security features and global accessibility. As of 2023, the service boasts server locations in over 65 countries, enabling users to connect on up to 10 devices simultaneously across various operating systems and devices, including macOS, Windows, Linux, iOS, Android, routers, and TV services. ProtonVPN has been praised for its independently audited no-logs policy, a commitment to privacy that has been proven through non-compliance with law enforcement requests to reveal user data. The service has demonstrated its effectiveness in bypassing geoblocks, facilitating streaming and gaming with minimal impact on connection speeds. Additionally, ProtonVPN offers malware, ad, and tracker blocking, as well as a kill switch feature for added security. In August 2023, ProtonVPN expanded its support by introducing a new app specifically for Linux users. Moreover, in a rare Black Friday sale in November 2023, ProtonVPN offered a monthly subscription at a discounted rate of $4 for a total of 30 months, making it an attractive option for those seeking a reliable and secure VPN service.

name: PROTON TECHNOLOGIES
description: Proton Technologies is a company that offers a suite of services, including ProtonVPN. Dedicated users can pay around $8.63 for a monthly plan to access the entire suite. [Proton Technologies, Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: WINDSCRIBE
description: Windscribe is a free Virtual Private Network service that allows users to access 10GB of data per month, unlimited connections, and server locations in over 10 countries. It was selected as the best free VPN due to its high security and wide range of server locations compared to other free VPNs. Windscribe has over 500 servers in more than 60 countries and can be configured for routers, smart TVs, and other devices in addition to standard operating systems. [Windscribe, Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: EXPRESSVPN
description: ExpressVPN is a Virtual Private Network (VPN) service provider renowned for its high-speed connections with no lag, making it an ideal choice for frequent travelers, gamers, and streamers. According to Engadget in 2023, ExpressVPN passed rigorous geoblock, streaming, and gaming tests, solidifying its position as one of the fastest VPNs in the market. The service boasts an extensive network of 2,000 servers spread across 160 cities, offering unparalleled access to a multitude of locations. In a significant enhancement, ExpressVPN now features an in-house password manager, ExpressVPN Keys, which is included with the subscription. This tool facilitates secure management and auto-filling of logins across various sites, streamlining the process of toggling between multiple streaming and gaming accounts. Subscription costs for ExpressVPN range from $8.32 to $12.95 per month, depending on the term of the plan. The service supports a wide array of devices, from smart TVs to game consoles, and includes a kill switch feature called Network Lock to ensure data safety in case of a lost connection.

name: EXPRESSVPN KEYS
description: ExpressVPN Keys is an in-house password manager offered by ExpressVPN to manage and autofill logins across sites included with the subscription. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: NETWORK LOCK
description: Network Lock is a kill switch feature included in ExpressVPN that keeps data safe even if the connection to the VPN is lost. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: CYBERGHOST
description: CyberGhost, a reputable Virtual Private Network (VPN) service provider, offers its users the convenience of simultaneous connectivity on up to seven devices. The monthly subscription fee ranges from $2.11 to $12.99, varying based on the subscription term. Known for its user-friendly approach, CyberGhost supports a wide array of gadgets including routers, computers, smart TVs, and more, providing detailed instructions for setting up cross-platform connections. In a significant move, the company has recently expanded its network of servers to cover 100 countries, with new additions such as Bolivia, Ecuador, Peru, Uruguay, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, Guatemala, and the Dominican Republic. Demonstrating a commitment to security and transparency, CyberGhost completed an independent security audit conducted by Deloitte earlier this year. The company also runs a vulnerability disclosure program and provides access to a transparency report, which elucidates the requests for its data, ensuring that users are well-informed about their privacy and security.

name: DELOITTE
description: Deloitte is an independent auditor that completed a security audit of CyberGhost earlier this year. [Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: SURFSHARK
description:
Surfshark, a Virtual Private Network (VPN) service provider, is renowned for offering simultaneous connections on an unlimited number of devices without imposing any bandwidth restrictions. This makes it an attractive choice for users who require robust privacy and security across multiple platforms. Surfshark is compatible with Windows, Mac, Android, iOS, and Linux, and further enhances user convenience with browser extensions for Chrome, Firefox, and Edge. Subscription costs range from $2.49 to $12.95 per month, depending on the plan chosen.

In a significant move, Surfshark recently underwent its first independent audit, demonstrating a commitment to transparency and security. The company has also introduced QR-code-enabled login across devices, streamlining the authentication process, and expanded support for alternative ID profiles, catering to a diverse user base.

Notably, Surfshark's Black Friday deal for 2023 offers up to 86 percent off on two-year plans, with an additional four months of service provided for free, depending on the plan selected. This deal solidifies Surfshark's position as one of the best and most affordable VPN services in the market, making it particularly appealing for individuals looking for a reliable and cost-effective privacy solution.

name: NORDVPN
description: NordVPN is a VPN service provider that did not make the cut for the best services due to being overhyped and underwhelming. Its pricing, up to $14.49 for a “complete” subscription, seemed high compared to other services, and its free or lower cost plans were not as competitive. [Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: GOOGLE ONE VPN
description: As of early 2023, Google One subscriptions include access to the company’s VPN. It works similarly to other VPNs, hiding online activity from network operators. Google One subscribers can access the VPN in 22 countries on Android, iOS, Windows, and Mac devices, and they can share VPN access with up to five people who are on their One plans. The Google One VPN has not been fully tested yet [Engadget, 2023-10-16]

name: AFTERBUZZ TV
description: AfterBuzz TV is a media outlet that interviewed Travis Kelce in 2016, where he played the game "Kiss, Marry, Kill" and mentioned Taylor Swift. [The Age, 2023-09-26]

name: VULTURE
description: Vulture is a media outlet that reported on Travis Kelce's visit to New York City, coinciding with Taylor Swift's presence there while she was re-recording her 1989 tracks. [The Age, 2023-09-26]

name: THE AGE
description: The Age, a reputable news organization, has been actively covering a range of significant stories in 2023. On September 26, 2023, The Age published an insightful article exploring the potential romantic relationship between pop sensation Taylor Swift and NFL star Travis Kelce. The piece delved into the implications of this high-profile connection on both pop culture and the National Football League, offering readers a unique perspective on how celebrity relationships can intersect with and influence various aspects of society. Later, on November 7, 2023, The Age reported on the financial dealings of Donald Trump, specifically focusing on the increase in the ground lease on one of his properties. This development was highlighted as a contributing factor to the former president's growing wealth, providing a detailed analysis of the financial aspects and the broader implications within the real estate and political landscapes. Through these diverse topics, The Age demonstrates its commitment to delivering comprehensive and timely news coverage to its audience.

name: GETAWAY CAR
description: A “getaway car” is a term often used in pop culture to describe a vehicle used to escape after an event. Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce were spotted together in a “getaway car” outside the stadium, potentially a nod towards Swift’s 2017 track. [The Age, 2023-09-26]

name: OUIJA BOARDS
description: Ouija boards are tools used in attempts to converse with the dead, which are considered spiritually dangerous practices by Fr. Dan Reehil, an exorcist priest.[]

name: FR. DAN REEHL
description: Fr. Dan Reehil is a priest of the Diocese of Nashville who received exorcism training in 2018 at Ateneo Pontificio Regina Apostolorum in Rome and was installed as the exorcist of the Diocese of Nashville that same year. He warns against the use of Ouija boards and other attempts to converse with the dead.[]

name: DIOCESE OF NASHVILLE
description: The Diocese of Nashville is a religious organization within the Catholic Church that chose and installed Fr. Dan Reehil as its exorcist.[]

name: DEMONS
description: According to Fr. Dan Reehil, as reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on 2023-10-30, DEMONS are spiritual entities that engage in deceptive practices and impersonation of deceased individuals. These activities are facilitated when humans open themselves up to demonic interaction through the use of Ouija boards and other forms of occult practices. The descriptions provided are consistent, emphasizing the entity's capacity for deceit and the methods by which humans might inadvertently invite their presence.

name: REEHIL
description: Reehil is an individual who warns against the use of Ouija boards, stating that they can open one up to demonic activity [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: OUIJA BOARD
description: The Ouija board, a product currently marketed by Hasbro as a toy or board game, has a historical background that dates back to the late 19th century. Initially developed as a parlor game, it has been used in purported attempts to communicate with the dead or the spirit world. Despite its commercial categorization as a game, the Ouija board holds a significant place in the realm of spiritual and paranormal activities, where it is believed by some to facilitate connections with the spirit world. This dual identity as both a commercial product and a tool for spiritual communication underscores the complex dynamics and perceptions surrounding the Ouija board within various communities.

name: HASBRO
description: Hasbro, a renowned company in the realm of entertainment and gaming, is currently involved in the production of diverse products that cater to a wide range of interests. Notably, Hasbro markets the Ouija board as a tool for communicating with the spirit world, a claim that has captured the imagination of many enthusiasts seeking paranormal experiences [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]. Additionally, the company has expanded its gaming portfolio with the introduction of Jenga: Super Mario Edition, a unique twist on the classic Jenga game that is themed around the beloved Super Mario universe. This innovative game was made available for sale during the Black Friday deals at Amazon, offering fans an exciting opportunity to add a new dimension to their gaming collection. Through its varied offerings, Hasbro continues to engage and entertain audiences with its creative and imaginative products.

name: KENNARD NOVELTY COMPANY
description: The Kennard Novelty Company was the original mass-producer of the Ouija board, which was later sold to Parker Brothers in 1967 [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: PARKER BROTHERS
description: Parker Brothers is a company that purchased the Kennard Novelty Company in 1967, taking over the production of the Ouija board [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: SPIRIT COMMUNICATION
description: Spirit communication is an activity that involves attempting to contact the spirit world, often using tools like the Ouija board [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: FATHER REEHL
description: Father Reehil is a priest who disagrees with the characterization of the Ouija board as a toy or board game, viewing it as a form of divination with profound spiritual consequences. He has personally seen cases of demonic oppression stemming from Ouija board usage. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: DIVINATION
description: Divination, including the use of the Ouija board, is condemned by the Bible numerous times, according to Father Reehil. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: DEMONIC OPPRESSION
description: Demonic oppression is a phenomenon that Father Reehil has witnessed in six cases connected to Ouija board usage, resulting in night terrors, suicidal ideation, despair, and in one case, a man being impaled with chicken bones. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: ROLAND DOE
description: Roland Doe is a young teenage boy from Maryland whose purported demonic possession, connected to Ouija board usage, led to numerous major exorcisms in 1949. His story was adapted into the 1971 book "The Exorcist" and the 1973 movie. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: THE EXORCIST
description: "The Exorcist" is a 1971 book by William Peter Blatty and a 1973 movie starring Ellen Burstyn and Linda Blair, based on the story of Roland Doe's demonic possession. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-10-30]

name: KEVIN ROOSE
description: Kevin Roose is a journalist from The New York Times who was impressed by ChatGPT, calling it the best AI chatbot ever released to the general public. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: THE ATLANTIC
description: The Atlantic is a magazine that included ChatGPT in its "Breakthroughs of the Year" for 2022 as part of the generative-AI eruption that may change our mind about how we work, think, and perceive human creativity. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: DEREK THOMPSON
description: Derek Thompson is a writer for The Atlantic who discussed the potential impact of generative AI, including ChatGPT, on human creativity and work. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: MIT STUDY
description: An MIT study showed that ChatGPT decreased the amount of time it took workers to complete tasks like writing cover letters, "delicate" emails, and cost-benefit analyses by 40% while increasing output quality by 18%, as measured by third-party evaluators. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: GPTS
description: GPTS, or Generative Pre-trained Transformers, are a cutting-edge technology developed by OpenAI that introduces an unprecedented level of personalization, surpassing the capabilities of ChatGPT as of today. Purpose-built to simplify tasks, GPTs have the potential to disrupt the niche market that has developed around creating and editing prompts for ChatGPT. These versatile tools enable the building of custom AI systems that can be trained on specific data sets to perform tasks tailored to individual needs. Whether it's answering detailed questions about ingredients for a particular recipe or generating code that adheres to best practices, GPTs offer a wide range of applications designed to enhance user experience and efficiency. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-30]

name: WHOLE FOODS
description: Whole Foods is a grocery store that will be open during the holiday season on a limited schedule, with hours of operation varying by location

name: CVS
description: CVS is a company with locations that will be open on Thanksgiving, although not all stores will be open. On Black Friday, CVS locations will operate during regular hours. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-06]

name: DUNKIN’ DONUTS
description: Dunkin’ Donuts, a coffee chain, will be open on Thanksgiving Day but with limited hours. Opening and closing times of stores on the holiday vary based on location. On Black Friday, Dunkin’ Donuts will reopen with its usual hours of operation based on each store. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-06]

name: WALGREENS
description: Most Walgreens stores will be closed on 23 November 2023, according to a press release shared by the brand on 16 November 2023. While this is the first time that Walgreens has closed its doors on the holiday, some 24-hour stores will still be open during certain hours on Thanksgiving Day, depending on store location. Walgreens stores will reopen on 24 November 2023, with opening and closing times depending on the location of the store. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-06]

name: DIGITAL GIFTS
description: Digital gifts are online or electronically delivered presents, such as gift cards, subscriptions, and other digital content, that can be purchased as late as Christmas Day. [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: DISNEY BUNDLE
description: The Disney Bundle, a monthly subscription service curated for film and TV enthusiasts, sports aficionados, and families, offers ad-supported access to a trio of streaming platforms: Disney Plus, Hulu, and ESPN Plus. Priced at $14.99 per month, this package enables subscribers to enjoy a diverse array of content, spanning from beloved Disney films and series, popular sitcoms on Hulu, to live sports events and in-depth analysis on ESPN, making it a comprehensive entertainment solution. As of December 2023, The Verge and Polygon both highlight the Disney Bundle's value in providing a wide spectrum of content, reinforcing its appeal to a broad audience.

name: PLAYSTATION PLUS
description: PlayStation Plus is a subscription service that grants users access to free titles, discounts, online gaming, and cloud-based backups. Memberships start at $9.99 a month, and gift cards are available at Amazon, Best Buy, and Target for $30

name: NINTENDO SWITCH ONLINE
description: Nintendo Switch Online is an annual subscription service starting at $19.99 a year, available at Amazon, Best Buy, and GameStop. It allows users to play more than 70 retro games from NES, SNES, and original Game Boy eras, play online with friends, and access cloud saves

name: NINTENDO SWITCH ONLINE + EXPANSION PACK
description: Nintendo Switch Online + Expansion Pack is an annual subscription service that, in addition to the benefits of the Switch Online membership, grants access to Game Boy Advance, Sega Genesis, and Nintendo 64 games, as well as DLC content for some titles. Individual plans cost $49.99, and family plans are available via gift card at Amazon and Walmart for $71.89 ($8 off)

name: GAMESTOP GIFT CARD
description: A GameStop gift card is a versatile option for gamers, available at Amazon and GameStop. It can be used to purchase accessories and games for any console

name: GETYOURGUIDE GIFT CARD
description: A GetYourGuide gift card serves as a versatile and convenient tool for accessing guided tours and engaging tourist attractions across diverse global destinations. This gift card enables its holder to embark on thrilling explorations, such as scaling the heights of Italy's Mount Etna, an active volcano, or experiencing the adrenaline-pumping adventure of swimming with sharks in the exotic waters of Cape Verde. Perfect for travel enthusiasts and adventure seekers, the GetYourGuide gift card offers a wide array of experiences, making it an ideal gift for loved ones who wish to enrich their travels with unforgettable activities. As noted by The Verge on December 24, 2023, it provides an easy and enjoyable way to discover the world's wonders.

name: PACK & GO GIFT CARD
description: A Pack & Go gift card (Amazon and Target) covers almost everything your giftee will need while on vacation. They can use it on a Southwest Airlines flight, buy gas from Chevron or Texaco if they’re on a road trip, and even book an Airbnb or place a Grubhub order [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: ROSETTA STONE MEMBERSHIP
description: For aspiring polyglots, a Rosetta Stone membership will make it easy to learn everything from French to Arabic to Japanese from the comfort of their home. Along with lessons, memberships come with helpful extras, including speech recognition tech to get the accent just right. At the moment, Rosetta Stone is offering up to 50 percent off of its plans, with the 12-month tier for learning just one language starting at $126 ($42 off) [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: UBER GIFT CARD
description: A gift card to a rideshare service like Uber (Amazon, Best Buy, Target) will come in handy when they need a ride to the airport. It will also come in handy if their New Year’s Eve plans include popping a few celebratory shots [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: LYFT GIFT CARD
description: A gift card to a rideshare service like Lyft (Amazon, Best Buy, Target) will come in handy when they need a ride to the airport. It will also come in handy if their New Year’s Eve plans include popping a few celebratory shots [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: PELOTON SUBSCRIPTION
description: Peloton’s $12.99 monthly subscription offers thousands of streamable fitness classes revolving around a variety of different workouts, ranging from strength training to stretching. It’s a service that’s available to everybody [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: SOUTHWEST AIRLINES, CHEVRON, TEXACO, AIRBNB, GRUBHUB
PELOTON
description: Peloton offers a $12.99 monthly subscription service that provides access to thousands of streamable fitness classes covering various workouts, from strength training to stretching, available to everyone regardless of owning a Peloton device ["The Verge", 2023-12-24]

name: HEADSPACE
description: Headspace is a well-regarded meditation and mindfulness application that offers a diverse range of guided meditation sessions, sleepcasts, and curated yoga and fitness videos to its users. The app is designed to assist individuals in enhancing their mental health, promoting relaxation, and improving sleep quality through expert-taught meditations. As of 2023, Headspace typically charges $12.99 per month or $69.99 per year for subscriptions, as reported by "The Verge" on December 24, 2023. However, in a special Black Friday deal for 2023, mentioned by Engadget on November 19, 2023, new and returning subscribers can take advantage of a 50 percent discount, paying only $35 for a year of access or $6.50 per month for those preferring a more frequent payment method. This deal provides an excellent opportunity for individuals interested in exploring the benefits of meditation and mindfulness at a reduced cost.

name: FITBIT
description: Fitbit offers Premium subscriptions starting at $9.99 a month, accessible to all users, even without owning a Fitbit device. Memberships include thousands of guided and customizable workouts, covering a range from martial arts to meditation, and additional programs on nutrition. Fitbit also provides an option for one-on-one sessions with a professional health coach for an extra $54.99 per month ["The Verge", 2023-12-24]

name: CLASSPASS
description: ClassPass is a subscription service that allows users to access thousands of gyms, fitness studios, salons, and spas in their local area ["The Verge", 2023-12-24]

description:
"FRESH N LEAN is a meal prep service dedicated to providing a healthy selection of meal kits. This service is particularly beneficial for individuals who are too busy to prepare meals daily. This service is particularly useful for individuals who are too busy to cook regularly, as it simplifies the meal preparation process. Blue Apron also offers a thoughtful gifting option, allowing users to share the benefits of convenient and nutritious meal kits with friends or family members who might be struggling to find time for meal prep amidst their busy schedules. As of 2023, Blue Apron continues to be a popular choice for those seeking to maintain a healthy lifestyle without sacrificing convenience.

name: HELLOFRESH
description: HelloFresh, a renowned meal kit service, provides a diverse range of meal options tailored to suit various dietary preferences and lifestyles. As highlighted by "The Verge" on 2023-12-24, HelloFresh is particularly known for its healthy selections, making it an ideal choice for individuals looking to maintain a balanced diet amidst their busy schedules. Moreover, the service can be gifted to someone who finds it challenging to prepare healthy meals daily, offering a convenient and thoughtful solution to their meal prep needs.

name: EATER WINE CLUB
description: Eater Wine Club is a subscription service that sends two or four bottles of wine chosen by an Eater expert every month, showcasing wines from all over the world [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: SUR LA TABLE

name: GOLDBELLY
description: Goldbelly offers a monthly ice cream subscription that allows recipients to enjoy up to six pints of ice cream or 24 ice cream sandwiches a month, sourced from small creameries all over the country [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: STARBUCKS
description: Starbucks is a coffee chain where a gift card can help someone get their caffeine fix whenever, wherever [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: DOORDASH
description: DoorDash, a prominent player in the food delivery industry, offers a versatile platform for food enthusiasts to enjoy meals from a wide array of restaurants. As highlighted by The Verge on 2023-12-24, one unique aspect of DoorDash is its gift card feature, which makes it an excellent choice for gifting to friends and family who are passionate about food. This allows recipients to indulge in their favorite dishes from participating eateries at their convenience. Additionally, The Verge reported on 2023-10-26 that DoorDash is utilized by Thai Food Near Me, a specific restaurant, to enhance and streamline their food offerings and delivery services, demonstrating DoorDash's utility not only for consumers but also for businesses looking to optimize their operations.

name: VINYL ME, PLEASE
description: Vinyl Me, Please is a company that offers subscriptions for vinyl records. Giftees receive vinyl records from their choice of music genre every month, along with booklets to learn more about the record and access to exclusive discounts. Three-month subscriptions start at $128 and come with a total of four records (one of which is a limited-time bonus) [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: TICKETMASTER
description: Ticketmaster, a prominent company in the event ticketing industry, has faced criticism for its monopolistic practices, which have been linked to the escalating cost of concert tickets, as reported by Polygon on November 7, 2023. Despite these controversies, Ticketmaster also offers a service that allows individuals to gift experiences to their loved ones through gift cards, enabling them to attend live performances by popular artists such as Olivia Rodrigo, Bad Bunny, and The Rolling Stones, as highlighted by The Verge on December 24, 2023. This dual role positions Ticketmaster as both a significant player in the ticketing market and a provider of personalized gift options for music enthusiasts.

name: KINDLE UNLIMITED
description: Kindle Unlimited is a subscription service that grants members access to millions of ebooks and select audiobooks [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: COMIXOLOGY UNLIMITED
description: Comixology Unlimited is a subscription service that allows access to over 45,000 comics and graphic novels, as well as more than 2,400 manga titles from a phone or tablet. Subscribers also get discounts on select digital books [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: BOOK OF THE MONTH
description: Book of the Month is a membership service that curates a small selection of five to seven bestsellers and classics for members every month. A three-book plan currently starts at $59.99 [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: ADOBE CREATIVE CLOUD
description: An Adobe Creative Cloud subscription, priced at $59.99 per month, is a suitable gift for creative professionals, offering access to a suite of popular services including Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere Pro, InDesign, and other Adobe apps. [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: CODECADEMY
description: Codecademy is a coding educational platform that can assist someone looking to learn how to code. A subscription to Codecademy, priced at $29.99 per month, can help build a portfolio with online courses, a community, fun events, cheat sheets, and other resources. There is a special plan for individuals aiming to change career paths, which includes all the aforementioned features plus technical interview help. This plan is currently available for $120 a year (half off) with the promo code BYE2023. [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: CRAFTSY
description: A Craftsy membership, priced at $113 a year, is a good gift for individuals interested in arts and crafts. It provides access to over 2,000 live and on-demand classes led by experts covering a variety of topics from baking and cake decorating to woodworking and painting. Members can also connect with other crafters in the Craftsy community and attend live events. [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

name: GIFT CARDS
description: Gift cards from major retailers such as Amazon, Best Buy, Walmart, and Target are versatile gifts that offer recipients a wide range of options to choose from. [The Verge, 2023-12-24]

description: Christian Pulisic, affectionately known as 'Captain America', is a highly skilled soccer player who has made significant waves in the sport. As reported by The Independent - Sports on November 15, 2023, Pulisic left Chelsea, a move that opened up opportunities in the attacking midfield positions. Earlier, on October 14, 2023, Sporting News highlighted his exceptional performance during the USA vs. Germany match. During this game, Pulisic showcased his prowess by scoring a goal and achieving a high pass completion rate, successfully completing 27 of 29 passes. He further demonstrated his offensive capabilities by creating two chances, solidifying his reputation as the most electric and incisive player on the U.S. team.

name: LUCA DE LA TORRE
description: Luca de la Torre, a professional soccer player, was notably substituted into the USA vs. Germany match at halftime in place of Gio Reyna, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-10-14. Despite his entry into the game, de la Torre struggled to effectively defend against the German team. The substitution raised questions among fans and analysts about the decision-making process, pondering why de la Torre was selected over other potential replacements such as Johnny Cardoso or Lennard Maloney. This event highlights de la Torre's role in the national team and the strategic considerations that go into match decisions at an international level.

name: CAMERON CARTER-VICKERS

description: Johnny Cardoso, a soccer player, made a notable appearance during the USA vs. Germany match on October 14, 2023. He was brought into the game for a 15-minute stint towards the end, during which he demonstrated commendable control and presence on the field. Cardoso managed to lose possession only once amidst his 10 touches, showcasing his ball-handling skills under pressure. He also successfully completed a tackle, a testament to his defensive capabilities. name: MAYFLOWER
description: The Mayflower is a historical event that refers to the ship that brought the Pilgrims to America, which is often associated with Thanksgiving Day. [The Age, 2023-11-15]

name: THANKSGIVING DAY
description: Thanksgiving Day is a holiday celebrated in the US and has ties to colonial aggression, which has been increasingly questioned by many in the US. [The Age, 2023-11-15]

name: ELI ROTH
description: Eli Roth, a renowned filmmaker and actor, has directed over 20 films and produced more than double that number, showcasing his extensive experience and influence in the film industry. He is best known for his role as Sgt. Donny "The Bear Jew" Donowitz in Quentin Tarantino's critically acclaimed film, Inglourious Basterds (2009). More recently, Roth appeared in The Idol, playing a Live Nation representative, an experience that he credits with "switching up my brain to use another side of my creativity." This personal experience as an actor, according to Roth, makes him an "actor's director," as he understands the challenges actors face and is able to connect with them on a deeper level. This insight into the acting process has contributed to his success as a director, as actors appreciate his empathetic approach. Roth co-created the film "Thanksgiving," recognizing the potential for horror in the materialistic shift of the holiday, further demonstrating his creative versatility and ability to find unique angles in storytelling. His work on The Idol and Thanksgiving highlights his ability to seamlessly transition between acting and directing, enriching both experiences with his multifaceted talents.

name: GREG RENDELL
description: Greg Rendell is a filmmaker who co-created the film "Thanksgiving" with Eli Roth. [The Age, 2023-11-15]

name: TRAMPLE VIDEOS

name: THANKSGIVING (FILM)
description: "Thanksgiving" is a horror film co-created by Eli Roth and Greg Rendell that critiques the commercialization of the holiday and explores class divisions. [The Age, 2023-11-15]

name: DAWN OF THE DEAD
description: "Dawn of the Dead" is a 1978 horror film by George Romero that critiques consumerism and has been referenced as an influence on the film "Thanksgiving". [The Age, 2023-11-15]

name: MICROSOFT XBOX CONTROLLER
description: The Xbox controller is a gaming accessory designed by Microsoft. It is a refined version of the Xbox One wireless model, featuring added texture around its grips, a capture button, and compatibility with various platforms including PC, Xbox consoles, Steam Deck, Android, and iOS. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: 8BITDO USB ADAPTER 2
description: The "8BITDO USB ADAPTER 2" is a versatile gaming accessory developed by 8BitDo, priced at $19.99. This adapter serves as a compatibility bridge, enabling the use of Xbox controllers on Nintendo Switch consoles, as well as on other devices such as Macs and Raspberry Pi systems. Additionally, it is noted for its seamless integration with the DualSense controller, making it a valuable tool for gamers looking to utilize their PlayStation controllers on the Switch. The adapter is praised for its clever design and perfect performance once paired, offering an expanded range of controller options for gaming across multiple platforms.

name: NICOLE CARPENTER
description: Nicole Carpenter is a member of the Polygon team who endorses the Xbox controller for its comfort, texture, and weight. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: PC GAMING
description: PC gaming is an activity that involves playing video games on a personal computer. Polygon's What to Buy section provides recommendations for the best gaming hardware and accessories for PC gaming. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: DUALSENSE
description: DualSense is the official controller for the PS5, offering precise control and advanced features such as realistic-feeling haptic feedback, gyroscopic motion controls, and adaptive triggers that can provide tension for more realistic actions in games that support these features. It is also compatible with PC games through SteamInput API and can be used for PS Remote Play on Android devices. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: STEAM
description: Steam is a gaming platform that recognizes the DualSense controller as a first-class citizen through its SteamInput API, ensuring compatibility and support for many PC games. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: XBOX CONTROLLER
description: Xbox controller is mentioned alongside the DualSense as a compatible controller for PC games, and DS4Windows can emulate the DualSense as an Xbox controller for game compatibility. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: DS4WINDOWS
description: DS4Windows is an app that can be downloaded to ensure game compatibility on PC by emulating the DualSense as an Xbox controller, offering customizable settings for button mapping. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: PCGAMINGWIKI
description: PCGamingWiki is a site that provides information on which PC games support the DualSense’s haptics and adaptive trigger features, guiding users through the steps to get them working. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: DUALSENSE EDGE
description: DualSense Edge is Sony’s pro-grade controller, compatible with the PS5, featuring replaceable stick modules and an intuitive interface for remapping controls and setting schemes. [Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: NINTENDO SWITCH PRO CONTROLLER
description: Nintendo’s Switch Pro controller is a gaming controller with motion control support, a rechargeable battery, and a Nintendo-style face button layout. It supports NFC and has advanced haptics. [Source: Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: THIRD-PARTY SWITCH CONTROLLER
description: A third-party Switch controller is a gaming controller that is not made by Nintendo but is compatible with the Switch. It can wake the console from sleep by pressing the home button and then shaking the controller. However, it doesn’t support NFC and its haptics aren’t as good as Nintendo’s. [Source: Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: NFC
description: NFC (Near Field Communication) is a technology that allows for short-range wireless communication between devices. It is supported by Nintendo’s Switch Pro controller but not by the third-party Switch controller. [Source: Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: HAPTICS
description: Haptics is a technology that provides tactile feedback to the user. The quality of haptics in the third-party Switch controller is not up to par with Nintendo’s Switch Pro controller. [Source: Polygon, 2023-11-17]

name: CALIFORNIA’S PRIVACY PROTECTION AGENCY (CPPA)
description: The CPPA is a state privacy regulator in California that is preparing to put guardrails on AI by publishing draft regulations for automated decisionmaking technology (ADMT). The draft regulations are inspired by the EU's GDPR and aim to provide opt-out rights, pre-use notice requirements, and access rights for state residents to understand how their data is used for AI and automation. The CPPA's approach is risk-based and could have significant implications for US adtech giants like Meta, which rely on user profiling for targeted advertising. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: ASHKAN SOLTANI
description: Ashkan Soltani is the executive director of the CPPA who described the draft regulations as the most comprehensive and detailed set of rules in the AI space. He also mentioned that the CPPA's approach to regulating ADMT is risk-based. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: EUROPEAN UNION (EU)
description: The European Union is a region that has inspired the CPPA's draft regulations with its General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), which grants individuals rights over automated decisions with legal or significant impact. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: AI ACT
description: The AI Act is a draft legislation in the EU that is a dedicated risk-based framework for regulating applications of artificial intelligence. It has been in draft form since 2021 and is currently at a delicate stage of co-legislation. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: US FEDERAL PRIVACY LAW
description: US lawmakers have failed to pass a comprehensive federal privacy law, highlighting the limitations of presidential Executive Orders in addressing privacy concerns. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: CPPA
description: The California Privacy Protection Agency (CPPA), established in 2019, is a regulatory body that has been instrumental in advocating for privacy rules inspired by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). The CPPA played a significant role in the implementation of the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) in 2020, which aimed to enhance privacy rights for California residents. As of 2023, the agency is considering draft regulations to govern the use of Automated Decision-Making Technologies (ADMT) and to address risk assessment requirements. The CPPA is planning to introduce a regime that focuses on access and opt-out rights concerning businesses' utilization of ADMT. This will enable state residents to request an opt-out from having their data used for ADMT, with only a limited set of exemptions where the use of data is essential for security, fraud prevention, safety, or to provide goods or services requested by the consumer. Additionally, the CPPA is mandating that businesses provide pre-use notices to consumers, giving them the opportunity to opt-out of their data being used for automation or AI purposes, or to exercise their access rights to gain more information about the intended use of these technologies. The agency's objective is to impose a compliance cost on businesses that attempt to restrict consumers' ability to opt-out of the application of automation or AI to their data, thereby ensuring a fair and transparent data usage environment.

name: CCPA
description: The California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) is a privacy law that came into effect in early 2020, inspired by the EU's GDPR, and affords protections and controls to California residents. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: ADMT
description: Automated Decision-Making Technology (ADMT), a sophisticated technology utilized by businesses for making decisions grounded in data processing and AI models, is currently under regulatory scrutiny by the California Privacy Protection Agency (CPPA). As of November 27, 2023, the CPPA is planning to introduce regulations that will empower California residents with the right to opt-out of having their data used for ADMT purposes. These regulations, however, will include specific exemptions for scenarios involving security, fraud prevention, safety, or when the consumer requests a particular good or service. The CPPA's proposed measures aim to balance the protection of individual privacy rights with the practical necessities of using ADMT in various essential sectors.

name: VINHCENT LE
description: Vinhcent Le is a member of the CPPA's board and the New Rules Subcommittee, which drafted the proposed regulations for ADMT. He commented on the draft regulations, emphasizing California's lead in supporting privacy-protective innovation in emerging technologies. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: CALIFORNIA PRIVACY PROTECTION AGENCY (CPPA)
description: The California Privacy Protection Agency (CPPA) is a government agency that is proposing new rules for automated decision-making technologies (ADMT) and profiling of consumers. The proposed rules aim to address significant effects concerning consumers, such as employment opportunities, and the processing of personal information in various contexts. The CPPA is also considering whether the rules should apply to profiling for behavioral advertising, profiling children under the age of 16, and the use of personal information to train ADMT. The draft proposal marks the start of the CPPA's rulemaking process, which will include a public consultation component. The timeline for the rulemaking process will be discussed at the upcoming board meeting on December 8, 2023. The final regulation could potentially be finalized in the second half of next year, with a grace period for compliance, making 2025 the earliest for the law to be up and running. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: AUTOMATED DECISION-MAKING TECHNOLOGIES (ADMT)
description: Automated decision-making technologies (ADMT) are systems, software, or processes that use machine learning, statistics, data processing, or artificial intelligence to process personal information and make or execute decisions or facilitate human decision-making. The CPPA's proposed definition for ADMT includes profiling, which is defined as any form of automated processing of personal information to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to a natural person and to analyze or predict aspects concerning that natural person's performance at work, economic situation, health, personal preferences, interests, reliability, behavior, location, or movements. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-27]

name: SORCERER FIREWALL BUILD
description: The Sorcerer Firewall Build in Diablo 4 is a strategic approach tailored for the Sorcerer class, designed to maximize damage output in the endgame scenario. This build centers around the potent use of the Firewall skill, a devastating area of effect ability that unleashes a wall of flames to incinerate foes. To complement the core skill, the strategy recommends a suite of additional abilities and enhancements. Fire Bolt, a quick and versatile spell, is included for single-target damage, while Inferno adds a powerful burst of flame to the mix, ensuring no enemy escapes the fiery onslaught. Teleport is essential for mobility, allowing the Sorcerer to reposition swiftly amidst the chaos of battle. Ice Armor and Flame Shield provide defensive capabilities, with Ice Armor offering a protective layer of frost to mitigate incoming damage, and Flame Shield creating a barrier of fire that not only shields but also deals damage to nearby enemies. The build is further enhanced by Legendary Powers and Unique items, as suggested by Polygon on 2023-10-18, although specific details on these enhancements are not provided. Overall, the Sorcerer Firewall Build is a well-rounded strategy that balances offensive firepower with defensive resilience, making it a formidable choice for players looking to dominate in Diablo 4's challenging endgame content.

name: SIMPLY HOMES
description: Simply Homes, a Portland, Maine-based startup, is dedicated to addressing the affordable housing crisis through innovative means. The company specializes in acquiring single-family homes located in blighted neighborhoods, utilizing AI technology to manage and interpret data for strategic acquisitions in the housing market. Once purchased, these properties undergo renovation to rejuvenate aging housing stock. Simply Homes then rents out the renovated homes to very low-income families, the elderly, and the disabled, or Section-8 voucher holders, ensuring accessibility to those most affected by the housing affordability crisis. As of December 7, 2023, Simply Homes has secured $22 million in funding to further expand and enhance its efforts in providing affordable housing solutions.

Known for their strategic gameplay, the Commanders implement zone coverage at a lower rate than average, showcasing a defensive strength that ranks them in the top-five for yards after catch (YAC) per reception. name: CURTIS SAMUEL
description: Curtis Samuel, a talented football player, serves as a wide receiver for the Commanders. Recently, he showcased his skills by scoring a touchdown in a strategic play where McLaurin acted as a decoy. However, Samuel's performance has been marred by health concerns; he was clearly not at his best in the previous week's game. Despite a lingering toe injury sustained during Week 8's match against the Eagles, which has persisted since then, Samuel was expected to play on Sunday against the Seahawks. Prior to his injury, he had been performing well, solidifying his position as a valuable player in the flex territory. This information was reported by Sporting News on November 11, 2023.

name: TERRY MCLAURIN
description: Terry McLaurin, a standout wide receiver for the Washington Commanders, is anticipated to be a key player in the team's offensive strategy. His exceptional skills and performance have garnered significant attention, making him a primary focus for opposing defenses. In the upcoming game against the Atlanta Falcons, McLaurin's performance data and projections suggest he will continue to be a dominant force on the field, posing a significant challenge for the Falcons' defense. However, the summary does not include any specific performance metrics or projections as they were not detailed in the provided descriptions. Nonetheless, it is clear that McLaurin's abilities are crucial for the Commanders and will be closely monitored by their opponents.

name: MARIO
description: "MARIO" is a widely recognized and beloved video game series developed by Nintendo. The franchise centers around the adventures of its titular character, Mario, a plumber who embarks on heroic quests in the 2D platformer genre. Mario's missions often involve rescuing Princess Peach, a recurring character in the series. The MARIO series boasts a diverse collection of games, including Super Mario Bros., Super Mario World, and New Super Mario Bros., each offering unique challenges and gameplay experiences. As of 2023, MARIO continues to captivate audiences with its engaging narratives and iconic characters, solidifying its status as a cornerstone in the gaming industry.

name: WONDER SEEDS
description: "Wonder Seeds, a unique game mechanic introduced in Super Mario Bros. Wonder, significantly alter the environment and gameplay dynamics. When activated, these seeds cause levels to undergo dramatic transformations, collapsing and contorting the surroundings in ways that break the traditional laws of the Mario game universe. This innovative feature adds an extra layer of challenge and wonder, enhancing the gaming experience by introducing unexpected twists and turns that players must navigate. As a result, Wonder Seeds play a crucial role in shaping the gameplay and environment in Super Mario Bros. Wonder, making the game more engaging and unpredictable."

name: PRINCE FLORIAN
description: Prince Florian is a royal bug character in Super Mario Bros. Wonder who joins the player on their journey, providing conversation and tips. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: BADGE SYSTEM
description: The badge system in Super Mario Bros. Wonder allows players to select special abilities ranging from helpful to playful to silly. Each unlockable upgrade or special move is assigned to a badge that can be found or purchased. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: SAFETY BOUNCE BADGE
description: The Safety Bounce badge in Super Mario Bros. Wonder allows the player to bounce back from falling into an abyss. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: SUPER MARIO WORLD
description: Super Mario World, a 2D Mario game, was released in 1990 and is often regarded by fans and gaming enthusiasts as the last "true new Mario game" before the potential release of Super Mario Bros. Wonder. This classic title, developed and published by Nintendo, marked a significant milestone in the Super Mario series, introducing innovative gameplay mechanics and level designs that set a high standard for future Mario games. Speculations have been circulating that Super Mario Bros. Wonder could be the first "true new Mario game" since Super Mario World, indicating a potential shift or evolution in the series that fans have been eagerly anticipating. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: SUPER MARIO 64
description: Super Mario 64 is a 3D Mario game that became the standard for Nintendo's experimentation with new gameplay elements such as magical hats, water guns, and galactic travel. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: MARIO MULTIPLAYER
description: Mario multiplayer is a game mode in Super Mario Bros. Wonder that allows up to four players to play together, featuring characters like Mario, Peach, Toad, Nabbit, and Yoshi. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: CRITTERS
description: Critters are characters in Super Mario Bros. Wonder that are perfect for players who prefer a little extra help. Nabbit and Yoshi are mentioned as examples, with Yoshi having a tongue attack and floaty jump. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: WII U
description: Wii U is a previous video game console by Nintendo. The text mentions that to survive after the Wii U, Nintendo had to bring together its console and handheld designers to create something new. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: WONDER
description: Wonder is a new video game for the Nintendo Switch that combines traditional elements with new innovations, described as being similar yet distinct from previous Mario games. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: SUPER MARIO BROS
description: Super Mario Bros is a popular video game series by Nintendo, to which Wonder is related as a new installment. [Polygon, 2023-10-18]

name: GIRLS TRIP
description: Girls Trip is a movie that the Girls Trip star, presumably Jada Pinkett Smith, has been associated with. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-19]

name: FICCI-IBA SURVEY
description: The FICCI-IBA survey is a survey carried out for the period January to June 2023, with 24 banks including public sector, private sector, and foreign banks participating. These banks represent about 79% of the banking industry, as classified by asset size [Zee Business, 2023-10-14]

name: INDIAN ECONOMY
description: The Indian economy posted an impressive 7.2% growth in the financial year ended March 2023 and 7.8% in the first quarter of the current fiscal year. Credit growth also continued to rise, signaling robust demand conditions in the Indian economy, as well as banks' improved appetite towards retail borrowers [Zee Business, 2023-10-14]

name: BANKING INDUSTRY
description: The banking industry, as represented by 24 banks in the FICCI-IBA survey, has seen a turnaround in health, marked by healthier bank balance sheets and a gross NPA ratio at a decade low [Zee Business, 2023-10-14]

name: SKYWATCHERS
description: Skywatchers are people worldwide who observe and capture images of celestial phenomena, such as the recent aurora light show triggered by a geomagnetic storm [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: AURORA LIGHT SHOW
description: A magnificent aurora light show was observed over the weekend, with northern lights visible as far south as Greece and Turkey, triggered by a strong geomagnetic storm [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: NATIONAL OCEANIC AND ATMOSPHERIC ADMINISTRATION (NOAA)
description: The U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) assesses the severity of space weather events using a 5-grade scale, and reported a strong G3 geomagnetic storm on Nov. 5 at 12:40 p.m. EST [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: GEOMAGNETIC STORM
description: A strong geomagnetic storm, peaking at a G3 level on the NOAA scale, occurred on Nov. 5, 2023, and was caused by solar material from two coronal mass ejections (CMEs) that hit Earth on Nov. 4 and Nov. 5 [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: CORONAL MASS EJECTIONS (CME)
description: Coronal mass ejections (CMEs) are large expulsions of plasma and magnetic fields from the sun's atmosphere that can cause geomagnetic storms when they collide with Earth [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: DEBBY THORNE
description: Debby Thorne is a skywatcher who captured a vibrant pink aurora display from Cullen on the Moray Firth in Scotland using an iPhone 14 Pro in night mode on Nov. 5 [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: IPHONE 14 PRO
description: An iPhone 14 Pro is a smartphone model that includes a night mode feature for capturing images in low light conditions, used by Debby Thorne to photograph the aurora [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE
description: The National Weather Service is a government agency where Angel Enriquez was working when he was alerted to the aurora light show and took photos [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: STEVE
description: STEVE is a mysterious phenomenon in the sky, characterized by a proton arc, that was observed and photographed by Steven Lomas and Martin McKenna during a geomagnetic storm. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: DUNSTANBURGH CASTLE
description: Dunstanburgh Castle is a location in Northumberland, UK, where Steven Lomas managed to photograph the STEVE phenomenon and vibrant auroras. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: STEVEN LOMAS
description: Steven Lomas is a photographer who managed to capture images of the STEVE phenomenon and auroras over Dunstanburgh Castle in Northumberland, UK. He has been photographing the aurora for 8 years. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: MARTIN MCKENNA<||>NIGHTSKYHUNTER
description: Martin McKenna, also known as Nightskyhunter, is a photographer who observed and captured images of the STEVE phenomenon during a geomagnetic storm. He has been observing aurora since 1998 with 180 displays. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: SPACEWEATHER.COM
description: Spaceweather.com is a website that provides information about space weather, including geomagnetic storms and their effects on Earth. [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-11-09]

name: DELTA SKYMILES® GOLD BUSINESS AMERICAN EXPRESS CARD
description: The Delta SkyMiles® Gold Business American Express Card is a credit card designed for small business owners who frequently fly with Delta. It offers a welcome bonus of up to 75,000 miles, free checked bags, priority boarding, and a $0 intro annual fee for the first year (then $99) [Fortune, 2023-12-12]

name: DELTA
description: Delta, a prominent airline in the aviation industry, extends a range of exclusive benefits to cardholders of the Delta SkyMiles® Gold Business American Express Card. These perks significantly enhance the travel experience for business travelers, encompassing complimentary checked bags, priority boarding privileges, flight credits, discounts on in-flight purchases, and comprehensive insurance coverage for baggage and car rentals. By leveraging these advantages, Delta aims to provide a seamless and rewarding flying experience to its loyal customers, particularly those who are cardholders of the Delta SkyMiles Gold Business Card.

name: AMERICAN EXPRESS
description: American Express, a prominent financial institution, offers a diverse range of credit cards tailored to meet the needs of various customers. Among these offerings are the Delta SkyMiles® Gold Business American Express Card and the Amex Cash Magnet Card. The Delta SkyMiles® Gold Business American Express Card, highlighted in a Fortune article dated 2023-12-12, is designed for business travelers, providing them with exclusive benefits and rewards, particularly when flying with Delta Airlines. The Amex Cash Magnet Card, mentioned in another Fortune piece from 2023-11-03, is geared towards individuals seeking cashback rewards on their purchases. To enhance the application process, American Express provides a card pre-qualification tool, enabling potential applicants to assess their chances of approval without any impact on their credit score. This feature, combined with the institution's commitment to offering valuable credit card options, positions American Express as a customer-centric financial service provider.

name: SMALL BUSINESS OWNERS
description: Small business owners are the target audience for the Delta SkyMiles® Gold Business American Express Card, who can benefit from the card's rewards and perks [Fortune, 2023-12-12]

name: DELTA SKYMILES GOLD BUSINESS CARD
description: The Delta SkyMiles Gold Business Card offers various perks for frequent Delta flyers, including free checked bags, priority boarding, flight credits, discounts on in-flight purchases, and insurance coverage for baggage and car rentals. Cardholders must use their SkyMiles number when booking Delta flights to receive priority boarding and must make eligible purchases totaling $10,000 or more in a year to receive a $100 Delta eCredit. The card also provides 20% back as a statement credit on eligible pre-purchased meals, in-flight food purchases, alcoholic beverages, and audio headsets on Delta flights. Baggage insurance and car rental loss and damage insurance are also included, with the latter requiring the cardholder to book the rental with the card and decline the collision damage waiver at the agency. [Fortune, 2023-12-12]

name: CHASE INK BUSINESS PREFERRED® CREDIT CARD
description: The Chase Ink Business Preferred® Credit Card is a financial tool designed for business owners, featuring an annual fee of $95. This card stands out with a substantial welcome bonus, offering 100,000 points to new customers who spend $8,000 within the first three months of opening the account. The rewards structure is particularly generous, providing 3x points per $1 spent, up to a combined total of $150,000, on essential business expenses such as shipping, internet, cable, phone services, and advertising on social media platforms and search engines. This makes it a more lucrative option compared to the Delta SkyMiles Gold Business Card. Additionally, the Ultimate Rewards points earned can be transferred on a 1:1 basis to partners like Virgin Atlantic or Flying Blue, enabling cardholders to book flights on Delta, thus enhancing the value and flexibility of the rewards program. [Fortune, 2023-12-12]

name: DON MCLEAN
description:
Don McLean, an iconic artist and musician, has made significant contributions to the music industry, selling over 50 million albums worldwide. He is best known for his hit song "American Pie" and continues to captivate audiences with his music. In December 2023, McLean was inducted into the Music City Walk of Fame by the Nashville Convention & Visitors Corp., recognizing his efforts in preserving Nashville's musical heritage and his global impact through song. This accolade adds to his already impressive list of honors, including a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame, induction into the Musicians Hall of Fame in 2022, and a star on the Las Vegas Walk of Fame.

McLean's career is not only marked by his chart-topping hits but also by his ability to convey the emotional impact of music. He recently released a new album titled "Christmas Memories: Remixed & Remastered," featuring classic Christmas tunes. In an exclusive interview with Fox News Digital, McLean shared a personal story about his mother's favorite song, "Silent Night," which he used to sing for her during the holiday season. The refreshed and upgraded songs on the album, such as "Winter Wonderland," felt dynamic to him, leading to the decision to release the album this holiday season.

Looking ahead, McLean is set to release another album, "American Boys," in February 2024, and is planning to tour again in the U.S. and possibly the Far East. Additionally, he is working on a children's book based on his song "Vincent," further showcasing his versatility as an artist. McLean's career has been the subject of a Paramount+ documentary titled "The Day The Music Died," highlighting his enduring influence in the music world.

name: CHRISTMAS MEMORIES: REMIXED & REMASTERED
description: "Christmas Memories: Remixed & Remastered" is a new album by Don McLean featuring his take on classic Christmas songs and beloved holiday standards. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: WINTER WONDERLAND
description: "Winter Wonderland" is a classic Christmas song that Don McLean and his band re-recorded and remixed for his new album "Christmas Memories: Remixed & Remastered." [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: AMERICAN BOYS
description: "American Boys" is an upcoming album by the renowned artist Don McLean, anticipated to be released in February 2024. This new addition to McLean's discography was announced by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 17, 2023. It is highlighted as another album by McLean, suggesting it follows a series of recent musical works by the artist. The album, titled "American Boys," promises to deliver the distinctive style and depth that McLean's fans have come to expect, making it a noteworthy release in the music scene.

name: JIM FERGUSON
description: Jim Ferguson is the bass player who is featured on the new version of "Winter Wonderland" on Don McLean's album "Christmas Memories: Remixed & Remastered." [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: YOUN SUK YEOL
description: Yoon Suk Yeol, the president of South Korea, made a memorable impression during a state dinner held by the Biden White House on April 26, 2023, by singing "American Pie" to the U.S. president. This event was reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 17, 2023, highlighting the unique and perhaps unexpected musical moment that occurred between the leaders of the two nations during their diplomatic meeting in the White House this year.

name: AMERICAN PIE
description: "American Pie" is an iconic 8 1/2-minute folk-rock ballad by Don McLean, which has been celebrated for over 50 years since its release. The song has held a significant place in music history, having once set the record for the longest No. 1 song on the Billboard Hot 100 for nearly half a century. Its cultural impact is further recognized by its addition to the Library of Congress National Recording Registry in 2017. "American Pie" has also been widely covered by notable artists such as Madonna and Garth Brooks, showcasing its enduring appeal and influence in the music industry.

name: VINCENT
description: "Vincent" is a song by Don McLean, a tribute to Vincent van Gogh, which was the second single off his "American Pie" album and was a hit in the U.S. and the U.K., reaching No. 1 on the singles chart in England [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: BILLBOARD
description: Billboard is an organization that publishes music charts, noting that "American Pie" hit No. 1 on the Billboard chart on Jan. 15, 1972, and that Don McLean commented on the record for longest No. 1 song being broken by Taylor Swift in Nov. 2021 [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: JACK NICHOLSON
description: Jack Nicholson, a renowned actor, is recognized for his insightful perspectives beyond his acting career. According to Don McLean, as shared in a FOX News - Lifestyle article dated 2023-12-17, Nicholson is a smart man, evidenced by his profound reflections on the emotional impact of music. In the same article, Nicholson also voiced his thoughts on a potential shift in the American public's preferences, suggesting that they might no longer seek out experiences that deeply move them emotionally. These descriptions paint a picture of Nicholson as a multifaceted individual with a keen understanding of both the arts and the evolving tastes of the audience.

name: NASHVILLE CONVENTION & VISITORS CORP.
description: The Nashville Convention & Visitors Corp., a prominent organization dedicated to the promotion and preservation of Nashville's rich musical legacy, recently inducted Don McLean into the esteemed Music City Walk of Fame. This recognition underscores McLean's substantial contributions to the global music scene and his unwavering commitment to safeguarding the unique musical heritage of Nashville. The induction ceremony, reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 17, 2023, highlights the Corp's ongoing efforts to honor individuals who have made a significant impact on the city's music culture and have shared its melodies with the world.

name: MUSIC CITY WALK OF FAME
description: The Music City Walk of Fame, an esteemed honor initiated by the Nashville Convention & Visitors Corp, serves to acknowledge and celebrate artists who have made substantial contributions to the preservation of Nashville's rich musical heritage and have enriched the world with their songs. This recognition was notably extended to Don McLean, a significant figure in the music industry, for his remarkable work in keeping Nashville's musical legacy alive and contributing to global music culture. The Music City Walk of Fame stands as a testament to the enduring impact of these artists on the music scene and their role in shaping the cultural identity of Nashville.

name: CONNIE VALENS
description: Connie Valens, the sister of the late Ritchie Valens, played a significant role in the music industry by inducting Don McLean into the Music City Walk of Fame, as reported by FOX News - Lifestyle on December 17, 2023. Ritchie Valens, a renowned musician, tragically passed away, and his legacy was immortalized in Don McLean's iconic song "American Pie." In recognition of the profound impact both her brother and McLean have had on music history, Connie Valens honored McLean with the induction, further solidifying the connection between the two artists.

name: RITCHIE VALENS
description: Ritchie Valens, a renowned artist in the music industry, tragically passed away, an event that was forever etched in the annals of music history by Don McLean's iconic song "American Pie." McLean's heartfelt tribute, released in 1971, paid homage to Valens and the significant impact he had on the music scene during his lifetime. Despite his untimely demise, Valens' legacy continues to inspire and influence musicians and fans alike, as evidenced by the repeated references in the FOX News - Lifestyle articles dated 2023-12-17. His story serves as a poignant reminder of the enduring power of music and the artists who shape it.

name: LIBRARY OF CONGRESS NATIONAL RECORDING REGISTRY
description: The Library of Congress National Recording Registry is an organization that added Don McLean's song "American Pie" to its registry in 2017. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-17]

name: PARAMOUNT+
description: PARAMOUNT+, a versatile streaming service, not only offers sports enthusiasts the opportunity to watch exciting matches like the Jamaica vs Canada game broadcasted in the USA as reported by Sporting News on 2023-11-17, but also caters to music lovers with its documentary production titled "The Day The Music Died," a deep dive into the life of Don McLean, as featured by FOX News - Lifestyle on 2023-12-17. This service demonstrates its commitment to providing a diverse range of content to engage various interests within its community.

name: COLORADO
description: Colorado, a college football team, faced a significant challenge in their Week 6 game against Arizona State on October 7, 2023, as they had allowed the most sacks in FBS up to that point, with a total of 30 sacks conceded [Sporting News, 2023-10-07]. Despite this, Colorado managed to secure a 27-24 victory over Arizona State on October 8, 2023, marking their first Pac-12 win of the season and breaking an eight-game conference losing streak [Sporting News, 2023-10-07]. This win brought their season record to 4-2. It's worth noting that there is a discrepancy in the dates provided for the game, with one source stating the game was on October 7, 2023, and another specifying October 8, 2023. For the purpose of this summary, the date of the game is considered to be October 8, 2023, as that is the date mentioned in the context of the game's outcome.

Among the titles featured on the platform are beloved classics such as "JoJo's Bizarre Adventure," alongside contemporary successes including "Jujutsu Kaisen," "Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba," and "Spy x Family." name: ROKU STREAMBAR PRO
description: The Roku Streambar Pro is a versatile and highly recommended product that seamlessly integrates a streaming device with a soundbar. This innovative device, introduced in the market as of December 13, 2023, by Polygon, offers users an enhanced entertainment experience with its superior sound quality and easy content accessibility. It features an HDMI connection, making it simple to set up and use with various devices. Moreover, the Roku Streambar Pro supports 4K HDR, ensuring that movies and TV shows are viewed in the highest possible resolution and color accuracy, thus delivering an optimal viewing experience.

name: HDR OPTIMIZER

name: VIZIO 5.1.2 SOUNDBAR WITH DOLBY ATMOS
