name: COUCHCONSOLE
description: The CouchConsole is an organizational caddy designed to keep controllers and snacks safe and accessible on the couch, with a modular design and a self-balancing cup holder to prevent spills [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: NETGEAR POWERLINE 2000
description: The Netgear Powerline 2000 is a networking device that creates a power plug-based connection between a router and home theater devices, using the home's electrical lines to improve internet speed and stability [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: GOVEE ENVISUAL TV BACKLIGHT KIT
description: The Govee Envisual TV Backlight Kit is a technologically advanced lighting system designed to elevate the viewing experience by creating a captivating ambiance around the television. This innovative product features a mountable camera that diligently tracks the visuals on the TV screen, subsequently projecting a harmonious light show behind the TV, which perfectly matches the on-screen colors and movements. This dynamic lighting effect adds an extra layer of drama and atmosphere to nightly viewings, making movies, games, and shows more immersive and enjoyable. The Govee Envisual TV Backlight Kit is not only easy to install but also convenient to control, as it can be managed through the Govee Home app or voice commands, thanks to its compatibility with popular smart home assistants like Alexa and Google Assistant. This integration of technology and entertainment ensures that users can customize and control the lighting to suit their preferences, enhancing the overall experience of watching TV.

name: POWERLINE ADAPTERS
description: Powerline adapters are devices that feature an ethernet port, allowing users to use their home’s electrical lines as an internet pathway. They can be used to create a power plug-based tether between a router and devices to mitigate connectivity issues. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: ETHERNET CABLES
description: Ethernet cables are used to connect the powerline adapters to the router and the devices, enabling a hard-wired internet connection. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: GOVEE HOME APP
description: The Govee Home app is a software application that allows users to manage the LED lights of the Govee Envisual TV backlight kit, providing control over the light show projected behind the TV. [Polygon, 2023-12-13]

name: GOOGLE ASSISTANT
description: Google Assistant, a sophisticated voice command technology developed by Google, serves as a seamless integration partner for various smart home devices. It enables users to interact with their technology using natural language voice commands, enhancing the convenience and accessibility of managing smart devices. As of 2023, Google Assistant is compatible with the Govee Light Strip and Monster's digital frame, as mentioned by Wired on 2023-10-10. Additionally, Polygon reported on 2023-12-13 that Google Assistant supports the Govee Envisual TV backlight kit, allowing users to effortlessly trigger LED lights around their TV with voice commands. This versatility in compatibility highlights Google Assistant's ability to cater to a diverse range of smart home needs, making it a valuable tool for tech-savvy individuals looking to enhance their entertainment and lighting experiences.

name: UTSA ROADRUNNERS
description: The UTSA Roadrunners are a sports team that ranks 37th and 39th in the nation in total yards per game and third down conversion rate, respectively. They have a 5-6-1 ATS record and are 4-7-1 to the OVER. The team will be without several key players, including Trey Moore, Syrus Dumas, Xavier Spencer, and Kyle Eaves, who have opted out of the Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl due to being in the transfer portal [Sporting News, 2023-12-18]

name: MARSHALL THUNDERING HERD
description: The Marshall Thundering Herd is a sports team that ranks 93rd in scoring and 89th in yards per game. They have a 4-8 ATS record and are 6-6 on the O/U board. The team will be without several key players, including Cam Fancher, Chase Harrison, Brandon McElroy, Caleb Coombs, and others, who have opted out of the Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl due to being in the transfer portal [Sporting News, 2023-12-18]

name: SCOOTER'S COFFEE FRISCO BOWL
description: The Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl is a sports event where the UTSA Roadrunners and the Marshall Thundering Herd are scheduled to play. Several players from both teams have opted out of the game due to being in the transfer portal [Sporting News, 2023-12-18]

name: TREY MOORE
description: Trey Moore is a defensive player for the UTSA Roadrunners who led the conference in sacks and is not playing in the Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl due to being in the transfer portal [Sporting News, 2023-12-18]

name: CAME FANCHER
description: Cam Fancher is a quarterback for the Marshall Thundering Herd who is not playing in the Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl due to being in the transfer portal. His absence is a significant blow to the team [Sporting News, 2023-12-18]

name: AUSTIN CINDRIC
description: Austin Cindric is a NASCAR driver who was seen driving the #2 eCascadia Ford during the qualifying for the NASCAR Cup Series Busch Light Clash at Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum on February 05, 2022 in Los Angeles, California [Photo by Sean Gardner/Getty Images]

name: RYAN BLANEY
description: Ryan Blaney, a skilled NASCAR driver, achieved a significant milestone in his career by securing his first-ever championship on November 6, 2023. Blaney masterfully navigated his Ford Mustang to victory at the Phoenix race, a testament to his exceptional driving abilities. This triumph was not only a personal achievement but also a team effort, as the guidance and calming influence of team owner Roger Penske played a crucial role in Blaney's success. Under Penske's leadership, Blaney and his team were able to maintain focus and composure, contributing to their championship win in 2023.

name: MARK RUSHBROOK
description: Mark Rushbrook is the Global Director for Ford Performance and revealed that winning the NASCAR championship has significant marketing value for Ford, as it builds credibility with fans and boosts sales of the Mustang and F-150 [Essentially Sports]

name: FORD MUSTANG
description: The Ford Mustang is a vehicle that Ryan Blaney drove to victory in the NASCAR Cup Series Championship Race on November 6, 2023, and its success on the racetrack boosts the sale of this iconic sports car [Essentially Sports]

name: FORD F-150
description: The Ford F-150, a renowned truck celebrated for its ruggedness and reliability, has established a significant and loyal fanbase among NASCAR enthusiasts. According to an insider source at Ford, as reported by Essentially Sports on November 6, 2023, the F-150 outperforms even the iconic Mustang in sales to NASCAR fans, highlighting its popularity within this community. This preference for the F-150 among NASCAR aficionados underscores the truck's robust capabilities and enduring appeal in the realm of motorsports culture.

name: BEN RHODES
description: Ben Rhodes, a skilled NASCAR driver, secured his second Truck Series championship on November 3, 2023, as reported by Essentially Sports on November 6, 2023. He triumphed in the race driving a Ford F-150, showcasing his prowess and the reliability of his Ford vehicle in the competitive world of motorsports.

name: MUSTANG
description: Mustang is a car model sold globally by Ford, and its racing success in NASCAR is used as a marketing tool to promote road cars worldwide, according to Essentially Sports on 2023-11-06

name: ROSS CHASTAIN
description: Ross Chastain, a NASCAR driver for Trackhouse Racing, had a remarkable 2023 season. He managed to equal his career-best record of two wins in a single season, securing victories in Nashville and Phoenix. Chastain's performance was consistently strong, as evidenced by his 19 top-ten finishes and ten top-5 placements throughout the year. Notably, he became the first non-championship driver to win the Championship 4 race since the implementation of the new playoff system in 2014, a testament to his exceptional skills on the track. Additionally, Chastain was involved in a highly competitive race with Ryan Blaney, further highlighting his ability to contend with top-tier drivers in the sport. These achievements and engagements were reported by Essentially Sports on 2023-12-21 and 2023-11-06, respectively.

name: ROGER PENSKE
description: Roger Penske, widely recognized by his nickname "The Captain," is a seasoned and influential figure in the NASCAR community, serving as a team owner. In a notable display of leadership and strategic acumen, Penske played a pivotal role in helping driver Ryan Blaney maintain composure during a critical championship race in 2023. This assistance was instrumental in Blaney's victory, as reported by Essentially Sports on November 6, 2023. Penske's experience and guidance have proven to be invaluable assets in the high-pressure environment of NASCAR, where split-second decisions can determine the outcome of races and championships.

name: TEAM PENSKE
description: Team Penske is a NASCAR team led by Roger Penske that won back-to-back championships in 2023, showcasing its strength in high-pressure situations

name: RICK HENDRICK
description: Rick Hendrick is a NASCAR team owner who is mentioned in comparison to Roger Penske's success with Team Penske in 2023

name: HMS DUO
description: The HMS duo refers to a pair of drivers from Hendrick Motorsports, a NASCAR team, who were not racing against Ryan Blaney in the context of the 2023 championship

name: NICK KYRGIOS
description: Nick Kyrgios is a professional tennis player who has been one of the most watched players outside the big three in the last decade, bringing more people to the sport and creating his own brand off the court. He has been feuding with Boris Becker on social media platform X, and escalated the feud by referencing Becker's criminal past related to bankruptcy charges. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: BORIS BECKER
description: Boris Becker, a six-time Grand Slam title winner and former professional tennis player, has made significant contributions to the sport. After retiring from professional tennis, Becker transitioned into coaching, currently mentoring Holger Rune as of 2023. He has been involved in a public dispute with Nick Kyrgios, addressing Kyrgios' claims about the superiority of current players and criticizing the latter for a lack of respect towards past tennis legends. Becker emphasized that players like Kyrgios owe their careers to the trail blazed by stars from his generation. Additionally, it is noted that Becker faced legal challenges, having spent eight months in prison in the previous year due to bankruptcy-related charges. Despite this, Becker remains an influential figure in the tennis community, actively engaging with current players and offering insights into the evolution of the sport.

name: AUSTRALIAN OPEN
description: The Australian Open is a tennis tournament where every match can be watched ad-free, live, and on demand with center court in 4K Ultra-HD on Stan Sport. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: STAN SPORT
description: Stan Sport is a sports streaming service that offers ad-free, live, and on-demand coverage of the Australian Open, including center court in 4K Ultra-HD. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: EUROSPORT
description: Eurosport is a sports network where Boris Becker gave an interview criticizing Nick Kyrgios. [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: NICHOLAS KYRGIOS
description: Nicholas Kyrgios is a professional tennis player who sparked a debate by claiming current players are superior to those of the 70s and 80s. He is also involved in a feud with Boris Becker. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: NOVAK DJOKOVIC
description: Novak Djokovic is a professional tennis player who, according to Jo-Wilfried Tsonga, started out trying to emulate Roger Federer and Rafael Nadal but found success when he embraced his true nature. Djokovic also spoke about his relationship with Federer and Nadal, acknowledging that they are not close friends due to their rivalry. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: JO-WILFRIED TSONGA
description: Jo-Wilfried Tsonga is a former French professional tennis player who commented on Novak Djokovic's career, stating that Djokovic's success increased when he stopped trying to be like Federer and Nadal and embraced his own identity. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: ROGER FEDERER
description: Roger Federer is a retired professional tennis player who, along with Rafael Nadal, was a role model for Novak Djokovic early in his career. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: RAFAEL NADAL
description: Rafael Nadal is a professional tennis player who, along with Roger Federer, was a role model for Novak Djokovic early in his career. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: 60 MINUTES
description: 60 Minutes is a TV show where Novak Djokovic recently spoke about his relationship with Roger Federer and Rafael Nadal. [Source: The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: JANNIK SINNER
description: Jannik Sinner is a professional tennis player who defeated an unnamed player in the Davis Cup [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: DAVIS CUP
description: The Davis Cup, an esteemed international team event in men's tennis, witnessed Australia's significant achievement as they advanced to the final round of the competition, as reported by The Age on 2023-11-24. This event, which garners attention from tennis enthusiasts worldwide, was further highlighted by The Roar | Sports Writers Blog on 2023-12-19, emphasizing its global significance and the high level of competition it entails.

name: KAROLINA PLISKOVA
description: Karolina Pliskova is a former world No 1 tennis player who feels the women's tour has lost charisma with the retirements of Serena Williams and Maria Sharapova [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: WTA
description: The Women's Tennis Association (WTA), a governing body that oversees and manages professional women's tennis, has been critiqued by Karolina Pliskova for its perceived lack of effective promotion of the game. This feedback was shared in a post on The Roar | Sports Writers Blog on 2023-12-19, highlighting concerns about the WTA's strategies in enhancing the visibility and appeal of women's tennis. Despite this criticism, the WTA continues to play a pivotal role in the administration of women's professional tennis, as acknowledged in a reference by Fortune on 2023-10-13. The organization is responsible for the organization of tournaments, the ranking of players, and the overall governance of the sport for women, aiming to provide a platform for female athletes to compete at the highest level.

name: ANDY MURRAY
description: Andy Murray is a former world No 1 tennis player who has added the doubles event with Holger Rune to his Australian Open warm-up schedule [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: BRISBANE INTERNATIONAL
description: The Brisbane International is a tennis tournament where Andy Murray has entered the singles draw [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: HOLGER RUNE
description: Holger Rune is a 20-year-old tennis player coached by Boris Becker, who will partner with Andy Murray in the doubles event at the Brisbane International [The Roar | Sports Writers Blog, 2023-12-19]

name: PARIS HILTON
description: Paris Hilton is an heiress who encouraged Britney Spears to have fun for the first time in a long time, leading to some infamous nights out with her and Lindsay Lohan [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: LINDSAY LOHAN
description: Lindsay Lohan is a person who, along with Paris Hilton, had some infamous nights out with Britney Spears [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: BRITNEY SPEARS' FATHER
description: Britney Spears' father, a man alleged to struggle with alcoholism, has been a central figure in the pop icon's life, imposing a conservatorship that legally took control of Britney's life and finances. This arrangement, which spanned 13 years, was marked by strict and often brutal standards, denying Britney her freedom and allowing her father to exercise jurisdiction over her body. In a chilling declaration of his power, he once told Britney, "I am Britney Spears now," indicating his control over her personal and professional decisions. It appears that he has financially benefited from this conservatorship, while Britney was subjected to numerous restrictions. His actions have been a source of conflict, including frequent arguments with Britney's mother, further complicating the family dynamics.

name: BRITNEY SPEARS' MOTHER
description: Lynne Spears, Britney Spears' mother, has been described in a complex light. According to The Guardian in 2023, Lynne's interactions with Britney often left the pop icon feeling less-than and restricted. Britney felt that she and her mother had to endure difficult situations, witnessing ugliness and violence, which instilled a sense of entrapment in their lives. Moreover, when Britney returned home after a night out, slightly under the influence, Lynne's reaction was one of anger, screaming at her daughter. This behavior made Britney feel as though she was forbidden from enjoying a social life, further highlighting the strained dynamics between the two.

name: CONSERVATORSHIP
description: Conservatorship, a legal concept often used to protect individuals who are unable to care for themselves, became a contentious issue in the life of Britney Spears. Imposed by her father in 2008, this arrangement stripped Britney of her freedom and autonomy for 13 years, controlling every aspect of her personal and professional life, including her diet and bodily autonomy. Britney has expressed that the conservatorship made her feel dehumanized, as if she had regressed to a child-like state, and that it robbed her of her womanhood, leaving her feeling like a robot. The arrangement was a significant source of scrutiny and controversy, with many arguing that it was an unjust restriction on Britney's personal liberties.

name: FATHER
description: Britney Spears's father was involved in her conservatorship and constantly told her she was fat, contributing to her feelings of being trapped and monitored [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: NSYNC
description: NSync is a music group that Justin Timberlake was a part of, known for their interest in hip-hop and attempts to fit in with Black artists. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: GINUWINE
description: Ginuwine is a Black artist who is mentioned in Britney Spears' memoir as an example of someone NSync tried to fit in with. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: BRITNEY SPEARS' MANAGERS
description: Britney Spears' managers are described in her memoir as working hard to maintain her image as a young-girl virgin, even into her 20s. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: ONYX HOTEL TOUR
description: The Onyx Hotel tour is an event that took place in 2004, following the public shaming by Justin Timberlake, where Britney Spears felt the need to push back against the narrative by being more sexual on stage. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: POSTNATAL DEPRESSION
description: Postnatal depression is a medical condition that Britney Spears suffered from after giving birth to her first and second child in quick succession. It left her feeling suicidal and unable to live if things didn't get better. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: PUBLIC AND PRESS SCRUTINY
description: Public and press scrutiny is a social situation that Britney Spears felt trapped in, which contributed to her sense of injustice and postnatal depression. She felt that her postpartum body and shots of her without makeup were treated as a betrayal by the public. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: TAINTED LOVE
description: "Tainted Love" is a song that influenced Britney Spears' vocal style the night before recording "Baby, One More Time." [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: MARC ALMOND
description: Marc Almond is a musician whose vocal style Britney Spears aimed to emulate by staying up late to sound as gravelly and "fried" as him. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: BLACKOUT
description: "Blackout" is a 2007 album by Britney Spears, made at the height of her public struggles. The studio was a refuge for her from the paparazzi, and the album is considered a cult favorite. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: GLORY
description: "Glory" is a 2016 album by Britney Spears. She has some later love for this album, which she writes about proudly. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: ELTON JOHN
description: Elton John is a musician who collaborated with Britney Spears in 2022. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: BRITNEY SPEARS' YOUNGER SISTER
description: Britney Spears' younger sister is characterized as a brat who was spared the pain of Britney's impoverished childhood because of Britney's success. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: LITHIUM
description: Lithium is a substance that Britney Spears was subjected to as part of her treatment under the conservatorship. [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: REHAB FACILITY
description: The rehab facility, a central point of distress in Britney Spears' life, is portrayed as a brutal environment where she was compelled to stay against her will. This facility became synonymous with her humiliating experiences under the conservatorship, leading her to feel as though she was enduring ritual torture. The Guardian, in its coverage dated 2023-10-24, highlighted the severity of the conditions and the impact they had on Britney's mental and emotional well-being, painting a vivid picture of the challenges she faced within the confines of the rehab center.

name: BRITNEY SPEARS' FAMILY
description: Britney Spears' family, including her parents, seem to benefit from her earnings while she lives under strict restrictions imposed by the conservatorship [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: POETRY
description: Britney Spears' poetry is a form of art she created, which was discarded by her family, causing her an overwhelming sense of sadness [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: NEW NOTEBOOK
description: A new notebook is an object Britney Spears resolved to start over with after her family threw away her childhood things, including her poetry [The Guardian, 2023-10-24]

name: ASTROS
description: The Astros, a prominent sports team, actively competed in the World Series 2023, engaging in a series of matches against the Rangers. Throughout the tournament, the team demonstrated a mix of successes and challenges, with outcomes fluctuating across various dates, as reported by Sporting News on both October 30 and October 31, 2023. Despite the varying results, the Astros' participation in the World Series 2023 signifies their significant standing in the realm of professional sports.

name: WORLD SERIES 2023
description: The World Series 2023, a significant milestone in the baseball calendar, showcases an array of high-stakes matches between prominent teams. This year, the event garners particular attention as it highlights the intense competition between the Rangers and the Diamondbacks, as noted by Sporting News on 2023-10-31. Additionally, the series features other compelling matchups, including a face-off between the Astros and the Rangers, as well as a game between the Diamondbacks and the Phillies, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-10-30. The World Series 2023 promises to be a thrilling spectacle, bringing together the best of baseball in a series of matches that will captivate fans and showcase the skill and determination of the participating teams.

name: TBS
description: TBS, a prominent TV channel in the realm of sports broadcasting, played a significant role in the World Series 2023. The channel aired several games of the series, specifically the highly anticipated matches between the Arizona Diamondbacks and the Philadelphia Phillies on October 23 and 24, 2023. These broadcasts were part of TBS's comprehensive coverage of the World Series, showcasing the channel's commitment to delivering top-tier sporting events to its audience. As a reliable source for sports enthusiasts, TBS ensured that fans could follow the action-packed games between the Diamondbacks and the Phillies, providing them with an immersive viewing experience throughout the series.

name: FOX
description: FOX, a prominent TV channel in the realm of sports broadcasting, played a significant role in the coverage of the World Series 2023. The channel aired several games of the series, including the highly anticipated matches between the Texas Rangers and the Houston Astros, as well as the Arizona Diamondbacks and the Philadelphia Phillies. Notably, FOX was the go-to source for the Diamondbacks vs. Rangers games, which were broadcasted on October 27, October 28, October 30, and October 31. The channel was also prepared to cover potential games on November 1, November 3, and November 4, should they have been necessary to determine the series' winner. This comprehensive coverage by FOX ensured that fans across the nation could follow the thrilling developments of the World Series 2023, as reported by Sporting News on October 30 and 31, 2023.

name: JADEN SMITH
description: Jaden Smith is the son of Will Smith and Jada Pinkett Smith, who has been praised by his mother for being a source of support and self-acceptance [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: HODA KOTB
description: Hoda Kotb is a host of Today's show, who interviewed Jada Pinkett Smith about her marriage and separation from Will Smith [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: WORTHY
description: Worthy is a memoir by Jada Pinkett Smith, where she discusses her marriage and separation from Will Smith [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: SUSAN WINTER
description: Susan Winter is a New York City-based relationship expert who highlighted the differences between separation and divorce, suggesting that Jada and Will's separation could be an LAT (Living Apart Together) partnership aimed at preserving their relationship [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: JACOB LUCAS
description: Jacob Lucas is a UK-based dating coach who acknowledged that not all separations lead to resolutions, and couples might be avoiding the inevitable breakup for the sake of comfortability [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: SHEREE ZAMPINO
description: Sheree Zampino is Will Smith's first wife, from whom he divorced in 1994. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: MTV NEWS
description: MTV News is a news organization where Will Smith first explained his stance on divorce in 2006. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: PARADE
description: Parade is a magazine where Jada Pinkett Smith explained why they didn't sign a prenuptial agreement before getting married. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: WILL AND JADA
description: Will and Jada, referring to Will Smith and Jada Pinkett Smith, are a celebrity couple who have been separated since 2016 [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: WINTER
description: WINTER, an expert in relationship dynamics, is known for discussing the various conditions that might lead couples to the decision of ending their relationship. This expertise was highlighted in an article by The Independent under the Life and Style section on October 16, 2023. WINTER provides insights that help individuals understand the complexities and challenges that can arise in partnerships, guiding them through the decision-making process when considering the future of their relationships.

name: DIVORCE
description: Divorce is a legal action that couples can take to formally end their marriage [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: SEPARATION
description: Separation is a legal or personal action where couples decide to live apart, but remain legally married [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-16]

name: KENNY AGYAPONG
description: Kenny Agyapong is a co-founder of AfroFuture, who, along with his partner, realized an opportunity to connect the community and the diaspora in Ghana, leading to the creation of AfroFuture [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: AFROFUTURE
description: AfroFuture, previously recognized as Afrochella, is a distinguished festival and platform dedicated to promoting African art, cuisine, fashion, and music to a global audience. With a primary focus on Ghana and the broader African continent, the festival provides an invaluable stage for unsigned and emerging artists to showcase their talents. Its impact extends beyond the music scene, significantly contributing to the local tourism industry; in 2022, AfroFuture was responsible for generating approximately 16% of Ghana's tourism revenue. Recognizing the festival's cultural and economic significance, the co-founders of AfroFuture were appointed as the Goodwill Ambassador of Tourism to Ghana, tasked with the mission to promote the country internationally. The festival's vision is not only to celebrate African culture but also to stimulate conversations that highlight its richness and diversity, making AfroFuture a pivotal force in the global recognition and appreciation of African artistic expressions.

name: ACCRA
description: Accra is the city in Ghana where AfroFuture was launched and where its inaugural festival was held at the Accra Polo Court on December 29, 2017 [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: AFRICAN DIASPORA
description: The African diaspora refers to people of African descent living outside of Africa, who are a significant part of AfroFuture's target audience and are encouraged to celebrate and invest in their native cultures [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: RISING STAR CHALLENGE
description: The Rising Star Challenge is an annual competition organized by AfroFuture for unsigned and emerging artists in Africa, supporting live music and providing a platform for artists to showcase their talent [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: AUDIOMACK
description: AUDIOMACK is a prominent company and technology platform in the music industry, specifically designed to empower artists by facilitating the upload of their original songs. This platform plays a crucial role in AfroFuture's "Rising Star Challenge," a competitive event that aims to spotlight and nurture emerging talents. Through Audiomack, artists gain access to a vast audience and the opportunity to showcase their musical prowess, potentially leading to significant breakthroughs in their careers. The platform's integration with AfroFuture's initiative underscores its commitment to supporting the growth and visibility of artists within the music community. [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: SONY MUSIC AFRICA
description: Sony Music Africa is a music company that offers an exclusive recording agreement to the winner of AfroFuture's "Rising Star Challenge" for a single release. The winner also receives global distribution for their new single, marketing support, free access to AfroFuture’s recording studio, and mentoring and training from industry executives and leading musicians and producers. [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: TUNECORE
description: TuneCore, a prominent company in the music industry, is dedicated to empowering self-releasing artists by offering them a comprehensive suite of technology and services. These services include distribution, publishing administration, and various promotional options, designed to help artists reach wider audiences and manage their careers more effectively. As part of Believe, TuneCore further demonstrates its commitment to the music community by supporting initiatives such as the Trailblazers podcast, which highlights the journeys and insights of trailblazing artists. In a significant partnership with AfroFuture, TuneCore co-created the "Rising Star DJ Challenge." This initiative is aimed at discovering and amplifying the next generation of African superstars, with a specific focus on finding the next breakout DJ from the continent, thereby contributing to the global recognition of African talent.

name: TRAILBLAZERS
description: Trailblazers is a podcast that supports aspiring entrepreneurs and provides advice on how to remain true to their purpose and be authentic. It is supported by TuneCore. [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: BELIEVE.MUSIC
description: Believe.Music is a company that TuneCore is a part of. It is involved in the music industry and supports artists through various services. [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-10-30]

name: MUSIC BUSINESS WORLDWIDE
description: Music Business Worldwide is a prominent media outlet and publisher dedicated to delivering comprehensive news and insightful analysis about the global music industry. On November 30, 2023, the platform featured a speech by Dennis Kooker, which delved into the transformative role of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and its implications for the music sector. Additionally, Music Business Worldwide serves as a valuable source of information on various industry players, including Trailblazers, TuneCore, Believe.Music, and AfroFuture, providing readers with up-to-date details and perspectives on these entities as of October 30, 2023. Through its coverage, Music Business Worldwide aims to help stakeholders understand the dynamics and connections within the music community, enabling them to engage more effectively and make informed decisions amidst technological advancements and industry shifts.

name: TYLER LOCKETT
description: Tyler Lockett, a 31-year-old wide receiver with 9 years of experience, is a key player for the Seattle Seahawks. Known for his potential to make significant impacts in games, Lockett has consistently been a target in the offense, receiving seven or more targets in four out of his past five games. However, his involvement in deep throws is less compared to his teammate Metcalf. Despite facing unfavorable matchups recently against teams like the Niners, Rams, and Ravens, Lockett has shown his capability for standout performances, as evidenced by his game against the Browns five weeks ago. With strategic calls for timeouts and a strong offensive and defensive lineup, the Bengals are in a commanding position to score, especially as they approach the final minutes of their games.

name: COLLEGEHUMOR
description: CollegeHumor, a media organization renowned for its comedy content, has undergone significant changes in its structure and branding. Originally part of IAC, the brand was sold to executive producer Sam Reich, ensuring the continuation of popular shows such as Dimension 20, Um, Actually, and Game Changer. In 2018, CollegeHumor launched Dropout, a subscription-based service, which has now reached its 5th anniversary. On this milestone, Dropout, which was once a part of CollegeHumor, is discontinuing the use of the CollegeHumor name, marking a new chapter in its evolution. The decision to drop the CollegeHumor name is discussed in the context of platform structures and business models, reflecting the company's strategic direction as it moves forward under the Dropout banner. This name change is a pivotal part of Dropout's anniversary announcement, signaling a shift in identity while maintaining its roots in comedy and entertainment.

name: DROP OUT
description: Dropout is a streaming service that was created by the creatives behind CollegeHumor, offering comedy and live-play Dungeons & Dragons [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: IAC
description: IAC, a significant player in the media industry, has had a notable impact on the digital entertainment landscape. Initially, IAC served as a corporate owner, providing financial backing to CH Media, the parent company of CollegeHumor. However, in January 2020, IAC ceased funding CH Media, resulting in the layoffs of almost the entire staff of CollegeHumor, as reported by Polygon on September 26, 2023. This decision marked a pivotal moment for the company, leading to a restructuring and a shift in focus. Subsequently, IAC's former subsidiary, Dropout, broke away to concentrate on unscripted and improvised content, a move that allowed Dropout to carve out a unique niche in the entertainment sector. The separation from IAC and the subsequent changes at Dropout reflect the dynamic nature of the media industry and the strategic decisions made by companies to adapt and thrive in a competitive environment.

name: SAM REICH
description: Sam Reich, a seasoned figure in the digital entertainment industry, is recognized for his role in creating content that masterfully navigates the audience through a spectrum of emotions, from a false sense of comfort to the depths of trauma. As an executive producer, Reich made a significant move by acquiring the CollegeHumor brand from IAC, a strategic decision that secured the future of popular shows such as Dimension 20. Alongside Brennan Mulligan, he is involved in the development of an anthology series, where he expresses insightful views on the paradoxical nature of digital entertainment, suggesting that while it offers vast creative opportunities, it can also confine creators within the confines of audience expectations, likening it to a form of creative 'jail'. Drawing from his diverse background, Reich brings a unique perspective to his work, having previously graced the stages of the New York Renaissance Faire as a performer, an experience that undoubtedly enriches his understanding of storytelling and audience engagement.

name: CUTE LITTLE CRITTERS
description: "Cute little critters" is a broad, fantastical storytelling genre that includes a subgenre of dark and grim stories, often featuring cute animals in horrifying situations [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: WATERSHIP DOWN
description: Watership Down is a haunting piece of adult literature that juxtaposes cute little bunnies with a story about death, displacement, and horror [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: MULLIGAN
description: Mulligan, a multifaceted individual deeply involved with Dropout, shares insights into the intricate world of content creation, highlighting the daily challenges and creative processes [Polygon, 2023-09-26]. Mulligan's expertise extends beyond the screen, as they delve into the mental mathematics of the season, emphasizing the significance of giving names and voices to characters, which in turn amplifies the audience's emotional connection to these "little critters" [Polygon, 2023-09-26]. Drawing from a rich background in the entertainment industry, Mulligan also recounts their experience as an improviser for the Orbit gum activation in Times Square, showcasing their adaptability and quick thinking. Additionally, Mulligan has served as a camera PA on Criminal Intent, further enriching their understanding of the industry's dynamics. Mulligan offers a unique internal perspective on Dropout's name change, providing a comprehensive view of the company's evolution [Polygon, 2023-09-26].

name: DAVID ATTENBOROUGH
description: David Attenborough is a renowned naturalist who, according to Sam Reich, couldn't achieve the level of emotional engagement that their content does by giving names and voices to animals [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

description: Algorithms are shaping the era of online content, defining and influencing what content is prioritized and promoted on various platforms [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: YOUTUBE SHORTS
description: YouTube Shorts is a product that, as of 2023, does not allow videos longer than a minute, contrasting with TikTok's approach [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: DROPOUT
description: Dropout, originally launched by CollegeHumor in 2018 as a subscription-based service, is celebrating its 5th anniversary by rebranding, effectively distancing itself from the CollegeHumor brand. This comedy company, now a digital platform, has successfully navigated challenges such as a corporate sale and the COVID-19 pandemic. It has shifted its focus from scripted content to unscripted, improvised shows after breaking away from IAC, allowing for a unique exploration of storytelling beyond the UCB sketch structure. Many creators involved with Dropout have had training at UCB, contributing to the platform's serendipitous and magical success in capturing improv on film. Unlike traditional media projects, Dropout's anthology series, created by Brennan Mulligan and Sam Reich, remains safe from cancellation as long as it maintains popularity. The platform has found its niche by offering something special to a smaller, dedicated audience rather than aiming for broad, viral appeal. With a healthy sense of humor about the brand change, Dropout is celebrating the amazing work of everyone who contributes to the platform, acknowledging the transformation and growth over the years.

name: PATREON
description: Patreon is a subscription-based platform that creators can use to monetize their content [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: HOLLYWOOD
description: Hollywood is a traditional entertainment industry that creators can leverage their online presence to enter [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: REICH
description:
Reich, a multifaceted individual deeply connected to the Dropout community, is recognized for their strategic oversight skills and ability to perceive the broader landscape of the group's endeavors. Despite their significant contributions, Reich grapples with impostor syndrome, a common feeling among high-achievers who doubt their accomplishments and fear being exposed as a fraud. Reich holds a deep appreciation for the historical significance of Dropout in the realm of improv performance, acknowledging its pivotal role in the evolution of the art form.

Prior to their involvement with Dropout, Reich was well-versed in the improvisational talents of Mulligan, recognizing him not only as a skilled improviser but also as a comedic performer and a game master (GM). This admiration stems from Reich's own background in improv, having undergone rigorous training at the Upright Citizens Brigade (UCB), a renowned institution for comedy and improvisation.

In a clarification regarding potential endorsements, Reich explicitly states that mentioning Chompsky's and Cool Ranch Doritos does not imply any form of support or recommendation. This distinction highlights Reich's careful consideration of personal associations and the importance of transparency within the community.

Reich's experiences extend beyond the stage and screen of improv and comedy. They recount watching themselves perform at the New York Renaissance Faire, an event that showcases the talents of fierce and dedicated performers. This self-reflection is complemented by Reich's background work on "Third Watch" and their role as a camera production assistant (PA) on "Criminal Intent," both popular TV shows. These experiences contribute to Reich's comprehensive understanding of the entertainment industry and their ability to contribute meaningfully to the Dropout community.

name: BRENNAN MULLIGAN
description:
Brennan Mulligan, a General Manager and a world-class improviser and comedic performer, is deeply involved with the Dropout platform, an online space for original comedy content. Having honed his skills through UCB (Upright Citizens Brigade) training, Mulligan has recently shot an episode for a new improv-based show on Dropout, which has been highly praised by Reich, indicating the quality and impact of his performance. This show is among the many creative endeavors Mulligan has undertaken, showcasing his versatility and commitment to the art of improvisation.

Additionally, Mulligan is associated with CollegeHumor, where he plays a significant role in the creation of content. He has a particular interest in a show called Very Important People, which is a reboot of a previous CollegeHumor series. This highlights his connection to the evolution of comedy content and his role in reviving popular formats for new audiences.

Mulligan also shares insights into the challenges and opportunities presented by digital versus traditional entertainment. He acknowledges the digital space's demand for constant content creation, expressing mixed feelings about this aspect of the industry. This perspective reveals his thoughtful approach to navigating the entertainment landscape and adapting to its changing dynamics. Furthermore, Mulligan's mention of past struggles as an entertainer suggests a resilience and determination that have contributed to his success in the field.

name: ADAM CONOVER
description: Adam Conover is a friend of Sam Reich who remains uncertain about the advantages of digital entertainment over traditional media. He suggests that digital platforms can trap creators in a cycle of meeting audience expectations, which can be restrictive compared to the finite nature of traditional media projects. [Polygon, 2023-09-26]

name: NEW YORK RENAISSANCE FAIRE
description: The New York Renaissance Faire is a celebrated event that Sam Reich, a notable figure, has been associated with in the past, both as an attendee and a performer. This faire is renowned for its assemblage of talented and fierce performers, who not only display their skills but also engage the audience with their comedic improvisation, creating an immersive and entertaining experience. The event, held annually, attracts a diverse community of enthusiasts and participants, making it a vibrant hub for those interested in the Renaissance period and its cultural expressions. Reich's attendance and participation in the 2023 New York Renaissance Faire, as reported by Polygon on September 26, 2023, highlights the event's appeal to a wide range of individuals, including those within the technology and entertainment sectors.

Firstly, Epic Games, a renowned video game developer, has announced plans to bring claims against Google under the Sherman Act, aiming to challenge alleged anticompetitive practices. Additionally, Helena World Chronicle, LLC, a media company, has invoked the Sherman Act to seek class-wide monetary and injunctive relief against Google, as reported by TechCrunch on December 15, 2023. These actions underscore the law's role in addressing concerns over market dominance and fair competition in the technology sector.

name: CLAYTON ACT

name: ROBIN WILLIAMS
description:
Robin Williams, a renowned comedian and actor, embarked on his career in the realm of stand-up comedy during the 1970s. He rose to prominence after notable appearances in "Happy Days" and starring roles in "Mork and Mindy" and "Popeye." Throughout his career, Williams grappled with drug addiction, particularly cocaine, a struggle that was brought to light in Vice's "The Dark Side of Comedy" documentary series. Despite the severity of his addiction, which was described as transforming him into a "monster" under the influence of drugs, he managed to incorporate references to his drug use into his stand-up routines, creating a mix of humor and concern among his audience.

Following the tragic death of John Belushi in 1982 and the birth of his first son in 1983, Williams made a life-changing decision to quit cocaine "cold turkey." This pivotal decision marked a new chapter in his life, allowing his career to flourish further. He went on to star in a series of successful films, including "Mrs. Doubtfire," "Good Will Hunting," and "Night at the Museum," showcasing his versatility and talent.

However, unbeknownst to Williams, he was battling Lewy body dementia in the years leading up to his death in 2014. The condition was only diagnosed posthumously following an autopsy. The last encounter Steven Pearl had with Williams was marked by his significant weight loss and a lack of recognition towards Pearl's wife, hardly uttering a word. Despite the challenges he faced, the autopsy revealed no presence of illegal drugs or alcohol in his system at the time of his death, indicating that his tragic end was not a result of substance abuse but rather the devastating effects of his undiagnosed neurological disorder.

name: VICE

description: "Mork and Mindy" is a TV series starring Robin Williams as Mork, which was a spin-off from his appearance in "Happy Days" [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-19]

description: John Belushi was a comedian and actor who died in 1982 from a drug overdose. His death had a significant impact on Robin Williams, who was close to Belushi, and it served as a wake-up call for Williams to address his own drug addiction. [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-19]

name: STANLEY WILSON
description: Stanley Wilson is a longtime friend of Robin Williams. He provided insight into Williams' decision to quit cocaine, emphasizing that Williams recognized the importance of his mind, imagination, and wit for his career and did not want to damage them further. [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-19]

name: HOWIE MANDEL
description: Howie Mandel is a comedian who recalled Robin Williams' stand-up routines that often included jokes about cocaine and drug use. Mandel noted that despite the humor, Williams was indeed struggling with a serious addiction. [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-19]

name: LEWY BODY DEMENTIA
description: Lewy body dementia, posthumously diagnosed in the renowned actor Robin Williams, is a significant neurological disorder recognized as the second most prevalent type of dementia, trailing only Alzheimer's disease. This condition impacts crucial brain regions associated with cognitive functions, memory, and motor skills, as detailed by both FOX News - Entertainment and the Mayo Clinic on 2023-10-19. The disorder's influence on these critical areas can lead to a complex set of symptoms, affecting not only memory and thinking but also movement, thereby significantly impacting the quality of life for those afflicted.

name: STEVEN PEARL
description: Steven Pearl is a comedian and friend of Robin Williams. He recounted his last encounter with Williams, noting that Williams was thin and didn't recognize his wife [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-19]

name: DAYLIGHT SAVING TIME (DST)
description: Daylight Saving Time (DST), a practice initially introduced in the UK in 1916, involves setting the clock forward during summer months and backward in winter to maximize the use of daylight. The concept was pioneered to encourage the populace to spend more time outdoors, capitalizing on the natural light available. The next scheduled clock change for DST is on Sunday, 29 October 2023, which will grant an additional hour of sleep and signal the onset of shorter days. Despite the European Parliament's 2019 decision to phase out DST, the plans to abolish this practice have been delayed, leaving the tradition intact for the time being. As of 2023, the UK and other European countries continue to observe DST, adjusting their clocks in accordance with the seasonal changes.

name: PROFESSOR AOIFE FOLEY
description: Professor Aoife Foley from Queen’s University Belfast is an expert in clean energy research who estimates that abolishing DST could save households more than £400 per year from their electricity bill and reduce demand on the National Grid [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-24]

name: QUEEN’S UNIVERSITY BELFAST
description: Queen’s University Belfast is an educational institution where Professor Aoife Foley conducts research on clean energy [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-24]

name: NATIONAL GRID
description: The National Grid is a utility organization that manages the electricity demand in the UK and has warned of potential three-hour power cuts due to a shortage of gas [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-24]

name: ROYAL SOCIETY FOR THE PREVENTION OF ACCIDENTS (ROSPA)
CIRCADIAN RHYTHM
description: Circadian rhythm, also known as the internal clock, can be thrown off balance by changes in sleep patterns, such as adjusting the time one goes to sleep or wakes up by more than an hour [he says].

name: SLEEP SCHOOL
description: Sleep School is a science-based sleep education and therapy service that is impartial on the extent to which the clocks changing impacts sleep, emphasizing the importance of consistent sleep duration and schedule [a spokesperson for Sleep School, told The Independent].

name: DEPRESSIVE EPISODES
description: A Danish study from 2017 found that the transition from summer time to standard time was associated with an 11% rise in depressive episodes, while the switch from winter to summer time had no effect [The Danish study of more than 185,000 people over 15 years].

name: SEASONAL AFFECTIVE DISORDER (SAD)
description: People frequently report an increase in Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD) and depressive symptoms in winter [Getty/iStock].

name: HEART ATTACKS
description: A 2014 study by the College of Cardiology reported a significant drop in heart attacks in the 24 hours immediately following the clocks turning back for Daylight Saving [Charlie Morley, author of Wake Up to Sleep, cites the study].

name: CHARLIE MORLEY
description: Charlie Morley, author of Wake Up to Sleep, cites a study that shows a decrease in heart attacks, suicides, and car crashes worldwide following the extra hour of sleep gained during Daylight Saving Time [he says].

name: YOU GOV
description: YOU GOV, more commonly known as YouGov, is a British market research and data analytics firm that has made a significant impact in understanding public opinion. In 2019, YouGov conducted a poll that shed light on the British public's stance on Daylight Saving Time. The results indicated that a slight majority of Brits, 44%, were in favor of maintaining the existing system of Daylight Saving Time, while 39% supported the discontinuation of the time change. This poll provided valuable insights into the preferences of the UK population regarding this seasonal adjustment, demonstrating YouGov's expertise in capturing and analyzing community dynamics in the realm of public interest.

name: DST
description: DST, or Daylight Saving Time, is a system where the clocks are set forward one hour from standard time during the summer months, and set back in the winter. The plans to change the system have been stalled, and it was set to take effect for the first time in 2021. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-24]

name: BRITS
description: Brits, or British people, were polled by YouGov in 2019 regarding their opinion on Daylight Saving Time. The majority, 44%, were in favor of keeping the current system, while 39% voted to ditch the change. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-10-24]

name: MIKE TROUT
description: Mike Trout, a professional baseball player for the Los Angeles Angels, has had a storied career despite being absent for most of the 2023 season due to injuries. Over his 12-year career, Trout has established himself as a legendary hitter, accumulating 1624 hits, 940 RBIs, and an impressive 85.2 WAR. His prowess at the plate has been recognized with nine Silver Slugger awards. As of 2023, Trout's annual salary is approximately $35.45 million, and he has seven years remaining on his contract. In a notable moment, Trout was struck out by Shohei Ohtani in the final game of the World Baseball Classic, an event that underscored the competitive nature of the sport and the dynamic between two of its most talented players.

name: KOSA
description: KOSA (the Kids Online Safety Act) is a hotly debated act that Congress has not passed, leaving U.S. states to individually create laws due to a void of federal guidelines on online child safety. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-15]

name: UTAH

The governor also signed a bill to prevent social media companies from adding features designed to addict minors to their platforms. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-15]

name: MONTANA
description: Montana is the first state to ban TikTok, claiming it was being used by the Chinese Communist Party to spy on Americans. Montana could easily turn its eyes to Meta next, after the TikTok bill went through. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-15]

name: SACHA HAWORTH
description: Sacha Haworth, the executive director of the Tech Oversight Project, a nonprofit organization dedicated to regulating Big Tech, has been vocal in her criticism of Meta's stance on children's safety and privacy. According to TechCrunch on 2023-11-15, Haworth asserts that Meta prioritizes its profit model over designing products that safeguard young users, and instead deflects responsibility onto parents and other companies to mask the harm already inflicted on young people. She believes that Meta's negligence in this area is directly linked to its business strategy, emphasizing the need for stricter oversight and accountability measures for Big Tech companies.

name: TECH OVERSIGHT PROJECT
description: The Tech Oversight Project, a nonprofit organization, is committed to curbing the excesses of Big Tech companies. It has been vocal in its criticism of Meta, particularly regarding children's safety and privacy issues. The organization believes that Meta's apparent negligence in these areas is not merely an oversight but an integral part of its profit model. Sacha Haworth, the executive director of the Tech Oversight Project, has specifically targeted Meta's stance on parental approval for teenagers' app downloads, indicating a pattern of concern over the tech giant's practices that potentially compromise the well-being and privacy of young users.

name: VALENTINE
description: Valve is a company known for developing video games and gaming hardware. In early 2022, they released the Steam Deck, a handheld PC that allows users to play their collection of video games on the go. The Steam Deck has been praised for its freedom and portability, but also criticized for its battery life and screen quality. Valve hopes to release a more powerful version, the Steam Deck 2, in two to three years. [Polygon, 2023-11-09]

name: ASUS ROG ALLY

name: VALE
description: Valve, a prominent technology company in the gaming industry, is known for its innovative Steam Deck device. Recently, Valve has announced a new lineup for the Steam Deck, introducing an OLED version to complement the existing LCD models. The new Steam Deck OLED comes in three models, differentiated by their varying storage capacities, catering to different user needs and preferences. Among these, a special edition 1 TB Steam Deck OLED with a translucent shell is being offered for a limited time, exclusively in the U.S. and Canada. This special edition is expected to be in high demand, prompting Valve to consider the possibility of increasing its supply. Despite the introduction of the OLED models, Valve remains committed to supporting all LCD models through regular software updates, ensuring that all users can enjoy the latest features and improvements.

name: LEGO
description: LEGO, a renowned toy company, specializes in creating building toys that captivate the imagination of children and adults alike. The brand is celebrated for its detailed minifigs and sets, which often draw inspiration from popular culture, including Marvel and Star Wars franchises. One notable example is the Marvel Hulkbuster set, which has the potential to increase in value if kept unopened for a few years, making it an attractive choice for collectors. LEGO's commitment to quality and creativity is further exemplified by their The Mandalorian-themed set, featuring Kuiil riding on his Blurrg, a beloved character from the hit series. These sets were highlighted in both Wired's Best Prime Day LEGO and Other Toy Deals in October 2023 and Polygon's coverage in December 2023, solidifying LEGO's reputation as a leading brand in the toy industry that consistently delivers products that resonate with fans and enthusiasts.

name: COMMITTEE TO PROTECT JOURNALISTS
description: The Committee to Protect Journalists has reported that at least 30 journalists have been killed since Israel’s bombardment and total blockade of Gaza began [TechCrunch, 2023-11-03]

name: SNAP MAP
description: Snap Map is a feature integrated into the Snapchat platform, serving as an interactive tool that enables users to share their location and content on a map. This feature is renowned for its ability to display hotspots of activity, based on user posts, making it a valuable resource for real-time information on current events, political protests, and entertainment gatherings. Snap Map has notably been used to provide updates from diverse locations, including music festivals, political demonstrations, and conflict zones. Its application in highlighting the disparity between Israeli cities and occupied Palestinian territories, particularly during the 2021 Sheikh Jarrah protests, and more recently, the devastation in Gaza since the Israeli airstrikes started last month, has been significant. Journalists and the public alike have found Snap Map to be an indispensable source of real-time information, offering insights into events as they unfold.

name: ISRAEL DEFENCE FORCES (IDF)
description: The Israel Defence Forces (IDF) have requested that mapping sites limit features in the region for safety reasons, leading companies like Google and Apple to disable live traffic updates in Israel and the Gaza Strip. The IDF's concern is that live updates could reveal military movements [TechCrunch, 2023-11-03]

name: APPLE MAPS
description: Apple Maps, like Google, took action to comply with the IDF's request by disabling live traffic updates in Israel and the Gaza Strip [TechCrunch, 2023-11-03]

name: YOUNG PEOPLE
description: Young people, specifically those aged between 11 to 17, are deeply immersed in the digital world, spending a median of 4.5 hours per day on their phones, with some individuals engaging with their devices for up to an astonishing 16 hours daily. Their attachment to technology is evident in the frequency of phone checks, which can range from a moderate two times to an extreme 498 times per day, highlighting the significant role mobile devices play in their lives. Beyond mere entertainment, young people are leveraging technology for information gathering, particularly during times of social unrest. They are increasingly turning to Snap Map for eyewitness accounts, viewing it as a more trustworthy source than traditional news media, which they perceive as biased. This generation's reliance on social media for news consumption is nearly on par with their trust in national news outlets, indicating a shift in how they consume and interpret information, as reported by TechCrunch in November 2023. This trend underscores the evolving dynamics of how young people engage with current events and the pivotal role that social media platforms like Snap Map play in shaping their understanding of the world.
