name: KIM KARDASHIAN
description: Kim Kardashian is a celebrity who criticized Roblox's parental controls after her son Saint encountered a minigame referencing her 2007 sex tape. She planned to sue Roblox for using her name and likeness in the game. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: SAIN
description: Kim Kardashian's son Saint encountered a minigame on Roblox that referenced her 2007 sex tape, leading to her criticism of the platform's parental controls. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

description: A community developer was involved in an incident where a video that violated Roblox's Community Rules got around its filters. The developer has been banned from the platform. [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: AMO
description: AMO, a company with substantial financial resources, was founded by the visionary behind Zenly. Under the leadership of CEO Antoine Martin, AMO has developed a groundbreaking social app designed to accommodate a massive scale, with the ambitious goal of attracting 100 million daily active users. This app stands out in the consumer social space by offering a unique feature: a spatial canvas where users can manipulate virtual objects, enabling them to express their multifaceted personalities in a creative and engaging manner. Martin describes the app as a reflection of the chaotic yet beautiful complexity of human nature, positioning AMO as a force for innovation and resilience in the tech industry. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-19]

name: ANTOINE MARTIN
description: Antoine Martin, a prominent figure in the tech industry, serves as the CEO of Amo, a company renowned for its innovative social app. This app, designed under Martin's leadership, offers users a unique spatial canvas to express their multifaceted personalities, distinguishing it from traditional social platforms. Additionally, Martin is recognized as the founder of Zenly, further solidifying his expertise and influence in the realm of social technology. He holds a strong belief that for a company to be truly indestructible, it must have 100 million daily active users, a milestone he aims to achieve with Amo's social app. Martin critiques existing social apps, asserting that they fall short in meeting the fundamental human needs for connection and self-expression, a gap he aims to bridge with his innovative approach.

name: PINTEREST
description: Pinterest is a platform where users can create and share mood boards, which is mentioned as a point of comparison for Amo's app. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-19]

name: ID
description: ID is a social application innovatively developed by Amo, aiming to redefine the social app experience by addressing the issue of loneliness while simultaneously offering a departure from the passive consumption patterns typical of traditional social platforms. Launched in 2023, ID introduces a unique feature where users can swipe through friends' profiles presented on notification cards, a mechanism that adds an element of emergent gameplay to the browsing experience. This interactive approach not only encourages users to engage more actively with the content but also promotes a sense of community by allowing them to categorize and add content from other profiles, fostering a creative and dynamic environment. Notably, ID closes automatically after the last card is swiped, a design choice that encourages users to take a break, thereby promoting a healthier relationship with technology and social media. This distinctive blend of features makes ID a standout choice for individuals seeking a more mindful and engaging social app experience.

name: LOS ANGELES
description: Los Angeles is a location mentioned as an example of how users can create themed sections on their profiles within the Amo app. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-19]

name: SOFTWARE DEVELOPERS
description: Software developers are mentioned as a potential user group for the Amo app, who might enjoy decorating their virtual space with stickers. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-19]

name: ZENLY
description: Zenly, a company founded by Martin, who is also the founder of Amo, is dedicated to revitalizing the social aspect of social apps. Previously, Zenly was an app created by Martin, showcasing the founder's commitment to enhancing social interactions through technology. In 2023, the company's focus is on rekindling the social experience in apps, aiming to bring people closer together in the digital age. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-19]

name: WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION
description: The World Health Organization (WHO), a leading authority on global health matters, has recently made two significant announcements. Firstly, WHO advises against the use of sugar substitutes for the purposes of weight loss or disease prevention, as reported by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-19. This guidance comes amidst ongoing debates about the efficacy and potential side effects of artificial sweeteners. Secondly, the organization has acknowledged loneliness as a public health epidemic, drawing attention to the issue of social isolation and its impact on individuals and their loved ones, as highlighted by TechCrunch on 2023-11-19. The WHO's recognition of loneliness as an epidemic underscores the importance of addressing mental health and social well-being in the context of public health initiatives.

name: MARTIN
description: Martin, the founder of Amo and the creator of Zenly, is a seasoned seller in the technology and entertainment community. He has been closely associated with Discogs, a popular platform for buying and selling music records. Martin understands the dynamics of community ownership, as evidenced by his acknowledgment of the community's strong emotional ties to Discogs, which can lead to upset when changes are made to the platform. This sentiment was particularly highlighted after Discogs' sale in late August, where only 11 of the site's largest stores were featured, leaving many sellers, including Martin, feeling disappointed. Despite this, Martin remains committed to learning by building in public, as he shared insights about the deliberate timing of ID's launch, another project he is involved in. He also has experience with eBay, noting that while its fees are approximately 1 percent higher than Discogs', the larger user base often makes it a more attractive option for sellers.

description: Ben Zvi Klein, a prominent figure in the discussion of Israel's real estate market, expressed his views on the market's resilience amidst challenging times, specifically during a period of war, as reported by Globes, Israel business news on December 3, 2023. Klein asserts that despite the current crisis, the real estate market will recover, drawing parallels to its ability to bounce back from previous hardships. He emphasizes that property owners, having learned from historical experiences, are not succumbing to the pressure to reduce prices or rents. This steadfastness, according to Klein, indicates that the market is returning to activity, suggesting a level of confidence and stability among property holders in the face of adversity.

On December 3, 2023, AMOSI contributed insights to Globes English | Israel Business Arena, addressing the question of why office rents have not decreased despite an oversupply and a decline in demand. In a separate but related commentary, AMOSI explained to Globes, a leading source for Israel business news, that property owners who acquired buildings through purchase groups such as BSR City are now reducing rents. This dual perspective showcases AMOSI's expertise in understanding the complexities of the real estate market and the strategies employed by property owners in response to changing market conditions.

name: APPLE AIRPODS PRO (USB-C)
description: The USB-C version of Apple’s AirPods Pro is available for $189, a $60 discount off Apple’s list price. This model delivers strong ANC, a superb transparency mode, and a pleasingly warm sound, and includes hands-free Siri access, Find My tracking, and fast pairing with other Apple devices. A recent update added an “Adaptive Audio” mode and improved dust resistance alongside the new charging port [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: APPLE AIRPODS (2ND GEN)
description: Apple’s second-gen AirPods are on sale for $89, $10 off their usual street price. These earbuds have a one-size-fits-all design that may not work for everyone, and there are better-sounding options for the money. However, they offer the usual AirPods perks in an unsealed design, making them a good choice for those committed to Apple devices [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER SOUNDCORE LIFE Q30
description: The Anker Soundcore Life Q30 is a pair of noise-canceling over-ear headphones available for $56, a $24 discount. They have a bass-heavy profile, multi-device pairing, and customizable EQ. The ANC is excellent for the price, but call quality is worse [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: SENNHEISER HD560S
description: Sennheiser HD 560S is a quality wired model recommended for critical listening, with an open-back design that lets in and leaks a lot of noise, but sounds spacious, detailed, and well-balanced [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: HYPERX CLOUD ALPHA
description: The HyperX Cloud Alpha is a gaming headset renowned for its comfort and superior build quality compared to the Stinger 2 model. As of 2023-10-10, Engadget reported that the HyperX Cloud Alpha is available for a discounted price of $60, which is $15 lower than its usual street price. The headset features a detachable microphone, making it a versatile choice for gamers seeking both functionality and value.

name: PRIME DAY GAMING HEADSET DEALS
description: Prime Day gaming headset deals refer to discounts offered on gaming headsets during Amazon's Prime Day event in October 2023. [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: STINGER 2
description: Stinger 2 is a gaming headset on sale for $35, matching the lowest price seen. It has a V-shaped sound signature, a cheap-feeling plastic design, and a mic that belies its low price. [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: APPLE 10.2-INCH IPAD
description: Apple's 10.2-inch iPad is on sale for $249. It is the most affordable iPad, suitable for budget-conscious consumers, and it has most of the crucial features expected in an Apple tablet. It received a score of 86 for its solid performance, sharp screen, TouchID-capable Home button, and good battery life. However, it still uses the old Lightning port instead of USB-C. [Source: Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY WATCH 6
description: The Samsung Galaxy Watch 6, a smartwatch tailored for Samsung and Android phone users, is currently available at its lowest price since its release, set at $269 during the October Prime Day sale. This price point is a continuation of the sale that initially dropped the price to $270, making it an attractive offer for potential buyers. The watch is noted for its comprehensive features and capabilities, including improved performance and updated health and fitness tracking tools. It is also designed to be smaller and lighter than its predecessors, with the Classic version featuring a spinning bezel for navigation. As of 2023, the Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 is considered the best smartwatch for Samsung users, offering a blend of style, functionality, and value.

name: BOSE QUIETCOMFORT 45
description: The Bose QuietComfort 45 headphones are a wireless headphone model that has been discounted to $230 for October Prime Day, $80 cheaper than their usual selling price. They are praised for their comfortable design, excellent active noise cancellation (ANC), and balanced audio quality [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON ECHO DOT
description: The Amazon Echo Dot is currently on sale for $23. It is a smart speaker with an orb-like design, good sound quality for its size, and Alexa integration. Additionally, it can act as an Eero WiFi booster, extending coverage by up to 1,000 square feet [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON ECHO SHOW 5
description: The Amazon Echo Show 5 is on sale for a record low of $40. It is a compact smart display with Alexa capabilities, suitable for those who want a space-saving device. It also features a sunrise alarm and tap-to-snooze functionality [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON KINDLE
description: The standard Amazon Kindle has been reduced to $75 for October Prime Day. The 2022 model offers 16GB of storage and a screen resolution of 300 ppi for clearer text. It is considered the best budget option in Engadget's ereader guide, ideal for reading and borrowing ebooks and audiobooks [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON KINDLE PAPERWHITE
description: The Amazon Kindle Paperwhite is available for $95 for an 8GB model during Prime Day. It offers additional features over the standard Kindle, such as a larger 6.8-inch screen, a more comprehensive front light, and IPX8-rated waterproofing. The deal applies to the ad-supported version, with an extra $20 for the no-ads version [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: $100 PLAYSTATION STORE GIFT CARD + $10 AMAZON CREDIT
description: Amazon is offering a promotion where purchasing a $100 PlayStation Store digital gift card and using the code PSN100 at checkout grants an extra $10 Amazon credit for future purchases. This deal is beneficial for those who frequently use Amazon and plan to buy PS5 games, renew PlayStation Plus subscriptions, or make other purchases [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: BLINK MINI
description: Blink Mini is a two-pack of wired security cameras that are on sale for $40 during Amazon's Prime Day event. They offer 1080p video recordings, support for two-way talk, and motion alerts [Engadget, 2023-10-10]

name: GOOGLE INDOOR NEST SECURITY CAM
description:
The Google Indoor Nest Security Cam, a versatile battery-powered security camera, is designed for use both indoors and outdoors. As of the 2023-10-10 Engadget report, the camera was on sale for $120 during Amazon's Prime Day event, a significant discount from its usual price of $180. Notably, the camera boasts a weather-resistant build, making it suitable for various environmental conditions. description: The 2023 Nobel Prize in chemistry is an award that honors three scientists, Moungi Bawendi, Louis Brus, and Alexei Ekimov, for their discovery and creation of quantum dots. The trio will split a prize of 11 million Swedish kronor, or about $1 million. The Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences announced the honor on October 4, 2023. [Source: Science News For Students, 2023-10-04]

description: Semiconductors are materials used in the creation of quantum dots. They include substances like graphene, selenite, and metal sulfides. [Science News For Students, 2023-10-04]

name: EKIMOV

description: Nokia Bell Labs, a prestigious research facility headquartered in Murray Hill, New Jersey, is known for its cutting-edge studies in the realm of technology and physics. The lab, where notable scientists Bawendi and Brus have contributed to significant advancements, has a particular focus on the study of nanoparticles. Researchers at Nokia Bell Labs require high-quality quantum dots, specialized components crucial for their investigations into the intricate physics of nanoparticles, as reported by Science News For Students on October 4, 2023. This facility serves as a hub for scientific exploration and innovation, driving the boundaries of knowledge in technology and entertainment-related fields. However, the direct link to entertainment is not explicitly mentioned in the provided descriptions, suggesting that Nokia Bell Labs' primary emphasis is on technological and scientific research.

name: 2023 CHEMISTRY NOBEL PRIZE
description: The 2023 Chemistry Nobel Prize was awarded to recognize the significant contributions of three individuals, including Bawendi, for their pioneering work in the development of quantum dots technology. This prestigious honor, announced on October 4, 2023, by Science News For Students, highlights the groundbreaking advancements made by these scientists in the field of chemistry, specifically in the area of quantum dots, which are nanoscale semiconductor particles with unique optical properties. Bawendi's work, in particular, has been instrumental in advancing the understanding and application of quantum dots, making him a notable recipient among the trio.

name: MARCUS BAWENDI

name: AURORA BOREALIS
description: The Aurora Borealis, also known as the Northern Lights, is a natural phenomenon most commonly observed in winter when skies get dark in the late afternoon. It can be seen in various locations in the UK, including the Isle of Lewis, Shetland Isles, Cairngorms, and Yorkshire Dales [The Independent - Travel, 2023-12-21]

name: ISLE OF LEWIS
description: The Isle of Lewis in Scotland hosts its own Dark Skies Festival in February, featuring events like live music, film, and theatre. It is a good location for observing the Northern Lights [The Independent - Travel, 2023-12-21]

name: SHETLAND ISLES
description: The Shetland Isles, the most northerly point in Britain, are close to the North Pole and offer several opportunities to see the Northern Lights during winter. The remote isle has plenty of tranquil countryside and coastal scenery, providing numerous spots to watch the lights away from light pollution [The Independent - Travel, 2023-12-21]

name: CAIRNGORMS

It is home to Ben Nevis, the highest peak in the UK, and an International Dark Sky Park. The park is busy all year due to its vast wilderness and wildlife [The Independent - Travel, 2023-12-21]

name: YORKSHIRE DALES
description: The Yorkshire Dales in England, with its northerly and light-pollution free location, is a great place to spot the aurora. The park is one of England’s Dark Sky Reserves and the largest in the UK. It has four Dark Sky Discovery sites and will be hosting a joint Dark Skies Festival with the North York Moors National Park in February 2024 [The Independent - Travel, 2023-12-21]

name: GEMINI
description: Gemini, unveiled by Google this week, is the tech giant's new flagship generative AI model designed to understand a wide array of data types including images, audio, videos, and text. However, the full capabilities of Gemini have not been released to the public yet. Instead, a "lite" version of the model, known as Gemini Pro, has been introduced. This scaled-down version has been integrated into Bard, Google's AI chatbot that competes with ChatGPT. Unfortunately, user feedback has been less than favorable, with reports of Gemini Pro providing incorrect information and displaying poor multilingual capabilities. Despite Google's claims of its advanced functionalities, Gemini Pro's performance issues have been a source of frustration for users, highlighting the potential limitations of the model in its current state.

name: VITOR DE LUCCA
description: Vitor de Lucca is a user who expressed disappointment with the performance of Gemini Pro on Bard, particularly with its incorrect responses to questions about 2023 Oscar winners. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: BENJAMIN NETTER
description: Benjamin Netter is a user who criticized Google Gemini's performance, stating that it is "complete trash" and struggles with giving a six-letter word in French. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: CHARLIE STROSS
description: Charlie Stross is a science fiction author who found many examples of confabulation in a recent blog post about Gemini Pro, including incorrect statements about his contributions to the Linux kernel. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: GEMINI PRO
description: Gemini Pro, a generative AI model developed by Google and part of the Gemini series, has recently come under scrutiny for its vulnerabilities and performance issues. According to TechCrunch on 2023-12-07, the AI model is not immune to "jailbreaks," which are prompts that can bypass safety filters, potentially allowing for the discussion of controversial topics. Furthermore, Gemini Pro has been reported to have poor multilingual capabilities and struggles with basic coding functions. It has also shown difficulties in summarizing potentially sensitive news topics, as evidenced by its provision of an outdated summary of the war in Ukraine. Additionally, the AI model failed to write a Python function for finding the intersection of two polygons, highlighting its limitations in practical coding tasks. These findings suggest that Gemini Pro may not be as versatile or reliable as initially anticipated in handling complex and sensitive information across various languages and coding contexts.

name: FIILP PIEKNIEWSKI
description: Filip Piekniewski is a person who tested Gemini Pro and found it unable to write the intersection of two polygons in Python, a function that wasn't ever implemented in Python and all AI models failed on. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: EDISON ADE
description: Edison Ade is a person who compared Gemini Pro with ChatGPT in creating a Tic Tac Toe game, where ChatGPT wrote the code on the first try while Gemini Pro took three tries. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: N KIRAN KUMAR
description: N Kiran Kumar is a person who tested Google's Bard with Gemini Pro update and found it unable to create a bugless snake game on the first try, while ChatGPT 3.5 free version provided correct bug-free code on the first attempt. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: ROBUST INTELLIGENCE
description: Robust Intelligence is a startup that sells model-auditing tools. Their AI security researchers managed to bypass the safety filters of Gemini Pro, getting it to suggest ways to commit illegal acts. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: GEMINI ULTRA
description: Gemini Ultra is the most capable version of the Gemini AI model, set to launch in the future. It is not yet available in Bard or other Google products. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: GPT-3.5

name: ONLINE SAFETY ACT
description: The Online Safety Act is a comprehensive UK legislation that has undergone a multiyear lawmaking process, designed to address a wide range of online harms in a technology-neutral manner. This act focuses on the context of the content rather than the technology used to create it, ensuring that tech firms have a duty of care to protect their users from illegal content such as child sexual abuse material (CSAM), terrorism-related content, and fraud, including those generated by AI and deepfakes. Additionally, the legislation tackles legal but harmful material, particularly targeting content that may endanger children, women, and girls. It also addresses concerns over end-to-end encryption, aiming to strike a balance between privacy and safety measures. The aim of the Online Safety Act is to create a safer digital environment by requiring technology companies to take proactive steps in dealing with harmful content, as reported by The Verge on November 9, 2023.

name: OFCOM
description:
OFCOM, the UK's regulatory body, plays a pivotal role in the digital rights and user privacy landscape. In anticipation of the upcoming year, OFCOM plans to initiate a consultation process to evaluate the implications of scanning encrypted messaging on these critical aspects. The organization is committed to a technology-neutral stance in its regulation of the Online Safety Act, focusing on the context in which technology is used rather than the technology itself. This approach underscores OFCOM's dedication to fostering a balanced environment that respects user rights while addressing safety concerns.

Moreover, OFCOM is actively involved in the establishment of a global online safety regulator network. This initiative aims to streamline the compliance process for tech firms operating in multiple countries, recognizing the need for harmonized standards in an increasingly interconnected digital world.

OFCOM has taken a proactive stance in regulating tech firms under the Online Safety Act, as evidenced by the guidelines it has published. These guidelines encompass various aspects, including rules for user blocking, the dissemination of crisis prevention information, and the requirement for risk assessments of recommendation algorithms. The body wields the authority to impose fines and block offending sites should they fail to adhere to the act, demonstrating its commitment to ensuring a safe and legal online environment.

As the UK regulator responsible for overseeing the implementation of the Online Safety Act, OFCOM is tasked with guaranteeing that tech firms are actively combating illegal content. This responsibility, as reported by The Verge on 2023-11-09, highlights OFCOM's pivotal role in shaping the digital landscape and maintaining the integrity of online platforms.

name: TECH FIRMS
description: Tech firms, including social media platforms, search engines, online and mobile games, and pornography sites, are expected to comply with the Online Safety Act by dealing with illegal content and demonstrating a proactive approach to user safety. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-09]

name: GILL WHITEHEAD
description: Gill Whitehead is Ofcom’s online safety lead who explains the duty of care that tech firms now have under the Online Safety Act and the need for them to conduct risk assessments and remove illegal content. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-09]

name: CLAIRE WISEMAN
description: Claire Wiseman is a lawyer who specializes in tech, media, telecoms, and data. She explains the aim of the Online Safety Act to encourage a switch from a reactive to a more proactive approach in dealing with illegal content. [Source: The Verge, 2023-11-09]

name: WHITEHEAD
description: Whitehead, a spokesperson for Ofcom, has been actively involved in discussions regarding the Online Safety Act. She elucidates that the Act is designed to tackle online harms in a manner that is impartial to the technology used, instead emphasizing the context in which these harms occur. Whitehead acknowledges the complexities tech companies face when adhering to varying regulatory frameworks across different countries and highlights the efforts being made to streamline operations for these firms on an international scale. Although Whitehead chose not to comment on a specific entity's cooperation, she did note that technology firms have generally responded positively to the guidelines set forth by Ofcom. Additionally, she addressed the potential implications of the Online Safety Act on end-to-end encryption, a critical aspect of data privacy, and the increasing role of artificial intelligence in identifying and mitigating illegal content online.

name: DIGITAL RIGHTS GROUPS
description: Digital rights groups are concerned about the potential invasion of user privacy and the breaking of apps' encryption systems that could result from the scanning measures proposed under the Online Safety Act.

name: ENCRYPTED MESSAGING
description: Encrypted messaging is a technology that ensures user privacy by preventing unauthorized access to messages. The potential impact of the Online Safety Act on encrypted messaging is uncertain, as Ofcom plans to consult on this next year.

name: WIKIMEDIA FOUNDATION
description: The Wikimedia Foundation is a nonprofit organization behind Wikipedia. It is finding it increasingly challenging to comply with different regulatory regimes across the world, including the EU's Digital Services Act. The foundation has a limited number of lawyers dedicated to EU regulations compared to larger tech companies.

name: REBECCA MACKINNON
description: Rebecca MacKinnon is the VP for global advocacy at the Wikimedia Foundation. She points out the challenges of complying with various regulations, especially for a nonprofit with limited resources, and highlights the differences in capacity between the Wikimedia Foundation and tech giants like Meta and Google.

name: DIGITAL SERVICES ACT
description: The Digital Services Act is a regulation enforced by the EU that impacts the moderation of content in European languages, including English, on platforms like Meta. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-19]

name: MIRANDA SISSONS
description: Miranda Sissons is the director of human rights at Meta, who stated that the company is assessing the feasibility of reviewing Arabic content by dialect and has large and diverse teams to understand local cultural context across the region, including in Palestine. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-19]

name: ABUKHATER
description: Abukhater, an individual deeply engaged in the discourse surrounding Meta's content moderation and translation practices, voiced concerns over the company's handling of Arabic content. According to a TechCrunch report on 2023-10-19, Abukhater highlighted that the balance of power between Israelis and Palestinians is evident in Meta's platform policies, impacting the representation and treatment of content related to these regions. Despite Meta's efforts to address these issues, Abukhater noted that problems persist, particularly during periods of heightened violence. Additionally, Abukhater addressed a specific mistranslation issue that gained attention, which Meta attributed to a "bug." This incident further underscored the complexities and challenges in managing multilingual content on a global scale, particularly in sensitive geopolitical contexts.

name: WADEA AL-FAYOUME
description: Wadea Al-Fayoume is a Palestinian-American child whose death, being investigated as a hate crime, is mentioned in the context of the impact of Meta's content moderation issues on real-world violence. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-19]

name: 7AMLEH
description: 7amleh is an organization that Meta communicated with regarding the mistranslation issue, attributing the problem to a "bug." [TechCrunch, 2023-10-19]

name: 404 MEDIA
description: 404 Media, a prominent media organization, was approached by Meta with a statement addressing the resolution of a significant issue. As reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-19, the problem pertained to inappropriate Arabic translations that were discovered in some of Meta's products. The report highlighted that Meta had successfully fixed the mistranslation issue, demonstrating the company's commitment to enhancing the accuracy and cultural sensitivity of its services. This action by Meta is crucial for maintaining positive user experiences and trust within the global community, particularly among Arabic-speaking users. 404 Media's coverage of this development underscores its role in keeping the public informed about important updates in the tech industry.

name: 7AMELEH
description: 7amleh is an organization that was informed by Meta about the "bug" causing mistranslation issues, as mentioned in TechCrunch's report on 2023-10-19[]

name: AL SAADI
description: Al Saadi is an individual who expressed frustration with Meta's treatment of Palestinians, both in occupied territories and across the diaspora, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-19[]

name: DOMINIC-MADORI DAVIS

name: WARLOCK
description: In the captivating world of Baldur's Gate 3, WARLOCK emerges as one of twelve distinctive classes, tailored for players drawn to the mystique of extreme knowledge-seekers. WARLOCKS strike a pact with otherworldly beings, harnessing ancient secrets to amplify their magical prowess. Centered around Charisma as their primary ability score, they embody formidable mental strength and the uncanny ability to broker deals with powerful entities. Unlike other dedicated caster classes, such as Wizards, WARLOCKS streamline their spellcasting by sacrificing the quantity of spells for unparalleled power; each spell slot they possess is of the highest level, and they uniquely recharge their abilities during a short rest rather than a long one. Proficient in simple weapons and light armor, WARLOCKS also demonstrate saving throws in Wisdom and Charisma, further solidifying their versatility. Upon embarking on their journey, WARLOCKS are equipped with two cantrips and two spells from the exclusive Warlock spell list, with some spells specific to their chosen subclass. This class is ideal for those seeking a magical path devoid of extensive preparation, offering a potent blend of power and convenience.

name: CHARISMA
description: Charisma, in the context of Baldur's Gate 3, is an Ability Score that significantly influences skills such as Persuasion, Deception, and Intimidation. It is the primary ability score for several classes, including Bards, Sorcerers, and Warlocks. Bards and Sorcerers rely on Charisma for their spellcasting and social interactions, while Warlocks utilize it to reflect their strong mental power and their unique ability to make deals with powerful creatures. This versatile score is essential for characters aiming to excel in diplomacy, manipulation, and the wielding of arcane power. [Polygon, 2023-12-18, 2023-12-01]

name: SPELLS
description: Spells are a game mechanic in Baldur’s Gate 3, with Warlocks starting with two spells from the Warlock spell list. Some of these spells are exclusive to the Warlock's subclass [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: CANTRIPS
description: Cantrips are a game mechanic in Baldur’s Gate 3, with Warlocks starting with two cantrips from the Warlock cantrip list. These cantrips include Blade Ward, Bone Chill, Eldritch Blast, Friends, Mage Hand, Minor Illusion, Poison Spray, and True Strike [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: THE FIEND
description: The Fiend is a subclass of the Warlock class in Baldur’s Gate 3. Warlocks with this subclass have made a deal with a hellish fiend and receive a feature called “Dark One’s Blessing” and two exclusive spells, Burning Hands and Command [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: THE GREAT OLD ONE
description: The Great Old One is a subclass of the Warlock class in Baldur’s Gate 3. Warlocks serving this subclass are bound to a mysterious being from the Far Realm and receive a feature called “Mortal Reminder” and two exclusive spells, Dissonant Whispers and Tasha’s Hideous Laughter [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: DROW
description: Drow is a race in Baldur’s Gate 3 that adds weapons like rapiers and hand crossbows to the Warlock class through the Drow Weapon Training feature [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: HUMANS
description: Humans and Half-Elves are races in Baldur’s Gate 3 that add spears, pikes, halberds, and glaives along with shields to the Warlock class through the Civil Militia feature [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: GITHYANKI
description: Githyanki is a race in Baldur’s Gate 3 that means Warlocks get medium armor along with longswords and greatswords through the Martial Prodigy feature [Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: WARLOCK SUBCLASS
description: The Warlock subclass is a feature in Baldur’s Gate 3, offering unique abilities and builds for players. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: FEATS
description: Feats are game features in Baldur’s Gate 3 that allow players to gain specific abilities or bonuses, such as increasing Strength or Dexterity by 1, to a maximum of 20, and reducing the number needed to roll a Critical Hit while attacking. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: BUILD
description: Build refers to the strategy of combining classes, subclasses, and feats in Baldur’s Gate 3 to create a character with specific strengths and abilities. [Source: Polygon, 2023-12-01]

name: CANNABIS
description: Cannabis, a psychoactive substance utilized by individuals in various forms including inhaling and consuming edibles, has recently been associated with potential risks to pregnancy outcomes. According to a study highlighted by Live Science on December 13, 2023, the use of Cannabis during pregnancy may lead to babies being born smaller than expected for their gestational age, along with other adverse effects. This information underscores the importance of understanding the implications of Cannabis use, particularly in sensitive periods such as pregnancy, to make informed decisions regarding health and well-being.

name: PREGNANCY
description: Pregnancy is a physiological state during which the use of cannabis may lead to adverse outcomes, including small birth size and other poor outcomes [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: DR. TORRI METZ
description: Dr. Torri Metz is the first study author, an associate professor of obstetrics and gynecology at University of Utah Health, who evaluated the risks associated with cannabis use during pregnancy [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: UNIVERSITY OF UTAH HEALTH
description: University of Utah Health is a health institution where Dr. Torri Metz, an associate professor of obstetrics and gynecology, is affiliated [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: JAMA
description: JAMA, a prominent journal in the medical field, published a significant study highlighting the connection between cannabis use during pregnancy and adverse outcomes. This study was featured in Live Science's list of The Most Interesting Articles on December 13, 2023. Additionally, JAMA, as an organization, further explored this topic by releasing a podcast interview with Dr. Metz, who provided expert insights and discussed the findings of the study in detail. These dual contributions by JAMA underscore its commitment to disseminating critical research and fostering informed discussions on public health issues, particularly concerning the effects of substance use on maternal and child health.

name: PLACENTA
description: The placenta is an organ that supplies a growing fetus with nutrients and oxygen while removing waste from the womb, and its dysfunction has been linked to poor pregnancy outcomes [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: FROZEN URINE SAMPLES
description: Frozen urine samples were used in the study, which may have experienced some degradation over the years, although they were stored appropriately [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: POOR PREGNANCY OUTCOMES
description: Poor pregnancy outcomes, including small birth size, have been linked to cannabis use during pregnancy in a recent study [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: ALTERNATIVE METHODS
description: Alternative methods of treating conditions for which cannabis is used were suggested by Dr. Metz in a podcast interview with JAMA [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: DR. METZ
description: Dr. Metz is a medical professional who commented on the study's findings and suggested discussing alternative methods of treatment with patients who use cannabis [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-12-13]

name: CONOR MCGREGOR
description: Conor McGregor, a renowned professional mixed martial artist and boxer, has made significant waves in the combat sports industry with his high-profile career. Known for his prowess in both MMA and boxing, McGregor has faced notable opponents such as Floyd Mayweather, with whom he engaged in a boxing match where he claimed to have landed more punches than Canelo Alvarez did in his bout with Mayweather. McGregor's past fights, including those against Dustin Poirier and Khabib Nurmagomedov, have been highly lucrative, drawing large numbers of pay-per-view (PPV) buys. Recently, McGregor sparked a quarrel on X (formerly Twitter) with Canelo Alvarez, a development that has led to discussions about a potential crossover boxing match between the two. This potential fight could have significant implications for Alvarez's net worth and status as a billionaire, given McGregor's track record of high-earning events.

name: GOLDEN BOY PROMOTIONS
description: Golden Boy Promotions is a boxing promotional company that, along with DAZN, signed a $365 million deal with Canelo Alvarez. [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-18]

name: US COPYRIGHT
description: US Copyright is a legal concept that protects the rights of creators, in this case, the rights of xDavidxLeahx for the content created on 20230929183529 [Essentially Sports, 2023-10-18]

name: PAY-PER-VIEW (PPV) SALES

name: POTENTIAL FIGHT
description: The potential fight between Conor McGregor and Canelo Alvarez is an event that could help Canelo come a step closer to surpassing Floyd Mayweather's net worth and achieving billionaire status[]

name: JACK-O’-HEAD ARMOR
description: The Jack-o’-Head armor is a piece of head armor in Monster Hunter Now that comes with the Solidarity (Pumpkin Hunt) skill. This skill increases attack power when multiple players have it active, and the effect is amplified during the Halloween event [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: SOLIDARITY (PUMPKIN HUNT) SKILL
description: Solidarity (Pumpkin Hunt) is a party-based skill in Monster Hunter Now that increases attack power when multiple players have it active. The skill's effect is increased by five during the Halloween event [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: PUMPKIN TICKETS
description: Pumpkin Tickets are in-game items that can be obtained by taking down Halloween-themed Kulu-Ya-Ku holding a pumpkin rock in Monster Hunter Now. These tickets can be collected even after the Halloween event ends if the Kulu-Ya-Ku was tagged with paintballs during the event [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

name: KULU-YA-KU
description: Kulu-Ya-Ku is a monster in Monster Hunter Now that appears in all three habitats (Forest, Desert, and Swamp). During the Halloween event, a Halloween-themed Kulu-Ya-Ku holding a pumpkin rock will appear in larger numbers than usual, and defeating these monsters rewards players with Pumpkin Tickets [Polygon, 2023-10-25]

description: Vivek Ramaswamy is a Republican political candidate who has accused TikTok of being a threat to national security and has proposed barring anyone under 25 from voting, unless they serve in the military or pass a civics exam [TechCrunch, 2023-10-02]

name: VACCINIUM MACROCARPON
description: Cultivated cranberry (Vaccinium macrocarpon) is a young agricultural crop compared to many valuable plant species that were domesticated over thousands of years. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: HENRY HALL
description: Henry Hall, a Revolutionary War veteran, found that covering cranberry bogs with sand fertilized the vines and retained water around their roots, initiating cranberry cultivation in 1816 in Massachusetts. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: MASSACHUSETTS
description: Massachusetts is where cranberry cultivation began in 1816, initiated by Henry Hall. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: NATIVE AMERICANS
description: Native Americans used wild cranberries as an important food source in puddings, sauces, breads, and a high-protein portable food called pemmican. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: PEMMICAN
description: Pemmican is a high-protein portable food made from a mixture of dried meat and rendered animal fat, sometimes studded with dried fruits, including cranberries. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: BUTTERFLIES AND HONEYBEES
description: When cranberries don’t self-pollinate, they rely on bumblebees and honeybees to transport their pollen from flower to flower. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: CRANBERRY BLOSSOMS
description: A cranberry blossom has four petals that peel back when the flower blooms, exposing the anthers which contain the plant’s pollen. [Scitechdaily | Science Space And Technology News 2017, 2023-11-21]

name: SCALABLE CAPITAL
description: Scalable Capital, a Munich-based neobroker, has established itself as a significant player in the European financial technology landscape. The company, which initially began as a digital wealth management platform, has evolved into a full-service brokerage firm, catering to a clientele with an average age of 35, suggesting a focus on customers with more disposable income. As of December 7, 2023, Scalable Capital has raised over $345 million in funding, with the most recent round of $65 million on a flat $1.4 billion valuation, contributing to a total of $180 million raised in 2021 alone. The startup boasts a robust customer base of over 600,000, with 1.2 million savings plans and nearly €17 billion under management. Scalable Capital's product suite is comprehensive, encompassing ETFs, stocks, funds, bonds, cryptocurrencies, derivatives, and loans, all designed to make investing in financial markets more accessible to a broader audience. Despite its growth and diversification, the company has chosen not to pursue a banking license, opting instead to concentrate on product development and market expansion within the six European countries where it is currently active, as well as entering new markets.

name: BALDERTON
description: Balderton is leading the €60 million investment round in Scalable Capital, with participation from HV Capital and other unnamed existing backers. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: HV CAPITAL
description: HV Capital is participating in the €60 million investment round in Scalable Capital from its new growth fund. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: ERIK PODZUWEIT
description: Erik Podzuweit is the co-CEO of Scalable Capital, who co-founded the company with Florian Prucker. He confirmed that the company still has the majority of the money from the last funding round in the bank, but this extra injection means it can be a little more aggressive in its approach. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: FLORIAN PRUCKER
description: Florian Prucker is the co-founder of Scalable Capital. [Source: TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: FREETRADE
description: Freetrade is a competitor in the U.K. market with clear European ambitions. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: LIGHTYEAR
description: Lightyear is another competitor in the U.K. market with ambitions to expand in Europe. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: TRADE REPUBLIC
description: Trade Republic, a rival of Scalable Capital among startups, has secured a full banking license from the European Central Bank. It is backed by Sequoia and was last valued at $5.3 billion in June 2022. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: ING
description: ING is one of Scalable Capital's banking partners, working with the company in lieu of it having a banking license. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: ECONOMY
description: The general state of the economy, with inflation and unfavorable interest rates, has a chilling effect on consumers' inclination to take risks and invest. [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: RANA YARED
description: Rana Yared is a general partner at Balderton Capital. She is joining the board of Scalable Capital with this round. Yared praised Scalable Capital's platform and the vision and execution of its founders, Erik and Florian, in a statement [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: ERIK
description: Erik is one of the founders of Scalable Capital, mentioned in the statement by Rana Yared, general partner at Balderton Capital [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: FLORIAN
description: Florian is one of the founders of Scalable Capital, mentioned in the statement by Rana Yared, general partner at Balderton Capital [TechCrunch, 2023-12-07]

name: DENNIS KOOKER
description: Dennis Kooker, a prominent executive at Sony Music, has been actively engaged in discussions about the impact of artificial intelligence (AI) on the music industry. In a speech given on 2023-11-30, Kooker addressed the challenges posed by unauthorized AI-generated replicas of music, while also highlighting the potential of legitimate AI startups to enhance creativity. He spoke on behalf of Sony Music, detailing the company's efforts to remove infringing AI content from online platforms and its commitment to maintaining a fair playing field for artists. Kooker further outlined the principles that Sony Music believes are essential for generative AI platforms, emphasizing the need for human creators' vision to guide AI development. These principles are aimed at ensuring the protection of intellectual property and artists' rights in the era of AI, and Kooker expressed Sony Music's desire for Congress to embrace these guidelines. Through his role as a speaker and representative of Sony Music, Kooker has become a key voice in the conversation about AI's role in the music industry.

name: NO FAKES ACT
description: The No FAKES Act is a policy drafted by senators that would create a federal property right in one’s voice or visual likeness and protect against unauthorized AI-generated replicas [Source: Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: VERMILLIO
description: Vermillio is an AI company that partnered with Sony Music Entertainment and Legacy Recordings on a generative AI project involving a reissue and remix of an album [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: THE ORB
description: The Orb is a music group that was involved in a generative AI project with Sony Music Entertainment and Vermillio [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: DAVID GILMOUR
description: David Gilmour is a musician who was involved in a generative AI project with Sony Music Entertainment and Vermillio [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: LEGACY RECORDINGS
description: Legacy Recordings is a music label that partnered with Sony Music Entertainment and Vermillio on a generative AI project [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: SONY MUSIC ENTERTAINMENT
description: Sony Music Entertainment is a part of Sony Music that has engaged in a generative AI project with The Orb, David Gilmour, and Vermillio [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI TECHNOLOGY
description: AI Technology, which has recently gone mainstream about a year ago, is a significant force in the realm of technology and entertainment, particularly in the music industry. It comprises a set of tools and techniques capable of creating music and other artistic works, driving innovation and presenting new opportunities for creators. However, the rapid adoption of AI technology has also brought to the forefront numerous issues that legislators and regulators around the world are addressing. These issues include the rights of human creators, the need for accurate recordkeeping, and the importance of transparency in the creative process. The potential impact of AI on the music industry is twofold: it can foster creativity and efficiency, but it also necessitates careful consideration of legal and ethical implications to ensure that human artists are fairly recognized and compensated for their contributions.

name: INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
description: Intellectual property is a legal concept that refers to creations of the mind, such as music, that can be protected and monetized in the new world of AI [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AARON JONES
description: Aaron Jones, a key running back for the Green Bay Packers, has been a valuable Super FLEX option with a 1.1x multiplier in the FanDuel lineup, particularly for the Thursday Night Football game against the Lions in September 2023. His health and participation are essential for the team's offensive strategy. However, as of December 7, 2023, Jones is dealing with a sprained MCL, an injury that has led to his status being considered week-to-week by the team, potentially impacting his availability and performance in upcoming games.

name: DANNY ELFMAN
description: Danny Elfman, a renowned composer celebrated for his contributions to iconic projects such as Batman, Spider-Man, The Simpsons, and the films of Tim Burton, has had a multifaceted career in the entertainment industry. Before transitioning into composing, Elfman was a member of the new wave band Oingo Boingo. Inspired by performances from Childish Gambino and Janelle Monáe at Coachella 2019, he decided to merge his cinematic compositions, Oingo Boingo hits, and experimental tracks for a dynamic live show. In 2022, Elfman made a surprising appearance at Coachella, where he showcased his new music album, "Big Mess," to an enthusiastic audience. Beyond his festival performances, he has also collaborated with director Noah Baumbach on the film "White Noise" and continues to tour, performing his symphonic works. However, Elfman's career has not been without controversy; in 2018, he faced a sexual misconduct lawsuit, which he settled out of court while vehemently denying the allegations as "vicious and wholly false." Despite this, Elfman remains a significant figure in the music and film industry, known for his innovative and influential compositions.

name: COACHELLA
description: Coachella, a renowned music festival, made headlines in 2022 when Danny Elfman took the stage, offering a unique performance that blended his iconic film music, Oingo Boingo hits, and experimental songs for an enthusiastic crowd. This rock-infused turn by Elfman, known primarily for his film scores, surprised many movie buffs and showcased his versatility as a musician. It's worth noting that the festival faced a significant setback in 2020 when it was canceled due to the COVID-19 pandemic, but it has since rebounded, continuing to attract a diverse array of musical talents and passionate audiences.

name: TIM BURTON
description: Tim Burton is a filmmaker who has collaborated with Danny Elfman on numerous projects, including films like Pee-wee’s Big Adventure, Beetlejuice, and Edward Scissorhands. [Polygon, 2023-10-13]

name: OINGO BOINGO
description: Oingo Boingo, a new wave band that Danny Elfman was a part of before he established his composing career, is known for hits such as the 1985 single "Weird Science," which marked the peak of their popularity. In a nod to his musical roots, Elfman incorporated Oingo Boingo's songs into his set at Coachella 2022, showcasing the enduring influence of the band's unique sound.

name: THE NIGHTMARE BEFORE CHRISTMAS
description: The Nightmare Before Christmas is a stop-motion film produced by Tim Burton, where Danny Elfman composed the music and provided the singing voice for Jack Skellington. [Polygon, 2023-10-13]

name: HENRY SELICK
description: Henry Selick is the director of The Nightmare Before Christmas, a film that was a transformative milestone for Danny Elfman. [Polygon, 2023-10-13]

name: WALT DISNEY ANIMATION
description: Walt Disney Animation, a renowned studio with a century-long legacy, celebrated its centennial in 2023 by releasing a new movie titled "Wish," as noted by Polygon on December 12, 2023. The studio is celebrated for its history of creating beloved animated films and iconic characters that have captured the hearts of audiences worldwide. name: USPS
description: The United States Postal Service (USPS), a significant player in the package delivery industry, recently increased the price of its Media Mail service by an average of 7 percent. Media Mail is a service primarily utilized for the shipment of media products, including books, music, and movies. This price hike comes shortly after Discogs, a popular online marketplace for music, raised its fees, potentially impacting the cost of shipping for sellers and buyers alike. Despite this, USPS continues to offer its Priority Mail Express and Priority Mail services for package delivery, with specific deadlines for Christmas delivery. Packages sent via Priority Mail Express must be dispatched by December 21st, while those sent through Priority Mail should be on their way by December 23rd to ensure arrival by Christmas Eve. For First-Class Mail packages and those sent via USPS Ground Advantage, the deadline is December 20th. These adjustments in service and pricing reflect the ongoing dynamics within the USPS, aiming to balance operational costs and customer needs during peak shipping seasons.

name: BIG WHITE
description: BIG WHITE, situated in the Okanagan Highlands of Canada, is renowned as a beginner-friendly family ski resort, catering to novice skiers and those eager to learn the art of skiing through its less steep slopes and ample shelter. Spanning 2,800 acres, the resort offers a variety of terrain, including tree runs, which are purpose-built to facilitate ski-in/ski-out access, enhancing the overall skiing experience. BIG WHITE's commitment to providing a suitable environment for beginners and intermediates, along with its focus on powder skiing, has solidified its reputation as 'Canada's favourite family resort', making it an ideal destination for families and individuals looking to enjoy the winter sports in a welcoming and accessible setting.

name: BANFF NATIONAL PARK
description: Banff National Park, a jewel of natural splendor in Canada, is renowned for its breathtaking landscapes and is home to Lake Louise, a prominent feature that also houses one of the largest ski resorts in the region. The park is not only a single destination but a hub for multiple ski resorts, providing visitors with an exceptional variety of experiences and thousands of acres to explore on skis. Its popularity among skiing enthusiasts is underscored by the stunning views and the expansive opportunities for winter sports, making it a must-visit location for anyone interested in combining the beauty of nature with the thrill of skiing. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-10-25]

name: LAKE LOUISE
description: Lake Louise is the largest ski resort in Banff National Park, offering amazing views including that of Mount Assiniboine. It has areas suitable for beginners, intermediates, and advanced skiers, with the Back Bowls being good for more advanced skiers. Most people choose to base themselves in Banff, with a 45-minute drive to Lake Louise. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-10-25]

As reported by The Independent - Life and Style on 2023-12-12, this season often marks the first time partners witness each other's interactions with their families, potentially unveiling new aspects of their significant other and fostering a deeper bond. However, the holiday season is also linked to high stress levels and heightened emotions, as indicated by a poll conducted by the American Psychological Association. These dual dynamics of intimacy and stress make the holiday season a complex yet pivotal period in the lives of many.

name: CPC ALERT AND MOBILIZATION PROCESS
description: The CPC alert and mobilization process is quicker than GDPR enforcement for addressing unfair behaviors, taking months for the network to coordinate and arrive at a position to press on a trader they believe is infringing the law ["TechCrunch", 2023-11-30]

name: DIGITAL MARKETS ACT (DMA)
description: The Digital Markets Act (DMA) is a significant EU legislation enacted to regulate the digital market landscape, specifically targeting large online platforms such as Meta. This law imposes stringent restrictions on the use of personal data for advertising purposes, mandating that platforms must obtain explicit consent from users before utilizing their data for targeted advertising. The DMA's overarching goal is to ensure fair competition within the digital markets by controlling data usage and practices of these major tech companies, thereby protecting consumer rights and promoting a level playing field for all market participants.

name: VERY LARGE ONLINE PLATFORMS (VLOPS)

name: ZAMORA
description: Zamora, a Venezuelan individual and the founder of AOG, has been recently embroiled in the airline parts scandal, where he is accused of falsifying records for aviation components. According to The Sydney Morning Herald (2023-10-16), Zamora was approached for comment through friends and his barrister regarding the scandal. The Telegraph (2023-10-16) provides additional context, noting that Zamora began his career in aviation in 2010 as an account manager at AJW before founding AOG in 2015. He is described as a savvy operator, demonstrating a deep understanding of the aviation industry, and also has a passion for technology, evidenced by his interest in techno DJing. Despite his professional acumen and personal interests, Zamora now faces serious allegations that could have significant implications for his career and the aviation industry.

name: AOG
description: AOG, a company founded by Zamora in 2015, specializes in the sale of aviation parts, particularly smaller components for jet engines. Initially growing at a steady pace, AOG experienced a significant financial upturn by early 2020, boasting net assets of £2.2 million ($4.2 million) prior to the COVID-19 lockdowns. However, the company has been embroiled in controversy, facing allegations of passing off old parts as new and falsifying records for these components. As of 2023, AOG's website is offline, and attempts to contact the company are met with hold music, indicating potential operational issues or a response to the ongoing accusations.

name: CFM
description: CFM, a prominent company in the aviation industry and a joint venture between GE and Safran, has recently been thrust into the spotlight due to a forgery scandal involving suspect turbine blades. The company, known for manufacturing jet engines, is currently in the process of auditing over 500 suppliers to determine the extent of the items that could be implicated in the scandal. Reassuringly, the parts identified thus far do not include the most critical components, known as life-limited parts, which are subjected to the highest levels of stress in a jet engine and are meticulously monitored by manufacturers during their operational life on the plane. In a related development, CFM is pursuing a legal case against AOG, alleging that the company had been engaging in fraudulent activities by passing off old aviation components as new ones, a practice that could potentially compromise the safety and reliability of jet engines. This legal action underscores CFM's commitment to upholding the highest standards of quality and integrity in the aviation industry.

name: GE
description: GE is a company that, along with Safran, forms the joint venture CFM, which manufactures engines. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-16]

name: SAFRAN
description: Safran is a company that, along with GE, forms the joint venture CFM, which manufactures engines. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-16]

name: AIRLINE PARTS
description: Airline parts are components used in the aviation industry, which must meet exacting specifications and are often certified. The market for these parts is lucrative, with some parts costing thousands of dollars. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-16]

name: VERIFICATION DOCUMENTS
description: Verification documents are important for ensuring that airline parts meet the required specifications and are certified. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-16]

name: AJW

name: MULTIFLIGHT
description: Multiflight, a Leeds-based engineering and parts supply company, is known for its expertise in the aviation industry. Steve Borrowdale, serving as the managing director of Multiflight, recently shed light on the complexities involved in the maintenance and repair of jet engines, specifically highlighting the challenges of introducing new parts into such sophisticated machinery. This insight was shared in an article published by The Sydney Morning Herald on October 16, 2023. The company's position in Leeds allows it to serve a wide range of clients, offering both engineering services and supplying essential parts for various aviation needs.

name: STEVE BORROWDALE
description: Steve Borrowdale, the managing director of Multiflight, a Leeds-based engineering and parts supply company, is deeply involved in the intricate processes of the aviation industry. Multiflight is known for its rigorous vetting of sellers, ensuring they possess the necessary experience and approval certifications. The company also meticulously inspects parts from new suppliers, demonstrating a commitment to safety and quality. Borrowdale acknowledges that sneaking unauthorized parts into a jet engine is a challenging task, and the absence of serial numbers on components could potentially simplify the process of falsifying documents. However, he emphasizes that such an act would still require a high level of skill and expertise. Through his leadership, Multiflight maintains a strong reputation for maintaining the integrity of the parts they supply, contributing to the overall safety and reliability of the aviation sector.

name: B&H WORLDWIDE
description: B&H Worldwide is a logistics firm that partnered with AOG to distribute parts from its hub in Frankfurt. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-16]

name: THE TELEGRAPH, UK

This marked a significant shift, as it was the first instance of a federal judge having the authority to make decisions for a substantial number of these cases, thereby streamlining the legal proceedings. According to TechCrunch on 2023-10-30, Tears of the Kingdom is a strong contender for the prestigious Game of the Year award for 2023. The game has been widely praised for its successful blend of old and new, making it a standout title in the Zelda franchise and a must-play for fans of the series and newcomers alike."

name: WORLD OF WARCRAFT

Developed by Blizzard Entertainment, the game has seen extensive evolution over the years, akin to the ship of Theseus, where practically every feature and zone has been remade and refined. In 2019, Blizzard Entertainment responded to the nostalgia of its vast community by launching World of Warcraft Classic, alongside the modern version of the game, allowing players to experience the game in its original form as well as enjoy the updated features and content of the current iteration. This dual offering caters to both the veterans who long for the early days of Azeroth and the newcomers who are eager to explore the rich, ever-changing world of Warcraft."

Gamers want to revisit their favorite games as they originally were, and developers who re-release games pay attention to their communities. The demand for nostalgia in gaming is driven by the love for classic games [TechCrunch, 2023-10-30]

Despite this setback, the team fought hard, giving themselves a chance to win, and their coach expressed pride in their effort. The All Blacks never consider themselves favorites, understanding that in high-stakes games, performance must be at its peak. They are potentially on the brink of making history as the first team to win the Webb Ellis Cup for a third time, a testament to their skill and dedication. The team's members are defending their reputation after a spray, further highlighting their commitment to the sport and their country.

In 2016, Bill Kenwright, a long-standing figure in the club, sold a 49.9% stake to Farhad Moshiri, marking a significant shift in ownership. Moshiri later increased his shares to a commanding 94%, becoming the majority shareholder. This transition, however, was not without its challenges. The club faced a tough battle against relegation, a situation that put immense pressure on the team and its management. Additionally, fan confidence in Kenwright waned, reflecting the broader community's concerns about the direction and stability of the club.

Despite these hurdles, Everton Football Club continues to navigate the complexities of professional sports, demonstrating resilience and the capacity to adapt to changing circumstances. name: THAI FOOD NEAR ME
description: Thai Food Near Me is a Thai restaurant situated in the bustling Murray Hill neighborhood of Manhattan, New York. The restaurant's name, which went viral in the spring of 2023, is a clever play on a common Google search term, designed to leverage SEO and capitalize on the search algorithm for enhanced online discoverability. Despite the name's intention to game the Google search algorithm, its notoriety has primarily been driven by word of mouth and online mentions. Interestingly, the location has seen at least four other Thai restaurants come and go, as evidenced by records on defunct delivery and review websites. In August 2023, Travis stumbled upon Thai Food Near Me on Yelp while searching for nearby dining options, further highlighting the restaurant's digital presence and appeal to those craving authentic Thai cuisine.

name: SEO
description:
SEO, or Search Engine Optimization, is a multifaceted profession and concept that involves the strategic enhancement of online content to improve a website's ranking in search engine results, particularly on Google. This set of strategies, used by individuals and businesses alike, became increasingly regulated and mainstream around the turn of the century, leading to a higher demand for SEO consultants. SEO professionals, such as Duane Forrester, Cade Lee, Missy Ward, and Daron Babin, have worked in this field both before and after significant shifts in the industry, including Google's takeover of the search engine market.

The practice of SEO includes both "white hat" tactics, which are approved by search engines, and "black hat" tactics, which manipulate search engine algorithms. The latter has been criticized for distorting search results and affecting the usefulness of search engines. Some SEOs have engaged in guideline-violating tactics to achieve higher rankings, which can alter the online experience for users. For instance, Daron Babin used SEO to promote offshore casinos and Viagra, while Missy Ward started doing SEO as early as 1998.

SEO professionals are often stereotyped as individuals willing to bend rules for higher visibility and financial gain, which can sometimes lead to discomfort in customer meetings. Despite this stereotype, many SEOs are concerned about the changes in Google's operations and the impact on their ability to optimize effectively. Google has improved over time at catching SEOs playing tricks on the algorithm, which has led to a more regulated environment.

SEOs, or Search Engine Optimizers, are known for their access to a lot of money and the lavish lifestyle they lead at conferences and events. They are eager to let loose in person after years of being friends online, showcasing a vibrant community aspect to the profession. Thai Food Near Me is an example of a business that uses SEO to improve its ranking in Google search results, demonstrating the practical application of SEO in the real world. The actions of SEOs matter for all of us on a daily basis, as they can significantly influence how we perceive the world through search engine results.
