Cardholders earn "Rewards Points" that can be redeemed at a rate of 1 cent per point, with points earnings rounded to the nearest whole number. The card allows for immediate redemption to offset the credit card balance, direct deposit into a Fifth Third checking or savings account, and automatic redemptions, enhancing convenience and flexibility.

The Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card provides additional perks such as cell phone protection, contactless payments, and the ability to easily lock the card through the Fifth Third mobile app, ensuring security and peace of mind. It also includes Mastercard ID Theft Protection, further safeguarding cardholders' financial information.

For those considering balance transfers, the card offers an introductory 0% APR for the first 12 billing cycles after account opening, transitioning to a variable APR of 20.74%–29.99% thereafter. Contrary to one of the descriptions, the card does not charge foreign transaction fees, making it a suitable choice for international travel. There is no convenience check fee, and late payment fees can reach up to $40.

The lack of an annual fee means that the card can benefit the credit profile even if not used regularly, providing a low-maintenance option for maintaining a positive credit history. However, it does not currently offer a welcome bonus to new members, and its benefits are relatively slim compared to other cards in the market. Card details are accurate as of the publish date (2023-11-13) but are subject to change at any time at the discretion of the issuer.

name: FIFTH THIRD
description: Fifth Third, a financial institution primarily operating in the Midwest with branches spanning from Illinois to West Virginia and down to Florida, offers a variety of banking services including checking and savings accounts. The bank is notably associated with the Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card, a credit card designed with a simple rewards structure and no annual fee. This card is exclusive to those who already have an established relationship with Fifth Third. Cardholders enjoy the flexibility of redeeming their cash back rewards either as a direct deposit into their Fifth Third checking or savings account or as a statement credit, enhancing their banking experience and financial management capabilities.

name: CREDIT CARD REWARDS
description: Credit card rewards refer to the benefits, such as cash back, points, or miles, that credit card issuers offer to cardholders for using their cards. The Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card offers a 1.67% return rate on all purchases. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: CREDIT CARD FEES
description: Credit card fees are charges that cardholders may incur for various transactions or actions, such as annual fees, foreign transaction fees, convenience check fees, and late payment fees. The Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card has no annual fee, no foreign transaction fee, and a late payment fee of up to $40. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: CREDIT CARD APR
description: Credit card APR (Annual Percentage Rate) is the interest rate charged on unpaid balances. The Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card offers an introductory 0% APR for balance transfers for the first 12 billing cycles after account opening, with a variable APR of 20.74%–29.99% thereafter. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: STATEMENT CREDIT
description: Statement credit is a redemption option available for the rewards earned with both the Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card and the American Express Cash Magnet® Card. For the Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card, cardholders can instantly apply their points as a statement credit to offset their balance right after the rewards are posted to their account, with no minimum redemption threshold. In contrast, for the American Express Cash Magnet® Card, statement credits are also a means to redeem rewards but are applied to the account within three days of redemption. However, it's important to note that these statement credits cannot be used to cover the minimum amount due on the card.

name: DIRECT DEPOSIT
description: Direct deposit is a redemption option for the rewards earned with the Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card. Cardholders can request a direct deposit into their Fifth Third checking or savings account if they don't currently have a balance on their credit card or if they'd like to use their funds in some way. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: APPLE PAY
description: Apple Pay is a contactless payment service that allows users to add their Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card for touch-free payments [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: GOOGLE PAY
description: Google Pay is a contactless payment service that allows users to add their Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card for touch-free payments [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: SAMSUNG PAY
description: Samsung Pay is a contactless payment service that allows users to add their Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card for touch-free payments [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: FIFTH THIRD MOBILE APP
description: The Fifth Third mobile app is a tool that allows cardholders to activate and deactivate their Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card at will, providing a way to lock the card if it goes missing [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: MASTERCARD ID THEFT PROTECTION
description: Mastercard ID Theft Protection is a service that monitors the internet, including the dark and deep web, for any compromised sensitive information of Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card holders [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: CAPITAL ONE QUICKSILVER CASH REWARDS CREDIT CARD
description: The Capital One Quicksilver Cash Rewards Credit Card is a no annual fee credit card that offers an unlimited 1.5% cash back return on all purchases. It also provides additional benefits such as 5% cash back on hotels and rental cars booked through Capital One Travel, a $200 welcome bonus after spending $500 in the first 3 months, and six months of free Uber One membership through Nov. 14, 2024. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: CITI® DOUBLE CASH CARD
description: The Citi® Double Cash Card is a no annual fee credit card that earns 1% back when a purchase is made and 1% back when the purchase is paid off, resulting in a 2% cash back return everywhere. However, it lacks certain benefits such as a welcome bonus, foreign transaction fee waiver, and cell phone insurance. [Source: Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: CASH BACK REWARDS
description: Cash back rewards are a financial benefit offered by the Fifth Third 1.67% Cash/Back Card. Cardholders earn a fixed 1.67% return for all purchases [Fortune, 2023-11-13]

name: IOT ANALYTICS
description: IoT Analytics is a company that provides insights and analysis on the Internet of Things (IoT) and related technologies. They have defined digital twins and analyzed the digital twin market in a March 2023 article and a report[IoT Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: DIGITAL TWINS
description: Digital twins are a virtual model replicating the behavior of an existing or a potential real-world asset, system, or multiple systems. IoT Analytics has presented a three-dimensional, cuboid model to classify digital twins based on life cycle phase, hierarchical levels, and use/purpose of implementation[IoT Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: DIGITAL TWIN MARKET
description: The digital twin market, as defined by IoT Analytics, revolves around the software spending for digital twin solutions. This market is segmented into two categories: the broad digital twin market, which encompasses all software solutions offering digital twin capabilities, and the narrow digital twin market, focusing solely on the expenditure for software specifically designed for digital twin applications. As of 2023, the market is witnessing a significant expansion, largely fueled by organizations' commitment to sustainability. A report by the Capgemini Research Institute in 2022 revealed that 57% of surveyed organizations cited improving sustainability as a primary motivation for investing in digital twin technology, while 51% were confident that digital twins would facilitate the achievement of their environmental sustainability objectives. This trend highlights the increasing recognition of digital twins as a crucial tool in the pursuit of sustainable business practices.

name: SUSTAINABILITY
description: Sustainability is a concept that refers to meeting the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs. It has been discussed in approximately 21% of recent CEO earnings calls and is a tailwind macro factor for the digital twin market[IoT Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: CAPGEMINI RESEARCH INSTITUTE
description: The Capgemini Research Institute, a renowned organization dedicated to exploring and analyzing various technological topics, released a significant report in 2022 focusing on the digital twin market. According to the findings published by the Institute and corroborated by IoT Business News on November 18, 2023, 57% of organizations surveyed are actively investigating the use of digital twins as a means to enhance their sustainability efforts. Furthermore, the report highlighted that 51% of these organizations are optimistic that digital twins will play a pivotal role in achieving their environmental sustainability objectives. This data underscores the growing recognition of digital twins as a strategic tool for organizations looking to improve their environmental impact and operational efficiency.

name: SUSTAINABILITY GOALS
description: Sustainability goals are a major factor driving the growth of the digital twin market. Many companies are exploring digital twins to optimize resource usage, reduce carbon emissions, and improve supply and transportation networks. [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: ADEN
description: Aden, a Chinese integrated facility service provider, created a digital twin for one of its commercial centers in Chengdu, China. The digital twin was designed to help facility managers inspect, maintain, and repair building assets. 3D simulations assist facility managers in visualizing, predicting, and optimizing energy consumption, and the expected benefits include lower annual energy consumption, water usage, and waste. [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: SIEMENS
description:
Siemens, a renowned technology company, has developed a groundbreaking prototype virtual sensor for large motor applications, leveraging digital twin technology. This innovative sensor simulates the operation of a physical sensor inside a motor, enabling operators to monitor the motor's temperature in real-time through augmented reality (AR) headsets. The development of this virtual sensor is part of Siemens' strategy to address challenges in motor temperature monitoring and enhance revenue opportunities.

Moreover, Siemens has expanded its partnership with AWS to further explore and advance digital twin technology, demonstrating their commitment to staying at the forefront of technological innovation. In addition to this collaboration, Siemens has joined forces with Ansys and Microsoft, integrating physics-based simulation capabilities with Azure Digital Twin and IoT data. These strategic partnerships underscore Siemens' dedication to creating comprehensive and sophisticated solutions for their clients, combining the strengths of various tech giants to deliver cutting-edge digital twin applications.

name: MICROSOFT AZURE
description: Microsoft Azure is a cloud hyperscaler that has introduced digital twin platforms like Azure Digital Twins, which allows for interconnecting various data sources and building digital twin topology. They have partnered with Ansys to help customers envision digital twins on a large scale by integrating physics-based simulation capabilities with Azure Digital Twin and IoT data.

name: ANSYS
description: Ansys is a simulation company that brings specialized expertise in creating accurate, high-fidelity models of physical entities. They have partnered with Microsoft Azure to integrate physics-based simulation capabilities with Azure Digital Twin and IoT data to allow Twin Builder users to run scenarios and obtain predictions on how their systems will behave.

name: TATA CONSULTANCY SERVICES
description: Tata Consultancy Services is a company that has collaborated with Ansys and Microsoft to integrate Ansys’s Twin Builder’s physics-based simulation capabilities with Azure Digital Twin and IoT data.

name: DIGITAL TWIN
description: Digital twin is a technology that allows for the simulation of physical assets in a virtual environment. It is being used by companies like Siemens, AWS, Microsoft Azure, and Ansys to create more robust, responsive, and accurate data twins that can be scaled and integrated seamlessly into broader IT ecosystems.

name: PLATTFORM INDUSTRIE 4.0
description: Plattform Industrie 4.0, as detailed in the Iot Business News article dated 2023-11-18, is an organization that has forged a partnership with CESMII. The primary objective of this collaboration is to develop and implement standards that facilitate smart, sustainable competition among manufacturers in both Germany and the United States. By establishing these guidelines, Plattform Industrie 4.0 and CESMII aim to enhance the capabilities of manufacturers to operate efficiently and competitively in the era of Industry 4.0, leveraging technology to drive innovation and sustainability.

name: CESMII
description: CESMII, the Clean Energy Smart Manufacturing Innovation Institute, has forged a significant partnership with Plattform Industrie 4.0, as reported by Iot Business News on November 18, 2023. This collaboration is aimed at establishing comprehensive standards for manufacturers in both Germany and the United States. The primary goal is to enhance smart, sustainable competition by addressing the challenges associated with Industry 4.0 and Smart Manufacturing, ensuring that these entities can operate more efficiently and responsibly in the evolving technological landscape.

name: DTC DIGITAL TWIN INTEROPERABILITY FRAMEWORK
description: The Digital Twin Consortium (DTC) released the Digital Twin System Interoperability Framework to unify a nascent ecosystem of high-value, multi-vendor services that can seamlessly ‘plug into’ a multi-dimensional, interoperable system of systems [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: DTC
description: DTC, the Digital Twin Consortium, is a collaborative partnership of industry, academia, and government experts that aims to accelerate the development and adoption of digital twin-enabling technologies [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: IDTA<||INDUSTRIAL DIGITAL TWIN ASSOCIATION
description: IDTA, the Industrial Digital Twin Association, collaborated with DTC to work on standardization requirements, enabling interoperability through discussions, aligning work in horizontal domains, and collaborating on open-source projects, contributions, and reference implementations [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: OPC FOUNDATION
description: OPC Foundation collaborated with DTC to accelerate the development and adoption of digital twin-enabling technologies, promoting interoperability standards and processes to advance the use of digital twins in manufacturing across multiple industries [Iot Business News, 2023-11-18]

name: DIGITAL TWIN TECHNOLOGIES
description: Digital twin technologies are a type of technology that creates virtual replicas of physical objects or systems, often used for monitoring and predictive maintenance in various industries. The importance of interoperability between digital twin technologies and existing systems is a concern for businesses, as mentioned in "Digital twin market: Analyzing growth and 4 emerging trends" published by Iot Business News on 2023-11-18

name: IOT BUSINESS NEWS
description: Iot Business News is a news source that published an article titled "Digital twin market: Analyzing growth and 4 emerging trends" on 2023-11-18, discussing the growth of the digital twin market and emerging trends

name: EXISTING SYSTEMS
description: Existing systems refer to the current software solutions and technologies used by businesses in their operations. Interoperability with digital twin technologies is a concern for these systems, as highlighted in "Digital twin market: Analyzing growth and 4 emerging trends" published by Iot Business News on 2023-11-18

name: DUBAI
description: Dubai, a city in the United Arab Emirates, is renowned for its luxury, rich history, and heritage, providing a myriad of activities and experiences that change with the seasons. In the winter, visitors can immerse themselves in the city's past, exploring its historical sites and cultural landmarks. By May, Dubai transforms into a sunseeker's paradise, boasting average temperatures around 30 degrees, ideal for enjoying its numerous beach clubs, splash parks, and sunset cruises. The city is also a hub for events, hosting the prestigious Dubai Design Week, the delightful Dubai Food Festival, and the entertaining Dubai Comedy Festival, catering to a variety of interests. This comprehensive guide to Dubai's seasonal offerings was published by The Independent - Travel on 2023-11-17, providing insights into the city's diverse experiences for travelers seeking winter sun or springtime breaks.

name: BRITISH AIRWAYS HOLIDAYS
description: British Airways Holidays, a trusted name in the travel industry, offers exceptional value breaks in Dubai, ensuring quality and peace of mind for its customers. The company provides ATOL protection, which safeguards travelers in the event of unforeseen circumstances, along with flexible payment options for convenience. British Airways Holidays also includes a 23 kg baggage allowance per person, catering to the needs of its travelers, and a 24-hour dedicated support helpline for assistance at any time. These features, mentioned in The Independent - Travel on 2023-11-17, highlight the comprehensive services British Airways Holidays provides, making it a reliable choice for those seeking a stress-free travel experience.

name: ATOL
description: ATOL is an organization that provides protection for travelers booking with British Airways Holidays, ensuring safety and security for both the traveler and their money [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI DESERT
description: Dubai's desert offers a wealth of outdoor activities during the winter months, including dune buggies, quad biking, and desert safaris [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: ARABIAN ORYX
description: The Arabian Oryx is a species of antelope that can be found in the Dubai desert and was saved from the brink of extinction [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUNE SAFARIS
description: Dune safaris are a traditional activity in Dubai's desert, offering experiences like henna tattooing, dance shows, and culminating in an evening BBQ dinner [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI CREEK
description: Dubai Creek, situated in the historic Deira district of Dubai, is a significant waterway that offers a unique blend of traditional and modern experiences. As noted by The Independent - Travel on 2023-11-17, it is here that travelers can find the traditional wooden boats known as abras, which are the oldest form of public transport in the city. These boats provide a short trip across the river, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in local life and culture. Additionally, Dubai Creek is a prime location for an evening dinner cruise, where one can enjoy the stunning night lights of the city while dining, offering a memorable way to experience Dubai's vibrant atmosphere.

name: AL FAHIDI HISTORICAL NEIGHBOURHOOD
description: The Al Fahidi Historical Neighbourhood is a historic area in Dubai located along the creek. It features original buildings and preserved infrastructure, including traditional wind towers and the Al Fahidi Fort, one of the oldest buildings in Dubai, built in 1787. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: HATTA
description: Hatta is a nearby area to Dubai with craggy mountains and lush valleys that cradle citadels, towers, and forts. It offers historical and heritage sites, as well as scenic views from the Hajar mountains, one of the highest ranges in the Arabian peninsula. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: HATTA HERITAGE VILLAGE
description: Hatta Heritage Village is a reconstruction of a traditional mountain village in Hatta. It provides insights into how life was lived centuries ago. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI DESIGN WEEK
description: Dubai Design Week is the region’s largest creative festival, held around the start of November. It highlights pioneering designers and creative works through exhibitions, installations, talks, workshops, and markets. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: THE DUBAI FOOD FESTIVAL
description: The Dubai Food Festival is an event that celebrates the local culinary scene, held at the beginning of May. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI COMEDY FESTIVAL
description: The Dubai Comedy Festival, a highly anticipated event in the entertainment calendar of Dubai, takes place later in May. This festival is renowned for gathering some of the most celebrated names in the comedy world, offering a delightful showcase of humor and cultural activities. Despite the descriptions being identical, the information is reaffirmed, indicating the festival's consistent commitment to providing top-tier comedic entertainment. The event is widely covered by media outlets such as The Independent, highlighting its significance in the regional and international comedy scene.

name: AKIRA BACK
description: Akira Back is a restaurant in Dubai that serves Japanese dishes prepared with Korean and international flavors. It has a huge terrace with incredible views across Dubai Marina. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: FISH BEACH TAVERNA
description: Fish Beach Taverna is a restaurant in Dubai known for Aegean seafood served in a coastal setting. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: SĀN BEACH
description: SĀN Beach is a beach club in Dubai where visitors can relax in luxury cabanas or on daybeds. [The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI FOOD FESTIVAL
description: The Dubai Food Festival is an event that celebrates the local culinary scene and takes place at the beginning of the month, highlighting the diverse food culture in Dubai[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: WILD WADI WATERPARK
description: Wild Wadi is Dubai's first-ever waterpark, known for its exhilarating rides, surfing machines, and wave pool, providing fun for adults and kids alike[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: LAGUNA WATERPARK
description: Laguna Waterpark is one of the newer water parks in Dubai, located on the coast with an infinity pool, its own beach, thrilling slides, and a boat-themed kids pool[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: BURJ KHALIFA
description: The Burj Khalifa is an iconic landmark in Dubai, offering stunning sunset views across the city[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: BURJ AL ARAB
description: The Burj Al Arab is a landmark in Dubai known for its night-time lights[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI FRAME
description: The Dubai Frame is a 153-metre-high structure resembling a massive picture frame, providing incredible views of Old and New Dubai[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: DUBAI OPERA
description: The Dubai Opera is a venue for indoor concerts and theatre shows, offering entertainment with air-conditioned comfort[The Independent - Travel, 2023-11-17]

name: BRITISH AIRWAYS
description: British Airways, a renowned airline company, offers a diverse range of travel services as highlighted in a seasonal guide by The Independent - Travel on 2023-11-17. The entity is celebrated for providing flights and hotel deals for travel to Dubai, catering to the needs of individuals seeking to explore the vibrant city. Moreover, British Airways enables its customers to utilize Avios, a loyalty program currency, to pay for flights and even part-pay for holidays, enhancing the flexibility and affordability of travel experiences. This dual functionality of Avios for flights and holiday packages underscores British Airways' commitment to rewarding customer loyalty and providing comprehensive travel solutions.

name: AARON RODGERS
description: Aaron Rodgers, a professional football player known for his tenure as the quarterback for the Green Bay Packers, made headlines in the summer of 2022 when he revealed that he had taken ayahuasca. Rodgers credited this experience with significantly enhancing his performance, leading to two of the best seasons of his career with the Packers. However, in a significant turn of events, Rodgers is no longer with the Green Bay Packers as of the 2023 season, marking a notable change in the team's lineup. Despite his departure, his impact on the Packers, especially during the seasons following his ayahuasca experience, remains a topic of interest and discussion in the NFL community.

name: MYR GIBBS
description: Myr Gibbs is a player for the Lions, a football team, and is featured as a Super FLEX option with a 1.2x multiplier in the FanDuel lineup for the Thursday Night Football game against the Packers. [Source: Sporting News, 2023-09-26]

name: BRAZIL HEAT WAVE
description: A heat wave in Brazil forced Taylor Swift to postpone the second night of her Eras Tour shows in Rio de Janeiro. The decision came after one of Swift's fans died during her first performance in the country [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: ANA CLARA BENEVIDES
description: Ana Clara Benevides is a 23-year-old fan of Taylor Swift who died from a cardiac arrest during Swift's first performance in Brazil. Swift postponed a show in Rio de Janeiro following Benevides' death [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: SWIFT'S VERSION ALBUMS
description: Swift's Version albums are re-recorded versions of Taylor Swift's first six studio albums, released after the original master recordings were sold to an investment fund. The albums include Fearless (Taylor's Version), Red (Taylor's Version), Speak Now (Taylor's Version), and 1989 (Taylor's Version) [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: BIG MACHINE RECORDS
description: Big Machine Records is Taylor Swift's longtime label, which was acquired by music mogul Scooter Braun in 2019, leading to the loss of the master recordings of Swift's first six studio albums [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: SCOOTER BRAUN
description: Scooter Braun is a music mogul who acquired Taylor Swift's longtime label, Big Machine Records, in 2019, gaining the rights to the master recordings of Swift's first six studio albums. He later sold the masters to an investment fund in a deal believed to be over $300 million [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: TREE PAINE
description: Tree Paine is Taylor Swift's publicist, who was forced to publicly deny rumors about Swift's relationship with Joe Alwyn [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-12-06]

name: SAMU KEREVI
description: Samu Kerevi, a dedicated Wallabies rugby player from Australia, has been actively contributing to the team's improvement efforts. Despite facing some challenges during the Rugby World Cup, which led to his disappointment in his performance, Kerevi managed to regain his form by the end of a couple of matches. Interestingly, he was temporarily replaced by Lalakai Foketi for the pool win against Portugal. However, Kerevi has made it clear that he has no intentions of retiring from international rugby. A notable fan of Eddie Jones, the team's coach, Kerevi acknowledges and appreciates the hard work and dedication Jones invests in the team, even when the outcomes do not meet their high expectations. Recently, Kerevi was spotted at Stade Roger Baudras during a training session, demonstrating his commitment to honing his skills and contributing to the Wallabies' success.

name: LALAKAI FOKETI
description: Lalakai Foketi is a rugby player who replaced Samu Kerevi in the lineup for the pool win against Portugal at the Rugby World Cup. [Wide World Of Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: WILL SKELTON

name: WIDE WORLD OF SPORTS
description: Wide World Of Sports is a media outlet that interviewed Samu Kerevi and asked him to deliver a message to disillusioned Wallabies fans [Wide World Of Sports, 2023-10-07]

name: AUSTRALIAN RUGBY
description: Australian Rugby is a sport with a history of influence from rugby league and AFL, and has been more professional than the rest of the world when it was amateur. The sport is currently facing challenges in player development and system change, as highlighted by the performance in the recent tournament and the need for reform.[]

name: RUGBY AUSTRALIA (RA)
description: Rugby Australia (RA) is the governing body for rugby in Australia. It is involved in the reform of the game at a high-performance level and has proposed a centralised high-performance program. RA's involvement in Les Kiss' appointment as Reds coach is also mentioned.[]

name: LES KISS
description: Les Kiss is a former State of Origin winger turned coach who has spent the best part of two decades coaching in Ireland and England. He was appointed as Reds coach by Rugby Australia.[]

name: BRAD THORN
description: Brad Thorn is a person who was replaced by Les Kiss as the Reds coach.[]

name: ACT BRUMBIES
description: The ACT Brumbies is a rugby team in Australia that is part of the Australian Super Rugby sides. It is mentioned in the context of not wanting to give up its commercial assets.[]

name: CENTRALISED HIGH-PERFORMANCE PROGRAM
description: A centralised high-performance program is a proposed reform in Australian Rugby aimed at maximizing the development of players. It would include a national player-contracting model, and alignment of key high-performance staff, such as coaching, strength and conditioning, and medical to operate as one national system.[]

name: GARETH SOUTHGATE
description: Gareth Southgate is the coach of the England national football team. Source: The Independent - Sports, 2023-11-15

name: MASON MOUNT
description: MASON MOUNT, a professional football player, recently transitioned from Chelsea to Manchester United, as reported by The Independent - Sports on 2023-11-15. His departure from Chelsea opened up opportunities in the attacking midfield positions for other players within the team. Despite the move, Mason Mount's skills and abilities are anticipated to significantly contribute to Manchester United's attacking strategy, as noted by The Guardian on 2023-12-06. name: AMERICAN EXPRESS CASH MAGNET® CARD
description:
The American Express Cash Magnet\u00ae Card is a credit card designed to provide users with a straightforward cash back reward system. It offers a flat rate of 1.5% cash back on all purchases, making it a no-nonsense addition to one's wallet. The card comes with no annual fee and provides an introductory 0% APR for the first 15 months on purchases and balance transfers, which can be beneficial for new cardholders looking to finance large purchases or consolidate debt. Rewards are redeemed as statement credits, simplifying the redemption process.

Despite its attractive cash back rate and fee structure, the American Express Cash Magnet\u00ae Card may not be the ideal choice for frequent international travelers. It charges foreign transaction fees, which can add up when used abroad. Additionally, the card's travel benefits are limited compared to other cards in the American Express lineup, lacking comprehensive travel insurance or perks such as airport lounge access.

However, the card does offer some additional benefits to enhance the user experience. American Express Experiences provide cardholders with access to exclusive events and offers. The car rental loss and damage insurance can offer peace of mind when renting a vehicle. The Global Assist Hotline is available to assist with emergencies while traveling, and the Plan It feature allows cardholders to manage large purchases by breaking them into monthly payments with a fixed fee. Overall, the American Express Cash Magnet\u00ae Card is a solid choice for individuals seeking a simple cash back card with no annual fee, but it may not be the best option for those who frequently travel abroad or require extensive travel benefits.

It is also the setting for a mainline quest that involves lifting a curse, a critical objective that must be completed to progress in the game. name: MEDITERRANEAN LIFESTYLE
description:
The Mediterranean lifestyle, a traditional way of living centered around a plant-based diet, is rich in fruits, vegetables, legumes, nuts, whole grains, and healthy oils, particularly olive oil. This lifestyle advocates for a moderated consumption of fish and dairy products, while red and processed meats or sweets are consumed very rarely. Spices are preferred over salt to enhance the flavor of dishes, reflecting a culinary tradition that values freshness and health. Communal meals are a cornerstone of the Mediterranean lifestyle, fostering social connections and conviviality. Regular physical activity and the inclusion of a short midday nap, known as a siesta, are also integral to this lifestyle, promoting overall well-being.

Research has shown that the Mediterranean lifestyle is not only feasible but also adaptable to local contexts, as demonstrated in a study conducted in the UK over ten years. Participants who adopted this lifestyle experienced a reduced risk of cancer and cardiovascular disease. Moreover, the use of fresh, local products and ingredients in meals, a key feature of the Mediterranean lifestyle, has been linked to lower all-cause and cause-specific mortality rates, as reported in the Mayo Clinic proceedings in 2023. These findings underscore the potential health benefits of embracing the Mediterranean lifestyle, regardless of geographical location.

name: MERCEDES SOTOS-PRIETO
description: Mercedes Sotos-Prieto is an assistant professor at the Department of Preventive Medicine, Public Health, and Microbiology at the Universidad Autónoma de Madrid. She is involved in research exploring the feasibility and impact of adopting the Mediterranean diet and lifestyle among non-Mediterranean populations. [Source: Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: UNIVERSIDAD AUTÓNOMA DE MADRID
description: The Universidad Autónoma de Madrid is an educational institution where Mercedes Sotos-Prieto works as an assistant professor. It is also the base for research on the Mediterranean lifestyle. [Source: Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: HARVARD CHAN SCHOOL OF PUBLIC HEALTH
description: The Harvard Chan School of Public Health is an educational institution in the USA that collaborates with the Universidad Autónoma de Madrid in research on the Mediterranean lifestyle and its impact on non-Mediterranean populations. [Source: Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: MEDLIFE INDEX
description: The MEDLIFE index, a comprehensive Mediterranean lifestyle assessment tool, was designed and developed by Sotos-Prieto and her team. This index, detailed in Advanced Science News on 2023-09-26, evaluates an individual's adherence to the Mediterranean way of life through a questionnaire. It focuses on three main components: food consumption, dietary habits, and physical activity. Beyond just diet and exercise, the MEDLIFE index also takes into account rest, social habits, and conviviality, providing a holistic view of lifestyle. It serves as a valuable tool for researchers to analyze the health benefits of a Mediterranean-like lifestyle, capturing the synergistic effects of various lifestyle aspects and enabling the dissection of the influence of individual components, such as hours of sleep and socializing with friends.

name: SOTOS-PRIETO
description: Sotos-Prieto is a distinguished scientist recognized for contributing significantly to the fields of health and lifestyle studies. In a recent publication by Advanced Science News on September 26, 2023, Sotos-Prieto discussed the intricate relationship between napping and cardiovascular diseases, highlighting the positive effects of short naps on heart health. Additionally, Sotos-Prieto led a comprehensive study that evaluated the impact of a Mediterranean-like lifestyle on overall health, specifically focusing on the MEDLIFE index components. The scientist explained the associations between these components and mortality rates, suggesting that the benefits of the Mediterranean lifestyle might be underestimated due to insufficient data on key variables such as olive oil consumption. Through these studies, Sotos-Prieto has provided valuable insights into how lifestyle choices can influence health outcomes, emphasizing the importance of both rest and diet in maintaining cardiovascular health.

name: OLIVE OIL CONSUMPTION
description: Olive oil consumption is a prominent component of the Mediterranean diet that was not fully accounted for in the study due to lack of detailed information, potentially leading to an underestimation of the Mediterranean lifestyle's health benefits [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: SIESTA
description: The siesta, a traditional brief afternoon nap in Mediterranean countries, was found to have an unclear health impact in the study, with specific napping habits associated with higher risk of mortality and cardiovascular disease, but the researchers did not have detailed information on frequency and duration, which weakens their conclusion [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: NAPPING
description: Napping is an activity that, when short in duration (0 to 30 minutes), is associated with lower incident cardiovascular disease [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: CARDIOVASCULAR DISEASES
description: Cardiovascular diseases are health conditions that can be influenced by napping duration, with short naps showing a lower incidence [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: MEDITERRANEAN DIET
description: The Mediterranean diet is a part of the Mediterranean lifestyle that emphasizes the use of fresh, local products and ingredients [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

name: CULTURAL ADAPTATION
description: Cultural adaptation refers to the process of making the Mediterranean lifestyle more appealing and practical for diverse populations in non-Mediterranean countries [Advanced Science News, 2023-09-26]

description: Nijisanji, a prominent VTuber (Virtual YouTuber) agency, is known for its stringent policies that include nondisclosure agreements (NDAs) enforced upon its talents. These NDAs are designed to protect the identities of the VTubers and the reasons behind their graduations from the agency, ensuring a level of privacy and security. Additionally, Nijisanji offers its talents a platform for content creation, fostering a creative environment while also maintaining certain restrictions on the type of content they can produce post-contract expiration. This dual approach of supporting VTuber creativity while safeguarding proprietary information reflects the agency's commitment to both its talents' growth and the preservation of its unique brand and community dynamics.

name: HOLOLIVE
description: Hololive, a prominent VTuber (Virtual YouTuber) agency, experienced a significant 50% growth in its 2023 financial report, showcasing its success and expansion in the virtual content creation industry. However, the agency has been noted for providing its creators with limited freedom in terms of presentation, as they are often strictly tied to the avatars associated with Hololive, which can impact the personal branding and creative expression of the talents. In a recent development, Hololive announced the shutdown of its Chinese division and the graduation of talents from its Holostars division, with minimal details provided to the public, indicating potential strategic shifts or challenges within the company's global operations. Despite these changes, Hololive continues to be a major player in the VTuber scene, managing a roster of digital entertainers who engage with audiences through live streams, videos, and social media, primarily in Japanese and English-speaking markets.

name: HOUSING MARKET
description: The housing market in the U.S., a significant economic sector, has been a topic of concern and analysis as of 2023. Initially, there were warnings of a potential crash attributed to the rapid escalation of home prices and the high mortgage rates, as reported by Fortune on October 6, 2023. However, the market was also noted for potentially retaining some of its momentum due to the demographic advantage of millennials reaching prime homebuying age and the steady issuance of single-family building permits. Despite these factors, the housing market has indeed entered a downturn, with existing home sales plummeting to levels reminiscent of the Great Recession. This downturn, described as a 'deep freeze', has set in earlier than anticipated, as reported by Fortune on October 20, 2023. The confluence of surging prices, high mortgage rates, and unexpected sales decline presents a complex scenario for the housing market's future.

name: GREAT RECESSION
description: The Great Recession was a significant economic downturn that occurred around 2008, often used as a benchmark for comparing current economic conditions. The housing market is currently experiencing sales levels similar to those seen during the Great Recession, as noted by Fortune on 2023-10-20.

name: DAVID BASZUCKI
description: David Baszucki, the CEO of Roblox, a gaming and metaverse platform, envisions the company as a next-generation social network and communication tool with a goal of reaching a billion daily active users. Baszucki is leading Roblox's efforts to grow and expand its platform, targeting a broad age demographic, including adults, and exploring the integration of AI technologies to enhance the user experience. He believes in the long-term potential of VR for immersive 3D experiences and is committed to ensuring Roblox performs well on all devices. During an interview at the Code Conference, Baszucki discussed the company's plans to expand its audience to adults, the integration of AI into the platform's operations, and the reasons for the delay in adding PlayStation support, emphasizing the focus on mobile quality and the expansion of the creator community's business opportunities. Additionally, he is optimistic about Roblox's future in China and is working on an autonomous version of the platform for the Chinese market. The company's expansion strategy includes hiring and, when necessary, layoffs to align with business needs. Baszucki's vision for Roblox includes the potential for virtual doppelgangers in a virtual space and the exploration of hosting a dating app, further diversifying the platform's offerings.

name: CODE CONFERENCE
description: The Code Conference is an event where David Baszucki, CEO of Roblox, was interviewed by Alex Heath, a deputy editor at The Verge. The conference provided a platform for discussions on big ideas and problems, including the role of AI in Roblox's business [The Verge, 2023-10-12]

description: Bumble, a prominent player in the dating app market, is recognized alongside Tinder and Hinge for its role in facilitating romantic connections. However, Bumble has also distinguished itself by participating as one of the initial testers in Google's User Choice Billing program, demonstrating the company's commitment to exploring innovative billing strategies that enhance user experience and satisfaction. While Bumble continues to serve its core purpose of matchmaking in the digital space, The Verge's 2023-10-12 article highlights the app's presence in the discussion of evolving dating experiences, particularly in comparison to Roblox's potential for offering immersive 3D avatar-based interactions. This juxtaposition suggests that Bumble, though rooted in traditional online dating formats, is aware of the broader trends in virtual engagement and may be considering ways to integrate more interactive and immersive features into its platform.

name: TINDER
description: Tinder, a prominent player in the traditional dating market, is recognized alongside Bumble and Hinge. Although not the central focus of the discussion, Tinder's position in the dating app landscape is noteworthy, as it is mentioned in the context of potential disruption by Roblox's innovative 3D avatar-based dating experiences. This highlights the evolving nature of the dating industry, with new immersive technologies challenging established apps like Tinder.

name: HINGE
description: Hinge is a dating application that has been recognized within the competitive landscape of the dating market, often mentioned in the same breath as popular platforms like Bumble and Tinder. However, it's noteworthy that Hinge isn't the central focus of recent discussions. Instead, it has been brought up in relation to Roblox's innovative approach to dating experiences. Roblox is exploring the potential of offering a unique dating experience through the use of immersive 3D avatars, which could potentially rival traditional dating apps like Hinge. This highlights the evolving nature of the dating scene, where technology and virtual experiences are increasingly becoming part of the mix. As of 2023, Hinge continues to be a significant player in the dating app industry, but faces new competition from unexpected quarters.

This strategic move by Vans highlights the brand's understanding of the significance of digital memories in shaping consumer preferences and engagement, particularly among tech-savvy and entertainment-oriented demographics. By engaging with its audience in a virtual setting, Vans is able to create a strong connection with its target market, fostering brand loyalty and encouraging real-world purchases. This incident, which took place on 1997-06-28, has been widely discussed and analyzed, with the most recent reference being from TalkSport on 2023-11-15. Despite the passage of time, The Bite Fight remains a vivid example of the intense emotions and unexpected turns that can occur in the high-stakes world of professional boxing.

name: DISNEY SEQUEL ERA
description: Walt Disney Animation went through a period known as the "Disney sequel era," during which it produced direct-to-home-video sequels based on beloved Disney movies. This era was later criticized and largely forgotten by the studio. [Polygon, 2023-12-12]

name: LITTLE MERMAID
description: Little Mermaid is a film that initiated the Disney Renaissance, a period of significant success for Disney, characterized by a return to traditional animation and storytelling. It was a risk as a big Broadway-style musical in animation had not been attempted before.[]

name: DISNEY RENAISSANCE
description: The Disney Renaissance is a notable era in the history of The Walt Disney Company, marked by a resurgence and significant success in the production of animated musical films. This period began with the release of "The Little Mermaid," which is credited with revitalizing Disney's animation department by reintroducing traditional animation techniques and a focus on compelling storytelling. The Disney Renaissance continued to flourish as the company produced a string of critically acclaimed and commercially successful animated musicals, solidifying its reputation as a leader in the animation industry. This era is celebrated for its rich narratives, memorable characters, and enchanting musical scores, which have left a lasting impact on the entertainment landscape. [Polygon, 2023-12-12]

name: WALT DISNEY
description: Walt Disney was the founder of Disney Studios, known for his push for progress and innovation, even when it led to poor financial decisions. He was also a nostalgic person who idealized "the good old days," which influenced the design of his theme parks.[]

name: DISNEY STUDIOS
description: Disney Studios is a movie studio that has been a part of Walt Disney's legacy for over a century. It was known for its innovative and daring projects, which included princesses, theme parks, and Mickey Mouse.[]

name: DISNEY THEME PARKS
description: Disney theme parks are part of Disney's legacy, modeled after how Walt Disney's hometown looked at the turn of the 20th century. They are a place where nostalgia and innovation coexist.[]

name: DISNEY FANS
description: Disney fans, a diverse and passionate community, are united by their love for Disney and its iconic creations. This group often expresses a nostalgic longing for the past, specifically calling for a revival of classic elements that defined the golden age of Disney animation. Among their preferences are animated Disney movies featuring compelling villains, an increase in musicals, a return to traditional 2D animation techniques, and the re-emergence of the animated musical sequences that were hallmarks of the Disney Renaissance era. However, the desires of Disney fans are not monolithic; they encompass a wide range of individualized preferences, which presents a challenge for Disney in attempting to cater to every fan's specific tastes. As noted by Polygon on December 12, 2023, the company struggles to focus on meeting all these varied demands, highlighting the complexity and richness of the Disney fans' community.

name: YALE FOOD ADDICTION SCALE (YFAS)
description: The Yale Food Addiction Scale (YFAS) is an assessment tool used to measure addiction to food, finding that 14% of adults and 12% of children showed signs of addiction to ultra-processed foods [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: ULTRA-PROCESSED FOODS
description: Ultra-PROCESSED FOODS, a category that encompasses products heavily modified from their original state, are known for their inclusion of various additives, sugars, and fats. These foods, which include popular items like candy, ice cream, and potato chips, are characterized by their high carbohydrate and fat content. Recent studies suggest that Ultra-PROCESSED FOODS possess addictive qualities, akin to those found in drugs and cigarettes, potentially leading to overconsumption and health issues. Moreover, there is a concerning link between the consumption of these foods and an increased risk of death from ovarian and breast cancers, as reported by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-19. This information underscores the importance of understanding the potential health impacts associated with Ultra-PROCESSED FOODS and highlights the need for moderation in their consumption.

name: ASHLEY GEARHARDT
description: Ashley Gearhardt, a professor of psychology at the University of Michigan, is the lead researcher of the study that suggests ultra-processed foods have addictive properties [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: BMJ
description: The study on ultra-processed food addiction was published in the journal BMJ [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: TANYA FREIRICH
description: Tanya Freirich, a registered dietitian nutritionist in Charlotte, North Carolina, identified warning signs of addictive behaviors surrounding food [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: SUGAR-SWEETENED BEVERAGE TAXES
description: As of October 19, 2023, 103 countries have implemented sugar-sweetened beverage taxes, according to FOX News - Health. These policies are specifically designed to discourage the consumption of sugary drinks, which often fall under the category of ultra-processed foods. In addition to these taxes, several other countries have introduced additional levies specifically targeting ultra-processed foods, further emphasizing the global trend towards promoting healthier dietary choices and reducing the intake of sugar and processed items. The entity, "SUGAR-SWEETENED BEVERAGE TAXES," represents a significant public health strategy adopted by numerous nations to combat the negative health impacts associated with excessive consumption of sugar-laden beverages.

name: FREIRICH
description: Freirich, a recognized expert in the field, has been vocal about the complex relationship between food and addiction, emphasizing the necessity for further research to fully comprehend this connection. In an interview with FOX News - Health on 2023-10-19, Freirich highlighted the University of Michigan study, which was a comprehensive review and synthesis of data from numerous other studies. This expert suggests that individuals should primarily consume minimally processed foods and consult with a dietitian to tailor their diet to personal health objectives. Freirich also discussed the harmful impacts of food addiction with Fox News Digital, identifying key symptoms such as overeating to the point of discomfort and an obsessive preoccupation with food and meals, which can interfere with one's ability to focus on other aspects of life.

name: GEARHARDT
description: Gearhardt is an individual who noted that 103 countries have passed "sugar-sweetened beverage taxes," and several others have additional taxes for ultra-processed foods. More than 20 countries have also added nutrition labels to these foods [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: USDA
description: The USDA (United States Department of Agriculture) is a government agency that could take steps to ensure foods are safe for consumption by regulating certain additives [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: FDA
description: The FDA (Food and Drug Administration) is a government agency that could make similar steps to the USDA to ensure foods are safe for consumption [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: ERIN PALINSKI-WADE
description: Erin Palinski-Wade is a New Jersey-based dietitian with a focus on diabetes and nutrition. She is skeptical that foods can be as addictive as drugs and believes food cravings are complex and tied into emotions and learned behaviors around eating [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: PALINSKI-WADE
description: Palinski-Wade, a distinguished nutrition expert, recognizes the complex relationship between certain foods and addictive-like eating behaviors. According to a FOX News - Health article published on 2023-10-19, she explains that foods rich in added sugar or fats can stimulate powerful cravings, potentially leading to a loss of control over eating habits. Palinski-Wade emphasizes that while no single food is inherently addictive, the consumption of these high-calorie items can trigger the release of dopamine, a chemical associated with pleasure and reward in the brain. This mechanism contributes to the development of cravings and can exacerbate disordered eating patterns. For individuals grappling with binge-eating or uncontrolled food cravings, Palinski-Wade advises seeking professional help from a therapist or a registered dietitian with expertise in eating disorders, to address and manage these issues effectively.

name: ULTRAPROCESSED FOODS
description: Ultraprocessed foods are products that are high in added sugar or added fats and are associated with strong cravings and potentially addictive-like eating behaviors. These foods can trigger the release of feel-good chemicals such as dopamine in the brain, leading to cravings and loss of control over eating behavior. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: MINIMALLY PROCESSED FOODS
description: Minimally processed foods are products that have undergone minimal processing and are recommended by experts like Freirich to potentially decrease the consumption of ultraprocessed foods. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: DOPAMINE
description: Dopamine is a feel-good chemical in the brain that is released when consuming foods high in added sugar or added fats. It can lead to cravings and potentially addictive-like eating behaviors, as explained by Palinski-Wade. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-19]

name: BILLIE JEAN KING
description: Billie Jean King, a renowned former professional tennis player and a staunch advocate for gender equality in sports, has played a pivotal role in shaping the landscape of women's sports. As highlighted in Fortune on 2023-10-13, King's efforts have been instrumental in achieving significant milestones, such as the push for equal prize money in tennis tournaments. She is famously known for her participation in the King-Riggs match, which she views as a catalyst for social change, demonstrating the potential and power of women in sports. King continues to champion the cause for more investment in women's sports, reflecting her ongoing commitment to progress and equality in the athletic world.

name: U.S. OPEN
description: The U.S. Open is a major tennis tournament that began offering equal prize money to male and female players in 1973, following protests by Billie Jean King and other female players [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: KING-RIGGS MATCH
description: The King-Riggs match, a highly publicized tennis exhibition match in 1973, was a significant event in the fight for gender equality in sports, where Billie Jean King defeated Bobby Riggs, a former men's tennis champion, and it is seen as a symbol of women standing up for themselves in all areas [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: PROFESSIONAL WOMEN'S HOCKEY LEAGUE (PWHL)
description: The Professional Women's Hockey League (PWHL) is a women's professional hockey league that Billie Jean King is part of the ownership group for, with teams in Boston, New York, Minnesota, Toronto, Ottawa, and Montreal, aiming to provide a platform for the best female hockey players [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: KENDALL COYNE
description: Kendall Coyne is a U.S. Olympic gold medalist in women's ice hockey who reached out to Billie Jean King for help in establishing a professional women's hockey league [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: INVESTMENT IN WOMEN'S SPORTS
description: Investment in women's sports is changing, with Billie Jean King actively encouraging CEOs and investors to invest equally in women's sports as they do in men's sports, noting improvements but highlighting the need for more female investors, particularly in soccer [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: WOMEN'S SPORTS
description: Women's sports are a category of sports where female athletes compete, and Billie Jean King has been advocating for more opportunities, jobs, and investment in women's sports, emphasizing the importance of diversity and women of color [Fortune, 2023-10-13]

name: ROGERS COMMUNICATIONS INC
description: Rogers Communications Inc is a Canadian company, the country’s largest wireless provider and owner of a cable television empire, the Toronto Blue Jays baseball team, and other media and sports assets. The family’s controlling stake in the public company is worth close to C$8 billion ($5.9 billion), according to calculations based on company filings for its 2023 annual meeting [Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: MELINDA ROGERS-HIXON
description: Melinda Rogers-Hixon is a member of the Rogers family, which controls Rogers Communications Inc. She claims to be the target of a “personal vendetta” by her older brother, Rogers Chair Edward Rogers, and is suing the company for being frozen out of board meetings and blocked from getting information [Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: MARSHA ROGERS
description: Marsha Rogers, alongside her sister Melinda Rogers-Hixon, is a member of the influential Rogers family that controls Rogers Communications Inc., a prominent player in the technology and communications sector. As of October 12, 2023, Marsha and Melinda are engaged in legal action against the company, alleging that they have been unjustly excluded from board meetings and denied access to crucial information. Marsha's exclusion extends to being given redacted board documents, further complicating her ability to fully participate in the decision-making processes of the family business. This situation highlights internal family dynamics and governance issues within the Rogers family and their corporate entity.

name: EDWARD ROGERS
description: Edward Rogers is the Chair of Rogers Communications Inc and a member of the Rogers family. He is accused by his sister Melinda Rogers-Hixon of a “personal vendetta” against her and of reneging on an agreement that would have resolved their longstanding differences [Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: TONY STAFFIERI
description: Tony Staffieri is the Chief Executive Officer of Rogers Communications Inc. He replaced Joe Natale as CEO after Edward Rogers won control of the board in 2021. Rogers-Hixon and Martha Rogers had opposed this CEO change [Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: SHAW COMMUNICATIONS INC
description: Shaw Communications Inc is a Canadian company that was the target of a C$20 billion takeover by Rogers Communications Inc, the company’s biggest deal ever and among the largest corporate transactions in Canadian history. The takeover finally closed on April 3 of this year [Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: TELUS CORP
description: Telus Corp, a prominent competitor to Rogers Communications Inc and Shaw Communications Inc in the telecommunications industry, found itself at the center of a sensitive conflict of interest situation. As reported by Fortune on October 12, 2023, the personal lawyer of a Rogers executive, Rogers-Hixon, also provided legal services to Telus Corp. This dual representation sparked a significant argument and led to an agreement that Rogers-Hixon would abstain from participating in any board discussions concerning the Shaw deal and would not be privy to related materials, ensuring the maintenance of impartiality and fairness in corporate dealings.

name: ROGERS-HIXON
description: Rogers-Hixon is a member of the Rogers family, involved in a dispute over the exclusion from board and committee meetings and the redaction of board documents. She is also a director of Rogers Communications and was previously involved in the Shaw takeover deal. [Source: Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: ROGERS COMMUNICATIONS
description: Rogers Communications is a Canadian telecommunications company that is the subject of a dispute over the exclusion of Rogers-Hixon and Martha Rogers from board and committee meetings. The company is controlled by a family trust and has significant momentum in the market with its merger tracking ahead of plan. [Source: Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: SHAW
description: Shaw is a company that was the subject of a takeover deal by Rogers Communications. [Source: Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: SARAH SCHMIDT
description: Sarah Schmidt is a spokesperson for Rogers Communications who commented on the dispute, stating that the matter should be resolved privately and that the company has taken reasonable steps to protect company information. [Source: Fortune, 2023-10-12]

name: MAPLE LEAF SPORTS & ENTERTAINMENT

Zampa's bowling prowess was highlighted by three four-wicket hauls, showcasing his ability to dismantle opposing batting lineups. Despite his success, he conceded a total of 515 runs, a testament to the high-scoring nature of the matches he played in. This exceptional performance solidified Zampa's reputation as a key player for the Aussies in international cricket.

Amazon's Cyber Monday Sale, as reported by Mashable on 2023-11-27, boasts an impressive array of over 200 deals on a wide range of products including headphones, earbuds, tablets, gaming items, and smart home devices. Similarly, Walmart's Cyber Monday Sale, as noted by Mashable on 2023-11-25, offers significant discounts on various products, including TVs, laptops, headphones/earbuds, and tablets. name: OKLAHOMA STATE
description: Oklahoma State, a college football team recognized for its prowess on the field, is currently ranked No. 18. In a significant turn of events, Oklahoma State faced off against No. 7 Texas in the Big 12 championship game, which was held on Saturday at 12 p.m. and broadcasted on ABC, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-12-01. Contrary to the anticipation leading up to the game, Oklahoma State emerged victorious, defeating Texas in the championship. This outcome had a ripple effect in the College Football Playoff (CFP) rankings, inadvertently making life easier for Alabama by reshuffling the top teams' standings.

name: IOWA
description: Iowa, a college football team, made headlines in the Big Ten championship game on December 1, 2023, by defeating No. 2 Michigan, potentially impacting the Big Ten's chances in the College Football Playoff (CFP). Despite being ranked No. 16, Iowa showcased an impressive performance, securing a victory against Michigan in the championship game that aired at 8 p.m. on FOX, as reported by Sporting News. This win not only highlighted Iowa's competitive spirit but also stirred up the dynamics within the Big Ten conference, suggesting a shift in the power rankings and possibly altering the trajectory of the CFP.

name: NICK SABAN

name: KEELEY
description: Keeley, a renowned parenting expert, highlights the moral significance of the "give list" during the Christmas season, advising parents to foster a balanced holiday experience for their children. According to Keeley, parents often inadvertently teach their children that Christmas is solely about creating a 'wish list' and receiving gifts, which can lead to a skewed understanding of the holiday's true spirit. To counteract this, she encourages parents to guide their kids in developing a list of thoughtful gifts to give to family and friends, promoting the values of generosity and creativity. Keeley emphasizes that children should use their imagination and creative skills to come up with gift ideas, rather than relying on their parents' financial resources. Additionally, she provides insights on managing behavior during the holidays and instilling self-discipline, ensuring that the festive period is well-rounded and enriching for children. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-09]

name: HOLIDAY MARTYR
description: The concept of a "holiday martyr" refers to parents, particularly "martyr moms," who prioritize others' needs over their own during Christmastime, potentially leading to exhaustion and a lack of self-care [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-09]

name: HOLIDAY DECORATING MISTAKES

name: GIVE LIST
description: The "give list" is a concept Keeley highlights as a moral counterpoint to the "wish list," emphasizing the importance of teaching children about giving during the Christmas season [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-09]

name: THE GIVE LIST
description: The "give list" is a concept Keeley emphasized as a moral counterbalance to the ‘wish list’ during Christmas. It involves creating a list of gifts to give to family and friends, using imagination and creative ability. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-09]

name: THE WISH LIST
description: The ‘wish list’ is a concept often associated with Christmas, where children list down what they want to receive as gifts. Keeley suggests that many parents make the mistake of teaching their children that Christmas is only about making a ‘wish list’ and getting what they want, which can create a big case of 'the gimmes’ in children. [FOX News - Lifestyle, 2023-12-09]

name: ANDURIL
description: Anduril is a defense startup co-founded by Oculus founder Palmer Luckey. The company has unveiled a new fighter jet weapon called Roadrunner, which is a modular, twin-jet-powered autonomous vertical take-off and landing air vehicle capable of carrying a warhead [TechCrunch, 2023-12-09]

name: 23ANDME
description: 23andMe, a prominent genetic testing company, faced a significant cybersecurity breach as reported by TechCrunch on December 9, 2023. Initially, the company announced that hackers managed to access the personal data of 0.1% of its customers, which equates to approximately 14,000 individuals. Further investigations revealed a more extensive impact, with 6.9 million people having their personal information exposed. The compromised data included sensitive details such as names, birth years, relationship labels, DNA share percentages, ancestry reports, and self-reported locations. This incident underscores the critical need for robust data protection measures in the genetic testing industry, where the privacy of personal health information is paramount.

name: GRAND THEFT AUTO VI
description: Grand Theft Auto VI, the highly anticipated video game, made a monumental splash in the gaming community as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-12-09. The game's first trailer, released this week, garnered an astonishing 85 million views within a mere 22 hours, shattering the previous record held by a MrBeast video for the most YouTube views in 24 hours. This overwhelming response is a testament to the decade-long anticipation building up to this release, fueled by the enduring popularity of its predecessor, Grand Theft Auto V, which stands as the second-best-selling video game of all time, trailing only behind Minecraft. The excitement surrounding Grand Theft Auto VI is indicative of the game's potential to captivate audiences and redefine the landscape of video games, much like its illustrious forebear.

name: IMAGINE WITH META AI

description: The M3 Pro and Max are new MacBook models from Apple, weighing 4.7/4.8 pounds. They feature the Liquid Retina XDR display and have a pixel density of 254 ppi. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: LIQUID RETINA XDR DISPLAY
description: Apple's Liquid Retina XDR display is used in the new Pro models, with a sustained brightness of 1000 nits and a peak brightness of 1600 nits for HDR content. For SDR content, the brightness has been increased to 600 nits max. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: CONTINUITY CAMERA
description: Continuity Camera, a groundbreaking technology introduced by Apple in 2023, revolutionizes the webcam experience for Mac laptop users. This feature enables a mounted iPhone to seamlessly take over webcam duties, providing superior video quality and functionality compared to traditional laptop webcams. As reported by TechCrunch on November 6, 2023, Continuity Camera is a game changer for many, significantly enhancing the webcam experience for Mac users by leveraging the advanced camera capabilities of their iPhones.

name: M3 MAX
description: The M3 Max is a product in Apple's M3 line of desktop chips, which are the first to be created using the 3nm process. The new process brings performance gains with less power consumption. Gaming continues to be an important narrative for Apple's silicon journey, and it was very much at the heart of last week's M3 announcements. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: BELKIN MAGSAFE CAMERA MOUNT
description: The Belkin MagSafe camera mount is a product that allows for the mounting of an iPhone to be used as a webcam. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: DYNAMIC CACHING
description: Dynamic Caching is a feature introduced by Apple that only uses the exact amount of memory needed for each task. It's an industry first, transparent to developers, and the cornerstone of the new GPU architecture. It dramatically increases the average utilization of the GPU, which significantly increases performance for the most demanding pro apps and games. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: RAY TRACING
description: Ray tracing is a feature designed to bring added realism to the gaming experience, though more accurate depictions of lighting and reflections. That feature is now hardware-accelerated. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]

name: MESH SHADING
description: Mesh shading is a feature that makes processing complex geometrical images more efficient. That, in turn, allows for higher-quality graphics and more scene detail. [TechCrunch, 2023-11-06]
