name: RYAN PETERSEN
description: Ryan Petersen is the founder of Flexport. He forced out his hand-picked successor as CEO, ex-Amazon executive Dave Clark, so Petersen could once again run the company. [Cnbc | World Business News Leader, 2023-10-02]

name: DAVE CLARK
description: Dave Clark, a former high-ranking Amazon executive, served as the CEO of Flexport for a brief tenure of one year before being ousted by Ryan Petersen, as reported by CNBC | World Business News Leader on 2023-10-02. During his time at Flexport, Clark is recognized for orchestrating a significant acquisition, the $1.3 billion purchase of Deliverr from Shopify, which bolstered Flexport's supply chain technology specifically for last-mile deliveries. Following his departure from Flexport, Clark made comments on the social media site X, reacting to CNBC's report that shed light on the circumstances of his final days at the company, as noted by TechCrunch on 2023-10-07.

name: DELIVERERR
description: Deliverr is a company that was purchased by Flexport for $1.3 billion from Shopify, adding supply chain technology for last-mile deliveries. [Cnbc | World Business News Leader, 2023-10-02]

name: SHOPIFY
description: Shopify is a company that sold Deliverr to Flexport. [Cnbc | World Business News Leader, 2023-10-02]

name: BOBBY DE CORDOVA-REID
description: Bobby De Cordova-Reid, an attacker for Fulham, converted a penalty that sealed Jamaica's progression to the CONCACAF Nations League semifinal and qualification for Copa America 2024 [Sporting News, 2023-11-21]

name: ALPHONSO DAVIES
description: Alphonso Davies, a star soccer player for both Bayern Munich and the Canadian national team, scored the opening goal in the CONCACAF Nations League quarterfinal second leg match against Jamaica in the 25th minute, bringing the score to 1-0 and the aggregate to 3-1 as of 2023-11-21. Despite Davies' goal, Canada was unable to secure a win, resulting in Jamaica's qualification for Copa America 2024. Davies' performance highlights his significant impact on the Canadian team and his role as a key player in both international and club competitions.

name: BMO FIELD
description: BMO Field, situated in Toronto, Canada, served as the venue for the second leg match of the CONCACAF Nations League quarterfinals between Canada and Jamaica. According to reports from Sporting News on November 21, 2023, the match concluded with a 3-2 victory for Jamaica. This stadium, known for hosting significant sporting events, was the setting for this critical game in the CONCACAF Nations League tournament.

name: JANANI UMAMAHESWAR
description: Janani Umamaheswar, a notable figure in academia, holds positions at two distinct universities, showcasing her diverse expertise and contributions to the field. As an assistant professor in sociology at Southern Connecticut State University, she has been actively involved in teaching and research, even monitoring her course reviews on Rate My Professors. Unfortunately, since 2019, she has been subjected to strange and negative remarks on the site, which have had a significant emotional and professional impact on her, as reported by The Verge on October 25, 2023. Additionally, Janani is associated with George Mason University, where she works in the criminology department. However, her tenure at this institution has been marred by accusations from an individual identified only as S., who has alleged sexually harassing behavior on her part. These allegations, if substantiated, could further complicate her professional standing and personal well-being. Despite these challenges, Janani's dual roles at these universities highlight her commitment to education and her broad academic interests.

name: RATE MY PROFESSORS
description: Rate My Professors is a website platform that enables students to post anonymous reviews and comments about their professors, providing a space for the student community to share their experiences and insights. However, this anonymity can create anxiety for instructors, as it may lead to the posting of defamatory content. In a recent incident, Umamaheswar and Sinha reached out to the company behind Rate My Professors to request the removal of defamatory posts concerning Umamaheswar, highlighting the potential for misuse of the platform's anonymous review feature.

name: SOUTHERN CONNECTICUT STATE UNIVERSITY
description: Southern Connecticut State University, an esteemed educational institution, has been the workplace of Janani Umamaheswar, who served as an assistant professor in the sociology department. Prior to her appointment at Southern Connecticut State University, Umamaheswar was on a tenure track for four years at another university. However, the university has also been the site of a police report filed by a student, referred to as S., against Umamaheswar and two other professors. This is not the first time S. has come to the attention of university officials and the police; Detective William S. Rivera from the university police department has been involved in addressing issues with S. previously. The dynamics at Southern Connecticut State University, particularly within its sociology department, have thus been marked by both academic contributions and contentious interactions.

name: ALEX SINHA
description: Alex Sinha, the husband of Janani Umamaheswar, is a law professor at Quinnipiac University in Connecticut. In a recent event covered by The Verge on 2023-10-25, Sinha advised Umamaheswar to reach out to Rate My Professors regarding the removal of negative and strange comments posted about her. These comments were not only defamatory but also drew Sinha's attention when he observed unusual activity on his own personal website. The peculiar visits to his site originated from the same IP address that accessed Umamaheswar's online pages, adding a layer of complexity to the situation. This incident highlights Sinha's proactive role in addressing online defamation and his awareness of potential cyber-related issues affecting his and his spouse's digital presence.

name: QUINNIPIAC UNIVERSITY
description: Quinnipiac University, an esteemed educational institution located in Connecticut, was the workplace of Alex Sinha, a law professor, during the events in question. It was during Sinha's tenure at Quinnipiac University that Janani Umamaheswar, another individual in the academic community, started to receive negative reviews on Rate My Professors, a platform where students can share their experiences and opinions about their educators. The Verge, in an article dated 2023-10-25, highlighted these occurrences, providing insight into the dynamics of the university's law department and the broader academic environment.

name: UMAMAHESWAR
description: Umamaheswar, an Asian American academic and professor, has been dealing with a series of issues alongside her husband, Alex Sinha, and another individual, Tan. The trio has faced online abuse from a person identified as S., leading Umamaheswar and Sinha to file complaints with Twitter. The harassment extended beyond social media, as Umamaheswar also encountered defamatory posts on Rate My Professors and unusual activity on her professional website. Further complicating matters, S. accused Umamaheswar in a police report and through emails to school officials, creating a multifaceted dispute that has required investigation and action from various fronts.

name: S
description: S. is a student who filed a police report against Umamaheswar and two other professors at Southern Connecticut State University, accusing them of hacking her personal laptop and using students to follow her and look at her papers, making her feel unsafe. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: TITLE IX OFFICE
description: The Title IX office at Southern Connecticut State University handles discrimination and harassment complaints, including sexual, and was informed about the student's complaint against Umamaheswar. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: TITLE IX
description: Title IX, a federal law enacted in 1972, is designed to prohibit gender-based discrimination in educational institutions and programs. Initially, it served as a crucial tool in curbing discrimination and harassment against students and employees based on sex. However, the law has faced criticism for being manipulated and weaponized against marginalized and vulnerable groups on campuses, including faculty. Contrary to the common belief that it was introduced during the Obama era, Title IX was actually established much earlier. It was during the Obama administration that the policy gained significant attention for its efforts to protect students from harassment and sexual violence. Yet, this period also saw critiques regarding the weakening of due process under the law, highlighting the complex dynamics and challenges associated with its implementation and enforcement.

name: TRUMP ADMINISTRATION
description: Under the Trump administration, some of the policies related to Title IX were rolled back and changed, allowing accused individuals to receive more due process protections [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: SARAH VIREN
description: Sarah Viren is a professor and journalist who detailed false sexual harassment accusations against herself and her wife filed with the Title IX Office at Arizona State University. She also interviewed other academics who reached out to her after she shared her story [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: SHANTEL BUGGS
description: Shantel Buggs is an assistant professor at Florida State University whose research centers on culture, race and racism, gender, and work inequity in academia. She said she was stalked by an individual who has also threatened to throw acid, chop off hands, murder, and mutilate some of the academics [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: FLORIDA STATE UNIVERSITY
description: Florida State University is an educational institution where Shantel Buggs, an assistant professor, said she was stalked by an individual [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: VICTOR RAY
description: Victor Ray is a sociologist and associate professor at the University of Iowa who tweeted about his experience of being stalked by the same individual who has harassed him and his family, including death threats and lying about his background for years [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: UNIVERSITY OF IOWA
description: The University of Iowa is an educational institution where Victor Ray, a sociologist and associate professor, said he was stalked by an individual [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: OBAMA ADMINISTRATION
description: The Obama administration is associated with the well-intentioned policy of Title IX, which aimed to protect students but has had unintended side effects, weakening due process [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: SINHA
description: Sinha, an Asian American academic and professor at Hofstra University, has become notably vigilant in monitoring and documenting tweets from S., due to experiencing harassment and threats on social media, which he perceives as a direct danger to his family and a potential legal issue. Despite his concerns, Sinha's campus has not received any direct communications from S., to the best of his knowledge. His schools have been supportive and understanding of his experiences with online harassment. In 2023, Sinha co-authored a paper with a colleague from another university and felt a sense of responsibility to alert his co-author about S.'s history of hostile engagement on Twitter. Sinha is apprehensive about the repercussions of S.'s actions on his professional reputation, particularly during job interviews and performance evaluations. As a result of the ongoing situation, Sinha has significantly reduced his own social media activity, tweeting rarely and maintaining a low profile to protect himself and his career. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: S.
description: S. is an individual deeply entrenched in a pattern of cyberstalking, harassment, and racism, primarily targeting Asian American academics on Twitter. Initially fixated on someone else, S.'s attention shifted to Catherine Tan, an academic at Vassar College, whom S. subjected to name-calling and racist comments. In an attempt to escalate the situation, S. contacted Tan's employer, Vassar College, with the intent of getting her fired. This behavior is not isolated, as S. has also been posting outrageous, racist views and outlandish threats, causing distress to Sinha and his wife. S. has been observed watching Sinha and his wife in a public place, and despite multiple account bans, she has persistently recreated her presence under new handles. Additionally, S. has been accused of sexually harassing others on Twitter, sending letters to Title IX offices at Vassar and George Mason universities. S.'s actions have not gone unnoticed; Southern Connecticut State University officials and police have previously intervened in response to her threatening behavior towards Sinha, Umamaheswar, and Tan. The Verge, in its coverage dated 2023-10-25, highlights the severity and breadth of S.'s misconduct, emphasizing the need for continued vigilance and action against such online abuse.

name: TAN
description: Tan, an Asian American academic and professor, has been at the center of a complex and troubling situation involving allegations and counter-allegations with another individual, S. According to reports from The Verge on October 25, 2023, Tan, alongside Sinha and Umamaheswar, has filed complaints with Twitter against S. for online abuse. The harassment Tan experienced on Twitter included accusations of stalking and sexual harassment, which she vehemently denies. In response to the escalating online abuse, particularly from S.'s persistent actions, Tan felt compelled to warn her mutual contacts on the platform about S.'s behavior. Additionally, Tan herself has been accused by S. of sexually harassing behavior, leading to her email being blocked by Vassar officials, further complicating the dynamics between the two. Despite the severity of the accusations against her, Tan's actions in filing complaints and warning others indicate her efforts to address and mitigate the abusive behavior directed at her and others within her community.

name: ASIAN AMERICAN ASSISTANT PROFESSOR OF SOCIOLOGY
description: An Asian American assistant professor of sociology, who was at the University of Chicago and is followed by Tan on Twitter, received a threatening tweet from S. on November 9th, 2022. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: ASIAN AMERICAN ASTROPHYSICIST
description: An Asian American astrophysicist, who is followed by Tan on Twitter, received a threatening tweet from S. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: DETECTIVE WILLIAM S. RIVERA
description: Detective William S. Rivera is a police officer at Southern Connecticut State University who has been involved in addressing issues with S. and has had his email and phone number posted on social media by S. [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: RUTGERS UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF SOCIAL WORK
description: Rutgers University School of Social Work is an educational institution where a graduate student specializing in violence against women and children founded a Students Against Sexual Violence club

name: KNOW YOUR IX
description: Know Your IX is an organization that works around Title IX, focusing on issues related to sexual violence and harassment

name: VASSAR COLLEGE
description: Vassar College, a renowned educational institution, has been the workplace of Professor Catherine Tan. However, the college has recently been embroiled in a sensitive situation involving Tan. An individual, referred to as S., has contacted Vassar College, specifically addressing the Title IX office, to accuse Tan of sexually harassing behavior. This incident has escalated to the point where the stalker has attempted to get Tan fired from her position at the college, as reported by The Verge on October 25, 2023. The college, known for its commitment to academic excellence and a safe learning environment, is currently navigating the complexities of these allegations while ensuring due process is followed.

name: GEORGE MASON UNIVERSITY
description: George Mason University is an educational institution where S. sent a letter to the Title IX office accusing Janani Umamaheswar of sexually harassing behavior

name: HOFSTRA UNIVERSITY
description: Hofstra University is Sinha's campus, which did not receive any letters from S., as far as he knows

name: CATHERINE TAN
description: Catherine Tan is a professor who experienced cyberstalking and harassment, which escalated to the point where the stalker contacted her employer, Vassar College, in an attempt to get her fired. She decided to publicly acknowledge the stalker on Twitter and received support from other users and academics [The Verge, 2023-10-25]

name: THE INTERNET
description: The Internet, a global network of computers that enables the exchange of information and communication, has played a pivotal role in shaping the modern world. Initially more of a niche and less regulated space, it evolved into a mainstream platform around the turn of the century, leading to a surge in demand for SEO skills as businesses and individuals sought to navigate and optimize their online presence. However, the democratization of information facilitated by the Internet has a dual nature; while it has empowered people with access to a wealth of knowledge, it has also enabled the spread of anger and hatred through algorithms, amplifying negative behaviors. Additionally, the Internet has exacerbated the issue of cyberstalking, making it easier for individuals to engage in stalking behavior and for others to become victims of such harassment, as noted by The Verge in 2023. Engadget and The Verge, both reputable sources in technology and entertainment, highlight the complex dynamics and challenges associated with the Internet's impact on society.

name: RUBY FRANKE
description: Ruby Franke, a Utah mother of six, is known for her involvement in the YouTube channel "8 Passengers," where she and her husband Kevin Franke shared parenting advice. However, in a dramatic turn of events, Ruby pleaded guilty to child abuse charges on 2023-12-18, as reported by Fortune. The abuse, which she admitted to, involved convincing her two youngest children that they were evil and possessed, necessitating punishment for repentance. This led to the children being subjected to hours of forced physical tasks, working outdoors in the summer without sufficient water, repeated and severe sunburns, isolation, denial of food, and physical harm. During the hearing, Ruby was dressed in gray and white jail clothing and displayed emotion when pleading guilty to the fourth charge. Under the plea agreement, she agreed to serve a prison term, with the sentences to run consecutively. Additional instances of her abusive behavior include refusing to take a lunch to a kindergartener who had forgotten it at home and threatening to decapitate a young girl's stuffed toy as punishment for cutting things in the house. These actions further highlight the severity of the situation and the impact of her behavior on her children.

name: JODI HILDEBRANDT
description: Jodi Hildebrandt is a co-defendant in the case of child abuse involving Ruby Franke. He is described as a relationship counselor who influenced Franke to have a distorted sense of morality, leading to the abuse of her children. [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-18]

name: WINWARD LAW
description: Winward Law is the law firm representing Ruby Franke. They released a statement saying that Franke is a devoted mother committed to constant improvement, but was taken advantage of by her co-defendant Jodi Hildebrandt, who twisted her quest for improvement into something heinous. [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-18]

name: UTAH LAW
description: Under Utah law, second-degree aggravated child abuse can be charged if a person knowingly or intentionally inflicts serious physical injury to a child or causes or permits another to inflict serious physical injury to their child. Each charge carries a sentence of one to 15 years in prison. [Source: Fortune, 2023-12-18]

name: FRANKE
description: Franke, alongside her husband Kevin Franke, is a YouTube influencer known for her channel "8 Passengers," where she shared parenting advice and decisions with her audience. However, Franke has been embroiled in controversy as she admitted to abusing her 12-year-old son and 9-year-old daughter. The acts of abuse included kicking her son while wearing boots, holding his head under water, smothering his mouth and nose, forcing her daughter to work outside, run on dirt roads barefoot, and go without food and water. These actions were justified by Franke as necessary for obedience and repentance, and paradoxically, as acts of love. The information regarding the child abuse allegations and admissions was published by Fortune on December 18, 2023. The channel "8 Passengers" has faced significant criticism online due to these revelations.

name: HILDEBRANDT
description: Hildebrandt, alongside Franke, is a central figure in a legal case that has garnered attention, as detailed in a statement by Franke’s attorney and reported by Fortune on 2023-12-18. On August 30, Hildebrandt and Franke were arrested following an incident where Franke’s 12-year-old son managed to escape from Hildebrandt’s residence in Ivins, a city in southern Utah, and sought help from a neighbor to contact the police. In response to the allegations, Hildebrandt has voluntarily agreed to refrain from seeing patients until the matter is reviewed and addressed by state licensing authorities. The nature of the allegations and the specifics of the case are not detailed in the provided information, but it is clear that the situation has significant implications for Hildebrandt's professional activities.

name: 8 PASSENGERS
description: "8 Passengers" is a YouTube channel that was initiated in 2015 and ceased operations after seven years. The channel, run by Franke and her husband, primarily focused on sharing their unique and often controversial parenting decisions and advice with the online community. Notable incidents included banning their oldest son from his bedroom for seven months as a consequence of pranking his younger brother, refusing to bring lunch to a kindergartener who had forgotten it at home, and even threatening to decapitate a young girl's stuffed toy as punishment for her cutting things around the house. These actions sparked significant online debate and criticism, with many viewers expressing their disapproval of the couple's parenting methods. The information regarding these controversial decisions was sourced from Fortune, published on December 18, 2023. Despite the criticism, "8 Passengers" managed to maintain a presence on YouTube for a considerable period, indicating a level of interest and engagement from its audience.

name: ST. GEORGE POLICE DEPARTMENT
description: The St. George Police Department received a 911 call from a neighbor after Franke’s 12-year-old son escaped from Hildebrandt’s house. The caller reported that the boy was emaciated and had duct tape around his ankles and wrists. [Source: Fortune, Publish Time: 2023-12-18]

name: DOUGLAS TERRY
description: Douglas Terry is the attorney for Hildebrandt. He did not immediately return a phone call seeking comment on the allegations made against Hildebrandt in the statement by Franke’s attorney. [Source: Fortune, Publish Time: 2023-12-18]

name: FRANKE’S ATTORNEY
description: Franke’s attorney is a lawyer who made a statement regarding the allegations made against Hildebrandt. The source of this information is Fortune, published on 2023-12-18[]

name: KEVIN FRANKE
description: Kevin Franke is Franke’s husband who has filed for divorce. The source of this information is Fortune, published on 2023-12-18[]

name: ECHO SHOW 8
description: The Echo Show 8 is a product from Amazon that comes with a free trial of Alexa Together. It is described as the favorite among other Echo Show devices. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ALEXA TOGETHER
description: Alexa Together is an Amazon service that offers a free trial with the purchase of the Echo Show 8. It aims to replicate the tasks of a caregiver and usually costs $20 per month. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ECHO STUDIO
description: The Echo Studio is the best-sounding Alexa speaker from Amazon, but it is also quite expensive. The price matches a low that has been seen just once before. It offers more powerful sound in general, with noticeable changes on the low end. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: KINDLE KIDS
description: The Kindle Kids is a waterproof e-reader from Amazon that comes with adjustable warm lighting for reading at night. It is on sale for $80, which is $40 off the regular price. However, it lacks the adjustable warm lighting and waterproofing of the special edition. Amazon includes a protective case, a one-year subscription to Amazon Kids+, and a two-year no-questions-asked replacement guarantee with the purchase. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: FIRE MAX 11
description: The Fire Max 11 is Amazon's biggest, nicest, and most overpriced Fire tablet. It has a nice display and a new fingerprint sensor. The tablet can be used with a keyboard without resorting to Bluetooth. However, the Fire OS operating system is lacking in features, such as a decent app store. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MACBOOK AIR 2023
description: The 2023 MacBook Air is one of the favorite laptops of the year, according to WIRED. It has an excellent six-speaker sound system and a 1080p front camera. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: FIRE OS
description: Fire OS is an operating system that is criticized for lacking a decent app store

name: RAZER BLADE 14
description: The Razer Blade 14 is a laptop that earned an 8/10, WIRED Recommends award, featuring a gorgeous 16:10 display, plenty of USB ports, a full-size HDMI output, and an Nvidia RTX 3080 Ti, with the option to upgrade to the 40-series, giving it plenty of power to handle the toughest games [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: DAS KEYBOARD MACTIGR
description: The Das Keyboard MacTigr is a keyboard that pairs well with Apple's laptops and PCs, featuring a dedicated Mac layout, Cherry MX Red switches, a two-port USB-C hub, and a high-quality, all-metal build [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: STUDIO DISPLAY
description: The Studio Display is a 27-inch monitor with a 5K resolution, perfect for managing multiple apps simultaneously. It lacks HDR, resulting in colors that appear more contrasty and saturated compared to the neutral tones on Apple's Pro Display XDR. The monitor is equipped with a 12-megapixel camera, built-in mics, and speakers, making it ideal for video calls. This is the lowest price tracked for this product, as of 2023-10-10 [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: ASUS ROG RYUJIN II LIQUID COOLER
description: The Asus ROG Ryujin II Liquid Cooler is a cooling solution for high-end PCs. It is recommended for use with AMD's 16-core CPU due to the high heat generation of the CPU [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: AMD 16-CORE CPU
description: AMD's 16-core CPU is a powerful processor suitable for high-end 4K or 144-Hz gaming. It requires special cooling solutions like the Asus ROG Ryujin II Liquid Cooler due to its high heat generation [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: PLUGABLE USB-C TRIPLE DISPLAY DOCKING STATION
description: The Plugable USB-C Triple Display Docking Station is a device that supports up to three displays at once, either HDMI or DisplayPort for each. It includes six USB 3.0 ports and a gigabit Ethernet port. The dock can charge a laptop with an output of up to 60 watts and is particularly useful for creating a multi-monitor setup with a MacBook [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: SANDISK EXTREME PRO
description: The SanDisk Extreme Pro is a USB flash drive that balances speed, reliability, and price. It has a sleek aluminum case with a loop for attaching to a keyring and a slider to push out the USB-A plug. The product is fast, performs reliably, and comes with a lifetime warranty [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: ONEPLUS PAD
description: The OnePlus Pad is an Android tablet that is considered a worthy iPad alternative. It offers good performance, great battery life, and an excellent 144-Hz, 11.6-inch LCD display. The magnetic keyboard for the tablet is also recommended and is on sale for $100 ($50 off) [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: 9TH-GEN IPAD
description: The 9th-gen iPad is a tablet recommended for most people, even though it is one generation behind. It is a favorite iPad among the options available [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: TICWATCH PRO 5
description: The TicWatch Pro 5 is a smartwatch that stands out for its battery life, offering three days of average use. It is powered by Qualcomm’s Snapdragon W5+ Gen 1 chipset and runs on Wear OS 3. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MOBVOI
description: Mobvoi is the manufacturer of the TicWatch Pro 5, known for its unique dual-display technology that extends battery life. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY Z FLIP5
description: Samsung's Galaxy Z Flip5 is a folding flip phone with a larger cover screen, allowing users to perform tasks without opening the device. It is recommended by Wired for its size and functionality. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: GOOGLE PIXEL 7A
description: The Google Pixel 7A is a smartphone favored for its decent performance, AMOLED screen with a 120-Hz refresh rate, and reliable cameras. It lacks wireless charging but has a battery life of more than a day. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ONEPLUS 11
description: The OnePlus 11 is a fast-performing smartphone with a 120-Hz AMOLED screen, great speakers, and good battery life. It has an IP64 water- and dust-resistance rating. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: UGREEN
description: Ugreen is a company that produces a 145-watt charger with a 25,000-mAh battery, which is compact for its power. [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: UGREEN CHARGER
description: Ugreen's charger is a 145-watt charger with a 25,000-mAh battery, surprisingly compact for the power it provides. It has two USB-C ports and one USB-A port, capable of delivering 145 watts while charging, with one USB-C port at 100W and the other at 45W. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER NANO
description: The Anker Nano is a portable power bank, particularly suitable for phones. It has a 12-watt Lightning connector and a 22.5-watt USB-C version for the iPhone 15 or Android phones. Both connectors fold away when not in use. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER 2-IN-1 CHARGER
description: This 2-in-1 charger is featured in the guide to the Best MagSafe Accessories. It can charge your compatible wireless earbuds while simultaneously charging your iPhone at the maximum 15-watt rate. It supports iOS 17’s new StandBy mode, converting the iPhone into a bedside alarm clock. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER 3-IN-1 MAGSAFE WIRELESS CHARGING DOCK
description: The Anker 3-in-1 MagSafe Wireless Charging Dock, as described by Wired on 2023-10-10, is a super compact and versatile charging solution designed for Apple users. This innovative dock features a MagSafe pad that charges iPhones at a slanted angle, providing up to 15 watts of power, although it does not support fast charging. Adjacent to the MagSafe pad, there is a standard Apple Watch puck, which unfortunately lacks fast-charging capabilities as well. The design of the dock is triangular, with a dedicated space inside the triangle where users can place their AirPods Pro or any other wireless earbuds case for charging, making it a convenient all-in-one charging station for multiple Apple devices.

name: IPHONE 15
description: The iPhone 15 is a model of Apple's smartphone that is compatible with the 22.5-watt USB-C version of the Anker Nano and the Backbone One. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: 3-IN-1 WIRELESS CHARGER
description: A 3-in-1 wireless charger is a compact device that can charge an iPhone using a MagSafe pad, an Apple Watch using a built-in charger, and AirPods Pro or other wireless earbuds cases in the space inside the triangle [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER 737 POWER BANK
description: The Anker 737 Power Bank is a high-capacity power solution with an impressive 24,000 mAh capacity, designed to swiftly charge a wide range of devices including laptops, tablets, phones, and other electronic gadgets. Notably, it features a built-in display that allows users to keep track of essential stats such as the temperature and the remaining battery percentage, ensuring optimal performance and safety. With its ability to charge from zero to full in just an hour, the Anker 737 Power Bank stands out as a versatile and efficient charging companion for tech enthusiasts and professionals alike, as reported by Wired on 2023-10-10.

name: SATECHI FOLD-UP WIRELESS CHARGING STAND
description: Satechi's fold-up wireless charging stand is a portable device with a 10,000-mAh capacity. It can charge phones (up to 10 watts for phones, 7.5 watts for iPhones), wireless earbuds (5 watts), and has a USB-C port (10 watts) for a third device [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: EARBUDS
description: Earbuds are small wireless headphones that fit in the ear and are often sold with a charging case. They can support Qi wireless charging and have a USB-C port for charging a third device. The downside is that they offer slow charging, with up to 10 watts for phones, 7.5 watts for iPhones, 5 watts for earbuds, and 10 watts from the USB-C port [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: JABRA ELITE 7 ACTIVE
description: The Jabra Elite 7 Active are top-rated workout earbuds that came out in 2021. They are the smallest with the most comfortable fit, and the rubber tip keeps them securely in the ear during physical activities. They are IP57-rated to withstand sweat and offer 8 hours of battery life and up to 30 hours in the case [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER SPACE A40
description: Anker's Space A40 earbuds are feature-packed with noise canceling, wireless charging, and 10 hours of battery life. They sound good, are lightweight, and comfortable to wear, making them a strong competitor to Apple's AirPods [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ANKER LIBERTY 4 NC
description: Anker's Liberty 4 NC earbuds are another feature-packed pair of buds with great noise canceling. They are on sale for $80 ($20 off) [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: VITAMIX
description: Vitamix is a reputable company renowned for manufacturing professional-quality blenders, with the Vitamix 5200 model being a standout product. As of 2023, the Vitamix 5200 blender has been highly recommended by WIRED, praised for its powerful performance, durability, and versatility in blending smoothies, soups, and sauces. To make a cost-effective and environmentally conscious choice, purchasing a refurbished Vitamix blender is advised, as it allows customers to save money while reducing waste.

name: KITCHENAID
description: KitchenAid is a company that produces the Artisan Mini blender, which is better suited for smaller kitchens and households [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: NUTRIBULLET
description: NutriBullet is a company that produces the Smart Touch Blender, which comes with a 1,500-watt motor base, a 64-ounce pitcher, and a selection of presets for various blending tasks [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: KITCHENAID ARTISAN MINI
description: The KitchenAid Artisan Mini is a smaller version of the full-size, 5-quart mixer, better suited for smaller kitchens and households. It is on sale for $380 ($60 off) [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ZOJIRUSHI RICE COOKER
description: Zojirushi's rice cookers are a favorite at Wired, using "fuzzy logic technology" with a microcomputer to ensure perfectly cooked grains with minimal effort and no burned or wet spots. The product has been seen at a slightly lower price, but the current deal is still good [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: AEROGARDEN
description: This AeroGarden goes on sale frequently, and the price is right. Wired reviewer Louryn Strampe found it super easy to use for growing herbs. The light is bright, making it less ideal for a studio apartment [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: BEE'S WRAP
description: Bee's Wrap is an alternative to plastic wrap, made from organic cotton and sustainably sourced beeswax, along with jojoba oil and tree resin. They are waterproof and can be rinsed with cold water to avoid melting the wax [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: STASHER REUSABLE BAGGIES
description: Stasher reusable baggies are a Wired favorite, doing everything a single-use Ziplock bag does but are dishwasher-, freezer-, and microwave-safe. They can also be used to organize supplies like screws, crayons, and bobby pins [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: REZIP REUSABLE BAGGIES
description: Rezip reusable baggies are durable, freezer-safe, and easy to clean by placing them in the dishwasher. They are much cheaper than Stasher if you want to try reusable options [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: STASHER
description: Stasher is a brand of reusable baggies that are dishwasher-, freezer-, and microwave-safe, and can be used to keep supplies organized. They are one of the favorite products of the author and are recommended for their durability and ease of cleaning. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: REZIP
description: Rezip is a brand of reusable baggies that are durable, freezer-safe, and easy to clean by placing them in the dishwasher. They are cheaper than Stasher and are a good option for those wanting to try reusable baggies. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: HYDROJUG
description: The HydroJug is a water bottle that is one of the favorites of the author and is recommended for its size and weight, making it useful for those who are often unmotivated to fill smaller bottles. The sale price extends to a variety of colors. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: FLAMIN' HOT CHEETOS
description: Flamin' Hot Cheetos are a spicy snack that can be purchased in a multipack on Prime Day. The author, Louryn, accidentally conditioned herself to crave them before bed after getting a multipack a few years ago. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: 1ZPRESSO J-MAX
description: 1Zpresso's J-Max is a hand grinder that gets high marks from espresso gurus around the web. It is over triple the price of the Hario Skerton Pro, but it has always garnered high marks for its ability to deliver a very even fine grind. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: NINJA MAX XL
description: Ninja's Max XL is an air fryer that is notable for its space-saving design, which leaves countertop space for other tasks. The max crisp setting is perfect for making homemade fries with a nice amount of crunch, and you can even modify conventional oven recipes to work with the Ninja. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ELECTRIC KETTLE
description: An electric kettle is a device that heats water to a precise temperature quickly and conveniently. It is recommended for making pour-over coffee and has a gooseneck for precise pouring. The EKG+ model has a smooth pour and can hold its temperature for up to an hour before it auto shuts off, although the 2.5-foot cable could stand to be longer. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: AEROPRESS
description: The AeroPress is a portable coffee maker that is highly regarded by the WIRED Gear Team. It makes a high-quality cup of coffee and is easy to use and clean. This model can make up to 10 fluid ounces of coffee at a time, which is about a diner mug's worth. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: HELIX MIDNIGHT LUXE HYBRID MATTRESS
description: The Helix Midnight Luxe Hybrid Mattress is a mattress that includes two pillows and is available at a discounted price with the code DEALDAY25. It has six layers of foam and individually wrapped inner springs, making it comfortable for almost all sleeping positions. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: CASPER HYBRID BED
description: Casper's hybrid bed is a mattress that often reaches a price of $1,196 on Amazon. It is a neutral option that strikes a good balance between soft and supportive, with just enough bounce. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MY GREEN MATTRESS
description: My Green Mattress is a company that offers organic mattresses and mattress toppers. The organic mattress pick for kids is made from certified organic cotton, wool, and latex. The organic latex mattress topper is 2 inches high, has a zipper for removing the organic cotton cover, and stays in place without needing any straps. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: PHILIPS
description: Philips, a renowned technology company, is celebrated for its innovative smart home products, particularly its smart bulbs that seamlessly integrate with its smart home hub and a variety of third-party accessories. Alongside its contemporary contributions to the tech landscape, Philips has a rich history in co-developing the CD technology with Sony, marking a significant milestone in the evolution of digital media.

name: NETGEAR
description: Netgear is a company that produces the Nighthawk series of routers, which are well-regarded and featured in the Best Routers guide

name: EERO
description: Eero is a company that produces mesh routers, such as the Pro 6E, which is recommended by Wired for its ease of use and coverage of up to 2,000 square feet

name: SIMPLISAFE
description: SimpliSafe is a company that offers home security systems, including multiple motion, door, and window sensors, panic buttons, and key fob controllers

name: GOVEE
description: Govee is a company that produces smart lighting, including a diffused light strip that can be installed on walls, stairs, or other visible areas and supports various effects through its app

name: MONSTER
description: Monster is a company that produces a digital photo frame, which is not as highly recommended as options from Aura or Nixplay

name: GOVEE LIGHT STRIP
description: Govee Light Strip is a diffused light strip that can be installed on walls, stairs, or anywhere else in plain view. It comes with adhesive brackets, supports countless effects in the Govee app, and works with voice commands from Google Assistant or Alexa. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: GOVEE APP
description: The Govee app supports countless effects for the Govee Light Strip. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MONSTER DIGITAL FRAME
description: Monster's digital frame is a 1280p screen that gets crisp photos and can use Google Assistant or Alexa. It is cheaper than options from Aura or Nixplay but still offers good quality. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ECOFLOW RIVER 2 PRO
description: EcoFlow River 2 Pro is a portable power station with a large handle for easy carrying. The LiFeP04 battery inside is good for 768 watt-hours, making it perfect for keeping gadgets charged up on camping trips. The main downside is fan noise. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ECOFLOW
description: EcoFlow is a company that produces the EcoFlow River 2 Pro portable power station. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: TILE STICKER
description: Tile Sticker is a Bluetooth tracker sticker that can be stuck onto remotes, e-readers, or anything else you want to keep track of within a 150-foot range. This is the best price seen since last year. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: PETCUBE BITES 2
description: Petcube Bites 2 is a pet camera that holds more treats (1.5 pounds) and larger pieces (up to 1 inch in diameter) than some other pet cameras. It has an extensive four-microphone array that sounds great both ways. The Bites 2 Lite loses the laser and is made from plastic rather than aluminum, but it's significantly cheaper. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: BIKES 2
description: The Bites 2 is a video doorbell with a four-microphone array, offering good video quality at 1080p but with a limited field of view. It is one of the cheapest options available, even with a subscription service. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: BIKES 2 LITE
description: The Bites 2 Lite is a cheaper version of the Bites 2 video doorbell, made from plastic instead of aluminum. It is typically priced at $100 but is currently discounted to $80. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: NIU KQI3 PRO
description: The Niu KQi3 Pro is an electric scooter that is regularly on sale. It has a great range, typically going 18 to 20 miles on a single charge. It can reach a maximum speed of 20 miles per hour, has 9.5-inch tubeless tires for a comfortable ride, and reliable disc brakes. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: WITHINGS BODY+
description: The Withings Body+ is a smart scale that tracks health data including body fat, muscle mass, and total body water. It can display charts of health progress over time. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: WITHINGS BODY COMP
description: The Withings Body Comp is an upgraded model of the Body+ smart scale. It includes extra features to monitor heart health, such as a built-in heart monitor that analyzes cardiovascular health using vascular age data. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: WITHINGS BODY CARDIO
description: The Withings Body Cardio is a smart scale that is normally cheaper than the Body Comp. It is currently on sale, making it an even better deal. It includes features to monitor heart health. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: AQUARES WATER LEAK DETECTOR KIT
description: The Aqara Water Leak Detector Kit is designed to alert homeowners to water leaks using four sensors and a hub. It uses the LoRa standard for long-range communication and is recommended for larger properties. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: AQUARES DOORBELL
description: The Aqara Doorbell is a chunky doorbell with 1080p video quality and a wide 162-degree field of view. It can be powered by AA batteries or wired, and comes with an indoor hub for local video recording and Wi-Fi signal boosting. It is compatible with various smart home systems, including Apple's HomeKit Secure Video. [Source: Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: NANOLEAF LIGHT KIT
description: The Nanoleaf Light Kit is a product that allows for fun ambient lighting in any room, with each hexagon functioning as its own light that can be controlled and customized in color schemes and design. [Photograph: Nanoleaf, 2023-10-10]

name: EPICKA TRAVEL ADAPTER
description: The Epicka Travel Adapter is a budget pick in the Best Travel Adapters guide, working in over 150 countries and featuring four USB-A ports and a 15-watt USB-C port. [If you want to stay powered up on your travels, you need a travel adapter, and this one from Epicka is the budget pick in our Best Travel Adapters guide, 2023-10-10]

name: GOOGLE NEST HUB MAX
description: The Google Nest Hub Max is a smart display with a large screen and powerful speakers, recommended for its dual functionality as a photo frame and kitchen assistant. [The Google Nest Hub Max has a nice big screen and slim, powerful speakers to match. It's our favorite smart display for a variety of reasons, from how nicely it doubles as a photo frame to how great it is as a kitchen assistant, 2023-10-10]

name: THERABODY SMART GOGGLES
description: Therabody's Smart Goggles use heat, vibrations, and light pressure to massage the eyes and temples, with an app for customization and heart rate tracking to reduce stress and anxiety. [Therabody's Smart Goggles (9/10, WIRED Recommends) use heat, vibrations, and light pressure to massage your eyes and temples. The app lets you customize sessions and track your heart rate to help reduce stress and anxiety, 2023-10-10]

name: THERAFACE PRO
description: The TheraFace Pro is a self-care tool that exfoliates, clears up sinuses, and minimizes fine lines, with additional functions like microcurrent that may or may not work. [The TheraFace Pro is a very expensive self-care tool. We liked it, finding it exfoliated away blackheads, cleared up stuffy sinuses from allergies, and even minimized fine lines, 2023-10-10]

name: FOREO LUNA 3
description: The Foreo Luna 3 is a skincare device that exfoliates, clears up sinuses, and minimizes fine lines. It has microcurrent functions and has not often gone on sale in its yearish shelf life [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: WILLOW GO WEARABLE BREAST PUMP
description: The Willow Go Wearable Breast Pump is easy to use, clean, and portable. It is usually expensive but is currently priced similarly to a standard portable pump [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ELVIE STRIDE
description: The Elvie Stride is a breast pump that is recommended by Wired. It is currently on sale, which may help to cover the cost not covered by insurance [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: STROLLER
description: The stroller is all-around great, comes with an adapter for infant car seats, has great suspension, and folds down close to flat. It is a good deal for its regular price and even more worth purchasing right now [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: TUSHY CLASSIC 3.0 BIDET
description: The Tushy Classic 3.0 Bidet is affordable and easy to install on practically any toilet. It does not require an electrical plug or a hot water hookup and is recommended as the best budget bidet that's non-electric [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MULTIGROOM SERIES 9000
description: The Multigroom Series 9000, a high-end grooming tool, boasts a versatile array of attachments designed to cater to diverse grooming needs. This trimmer comes equipped with an adjustable guide for customizable length settings, a mini-foil shaver for precise detailing, a narrow-width head for hard-to-reach areas, a T-shaped head for straight and clean lines, and an ear/nose attachment for thorough grooming. Its stainless steel construction is a notable feature, setting it apart from the majority of consumer-level trimmers, as it signifies durability and quality typically found in professional-grade devices. The Multigroom Series 9000 is a comprehensive grooming solution, offering users the ability to trim, shave, and detail with precision and ease, all in one device.

name: COWAY AIRMEGA 250 AIR PURIFIER
description: The Coway Airmega 250 Air Purifier is recommended for larger rooms. It has automatic functioning that adjusts based on pollution levels. Product reviewer Matt Jancer has been using it for years in his New York City apartment. Filters are expensive but last nearly a year [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: DIGGS CARRIER
description: The Diggs carrier is a high-end pet carrier that works for cats or smaller dogs. It has safety features like seat belt clips and a buckle strap, and has been crash-tested. It has a five-star rating by the Center for Pet Safety. The only downside is that you can't see through the mesh to check on your pet [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: WIIM SUNRISE ALARM
description: The WiiM Sunrise Alarm is a gentle way to wake up, mimicking real sunlight by gradually brightening and changing color temperature. It also has a sunset feature for winding down before bed. It was the easiest to set up and use among all the sunrise alarms tested by WIRED reviewer Matt Jancer [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: MATT JANCER
description: Matt Jancer, a seasoned product reviewer for Wired, has extensively tested various gadgets and household items, showcasing his expertise in evaluating their performance and quality. Over the years, he has relied on the Coway Airmega 250 Air Purifier, attesting to its effectiveness in maintaining clean air in his environment. In addition to air purifiers, Jancer has also put the WiiM Sunrise Alarm and a 35-pint dehumidifier to the test, providing readers with insights into their functionality and utility. Notably, he has confirmed the durability of Hydro Flask water bottles, highlighting their robustness and reliability for everyday use. Through his comprehensive reviews, Matt Jancer offers valuable guidance to consumers seeking to make informed decisions about technology and entertainment products.

name: CENTER FOR PET SAFETY
description: The Center for Pet Safety is an organization that rates pet products. The Diggs carrier has a five-star rating from this organization [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: GRAVITY MOVE
description: The Gravity Move is a massage gun that is compact but effective in working sore muscles. It comes with four attachment heads, including a heated one. The only downside is that the case is small and can only fit the device and one head at a time. [Photograph: Gravity, 2023-10-10]

name: PET BED
description: Pet beds are available for sale, and if you stare longingly at your pet as they snooze in their tiny beds, you might want to consider investing in your own. It's expensive though, so the $100 discount is welcome. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: PRINTER
description: A printer is recommended by a WIRED reviewer after their last one died. It's wireless, good quality for prints and scans, and you can print from your phone. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: CANDLES
description: Candles are great buys to treat yourself or to gift others. They're 13.5 ounces, smell good, and are hand-poured in the US. The company also provides fun astrology insights. [Photograph: Loop, 2023-10-10]

name: EAR PLUGS
description: Ear plugs are stylish, have different-sized ear tips, and stay put much more easily than foam ones. They are reusable and are the Best for Sleep in the WIRED Best Earplugs guide. [Photograph: Loop, 2023-10-10]

name: PET HAIR REMOVER
description: A handy tool for removing pet hair from furniture. It works well and you don't have to worry about refilling sticky lint rollers. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: BASEPAWS
description: Basepaws is a company that provides genetic testing for cats. It gives breed percentages and states if they're a carrier or at risk of several health issues. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: TRAIL RUNNING SHOES
description: Trail running shoes have a wide toe box and are designed to switch easily between running on trails. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: PAWS
description: PAWS is a company that provides detailed PDF reports about pets, including breed percentages and health risk assessments [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ADRIENNE
description: Adrienne is a multifaceted individual with a keen interest in both parenting and fitness. As a proud mother, she is attentive to the needs of her 6-year-old son, ensuring that he has access to quality play equipment. She recently purchased a playset, paying full price for it, and has been impressed by its sturdiness and longevity, a testament to her commitment to investing in durable items for her child's enjoyment and safety [Wired, 2023-10-10]. In her personal life, Adrienne is an active runner, favoring shoes with a wide toe box. This choice reflects her need for footwear that can adapt to various terrains, whether she's hitting the trails or pounding the pavement, showcasing her versatile and dynamic approach to running [Wired, 2023-10-10].

name: SHOES
description: Shoes with a wide toe box are designed for versatility, allowing easy transition between running on trails and roads [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: RECYCLED CLOTHING BRANDS
description: Recycled clothing brands offer eco-friendly workout clothes that were surprisingly available on Amazon during Prime Day [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: DYSON V15 DETECT CORDLESS STICK VACUUM
description: The Dyson V15 Detect Cordless Stick Vacuum is lightweight, easily convertible to a handheld model, and features a green laser head to spot microscopic dust [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: LUPE CORDLESS VACUUM
description: Lupe's cordless vacuum is highly recommended, with a strong seal against the ground created by a composite foam roller, but it has a high price and produces loud noise [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: BEST BUDGET-FRIENDLY DYSON
description: The best budget-friendly Dyson vacuum is accessible due to a deal price, can be converted into a hand vacuum, and has a runtime of about 40 minutes [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: SHARK AI ULTRA 2-IN-1
description: The Shark AI Ultra 2-in-1 is a versatile and efficient vac-mop combo robot vacuum, designed to cater to the cleaning needs of modern households. Utilizing advanced laser navigation technology, it accurately maps the home environment, enabling users to conveniently subdivide vacuuming and mopping zones through a user-friendly app. This innovative device ensures thorough cleaning by effectively vacuuming various surfaces and meticulously scrubbing floors, all while avoiding the common issue of wetting carpets. The inclusion of a dedicated mopping bin further enhances its capability to leave floors spotless and dry. As a testament to its performance, the Shark AI Ultra 2-in-1 has received commendations from Wired in their 2023-10-10 publication, highlighting its superior cleaning abilities and intelligent design.

name: EUFY X9 PRO
description: The Eufy X9 Pro is a robot vacuum with mopping capabilities, featuring two mops that rotate at about 180 revolutions per minute. It is effective for mopping floors quickly and accurately, and the docking station dries the mops [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ROBOROCK
description: Roborock is a company that recently launched an upgrade to a robot vacuum model, which is a favorite of WIRED senior associate reviews editor Adrienne So for its consistent performance in cleaning [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: ADRIENNE SO
description: Adrienne So is a WIRED senior associate reviews editor who has tested and recommended the Shark AI Ultra 2-in-1 and the Eufy X9 Pro, and consistently uses a Roborock vacuum in her home [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: BISSELL LITTLE GREEN MACHINE CARPET CLEANER
description: The Bissell Little Green Machine Carpet Cleaner is a carpet cleaning product that made WIRED's list of the Best Carpet Cleaners and the Best Viral TikTok Gadgets. It is effective for cleaning furniture, stairs, and vehicles [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: SAMSUNG STICK VACUUM
description: Samsung's stick vacuum is a product that does not claim to use AI. It is a great vacuum for cleaning in midcentury modern homes, as noted in a review by Adrienne So [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: GREEN MACHINE
description: The Green Machine is a portable, cordless carpet cleaner from Bissell, suitable for cleaning furniture, stairs, and vehicles. It was featured in Wired's Best Carpet Cleaners and Best Viral TikTok Gadgets lists [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: YOTO PLAYER
description: The Yoto Player, a highly durable and portable speaker, is designed to cater to the diverse content needs of children aged 3 to 12. This innovative device allows for the playback of bedtime stories, music, and more by simply slotting in cards. It boasts a kid-friendly radio feature and a sleep mode, ensuring a safe and enjoyable audio experience for young listeners. The Yoto Player's capabilities and design have earned it a spot in Wired's Best Kids Speakers guide, published on October 10, 2023, solidifying its reputation as a top choice for parents seeking quality audio devices for their children.

name: GRIMLOCK T-REX MOTORCYCLE
description: The Grimlock T-Rex motorcycle is a toy that is described as the coolest one among a set of toys, suitable for sharing among siblings [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: LEGO ARTIFICIAL FLOWERS
description: LEGO artificial flowers are a set of buildable flowers that range from roses, poppies, daises, and snapdragons. They can be added to a favorite vase and are a long-lasting alternative to real flowers [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: SQUISHMALLOW PANCAKES
description: The Squishmallow pancakes are an adorable stack of pancakes complete with a butter-and-syrup flower garnish. They are part of a collection of Squishmallows on sale for Prime Day, including a narwhal, hedgehog, mushroom, and possum [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: MAGNA-TILES
description: Magna-Tiles are a STEM toy that is addicting for just about any kid. This set lets you build a road and cranes, making it a great choice for any construction enthusiast or as an add-on to any current Magna-Tiles owners [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: LEGO NINJAGO SET
description: The Lego Ninjago set is a 1,060-piece set that was originally commissioned as a limited run and then extended for its popularity. It is a reasonable price for a biggish set that looks like a relatively simple build with a ton of minifigs [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: LEGO CITY STUNTZ ULTIMATE STUNT RIDERS CHALLENGE
description: The Lego City Stuntz Ultimate Stunt Riders Challenge is a more interactive Lego set that comes with a 360-degree loop, a ring of fire, an “alien tower” vertical climb, a ramp, two toy motorcycles, and four Lego City minifigures. The three stunt challenges can be configured in a variety of different ways [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: SAMSUNG THE FRAME
description: Samsung's The Frame, a sophisticated and innovative television model, seamlessly integrates into the aesthetic of any room by resembling a piece of art when not in use. This unique design feature allows the TV to blend effortlessly into the background of a well-curated space, enhancing the overall ambiance and decor. As of the 10th of October, 2023, The Frame has been featured in Prime Day deals, offering potential buyers an exciting opportunity to acquire this stylish and functional addition to their home entertainment setup at a discounted price.

name: QUANTUM DOT-ENABLED OLED
description: This quantum dot-enabled OLED is the brightest organic LED display that has been tested. It has shockingly bright colors [Wired 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON FIRE TV
description: Amazon's Fire TV is a solid and affordable TV with Dolby Vision support and voice control using Alexa, featured in the Prime Day deals [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: HISENSE
description: Hisense is a company known for producing quality mid-tier TVs, including the U8K, which is featured in the Prime Day deals [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: HISENSE U7
description: The Hisense U7 is a TV with a 144-Hz native refresh rate, making games look smooth, and supports high dynamic range codecs for vibrant colors, part of the Prime Day deals [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: TCL
description: TCL is a company that offers a large-screen TV option with support for high dynamic range codecs and a built-in Fire TV interface, featured in the Prime Day deals [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: NANOLEAF 4D KIT
description: Nanoleaf's 4D Kit is a lighting system that enhances the visual experience of movies and video games by projecting the TV screen's colors onto the wall, recommended by Wired and part of the Prime Day deals [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: JBL BAR 1300X
description: The JBL Bar 1300X is a versatile soundbar that boasts detachable wireless speakers, allowing for flexible placement options without the clutter of cables. This innovative audio system delivers impressive Dolby Atmos immersion, enhancing the listening experience with its multi-dimensional sound capabilities. However, it's worth noting that the wireless speakers require charging between uses, which might be a consideration for continuous, uninterrupted audio enjoyment. As of 2023-10-10, the JBL Bar 1300X is featured in Prime Day deals, making it an attractive option for those looking to upgrade their home entertainment systems at a discounted price. The photograph provided by JBL on the same date showcases the sleek design and components of the soundbar, giving potential buyers a visual representation of its aesthetic and build quality.

name: YAMAHA SR-C20A
description: Yamaha's SR-C20A is an affordable soundbar with 100-watt forward-facing drivers that can outperform most TV speakers. It is budget-friendly and suitable for modest TV setups. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: ROKU STREAMBAR
description: The Roku Streambar is a device that combines sound enhancement with streaming capabilities. It is compact and ideal for homes with limited space, delivering good sound quality. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: TCL TV
description: TCL's mid-tier TV model is recommended for most people, featuring quantum dot technology and support for various HDR formats for vibrant colors. It includes a game mode that upscales 1080p to 120 frames per second and comes with Google TV instead of Roku. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: SENNHEISER LUXURY SOUNDBAR
description: Sennheiser's luxury soundbar features massive speakers with superior audio quality. It is one of the most expensive soundbars recommended by WIRED, rarely on sale, making the current price a good opportunity for interested buyers. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: YAMAHA ALEXA-ENABLED SOUNDBAR
description: This Yamaha soundbar includes Amazon Alexa built-in, allowing control of smart home gadgets. Its price has fluctuated recently, sometimes dropping as low as $180. [WIRED Recommends, 2023-10-10]

name: AMAZON ALEXA
description: Amazon Alexa is a voice-controlled assistant built into the Yamaha soundbar, enabling control of smart home devices [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: SMART SPEAKERS
description: Smart speakers are devices that can be set up throughout a home to facilitate control of various gadgets, including the Yamaha soundbar [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: GOPRO HERO10
description: GoPro recently reduced the price of the Hero10 Black, an action camera with an 8/10 rating from Wired, making it one of the most affordable action cameras on the market. The deal includes an extra battery, case, small tripod, and other accessories [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: CANON
description: Canon is a company that produces a mirrorless camera, which is the top pick in Wired's mirrorless camera guide. The R5 model is an upgrade with a 45-megapixel full-frame CMOS sensor, fast autofocus, and dual memory card slots [Wired, 2023-10-10]

name: SONY A7 III

name: AUTHORITARIANISM
description: Authoritarianism, a form of government where political freedoms are suppressed and power is concentrated in the hands of a select few, has been a topic of significant concern as it appears to be gaining momentum. According to Engadget (2023-10-01), the rise of authoritarianism is being exacerbated by the circulation of post-truth memes and the influence of algorithms on technology platforms, which can manipulate public opinion and foster an environment conducive to authoritarian control. Additionally, the article highlights how this political trend is impeding progress towards positive futures, partly due to the climate movement's limited and distorted understanding of democracy. These factors combined paint a complex picture of how authoritarianism is evolving in the digital age and its far-reaching impacts on society and the environment.

name: BIG TECH PLATFORMS
description: Big tech platforms are corporate entities that dominate the online media landscape. They have shifted the way we consume media and socialize, potentially impacting democracy and climate action. [Engadget, 2023-10-01]

name: ENERGY DEMOCRACY
description: Energy Democracy is a dynamic social movement that champions decentralized energy systems, emphasizing the utilization of renewable resources like wind, water, and solar power. Central to its philosophy is the promotion of local community control over energy resources, aiming to empower communities and reduce dependence on large, centralized energy production. The movement is recognized for its potential to be significantly advanced by climate activists leveraging the Internet as a tool for advocacy and mobilization. However, it faces challenges due to the prevailing media environment, which sometimes constrains the broader vision of democracy that Energy Democracy seeks to foster. Despite these obstacles, the movement persists in its efforts to reshape the energy landscape in favor of sustainability and community governance.

name: LIMBIC CAPITALISM
description: Limbic capitalism is a term coined by historian and addiction expert David Courtwright to describe the monetization of attention and the profit derived from hate and division in the current media ecosystem. [Engadget, 2023-10-01]

name: INTERNET

Beyond its role as a mere infrastructure for data transmission, it is often likened to a global endocrine system, operating on emotional and irrational impulses, much like human behavior, but without consciousness [Engadget, 2023-10-01]. However, the Internet's impact on society is not entirely positive; it has faced criticism for exacerbating societal divisions, facilitating deception, and provoking negative behaviors [The Verge, 2023-11-01]. Despite these challenges, the Internet remains a transformative force in how information is accessed, shared, and consumed on a global scale.

name: MARSHALL MCLUHAN

name: OWEN TEALE
description:
Owen Teale, a 62-year-old Welsh actor, has carved a significant niche in the entertainment industry with a career spanning several decades. He is best known for his role as the dark and brooding Ser Alliser Thorne in the hit series Game of Thrones, a character whose intense hatred towards Jon Snow Teale portrayed with remarkable depth, tapping into a sense of emptiness and nothingness to bring the character to life. His journey to success was not without its challenges; he was once suspended from his sixth-form college for organizing a Christmas party and even worked as Barry the Bear at Barry Island Pleasure Park, a role from which he was later sacked. This setback led him to the Guildford School of Acting, setting the stage for his illustrious career.

Teale's acting prowess extends beyond Game of Thrones, having starred in the 1989 television adaptation of Catherine Cookson's romance, The Fifteen Streets. He has also showcased his talent on stage, spending four years with the Royal Shakespeare Company and earning a Tony Award for his performance in Ibsen's A Doll's House in 1997. Throughout his career, he has shared the screen with notable actors such as Sean Bean and Toni Collette, the latter of whom he credits for elevating his performance in the movie Dream Horse.

Despite being offered lead roles that did not materialize due to various reasons, Teale's dedication to his craft remains unwavering. As of 2023, he is set to bring his acting skills to Melbourne for an upcoming production, demonstrating his continued relevance and commitment to the art of acting.

name: GAME OF THRONES
description: "Game of Thrones is a widely acclaimed TV series that has captured the attention of audiences around the world. Within its intricate narrative, Owen Teale portrayed the character of Ser Alliser Thorne, a significant figure in the show who was involved in the notorious event of Jon Snow's murder. This event marked a pivotal moment in the series, showcasing the complex dynamics and power struggles that define Game of Thrones. Additionally, Sean Bean played the role of Ned Stark, a central character whose actions and decisions had a profound impact on the storyline. Together, these performances contributed to the rich tapestry of characters and events that make Game of Thrones a standout in the realm of television entertainment."

name: BARRY ISLAND PLEASURE PARK

He was accepted and awarded a study grant, which helped him escape South Wales and pursue a career in acting. [The Sydney Morning Herald, 2023-10-20]

description:
"The Fifteen Streets is a popular British television adaptation of Catherine Cookson's romance novel that has garnered a significant audience. The show features Owen Teale in a leading role, with appearances by Clare Homan and Sean Bean, making it a notable production in the realm of television drama." 

However, there is a contradiction in the descriptions provided. While both agree that "The Fifteen Streets" is a TV show and Owen Teale is a part of it, one mentions Clare Homan and the other mentions Sean Bean as co-stars. Without further context, it's unclear if these are from different adaptations or if both actors appeared in the same production. Assuming they are part of the same production, the summary includes both names, acknowledging their roles in the show. If they are from different adaptations, the summary might need to be adjusted to reflect that detail, but with the given information, a combined summary is provided.

This commendation highlights Collette's ability to not only deliver powerful performances herself but also to inspire and improve the acting skills of those working alongside her.

The movie stars Owen Teale and Toni Collette, who collaborated effectively on this project, bringing to life the unique bond between humans and a horse that defies all odds to become a racing legend. This acknowledgment highlights the collaborative and appreciative nature of the entertainment industry, where talent and hard work are celebrated, even when accolades are bestowed upon individual performances.

name: SPIDER-MAN 2
description:
"Spider-Man 2, released in 2023, is a video game that immerses players in a richly detailed and dynamic Spider-Man universe. The game features two playable characters, Miles Morales and Peter Parker, both embodying the iconic Spider-Man. Players can seamlessly switch between the two heroes, who share the spotlight in the main story, which sometimes swaps perspectives between them. Side missions are flexible, allowing either Spider-Man to tackle them, but key story beats are exclusive to one or the other, adding depth to their individual narratives.

The game's setting is a meticulously crafted three-borough New York City, where players can move with fluidity and grace, akin to a choreographed ballet of action. This environment is not only vast but also interactive, with randomized encounters that can involve both Spider-Men teaming up against random criminals, enhancing the cooperative gameplay experience.

Spider-Man 2 introduces new villains, Kraven the Hunter and Venom, to the series, while also revisiting familiar foes from previous games. The game includes a retelling of the Venom origin story for Peter Parker, providing a fresh take on this classic tale. Miles Morales' story takes more creative liberties, with Hailey Cooper returning as his love interest, adding a personal touch to his character development.

Overall, Spider-Man 2 offers an engaging and innovative gaming experience, blending action, storytelling, and character development in a way that appeals to both seasoned fans and newcomers to the Spider-Man franchise."

name: MIKAELA SHIFFRIN
description:
Mikaela Shiffrin, a professional Alpine skier, has carved a remarkable legacy in the sport, becoming a dominant force with an array of accolades to her name. As of 2023, she holds the record for the most World Cup wins in Alpine skiing history, surpassing any male or female skier, and has been crowned a 7x Skiing World Champion. Shiffrin's achievements also include two Olympic gold medals, five overall World Cup victories, and four world championship wins, solidifying her status as the youngest slalom champion in Olympic Alpine skiing history.

In 2021, Shiffrin made a triumphant return to the slopes for the first of two slalom races at Levi, following a period of intense pain and grief that led her to take a break from the sport. The loss of her father, Jeff Shiffrin, deeply affected her, prompting her to question her ability to ski again. However, she found solace and connection to her father through her passion for the sport, which she honored by dedicating her record-breaking achievement to him in an Instagram post in 2023.

Beyond her professional career, Shiffrin has also contributed to the success of the University of Denver's skiing team, winning multiple NCAA team titles. Her resilience, talent, and dedication to Alpine skiing have made her a celebrated figure in the world of sports.

name: EILEEN SHIFFRIN
description: Eileen Shiffrin, the mother of Mikaela Shiffrin, has played a pivotal role in her daughter's life and skiing career. Growing up, Eileen's own passion for skiing was cultivated by her parents, who regularly took her and her siblings to ski on Mt. Greylock during the winter season. This love for the sport was later passed down to Mikaela. Eileen, alongside her husband Jeff, reignited Mikaela's passion for skiing, supporting her not only emotionally but also academically. She managed Mikaela's schoolwork and served as her full-time traveling companion, ensuring that her daughter could focus on her skiing while maintaining her education. Additionally, Eileen pursued a career as a nurse, balancing her professional life with her dedication to her daughter's athletic endeavors.

name: JEFF SHIFFRIN
description: Jeff Shiffrin, the father of renowned skier Mikaela Shiffrin, played a pivotal role in nurturing and reigniting his daughter's passion for skiing alongside her mother, Eileen. Professionally, Jeff was an anesthesiologist with a specialization in cardiothoracic medicine, having completed his rotation at St. Elizabeth's Medical Center in Brighton, Massachusetts. His love for skiing was not only a personal hobby but also a significant influence on Mikaela's career, as he frequently skied in Vermont during his youth, a tradition he continued with his family. Tragically, Jeff's life was cut short on February 2, 2020, when he succumbed to a head injury sustained from an accidental fall. His legacy, however, lives on through Mikaela's continued success in the sport he so dearly loved.

name: ALPINE SKIING
description: Alpine skiing is a sport in which Mikaela Shiffrin excels, having made history with her numerous victories and records. [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]

name: ST. ELIZABETH’S MEDICAL CENTER
description: St. Elizabeth’s Medical Center in Brighton, Massachusetts, is where Eileen and Jeff Shiffrin met. Jeff was completing his cardiothoracic rotation there at the time. [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]

name: ASPN
description: Aspen is a snowy wonderland and ski destination where Eileen and Jeff Shiffrin took their first vacation together as a couple, reigniting Eileen's passion for skiing. [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]

name: UNIVERSITY OF DENVER
description: The University of Denver is an educational institution where Mikaela Shiffrin and Taylor Shiffrin won two NCAA team titles. [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]

name: TAYLOR
description:
Taylor, a multi-faceted individual, is prominently known for being the supportive brother of Mikaela Shiffrin, an accomplished skier. During her time of grief, Taylor encouraged Mikaela not to quit, referring to it as a moment of "selfishness" and invoking advice that their late father would have given, showcasing his role as a pillar of strength and guidance in her life (Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03).

Additionally, Taylor has a background in football, where he displayed a robust and determined playing style. Despite only taking the field for three second-half snaps, he fought for yardage on every carry, demonstrating his physical prowess and competitive spirit. However, his performance suggested some rustiness in processing his blocking and determining the best running paths, indicating a potential period of adjustment or return to the sport (CBSSports.com, 2023-10-12).

Furthermore, Taylor is associated with Inter Miami, a professional football club. While the exact role is not specified, he could be involved as a coach or manager, contributing to the strategic and operational aspects of the team (Sporting News, 2023-10-04). This connection to Inter Miami adds another layer to Taylor's involvement in the sports world, suggesting a broad range of interests and experiences within the athletic community.

name: EILEEN
description: Eileen is Mikaela Shiffrin's mother who witnessed her daughter's devastation and inability to cope with the pain, as mentioned in an article by Essentially Sports [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]
