description: The Audi FIS Alpine Ski World Cup is an event where the Skiing Federation's new rules are being applied, and Mikaela Shiffrin participated in 2021 and set a record in 2022 [Essentially Sports, 2023-11-03]

name: 2019 RUGBY WORLD CUP
description: The 2019 Rugby World Cup was a tournament that concluded with the final match between England and South Africa, marking several firsts in the sport's history. South Africa scored a try for the first time in a final, and the 32-12 victory gave them their third title, equaling a record. [Sporting News, 2023-10-20]

name: 2023 RUGBY WORLD CUP
description: The 2023 Rugby World Cup is a prestigious international tournament where top rugby teams from around the globe compete for the world championship title. Among the standout matches of this event is the highly anticipated semi-final clash between England and South Africa. This encounter marks a significant moment in rugby history, as it comes four years after the two nations faced off in an unforgettable final match during the 2019 Rugby World Cup, as reported by Sporting News on 2023-10-20. The 2023 semi-final promises to be a thrilling rematch, with both teams eager to prove their mettle and advance to the final, potentially setting the stage for a repeat of their previous historic confrontation.

name: ENGLAND RUGBY TEAM
description: The England Rugby Team, a national powerhouse in the sport, is making a significant impact in the 2023 Rugby World Cup. Having navigated through the tournament with an impressive undefeated record, the team has secured notable victories over Argentina, Japan, Chile, and Fiji. Their outstanding performance has propelled them to the semi-finals, where they are set to face a formidable opponent, South Africa, in a highly anticipated match. This summary consolidates information from both descriptions, highlighting the team's achievements and upcoming challenge in the Rugby World Cup.

name: SOUTH AFRICA RUGBY TEAM (SPRINGBOKS)
description: The South Africa Rugby Team, also known as the Springboks, is a national team competing in the 2023 Rugby World Cup. They have faced challenges, including losses to Ireland and victories over Scotland, Romania, and Tonga, leading to their semi-final clash against England. [Sporting News, 2023-10-20]

name: OWEN FARRELL
description: Owen Farrell, a key figure in the realm of rugby, is the captain of the England Rugby Team. Known for his exceptional skills and leadership, Farrell is set on inspiring his team to victory against the Springboks. His prowess was recently showcased when he kicked 20 points in the quarter-final match against Fiji, playing a crucial role in England's triumph. As of 2023, Farrell's dedication and performance are central to England's success in the rugby world, making him a pivotal player to watch in upcoming matches.

This engagement showcases U2's commitment to delivering exceptional experiences to their audience by embracing innovative concert settings.

name: SPHERE
description: SPHERE is a groundbreaking $US2.3 billion venue initially situated in Las Vegas, envisioned to revolutionize the concert industry by delivering a singularly unique and immersive experience for audiences. Designed with cutting-edge technology, SPHERE boasts vast video screens and advanced sound systems, enhancing the sensory experience of live performances. In an ambitious expansion plan, multiple SPHERE locations are in the works, enabling shows to seamlessly transition from one venue to another, thus broadening its reach and impact in the entertainment world. This strategic move, as reported by The Sydney Morning Herald on 2023-10-19, underscores SPHERE's commitment to becoming a global standard for immersive entertainment experiences.

name: HIPGNOSIS SONG MANAGEMENT
description: Hipgnosis Song Management is a company renowned for its efficient and timely fulfillment of duties to HSF, specifically in the areas of independent valuation and the preparation of interim results. This entity has demonstrated a distinctive approach to song management, which is projected to empower it to outperform the broader music market. This assertion is supported by the impressive 44% total return that the company has realized since the acquisition on the $440 million Transaction, as reported by Music Business Worldwide on 2023-09-28. Hipgnosis Song Management's strategies and execution in the music industry have positioned it as a leading player with a promising future.

name: HIPGNOSIS SONGS FUND (HSF)
description: Hipgnosis Songs Fund (HSF), an investment entity specialized in owning music copyrights, is currently facing concerns from its board regarding the valuation of the company's assets as reflected in its interim results. The board's apprehensions are centered on the credibility of the independent valuer, Citrin Cooperman, and the possible repercussions of any valuation inaccuracies on the overall shareholder value, as reported by Music Business Worldwide on December 19, 2023. These concerns highlight the importance of accurate asset valuation in maintaining investor confidence and the financial health of HSF within the music industry.

name: CITRIN COOPERMAN
description: Citrin Cooperman, a financial valuation firm, has been appointed by the Hipgnosis Songs Fund (HSF) board to independently assess the Net Asset Value of the fund's portfolio, which includes various music catalogues. Despite the recent hikes in interest rates, Citrin Cooperman has maintained an 8.5% discount rate for the valuation of HSF's assets. However, the company's credibility has come under scrutiny from Christopher Brown of JP Morgan, as reported by Music Business Worldwide on December 19, 2023. This controversy might affect the perception of Citrin Cooperman's impartiality and the reliability of its valuations within the music industry.

name: BOARD OF HIPGNOSIS SONGS FUND
description: The Board of Hipgnosis Songs Fund is responsible for overseeing the valuation of the company's investments in music catalogues and has appointed Citrin Cooperman to perform this specialist work.[]

name: CHRISTOPHER MILLS
description: Christopher Mills is an activist investor who was appointed as a non-exec Director by Hipgnosis Songs Fund's board last week.[]

name: HIPGNOSIS SONGS FUND
description: Hipgnosis Songs Fund, an organization dedicated to owning a distinctive collection of culturally impactful and iconic songs, is designed to generate robust long-term value. This belief is anchored in the anticipation of favorable structural trends within the music industry, as reported by Music Business Worldwide on 2023-09-28. However, the fund's board has expressed concerns regarding the valuation of their portfolio, which is assessed by Citrin Cooperman, as highlighted in a subsequent Music Business Worldwide article on 2023-12-19. Despite these worries, Hipgnosis Songs Fund continues to focus on leveraging the inherent strength and enduring appeal of its music assets to capitalize on industry growth.

name: JP MORGAN
description: JP Morgan, a prominent financial institution known for offering investment banking and financial services, actively monitors and evaluates Hipgnosis Songs Fund (HSF). As of December 19, 2023, JP Morgan has provided detailed analysis on HSF's valuation and credibility, demonstrating its expertise in assessing the music industry's investment opportunities. Additionally, the institution has assigned an 'overweight' rating to HSF's share price, indicating a positive outlook and suggesting that the shares are expected to outperform the market. This rating and analysis reflect JP Morgan's commitment to providing comprehensive insights to its clients, enabling them to make informed decisions in the dynamic world of entertainment and technology investments.

name: CHRISTOPHER BROWN
description: Christopher Brown, a financial analyst at JP Morgan, has been actively involved in the analysis of the Hipgnosis Songs Fund (HSF). In a recent note, Brown criticized the delay in HSF's results publication, questioning the credibility of Citrin Cooperman's valuation. This critique aligns with the concerns expressed by the HSF board regarding Citrin Cooperman's valuation, leading Brown to suggest that HSF's shares might weaken and that Citrin Cooperman's resignation could be a potential outcome. As of December 19, 2023, Brown's insights have been featured in Music Business Worldwide, providing valuable commentary on the financial dynamics within the music industry.

name: KROLL
description: Kroll is a valuation expert that was previously appointed to consider the reasonableness of Citrin Cooperman's assumptions for Hipgnosis Songs Fund's portfolio valuation [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-12-19]

name: HIPGNOSIS SONGS MANAGEMENT (HSM)
description: Hipgnosis Songs Management is a music management company that has a conflict of interest with HSF. It was asked to opine on the valuation of HSF's portfolio [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-12-19]

name: CLIMATE NEGOTIATIONS
description: Climate negotiations are a series of discussions among countries to address climate change, culminating in the 28th Conference of the Parties (COP28) in the United Arab Emirates, where delegates and activists gathered to discuss the future of fossil fuels [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: UNITED ARAB EMIRATES
description: The United Arab Emirates is a country that hosted the 28th Conference of the Parties (COP28), a top oil- and gas-producing nation that provided a platform for discussions on phasing out fossil fuels [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: COP28
description: COP28, or the 28th Conference of the Parties, is a significant United Nations climate conference that took place in 2023. This event, which falls under the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change, brought together countries from around the world with the shared goal of addressing climate change. A major focus of COP28 was the phase-out of fossil fuels, including coal, oil, and gas, as reported by The Verge on December 13, 2023. Additionally, the conference resulted in substantial commitments on the clean energy front. The final texts of COP28 emphasized the need to triple global renewable energy capacity by 2030, a target that was endorsed by over 100 countries. This demonstrates a collective effort to transition towards sustainable energy sources and combat the environmental impacts of climate change.

name: FOSSIL FUELS
description: "Fossil fuels, encompassing coal, oil, and gas, stand at the crux of a significant global shift towards cleaner energy alternatives. Despite the ambitious aim of countries to phase out these traditional energy sources in a historic agreement during the COP28 summit, as reported by The Verge on December 13, 2023, the conference did not achieve this objective. Nevertheless, the International Energy Agency projects a peak in demand for fossil fuels within this decade, signaling the onset of a broader transition in the energy sector. This forecast reflects the growing commitment of nations to reduce carbon emissions and invest in sustainable energy solutions, even as the immediate consensus on phasing out fossil fuels remains elusive."

name: PARIS ACCORD
description: The Paris Accord is an international agreement from 2015 to combat global warming, which does not explicitly mention coal, oil, or natural gas [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: SULTAN AHMED AL JABER
description: Sultan Ahmed Al Jaber is the president of COP28 and the CEO of the Abu Dhabi National Oil Company, whose letter to participating governments influenced the language of the final agreements [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: ABU DHABI NATIONAL OIL COMPANY
description: The Abu Dhabi National Oil Company is an oil company whose CEO, Sultan Ahmed Al Jaber, is also the president of COP28, potentially influencing the conference's outcomes [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: CLEAN ENERGY
description: Clean energy, including solar and wind power, is on the rise as cheaper alternatives to fossil fuels in most of the world. The International Energy Agency forecasts that nearly all of the world's new electricity supply over the next few years will come from renewable and nuclear energy. The agency called the global transition to clean energy "unstoppable" earlier this year and predicted that demand for coal, oil, and gas would peak this decade. [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: INTERNATIONAL ENERGY AGENCY
description: The International Energy Agency, initially founded to safeguard the world's fuel supply after the 1970s oil crisis, has forecast that the global transition to clean energy is "unstoppable" and that demand for fossil fuels will peak this decade. The agency also called for the tripling of renewable energy capacity globally by 2030, a goal that more than 100 countries had already pledged to do. [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: US AND CHINA
description: The US and China, the world's biggest greenhouse gas polluters, committed to working together toward the goal of tripling renewable energy capacity globally by 2030. This commitment was made when each country's climate envoys met in California in November. [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: SCIENCE
description: Science supports the negotiations for clean energy transition. The world, on average, is about 1.2 degrees Celsius hotter than it was before the industrial revolution, which has led to more devastating hurricane and wildfire seasons, droughts, and displacement of communities due to rising tides. [The Verge, 2023-12-13]

name: VERMONT
description: Vermont, a state in the United States, is poised to become a hub for online sports betting with the scheduled launch of legal platforms in January 2024. Major players in the sports betting industry, including Caesars, BetRivers, DraftKings, BetMGM, Fanatics, and ESPN Bet, are all planning to enter the Vermont market. DraftKings Sportsbook will offer a multi-part welcome offer similar to what is available in other states. The state's new sports betting law permits up to six online sportsbooks, ensuring a competitive and diverse betting landscape for residents and visitors alike.

name: FANATICS SPORTSBOOK
description: Fanatics Sportsbook, a betting company known for its innovative approach to sports betting, is scheduled to launch in Vermont in January 2024. As an online sports betting platform, Fanatics Sportsbook has previously made a mark in the industry by featuring various welcome offers for new sign-ups in other states. These offers have included a bet $5, get $200 in Bonus Bets, as well as a bet $10 over five days with $200 in Bonus Bets. Unique to Fanatics Sportsbook is its connection with the company's sports apparel and gear business, where new users are not only rewarded with betting incentives but also receive money to spend in the Fanatics Store as part of the welcome package. The exact welcome offer for Vermont's launch remains unknown, but given the company's history, it is anticipated to be equally enticing. Fanatics Sportsbook has applied for a license to operate in Vermont, a move that signals its expansion and commitment to providing a comprehensive betting experience intertwined with sports merchandise opportunities.

name: ESPN BET SPORTSBOOK
description: ESPN Bet Sportsbook, a dynamic and rapidly expanding online sports betting platform, has made a significant move by applying for a license to launch operations in Vermont, as reported by Sporting News on September 26, 2023. This platform, which entered the online sports betting market earlier in the year by acquiring and rebranding the old Barstool Sportsbook, has already made its mark in 17 different states since its November 2022 launch. Leveraging its ties with the renowned ESPN sports programming network, ESPN Bet Sportsbook has been able to offer enticing promotions to attract new users. In various states, the platform has provided a 100% deposit match bonus, capped at $1,000, albeit with a 20x wagering requirement. Additionally, new sign-ups have been greeted with a promo that rewards them with $200 in Bonus Bets, divided into four $50 Bonus Bets, upon placing a wager of any amount. These strategic moves and generous offers position ESPN Bet Sportsbook as a competitive and innovative player in the sports betting industry.

name: VERMONT BETTORS
description: Vermont bettors are a group of individuals who can take advantage of FanDuel's Early Sign Up Special, which offers an extra $100 in Bonus Bets for signing up early between now and Jan. 10, 2024. [Source: Sporting News, 2023-09-26]

name: BONUS BETS
description: "BONUS BETS are a common financial incentive in the sports betting industry, utilized by various sportsbooks including BetMGM, DraftKings, and FanDuel to attract new users. Specifically, BetMGM Sportsbook offers Bonus Bets as part of their welcome package, providing a refund in the form of Bonus Bets up to $1,500 if a new user's initial bet is unsuccessful. For bets exceeding $50, the refund is divided into five separate Bonus Bets. DraftKings Sportsbook also extends Bonus Bets as a promotional tool, which can be used for betting but are not withdrawable and must be utilized within seven days. FanDuel Sportsbook VT follows a similar pattern, enabling new bettors to wager without the risk of losing their own funds. These Bonus Bets can be applied in different amounts, but they too are subject to a seven-day expiration period. When a bet placed with Bonus Bets is successful, the bettor receives the winnings but not the original bet amount back. This financial product is designed to enhance user engagement and provide a risk-free betting experience for newcomers."

name: FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK VT
description: FanDuel Sportsbook VT is a sports betting platform in Vermont that offers a welcome bonus of $100 in Bonus Bets to new sign-ups before the site launches on Jan. 11, 2024, and an additional $200 in Bonus Bets for a $5 bet. The offer sometimes includes perks like a free three-month subscription to NBA League Pass [Source: Sporting News, 2023-09-26]

Despite having no teams in the four major US pro sports leagues, Vermont residents support Boston-based teams like the Red Sox (MLB), the Celtics (NBA), the Bruins (NHL), and the Patriots (NFL). College sports are also significant, leading to betting promos surrounding local college teams. [Sporting News, 2023-09-26]

name: ANDRÉ ONANA
description: André Onana is a 27-year-old goalkeeper for Manchester United, who played his last game for Internazionale against Manchester City in the Champions League final [The Guardian, 2023-10-28]

name: INTERNAZIONALE
description: Internazionale is an Italian football club, where André Onana played his last game before joining Manchester United [The Guardian, 2023-10-28]

name: EDERSON
description: Ederson is the goalkeeper for Manchester City, who performs as a de facto extra defender to maintain fluidity along the backline [The Guardian, 2023-10-28]

name: SIMONE INZAGHI
description: Simone Inzaghi, the manager of Inter (Internazionale), has been noted for his strategic decisions, particularly in contrast to Manchester United's manager, Erik ten Hag. A point of contention in their managerial styles is the deployment of goalkeeper André Onana high up the pitch, with Inzaghi potentially holding differing views on this approach as reported by The Guardian on October 28, 2023. This highlights Inzaghi's tactical acumen and his willingness to adapt and challenge conventional wisdom in football strategy.

name: HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
description: The House of Representatives is a legislative body that approved the P5.768-trillion national budget for 2024 on third and final reading, just before Congress adjourns for a month-long break [congress.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: NATIONAL BUDGET
description: The national budget is the financial plan of the government that shows its resources, how they will be generated and used over the fiscal period, and is used to achieve national objectives, strategies, and programs [dbm.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: DEPARTMENT OF BUDGET AND MANAGEMENT (DBM)
description: The Department of Budget and Management (DBM) is a government agency that defines the government budget and oversees its implementation [dbm.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: FERDINAND MARTIN G. ROMUALDEZ
description: Ferdinand Martin G. Romualdez is the House Speaker who noted that the budgeting process was marked by rigorous discussions, particularly concerning confidential and intelligence funds, and lauded the timely passage of the 2024 General Appropriations Bill [congress.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: GOVERNMENT ENTITIES
description: Government entities include the National Government, non-financial government-owned and -controlled corporations, government financial institutions, local government units, social security institutions, the Oil Price Stabilization Fund, the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas, and the Central Bank-Board of Liquidators. The National Government budget is allocated for the implementation of various government programs and projects, the operation of government offices, payment of salaries of government employees, and payment of public debts [congress.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: CONSTITUTION
description: The Constitution states that the President shall submit to the Congress within 30 days from the opening of every regular session, as the basis of the general appropriation bill, a budget of expenditures and sources of financing including receipts from existing and proposed revenue measures [congress.gov.ph, 2023-10-08]

name: NATIONAL BUDGET FOR 2024
description: The national budget for 2024 is set at P5.768 trillion, 9.5% higher than the 2023 budget of P5.268 trillion. This budget accounts for 21.7% of the gross domestic product (GDP) and is the first fully prepared by the current administration [dbm.gov.ph]

name: SHAYDA
description: "Shayda, directed by Noora Niasari, is a compelling film that delves into the multifaceted experiences of Iranian women. Centering around the narrative of a woman who courageously escapes a violent domestic situation and battles for the custody of her child, the movie highlights the resilience and strength of its protagonist. Beyond the harrowing themes of family violence and the diaspora experience, Shayda also celebrates the universal aspects of friendship, music, dance, and laughter, showcasing the indomitable spirit of its characters as they reclaim their freedom. The film has been widely screened across Europe, North America, and Australia, garnering praise for its nuanced portrayal of Iranian women's struggles and its ultimately hopeful message. Shayda stands as a testament to the power of cinema to explore complex social issues while maintaining a sense of optimism and human connection."

name: NOORA NIASARI
description: Noora Niasari, an Iranian woman who was raised in the Australian suburbs alongside her mother, is deeply immersed in Persian culture. She is recognized as the director of the film Shayda. Niasari masterfully intertwines the harsh realities of family violence with the rich, vibrant aspects of Iranian culture, such as music, poetry, and dance, in her film. Her aspiration is that the increased global recognition of Iranian women's resilience will catalyze the narration of more stories that reflect their experiences. This detailed insight into Niasari's work and vision is provided by The Guardian on October 1, 2023.

name: IRANIAN WOMEN
description: Iranian women, a group whose resilience and strength have been prominently showcased in the film Shayda, directed by Noora Niasari, are at the heart of renewed international attention as of October 1, 2023. Niasari, through her cinematic work, aims to catalyze a global conversation about the experiences of Iranian women, encouraging the telling of more stories that reflect their lives. This focus is particularly poignant given the context of oppressive laws that Iranian women have been battling, including the stringent hijab laws and the tragic death of Mahsa Amini, which have sparked widespread protests and calls for change. The Guardian, in its coverage on this date, highlights the dual narrative of artistic representation and real-world struggle, emphasizing the courage and determination of Iranian women in the face of adversity.

name: PERSIAN NEW YEAR
description: Persian New Year is a cultural event that is featured in the film Shayda. The character holds on to the rituals of Persian New Year as a way to connect with her culture amid the upheaval of escaping abuse and fighting for custody of her child. [The Guardian, 2023-10-01]

name: MAHSA AMINI
description: Mahsa Amini was a 22-year-old Iranian woman who died in custody after being arrested for allegedly not complying with the country's hijab laws. Her death sparked a wave of popular unrest in Iran. [The Guardian, 2023-10-01]

name: INFLUENZA
description: Influenza, commonly known as the flu, is a viral infection that affects millions of people in the U.S. each year, causing fever, body aches, and weakness. In severe cases, it can lead to hospitalization and death [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: ALLISON MILLER
description: Allison Miller is a Virginia-based communications director who experienced severe complications from the flu a decade ago, leading to the amputation of her left leg above the knee [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: BACTERIAL PNEUMONIA
description: Bacterial pneumonia is a severe lung infection that can be a complication of influenza, affecting both lungs and leading to more serious health issues [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: SEPSIS
description: Sepsis is a life-threatening condition that can develop from bacterial pneumonia, causing organ failure and potentially leading to septic shock [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: FLU VACCINE
description: The flu vaccine, a preventive medical treatment against influenza, was initially overlooked by Allison Miller, who, despite being 33 years old and otherwise healthy, did not get vaccinated. However, Miller has since become a vocal advocate for the flu vaccine, promoting it as a proactive measure to minimize the risk of severe flu and urging others to get vaccinated to prevent serious health outcomes. This shift in perspective highlights the importance of the flu vaccine in safeguarding health, as recognized by FOX News - Health in their coverage on October 18, 2023.

name: AMPUTATION
description: Amputation is a medical procedure that was necessary for Allison Miller due to a rare complication of life support, which led to the loss of her left leg above the knee [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: MILLER
description:
Miller, a 33-year-old woman, faced a harrowing experience when she contracted the flu without having received the flu vaccine, leading to severe health complications that dramatically altered her life. As reported by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-18, Miller's battle with the flu resulted in her being admitted to the Intensive Care Unit (ICU), where she ultimately lost her left leg above the knee. The severity of her illness also caused permanent lung damage and left her with below-average heart function, further emphasizing the potential life-altering consequences of the flu.

In the wake of her ordeal, Miller has become a vocal advocate for flu vaccination and awareness, urging others not to underestimate the flu as a mere inconvenience. She shares her story to highlight the importance of preventive measures and the potential severity of the flu, aiming to educate and encourage others to take their health seriously and consider getting vaccinated. Through her advocacy, Miller hopes to prevent others from suffering similar fates and to raise awareness about the critical role vaccinations play in public health.

name: VIRGINIA
description: Virginia is the location where Miller, the subject of the article, resides

name: DR. GREGG SYLVESTER
description: Dr. Gregg Sylvester is the chief health officer at CSL Seqirus, a New Jersey biopharmaceutical company. He notes that while Miller's experience is not typical, it may occur more often than known, and emphasizes the importance of getting a flu vaccine [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: CSL SEQIRUS
description: CSL Seqirus is a New Jersey biopharmaceutical company where Dr. Gregg Sylvester works as the chief health officer [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: FLU
description: The flu, also known as influenza, is a contagious respiratory illness caused by influenza viruses that primarily target the nose, throat, and sometimes the lungs. It is a disease that should not be underestimated, as it can lead to severe complications, including inflammation of the respiratory tract, which can allow secondary or bacterial infections to enter the body. The severity of the flu can range from mild to severe, and in some cases, it can be life-altering or even lead to death. This information is provided by FOX News - Health on 2023-10-18, emphasizing the importance of recognizing the flu's potential impact on health.

name: VACCINATION
description: Vaccination is a health measure recommended by the CDC to prevent the flu. It is important to be vaccinated before the flu season starts to protect oneself and others. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: SHE
description: She is a person, possibly a Virginia woman, who lost her leg to the flu and now urges people to get vaccinated and not waste time if they are sick with severe symptoms. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: SYLVESTER
description: Sylvester is a person who agrees with the importance of early care and being one's own patient advocate when symptoms of the flu start to change dramatically. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: CDC
description: The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) is a health agency that estimates there were nine million illnesses, four million medical visits, 10,000 hospitalizations, and 5,000 deaths related to the flu during the 2021-2022 influenza season. The CDC recommends that everyone 6 months and older get a flu vaccine every season, with rare exceptions. [FOX News - Health, 2023-10-18]

name: DISCOGS
description:
Discogs, a pivotal player in the vinyl record industry and a platform for buying and selling vinyl records and other music merchandise, has recently been in the spotlight for its business decisions. As a company, Discogs has invested in compliance with regulatory programs and privacy protection, positioning itself as a secure marketplace for its users. The platform has been a significant source of full-time employment for many, particularly in the vinyl record industry, with one European seller reporting that 80 percent of his business is conducted on Discogs. This highlights the platform's role in the vinyl renaissance, integrating seamlessly into any record business and facilitating a global community of music enthusiasts.

However, recent changes in fee structures and policies have caused tension among sellers and users. Discogs raised its fees, which has led to a steeper sales decline post-lockdown, impacting the financial stability of sellers who rely on the platform. The company's decision to charge on shipping costs has further exacerbated the situation, leading to frustration among sellers and a sense of threat to the community built around the business. The recent website redesign has also been met with mixed reactions from its users, with some speculating that the company is increasing its profit margins without offering improvements to its product in return. Despite requests for comment on these issues, Discogs has declined to provide a statement, leaving many within the community to interpret the changes as potentially detrimental to the platform's long-term success and the vinyl record industry it supports.

name: VINYL RENAISSANCE
description: The vinyl renaissance refers to the resurgence in popularity of vinyl records, which has occurred in tandem with the growth of Discogs. This event has made the site fairly integrated into any record business, regardless of whether a business has a brick-and-mortar storefront [The Verge, 2023-10-07]

name: EUROPEAN DISCOGS SELLER
description: A European Discogs seller, who has been on the platform since 2008 and requested anonymity for fear of retribution by the company, says he does 80 percent of his business on the platform. He does not operate a brick-and-mortar storefront but has four employees and nets around €20,000 a month on Discogs. According to him, his sales have shrunk by half over the past year, and he’s in the process of building his own site to try to move away from the platform [The Verge, 2023-10-07]

name: CONNECTICUT DISCOGS SELLER
description: A Connecticut seller, who also does the majority of his business on Discogs and requested anonymity for the same reasons, expresses frustration over the lack of control over what Discogs is doing and the feeling that it doesn’t make any sense [The Verge, 2023-10-07]

name: PAYPAL
description: PayPal, a financial technology company, has been a significant player in the realm of online transactions since its early days. The company charges fees on each transaction, with notably higher fees on international purchases, a policy that has added to the financial burden on sellers, especially after Discogs, a popular marketplace for music collectors, switched all its transactions to PayPal a year before the fee increase. Additionally, PayPal has been mentioned in relation to an issue concerning the platform's refund button, which has raised concerns among users. The requirement for every shipment to have a tracking number, while beneficial for security and transparency, can also add significant extra expense, particularly for international sales.

name: MELKISETHIAN
description: Melkisethian, a long-standing seller on the Discogs platform since 2011, has witnessed a notable increase in sales during the pandemic era, as reported in an unspecified source. This growth in sales came at a time when traditional brick-and-mortar sales were declining, demonstrating the resilience and adaptability of Melkisethian's online business model. However, as of 2023, Melkisethian expresses disappointment with Discogs, feeling that the website has not evolved or improved over the years, according to an article by The Verge published on October 7, 2023. Despite this sentiment, Melkisethian continues to thrive as a seller within the Discogs community, leveraging the platform for successful transactions amidst changing market conditions.

name: PANDEMIC
description: The pandemic created a record sales bubble as people stuck at home with their record players and stimulus checks had nothing to spend them on besides survival and things they could do at home[]

name: CONNECTICUT SELLER
description: The CONNECTICUT SELLER is a vendor based in the state of Connecticut, expressing dissatisfaction with Discogs, a popular online marketplace for music collectors. The seller feels that Discogs is actively hindering sales by increasing fees without providing any enhancements or improvements to its platform in return. This sentiment was reported by The Verge on October 7, 2023, shedding light on the challenges faced by some sellers within the Discogs community.

name: ORDER MINIMUM
description: Discogs has introduced an order minimum as a major shift for its marketplace, which had previously done considerable business in selling records under $10 and even under $5. [The Verge, 2023-10-07]

description: Teenage Engineering, a Swedish company, is renowned for its exclusive and innovative music making gear, which not only includes the Field range but also the recently revealed EP-133 K.O. II 64MB Sampler Composer, as reported by Engadget on 2023-12-19. The K.O. II sampler, in particular, is described as cost-friendly, cool, and a testament to the company's unique approach to design and functionality. Teenage Engineering's products are not only functional but also have an aesthetic appeal that sets them apart in the music gear industry. However, the company has also faced challenges, testing the loyalty of its fans more than usual in recent years, a point highlighted in the same Engadget article. Despite these challenges, Teenage Engineering continues to push boundaries and innovate in the realm of music devices.

name: FIELD RANGE
description: The Field range represents Teenage Engineering's most exclusive music making gear [Engadget, 2023-12-19]

name: EP-133 K.O. II 64MB SAMPLER COMPOSER
description: The EP-133 K.O. II 64MB Sampler Composer is a new product from Teenage Engineering, reasonably priced at $299 and featuring a retro desk calculator aesthetic [Engadget, 2023-12-19]

name: FADERGATE
description: Fadergate is an issue where users of the EP-133 K.O. II 64MB Sampler Composer reported defective faders, leading to speculation about the cause and potential impact on the device [Engadget, 2023-12-19]

name: JAMES TREW
description: James Trew, a skilled photographer, contributed to Engadget's coverage of the EP-133 K.O. II 64MB Sampler Composer in an article published on 2023-12-19. Not only did Trew provide the image for the piece, but he also authored the review, sharing his firsthand experiences with the device. In a bold move, Trew used the K.O. II without consulting the manual, offering readers a unique perspective on the gadget's user-friendliness and functionality. His dual role as both the photographer and the reviewer showcases his comprehensive understanding and engagement with technology and entertainment products.

name: POCKET OPERATORS
description: Pocket Operators are a series of music devices from Teenage Engineering, with the EP-133 K.O. II 64MB Sampler Composer taking design cues from this series [Engadget, 2023-12-19]

name: K.O. II
description: The K.O. II, developed by Teenage Engineering, is a portable music sampler device that offers the capability to play up to six stereo samples simultaneously. Despite its impressive sampling capacity, it has certain limitations, including restricted resampling options and a lack of effects, as well as the absence of a song mode for more complex compositions. This device is distinguished by its "Super segment hybrid display," which utilizes fixed icons to indicate different modes and functions, enhancing user interaction. The model number EP-133 hints that the K.O. II could be part of a broader series of products by Teenage Engineering, as reported by Engadget on December 19, 2023.

name: BATTERIES
description: Batteries are a technology that powers the K.O. II. The author has been using cheap rechargeable batteries for over a week, and they continue to function well. [Engadget, 2023-12-19]

name: RESAMPLING
description: Resampling is a technique used to merge separate sounds into one new sample, which helps avoid hitting the voice limit on devices like the K.O. II, but is not available on the K.O. II

name: INSTRUMENTS’ MACHINE

name: K.O. II SAMPLER

name: FIVE NIGHTS AT FREDDY'S
description:
"FIVE NIGHTS AT FREDDY'S" is a horror video game series created by Scott Cawthon, featuring an abandoned Chuck E. Cheese-style arcade restaurant where animatronics with strange and eerie origins come to life at night, presenting a unique and chilling experience for players. The series, which began in 2015, has garnered a surprising number of young fans, partly due to nostalgia for animatronic characters that date back to the 1980s. The game's intense atmosphere and possessed animatronics have made it a standout in the horror genre.

A movie adaptation of "FIVE NIGHTS AT FREDDY'S" has been in development since shortly after the game's launch. The film, rated PG-13, starts from scratch, mimicking the premise of the first game, and is designed to be more accessible to a younger audience than typical horror movies. However, the movie's backstory is parceled out awkwardly, and there's as much family melodrama as thrill-ride scares, which might not fully satisfy hardcore horror fans. The film contains cheap music-sting jump scares and some junior-level gore, making it a harder PG-13 than the average superhero movie, but not as intense as other PG-13 horror movies like "The Ring" or "Drag Me to Hell." The suggested age cutoff of 12 or 13 is deemed appropriate for the movie's content, as noted by Polygon on 2023-10-26.

name: XHERDAN SHAQIRI
description: Xherdan Shaqiri, a star midfielder for the Chicago Fire, made a significant impact on the team's recent victory against Inter Miami by scoring two goals (a brace) on October 4, 2023, as reported by Sporting News. Prior to the match, Shaqiri confidently stated that the team's preparation would not be altered by the presence or absence of Lionel Messi, demonstrating his focus and adaptability. In a pre-match commentary, he also expressed his enthusiasm for participating in high-stakes games and revealed his preference for Messi over Ronaldo, further highlighting his competitive spirit and admiration for the Argentine footballer.

name: MAREN HAILE-SELASSIE

name: SOLDIER FIELD
description: Soldier Field, a prominent venue in the realm of sports, notably hosted the highly anticipated Chicago Fire vs. Inter Miami game on October 5, 2023. The event was a significant milestone for the Chicago Fire, as it was not only sold out, but also set a record for the largest crowd ever to attend a Chicago Fire game, as reported by Sporting News on October 4, 2023. The overwhelming response and attendance at Soldier Field for this match underscore the strong community interest and support for both teams, marking a memorable day in the history of the Chicago Fire and Soldier Field.

name: CHICAGO FIRE
description: The Chicago Fire, a professional soccer team competing in the Major League Soccer (MLS), is set to face Inter Miami on Wednesday, October 4, 2023. According to reports by Sporting News on the same date, the team is not modifying its strategy in anticipation of whether global soccer icon Lionel Messi will participate in the match. Despite Inter Miami's mistakes during the game, the Chicago Fire has been unable to capitalize on them, further highlighting the competitive nature of their encounter.

name: TATA MARTINO
description: Tata Martino is the coach of Inter Miami who has been tight-lipped about Lionel Messi's injury status and return timeline. [Sporting News, 2023-10-04]

name: JORDI ALBA
description: Jordi Alba is a professional soccer player for Inter Miami. There is a timeline in place for his return to the team. [Sporting News, 2023-10-04]

name: GILL PRATT
description: Gill Pratt, a prominent figure in the field of robotics and technology, has had a distinguished career spanning both academia and industry. Initially, he was part of MIT's Leg Lab alongside Marc Raibert, where they contributed to significant advancements in robotics. In 2001, Pratt transitioned from MIT to Olin College, continuing his academic pursuits for nine years before taking on a role as a program manager at DARPA in 2010. His expertise and leadership were recognized by the Toyota Research Institute (TRI), where he was appointed CEO in 2015. Throughout his career, Pratt has been instrumental in driving innovation and research, making substantial impacts in the robotics community. This summary is based on information from TechCrunch's robotics newsletter, Actuator, published on 2023-10-01.

name: MARC RAIBERT
description: Marc Raibert is a person who founded the Leg Lab at Carnegie Mellon University (CMU) in 1980 and later moved it to MIT. He is known for his work on robot locomotion and is the founder of Boston Dynamics. [A version of this story originally appeared in TechCrunch’s robotics newsletter, Actuator. Subscribe for free here.]

name: BOSTON DYNAMICS
description: Boston Dynamics, established by Marc Raibert in 1992, is a pioneering robotics and artificial intelligence company renowned for its innovative designs and dynamic, energetic robots. The company gained significant recognition for its Atlas robot, developed for DARPA, and under the leadership of Rob Playter, has transitioned towards commercial ventures. To further advance the field of robotics research, Marc Raibert founded the Boston Dynamics AI Institute in 2022, which mirrors TRI in its dedication to pure research and is supported by major automakers. Despite the shared name causing some confusion, the institute operates independently from the company, focusing on the exploration and development of cutting-edge robotics technologies. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]

name: CARNEGIE MELLON UNIVERSITY (CMU)
description: Carnegie Mellon University (CMU) is an educational institution where Marc Raibert initially founded the Leg Lab in 1980. [A version of this story originally appeared in TechCrunch’s robotics newsletter, Actuator. Subscribe for free here.]

name: ROBOT LOCOMOTION RESEARCH
description: Robot locomotion research is a field of study that focuses on how robots can move and navigate their environment. Marc Raibert's Leg Lab at MIT was a pioneer in this field, working on dynamic and energetic robots. [A version of this story originally appeared in TechCrunch’s robotics newsletter, Actuator. Subscribe for free here.]

name: ATLAS ROBOT
description: Atlas is a robot designed by Boston Dynamics, known for its advanced capabilities and dynamic movements. [A version of this story originally appeared in TechCrunch’s robotics newsletter, Actuator. Subscribe for free here.]

name: DARPA
description: DARPA is an organization that funded the development of the Atlas robot by Boston Dynamics. It is known for its role in advancing technology and robotics [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]

name: OLIN
description: Olin is an educational institution where Gill Pratt transferred to in 2001 from MIT [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]

name: TOYOTA
description: Toyota is a major automaker that backs TRI and has a significant R&D budget focused on the development of cars. It is also interested in exploring areas beyond cars [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]

name: HYUNDAI
description: Hyundai, a major automaker, is leading the charge into the 22nd century by embracing the integration of software, robotics, and AI into its vehicles. The company's forward-thinking leadership is committed to investing in advanced technologies to transform the car industry. As part of this vision, Hyundai supports the Boston Dynamics AI Institute, demonstrating its dedication to innovation and the future of automotive technology, as reported by TechCrunch on 2023-10-01.

name: TRI
description: TRI, or Toyota Research Institute, is a multifaceted organization primarily dedicated to pure research, significantly backed by Toyota. Among its various divisions, one specializes in advanced automotive technologies that share significant overlap with the robotics space, focusing particularly on software and conceptual developments. This work is not only technologically innovative but also socially impactful, as TRI aims to support aging populations by building out technology designed to assist older individuals in living more independently. The information provided is based on a TechCrunch article published on October 1, 2023, which highlights TRI's dual commitment to technological advancement and societal welfare.

name: BENJAMIN BURCHFIEL
description: Benjamin Burchfiel, a senior research scientist at TRI, as highlighted in a TechCrunch article from 2023-10-01, has observed significant advancements in the integration of large language models to bestow cognitive intelligence upon robots. Despite this progress, Burchfiel emphasizes that these models are currently unable to manage intricate tasks, such as plugging in a USB device or picking up a tissue, indicating that there are still substantial challenges to overcome in achieving comprehensive robotic cognition.

name: BOSTON DYNAMICS AI INSTITUTE
description: The Boston Dynamics AI Institute, an organization distinct from the well-known Boston Dynamics company, is dedicated to advancing research in intelligence, dexterity, and mobility to create robots that are smarter, more capable, and dynamically mobile. While the name may initially suggest a direct affiliation with Boston Dynamics, the institute operates independently with a broader focus on AI. As of 2023, the institute is in its early stages of development and is actively seeking new talent to join its team. A significant highlight is the recent appointment of Kate Darling, who will spearhead the research on the ethics and societal implications of robotics and AI. The institute is particularly interested in addressing the needs of older individuals, aiming to assist them in living more independently through the development of technology. To achieve this, the Boston Dynamics AI Institute is working on enhancing current large language models to perform more complex tasks, such as plugging in a USB device or picking up a tissue, thereby bridging a critical gap in the capabilities of existing AI systems. This information is based on a TechCrunch article published on October 1, 2023.

name: KATE DARLING
description: Kate Darling is a researcher who will lead the team at the Boston Dynamics AI Institute focused on the ethics and societal impact of robotics and AI. Her team will explore questions related to the implementation and use of robotics, impact on the workplace, infrastructure, and other topics. This information is based on a TechCrunch article published on 2023-10-01.

name: LARGE LANGUAGE MODELS
description: Large language models are a technology that has advanced significantly, allowing robots to understand and execute tasks based on more detailed and nuanced instructions. However, they are not yet capable of handling tasks that require fine motor skills or more complex interactions. This information is based on a TechCrunch article published on 2023-10-01.

name: ROD BROOKS
description: Rod Brooks is an individual who made the observation that modern cars are akin to eldercare robots, highlighting the significant overlap between automotive technology and robotics in terms of software and concepts [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]

name: GROUP PSGOT
description: Group Psagot is an investment house seeking to raise funds to cover its debt to Mizrahi Tefahot Bank and to replace NIS 120 million in marketable bonds due for redemption in the coming eighteen months. The company recently sold a portion of its mutual funds business and its entire portfolio management business to Kessem of The Phoenix Holdings group for NIS 200 million, expecting a gain of NIS 90 million to be posted in its fourth quarter financials. The sale of mutual funds is equivalent to the entire company's current market cap, implying the rest of its business is valued at zero.

name: MIZRAHI TEFAHOT BANK
description: Mizrahi Tefahot Bank is a financial institution to which Group Psagot has a debt balance that it seeks to cover with the funds it plans to raise.

name: RANI ZIM
description: Rani Zim, an individual with significant financial resources, invested nearly NIS 130 million of his own capital to acquire a controlling 62% stake in Psagot through Group Psagot, a public company. Unfortunately, the investment house's value plummeted, leaving Zim's stake worth just NIS 64 million, a loss of about half his initial investment within a short time. This decline in value can be seen as an 80% decrease from the original investment. In an attempt to mitigate these losses, Zim has been seeking a buyer for his entire stake or at least a portion of it. Previously, he had hoped for a valuation of around NIS 400 million when he put Psagot up for sale a few months ago. As of November 5, 2023, Zim has stepped down from his position as the chairperson of Psagot, as reported by Globes, Israel business news.

name: THE PHOENIX HOLDINGS GROUP
description: The Phoenix Holdings group is a company that recently acquired one third of Group Psagot's mutual funds business and its entire portfolio management business through Kessem for NIS 200 million.

name: KESSEM
description: Kessem is an individual associated with The Phoenix Holdings group who recently completed the acquisition of a portion of Group Psagot's mutual funds business and its entire portfolio management business for NIS 200 million.

name: YANIV BENDER
description: Yaniv Bender is the CEO of Group Psagot, holding 7.4% of the company. He is mentioned as a potential participant in the acquisition of Rani Zim's stake in the investment house.

name: PSAGOT
description: Psagot, a financial services company in Israel, has experienced significant business growth, managing a substantial NIS 43 billion in assets, primarily through money market funds. However, this growth has not translated into profitability, as the company reported a loss of NIS 27 million for the first half of 2023, largely due to its non-bank credit business. Psagot recently restructured its holdings in this sector by selling a controlling stake in AppliCheck, one of its main assets, back to the company's founder, Meny Guy, and now retains a 20% share. The company has also undergone leadership changes, with Rani Zim stepping down as chairperson and being replaced by Daniel Leventhal. It is noteworthy that Psagot's value has declined by 80% since Rani Zim's acquisition of the company, indicating a period of financial challenge that predates the recent losses and leadership transition. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on November 5, 2023.]

name: DANIEL LEVENTHAL

name: APPLICHECK

name: MENY GUY
description: Meny Guy is the founder of AppliCheck who recently regained control of the company from Psagot. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on November 5, 2023.]

name: VINCENT NAMATJIRA
description: Vincent Namatjira, a prominent artist, views himself as a royal figure in the realm of art, utilizing humor and satire as powerful tools to confront and discuss themes of colonialism, the influence of the rich, white, and privileged, and the legacy of his great-grandfather, Eddie Koiki Mabo [The Guardian, 2023-10-16]. As the great-grandson of Mabo, a significant Indigenous rights activist, Namatjira has been inspired to create a series of portraits that are both unofficial and defiant, aiming to challenge and level the power dynamics between Indigenous people and the rest of the world. His art is described as a weapon, incorporating subversion informed by his experiences in systems dominated by powerful figures. Notable works include the 2016 series "Prime Ministers" and the 2018 painting "Vincent & Donald (Happy Birthday)," which features Vincent sharing a birthday cake with former U.S. President Donald Trump, further emphasizing his use of art to address and comment on global power structures and historical injustices [The Guardian, 2023-10-16].

name: EDDIE KOIKI MABO
description: Eddie Koiki Mabo was a significant Indigenous Australian figure, and Vincent Namatjira is his great-grandson. [The Guardian, 2023-10-16]

name: PRIME MINISTERS
description: Prime Ministers refers to a series of paintings by Vincent Namatjira in 2016, depicting seven Australian leaders of his great-grandfather's lifetime with grey eyes and white teeth, mugging for the viewer. [The Guardian, 2023-10-16]

name: VINCENT & DONALD (HAPPY BIRTHDAY)
description: Vincent & Donald (Happy Birthday) is a 2018 painting by Vincent Namatjira, where he and Donald Trump share a birthday cake, a bag of McDonald's, and a red hat that reads "Make APY Great Again." Both men were born on June 14. [The Guardian, 2023-10-16]

name: IWANTJA ARTS
description: Iwantja Arts is the studio where Vincent Namatjira paints his portraits, located in Indulkana. [The Guardian, 2023-10-16]

name: GLOBAL WARMING
description: Global warming refers to the long-term increase in Earth's average surface temperature. The pattern of surface temperature change over the past 40 years has featured a pronounced spatial structure, with some locations even cooling in spite of the global mean warming on the order of 1 K [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: RADIATIVE FEEDBACKS
description: Radiative feedbacks, a critical aspect of climate science, refer to the processes that either amplify or diminish the effect of a change in the Earth's energy balance. These feedbacks are intricately linked to the surface warming pattern, which initially triggers more stabilizing feedbacks. However, as the Earth system moves towards equilibrium, the emphasis shifts to less stabilizing feedbacks, as noted in studies by Senior and Mitchell (2000) and Rugenstein et al. (2020). Radiative feedbacks are particularly sensitive to spatial differences in warming, a fact highlighted by Eos: Earth and Space Science News on October 31, 2023. They play a crucial role in the Earth's radiation balance, responding to changes in surface temperature and contributing to the complex dynamics of global climate change.

name: TROPICAL PACIFIC
description: The tropical Pacific is a region where strong warming in areas of deep convection, such as the western Pacific, is communicated throughout the troposphere, leading to strong warming aloft and enhancing radiative emission to space. In contrast, parts of the eastern Pacific have cooled [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: DEEP CONVECTION
description: Deep convection is a process in the atmosphere that readily communicates surface conditions upward throughout the troposphere, making the western Pacific a climate sweet spot. This warmer air sitting atop the relatively cool waters in the eastern Pacific or Southern Ocean acts to stabilize the lowermost troposphere, allowing more extensive low-lying stratus and stratocumulus clouds to develop [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: LOW CLOUDS
description: Low clouds, such as stratus and stratocumulus, efficiently cool the planet and offset some of the initial warming. Their location and structure are crucial for their cooling effect [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: COUPLED CLIMATE MODELS
description: Coupled climate models are simulations used to understand the climate system. They create their own surface warming pattern that differs from the observed one. In these models, warming aloft is less pronounced, and relative to the observed case, the lower tropospheric inversion strength is decreased, and cloud cover is reduced through time [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: PATTERN EFFECT
description: The pattern effect refers to the impact of spatial differences in warming on radiative feedbacks and climate sensitivity. Understanding this effect benefits from contributions from virtually all climate research communities [Eos: Earth And Space Science News, 2023-10-31]

name: CLIMATE SENSITIVITY
description: Climate sensitivity is a measure of how much the Earth's temperature changes in response to radiative forcing. It has been historically estimated using simple energy balance models, but these methods underestimate the actual equilibrium climate sensitivity due to the evolution of the surface warming pattern [e.g., Senior and Mitchell, 2000; Rugenstein et al., 2020].

name: SURFACE WARMING PATTERN
description: The surface warming pattern refers to the spatial distribution of temperature changes on the Earth's surface. It has a significant impact on radiative feedbacks and climate sensitivity, as highlighted by three strands of research [e.g., Senior and Mitchell, 2000; Rugenstein et al., 2020; Winton et al., 2010; Lin et al., 2021].

name: OCEAN HEAT UPTAKE EFFICACY
description: Ocean heat uptake efficacy is the measure of how effectively the ocean cools the Earth when it takes up heat. It differs depending on where the heat is taken up, with higher latitudes cooling more effectively than low latitudes. This effect is another manifestation of the dependence of radiative feedbacks on surface temperature patterns [Winton et al., 2010; Lin et al., 2021].

name: US CLIVAR
description: US CLIVAR (U.S. Climate Variability and Predictability Program) is an organization that fosters research on climate variability and predictability. In May 2022, 140 scientists from different disciplines gathered for a US CLIVAR workshop in Boulder, Colo., to discuss the pattern effect and its implications for climate sensitivity [Publish Time: 2023-10-31].

name: 140 SCIENTISTS
description: 140 scientists from around the world and from different disciplines gathered for a US CLIVAR workshop in May 2022 in Boulder, Colo., to discuss the pattern effect and its implications for climate sensitivity [Publish Time: 2023-10-31].

name: CRAIG MORGAN
description:
Craig Morgan, a distinguished country music artist, is also a dedicated military service member, embodying the principle that "once a soldier, always a soldier." Morgan has served in the U.S. Army and Army Reserve, including stints with the prestigious 101st and 82nd Airborne Divisions, where he held the rank of staff sergeant and specialized as a fire support specialist. His military credentials are impressive, encompassing airborne, air assault, and rappel master certifications. Demonstrating his commitment to both his country and his craft, Morgan re-enlisted in the U.S. Army Reserve at the age of 59 in July 2023, proving that his military service is an integral part of his identity, not merely a past chapter.

In the realm of entertainment, Craig Morgan is known for his powerful voice and heartfelt songs. His newest project, the EP "Enlisted," set to debut on October 20, 2023, is a testament to his dual passions. The six-song EP includes renditions of some of his biggest hits, as well as two new tracks, and features collaborations with a star-studded lineup of "famous friends," including Trace Adkins, Luke Combs, Gary LeVox, Jelly Roll, Blake Shelton, and Lainey Wilson. Morgan's pride, honor, and humility in serving his country are evident in his music, which often reflects the values and experiences of military life.

Throughout his career, Morgan has maintained a strong connection with the military community, working closely with the USO and earning accolades such as the Army's Outstanding Civilian Service Medal and the USO Merit Award. Despite the challenges of balancing a demanding music career with military service, Morgan finds that his military mindset is easier to maintain than his music career, a sentiment that underscores his deep-rooted commitment to the armed forces. His ability to navigate both worlds with grace and dedication makes Craig Morgan a unique and respected figure in both the country music and military landscapes.

name: U.S. ARMY RESERVE
description: The U.S. Army Reserve, a military organization, has seen the dedicated service of Craig Morgan, who re-enlisted in July 2023 at the age of 59. Morgan's military career includes previous service in both the Army and the Army Reserve, where he was associated with the prestigious 101st and 82nd Airborne Divisions. During his time in service, he held the rank of staff sergeant and specialized as a fire support specialist. This re-enlistment marks Morgan's continued commitment to the U.S. Army Reserve, as reported by FOX News - Entertainment on 2023-10-16.

name: USO
description: The USO is a non-profit organization that Craig Morgan has worked with. He has earned the Army’s Outstanding Civilian Service Medal and the USO Merit Award. [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-16]

name: ENLISTED EP
description: "Enlisted" is a new EP by Craig Morgan that debuts on Oct. 20, 2023. The six-song project features renditions of some of his biggest hits, as well as two new songs. It includes collaborations with Trace Adkins, Luke Combs, Gary LeVox, Jelly Roll, Blake Shelton, and Lainey Wilson. [FOX News - Entertainment, 2023-10-16]

name: MUSIC CAREER
description: Having a music career refers to the professional activities of a musician, such as performing, recording, and touring. Craig Morgan is a country music artist who balances his music career with his military service ["FOX News - Entertainment", 2023-10-16]

name: MILITARY SERVICE

name: HUMAN ARTISTRY CAMPAIGN
description: The Human Artistry Campaign is a fledgling campaign whose goal is to ensure that AI doesn’t replace or “erode” human culture, which the NMPA joined earlier this year [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: NMPA
description: The National Music Publishers' Association (NMPA) is a prominent trade association that staunchly represents the interests of music publishers and songwriters. As detailed in a Music Business Worldwide report from 2023-11-30, the NMPA has taken a firm stance against the utilization of copyrighted works in AI training, contending that such practices fail the fair use test under almost all circumstances. The association bases its argument on the four factors of fair use: the purpose and character of the use, the nature of the copyrighted work, the amount and substantiality of the portion taken, and the effect of the use on the potential market for, or value of, the copyrighted work. In response to the perceived threat AI poses to the human creative class and the potential for copyright infringement, the NMPA is advocating for new regulations that would require AI developers to maintain detailed records of the data their algorithms utilize. Additionally, the NMPA distinguishes between music generated by AI and music created with AI assistance, supporting copyright protection for the latter while asserting that works principally created through AI should not be eligible for copyright. The NMPA's position underscores its commitment to preserving human culture and the rights of creators in the face of technological advancements.

name: MUSICAL ARTISTS
description: Musical artists are human creators of music. The NMPA is advocating for regulations and principles that ensure their interests are not subjugated in the development of AI technologies [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: MUSIC RIGHTS HOLDERS
description: Music rights holders are individuals or organizations that own the rights to musical works. The NMPA is advocating for their interests to be protected in the context of AI-generated music [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI-GENERATED MUSIC
description: AI-generated music is music created primarily through the use of AI technology. The NMPA argues that such works should not be copyrightable and should be treated like works in the public domain [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI-ASSISTED MUSIC
description: AI-assisted music is music created with the help of AI technology, where human creators use AI as a tool in the creative process. The NMPA states that such works should be entitled to protection under copyright law [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI COMPANIES
description: AI companies are facing lawsuits for producing works that are substantially similar to copyrighted originals, raising concerns about copyright infringement [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: UMG
description: Universal Music Group (UMG), a leading music company, aligns with the National Music Publishers' Association (NMPA) in their perspective regarding the utilization of copyrighted works for AI training. UMG firmly advocates against opt-out systems, asserting that such regimes incorrectly assume the legality of AI use of copyrighted content unless individual copyright holders explicitly object. Instead, UMG supports an opt-in approach, emphasizing the importance of maintaining robust copyright protections and ensuring that the use of copyrighted materials by AI respects the rights and wishes of copyright owners. This stance is highlighted in a report by Music Business Worldwide on November 30, 2023, where UMG's position is detailed, reinforcing the company's commitment to copyright integrity in the evolving landscape of technology and entertainment.

name: COPYRIGHT OFFICE
description: The Copyright Office is a government agency that receives submissions from the NMPA and UMG regarding the use of copyrighted works for AI training. [Source: Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI DEVELOPERS
description: AI developers are professionals who create AI algorithms and models. They are criticized by the NMPA and UMG for training AI on copyrighted works without permission. [Source: Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: FAIR USE
description: Fair use is a legal concept in copyright law that allows copyrighted materials to be used without permission in certain limited circumstances, such as for educational purposes or for reporting news. The NMPA and UMG argue that training AI on copyrighted works does not qualify as fair use. [Source: Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AI TRAINING
description: AI training involves the use of copyrighted works, which the NMPA argues is not fair use, as it can lead to the creation of competing works that reduce revenue from existing licensing markets [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-30]

name: AMAZON ECHO FRAMES
description:
Amazon's Echo Frames, now in their third generation, are a sophisticated blend of smart glasses and open-ear headphones, designed to cater to a variety of needs with different lens options. Users can choose from clear lenses starting at $269.99, prescription lenses, blue light filtering lenses priced at $299.99, and sunglass lenses at $329.99. The latest iteration of the Echo Frames has seen improvements in style and audio quality, although it still faces some challenges in function when compared to its competitors. The base model of the third-gen Echo Frames is available at $270, while the more expensive Carrera Cruiser model, though stylish, is not deemed to be $400 worth of tech and style by some critics.

The Echo Frames provide users with some control over notifications and feature a VIP Filter, allowing for prioritization of important alerts. They also enable users to issue Alexa commands, enhancing their smart capabilities. With a decent battery life of approximately five hours for media playback and calls, the glasses can be fully charged in about 2.5 hours. However, the design of the charging stand is not particularly user-friendly. Despite these advancements, the Echo Frames are not as compelling in terms of function as wireless earbuds or other smart glasses in the market. The audio quality, while improved, still has issues with bass, and the fit may not be suitable for those with a low nose bridge.

name: CARRERA
description: Carrera is a company that Amazon has partnered with to offer flashier styles of Echo Frames, including the Cruiser and Sprinter models, which are priced at $389.99. The Cruiser model comes with sunglass lenses and the Sprinter model offers the option of sunglass or blue light filtering lenses. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]

name: STRAY KIDS
description: Stray Kids is a music group whose songs were used to test the audio quality of the Amazon Echo Frames. The group's music, particularly the bass and baritone elements, did not come through well on the Echo Frames, even at maximum volume. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]

name: META SMART GLASSES
description: Meta Smart Glasses, a cutting-edge product in the realm of wearable technology, have garnered attention for their superior audio quality as compared to the Amazon Echo Frames. According to a review by The Verge on December 7, 2023, the Meta Smart Glasses deliver a richer sound experience, making them particularly well-suited for podcast enthusiasts and listeners who prefer less bass-heavy music. This distinction highlights the Meta Smart Glasses' capability to enhance audio clarity and fidelity, setting them apart in the competitive landscape of smart eyewear.

name: ECHO FRAMES
description: Echo Frames, a product by Amazon, are innovative smart glasses that incorporate open-ear audio technology and Alexa, Amazon's voice assistant, to offer users a hands-free experience. The device allows for interaction with Alexa while on the move, enabling functionalities such as making calls, replying to text messages, and receiving directions, although the latter is reported to be somewhat clumsy and not always precise. Most of its features are dependent on a Bluetooth connection to a phone, and for optimal performance, the Alexa app needs to be open and running in the background. Audio quality, while decent, is not as rich as anticipated, particularly for bass-heavy songs, and there is a notable level of audio leakage that might be distracting in quiet settings. Despite these drawbacks, the battery life has been enhanced, and the product can be conveniently paired with multiple devices. However, the charging stand has received negative feedback from users. This summary is based on reviews by The Verge, dated 2023-12-07.

name: MICHELIN
description: Michelin is an organization that awards stars to restaurants based on their quality. The review notes that the audio quality of the Echo Frames is so poor that the famous "cookin' like a chef I'm a 5-star Michelin" line from a song is reduced to zero-star Michelin. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]

name: SMART HOME
description: Smart home refers to the concept of a home environment that can be controlled and monitored using technology, such as voice assistants like Alexa. Alexa is noted to be more effective in controlling smart home devices than in replacing other voice assistants for mobile use. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]

name: ASSISTANT
description: Assistant is a generic term for voice assistants, which can include both Alexa and Siri. It is used to refer to the type of technology that Echo Frames aim to integrate into their product. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]

name: VIP FILTER
description: The VIP Filter, a feature exclusive to the Amazon Echo Frames, empowers users to meticulously curate their notification preferences. By enabling this customizable setting, users can specify which apps and contacts are permitted to send notifications directly to their Echo Frames, ensuring that only the most important communications reach them. This sophisticated feature helps manage the flow of information, providing a more controlled and personalized notification experience while utilizing the glasses. [The Verge, 2023-12-07]
