name: HILTON NISEKO VILLAGE
description: The Hilton Niseko Village is a hotel less than a minute's walk to the Niseko gondola. It has three Japanese restaurants, allows skiers to enjoy après in the hotel's onsen, and offers views of the volcano, Mount Yōtei, from its elegant rooms [The Independent - Travel, 2023-10-13]

name: MOUNT YŌTEI
description: Mount Yōtei is a volcano in Niseko, Japan, that offers scenic views from the Hilton Niseko Village and is a part of the ski destination's landscape [The Independent - Travel, 2023-10-13]

name: MACY'S THANKSGIVING DAY PARADE
description: Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade is an annual event that takes place in New York City, featuring various floats, balloons, and performers. [Source: The Independent - Life and Style, Time: 2023-11-11]

name: TURKEYS AND STUFFING INGREDIENTS
description: Turkeys and stuffing ingredients are traditional food items that Americans typically purchase for their Thanksgiving menus. [Source: The Independent - Life and Style, Time: 2023-11-11]

name: WAMPAANOAG INDIANS
description: The Wampanoag Indians were native to the land where the Pilgrims settled in Plymouth, Massachusetts. They helped the Pilgrims cultivate crops and survive their first harsh winter. [Source: The Independent - Life and Style, Time: 2023-11-11]

name: PILGRIMS
description: The Pilgrims were colonists who settled in Plymouth, Massachusetts, in the 17th century. They celebrated the first Thanksgiving in 1621 with the Wampanoag Indians. [Source: The Independent - Life and Style, Time: 2023-11-11]

name: LIBERIA
description: Liberia celebrates Thanksgiving on the first Thursday of November [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-11]

name: VEGAN AND VEGETARIAN OPTIONS
description: For Americans who don't eat meat or follow a vegan lifestyle, there are numerous vegan and vegetarian options available for Thanksgiving meals [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-11]

name: THANKSGIVING FAVOURITES
description: Thanksgiving favorites in America include yams topped with marshmallows, stuffing, cranberry sauce, cornbread, and pumpkin pie [The Independent - Life and Style, 2023-11-11]

name: CARIBBEAN BOX JELLYFISH
description: The Caribbean box jellyfish, scientifically known as Tripedalia cystophora, are remarkable marine creatures that inhabit tropical lagoons. Despite the absence of a central brain, these jellyfish possess an impressive capability for associative learning. This learning process is facilitated by their four nerve centers, known as rhopalia, which enable them to navigate and hunt effectively in their environment. They utilize their vision to steer through the intricate spaces between mangrove tree roots, demonstrating a sophisticated understanding of their surroundings by recognizing the contrast of the roots against the water. The study of their learning abilities provides valuable insights into how nerve cells can accomplish complex tasks such as learning without the presence of a traditional brain structure.

name: ASSOCIATIVE LEARNING
description: Associative learning is the ability of an organism to make mental connections between events and then change its behavior accordingly. It is typically associated with animals with complex nervous systems, but a new study shows that even simple nervous systems like those of Caribbean box jellyfish can exhibit this behavior [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: JAN BIELECKI
description: Jan Bielecki is a researcher who studies animal nervous systems at Kiel University in Germany. He and his colleagues published a study on September 22, 2023, in Current Biology, demonstrating that Caribbean box jellyfish can learn to avoid obstacles [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: KIEL UNIVERSITY
description: Kiel University is a German university where Jan Bielecki and his team conducted research on the learning abilities of Caribbean box jellyfish [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: CURRENT BIOLOGY
description: Current Biology is a scientific journal where Jan Bielecki and his colleagues published their findings on the learning abilities of Caribbean box jellyfish on September 22, 2023 [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: KEN CHENG
description: Ken Cheng is a biologist at Macquarie University in Sydney, Australia. He comments on the research that traces learning in Caribbean box jellyfish to their rhopalia, considering it a significant step in understanding the wiring of how learning works in these creatures. [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: GAËLLE BOTTON-AMIOT
description: Gaëlle Botton-Amiot is a neurobiologist who has studied sea anemones at the University of Fribourg in Switzerland. Her work suggests that sea anemones, like jellyfish, can learn. She raises questions about how learning works in jellyfish with four rhopalia and what happens if one is lost. [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: MACQUARIE UNIVERSITY
description: Macquarie University is an educational institution in Sydney, Australia, where Ken Cheng, a biologist, is affiliated. [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: SEA ANEMONES
description: Sea anemones are marine animals that belong to the cnidarian group. Gaëlle Botton-Amiot's work suggests that sea anemones can learn, similar to jellyfish. [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: CNIDARIANS
description: Cnidarians are a group of animals that includes both sea anemones and jellyfish. The learning ability in these different cnidarians suggests that learning might be widespread within the group, possibly inherited from a common ancestor. [Science News For Students, 2023-12-01]

name: CHASE YOUNG
description: Chase Young, a 24-year-old professional football player known for his prowess as a pass rusher, was recently traded to the San Francisco 49ers from the Commanders just before the 2023 NFL trade deadline. This strategic move by the 49ers was made with the intention of bolstering their defense, and Young has indeed been making a significant impact, recording five sacks in just eight games, showcasing a breakout season. His contract situation is of particular interest, as Spotrac.com estimates his annual salary to be around $17.8 million on a four-year deal. However, considering his potential and the value he brings to the team, especially given his past injuries which might have affected his market value, the actual figure could be higher. Young is listed as a free agent in 2024, but the 49ers are assessing his contract and potential market value with the aim of keeping him as a starter for the team in the upcoming season.

name: MONTEZ SWEAT
description: Montez Sweat is a defensive end who was traded by the Commanders, along with Chase Young, ahead of the 2023 NFL trade deadline [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: RANDY GREGORY
description: Randy Gregory is a player on the 49ers roster with an eight-digit salary but no guaranteed money left on his deal, making him a potential release to free up cap space [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: NICK BOSSA
description: Nick Bosa is a college teammate of Chase Young and fellow No. 2 pick who is also on the 49ers roster [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: 2024 NFL DRAFT
description: The 2024 NFL Draft is an upcoming event where NFL teams select newly eligible players [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: 2022 NFL TRADE DEADLINE
description: The 2022 NFL Trade Deadline is a past event where the 49ers acquired Christian McCaffrey [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: 2023 NFL TRADE DEADLINE
description: The 2023 NFL Trade Deadline is a past event where the 49ers traded for Chase Young [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: SPOTRAC.COM
description: Spotrac.com is a website that provides data on projected contracts for professional athletes. It projects that Chase Young should make about $17.8 million annually on a four-year deal. [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: RASHAN GARY
description: Rashan Gary is a professional football player who received a contract extension from the Green Bay Packers with an average annual value (AAV) of $24 million over four years, totaling $96 million, with $34.6 million guaranteed. His contract is considered when projecting Chase Young's potential deal. [Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: 2024 FREE AGENTS
description: The 49ers have 16 players set to be free agents in 2024, including Chase Young, with only two full-time starters among them[Source: Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: TASHAUN GIPPSON
description: Tashaun Gipson is a full-time starter for the 49ers and is set to be a free agent in 2024[Source: Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: CLELIN FERRELL
description: Clelin Ferrell is a full-time starter for the 49ers, set to be a free agent in 2024, and Chase Young is expected to take over his starting position[Source: Sporting News, 2023-10-31]

name: JESSEO PARK
description: Jeseo Park is a U.S. economist leading a Bank of America team that warned about turbulence in the housing market due to high mortgage rates [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: 2008 HOUSING CRASH
description: The 2008 housing crash, triggered by the collapse of subprime mortgages, is a historical event that is not expected to repeat due to differences in today's housing market [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: GLOBAL FINANCIAL CRISIS (GFC)
description: The Global Financial Crisis (GFC) was a significant economic downturn that started in 2008, partly due to the housing market crash [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: ADJUSTABLE-RATE MORTGAGES
description: Adjustable-rate mortgages, a type of financial product, have been historically associated with higher default rates when interest rates increase. This connection is particularly notable as their prevalence has significantly declined since the Global Financial Crisis (GFC). As of October 6, 2023, adjustable-rate mortgages now account for less than 5% of total purchase and refinance loans, a stark contrast to the over 35% they represented at the peak of the pre-GFC housing cycle. This shift indicates a change in consumer preference and lending practices, possibly due to the risks associated with adjustable-rate mortgages and the desire for more stable, fixed-rate financial products.

name: GFC
description: GFC refers to the Global Financial Crisis that occurred in 2008, which had a significant impact on the housing market and led to the implementation of new laws to prevent risky adjustable-rate mortgages [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: PAUL VOLCKER
description: Paul Volcker was the Fed Chair in the early 1980s who implemented hawkish policies that sent mortgage rates to 18% in a year's time, cooling inflation but sparking a recession [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: JEROME POWELL
description: Jerome Powell is the current Fed Chair who has been following a similar game plan to Paul Volcker's, raising interest rates aggressively to quash inflation [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: MILLENNIALS
description: Millennials, a significant demographic group, are currently reaching the prime age for homebuying, a development that holds the potential to support and maintain the momentum of the housing market, preventing it from collapsing. This trend, observed in 2023, suggests that the housing sector might benefit from the increased demand generated by this generation as they progress through life stages that typically encourage homeownership. As Millennials continue to age, their impact on the housing market is expected to be substantial, potentially shaping the future of real estate dynamics.

name: BABY BOOMERS
description: Baby boomers are a demographic group that had entered the prime homebuying age during the early 1980s, contributing to the favorable demographics of the period [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: PARK
description: Jeseo Park is an economist who, along with her team, has written about the housing market, suggesting that millennials reaching prime homebuying age could support the market and help retain momentum [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: HOME PRICES
description: Home prices are an economic indicator that could be supported by millennials reaching prime homebuying age and the steady holding of single-family building permits [Fortune, 2023-10-06]

name: JON COPELEY
description: Jon Copley, an esteemed ocean explorer and professor of ocean exploration and science communication at the University of Southampton in the U.K., is dedicated to unraveling the mysteries of the deep sea. With a wealth of experience under his belt, Copley has embarked on numerous expeditions to the farthest reaches of the ocean, including the world's deepest hydrothermal vents, the enigmatic "midnight zone" of Antarctica's icy depths, and the awe-inspiring undersea mountain chains. He is known for his assertion that our understanding of the deep ocean far surpasses that of the moon or Mars, highlighting the vast unexplored territories that lie beneath the waves. Copley is not only an explorer but also an author, having published books on deep sea exploration, such as "Deep Sea: 10 Things You Should Know" in 2023, which aims to address common questions and debunk myths surrounding the deep sea. Through his work, Copley contributes significantly to the scientific community and public knowledge about the ocean's uncharted territories.

name: UNIVERSITY OF SOUTHAMPTON
description: The University of Southampton is an educational institution in the U.K. where Jon Copley is a professor of ocean exploration and science communication [Source: Live Science, 2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA
description: The deep sea is a realm of myth and darkness, according to ocean explorer Jon Copley. It is a harsh habitat on Earth that has been explored by Copley, revealing strange life forms and interactions between deep sea animals [Source: Live Science, 2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA BIOLOGY
description: Deep sea biology is a field of science that studies the life forms and interactions in the deep sea. Jon Copley's book "Deep Sea: 10 Things You Should Know" updates information on deep sea biology, including sensory ecology and animal interactions [Source: Live Science, 2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA: 10 THINGS YOU SHOULD KNOW
description: "Deep Sea: 10 Things You Should Know" is a book authored by Jon Copley in 2023, available for order on Amazon in the U.K. The book is a comprehensive guide that addresses the top 10 questions about the deep sea, providing readers with a wealth of information on various aspects of deep sea life and environments. It also serves to debunk myths and clear up misconceptions that commonly surround the deep sea, making it an invaluable resource for anyone interested in marine biology and oceanography. Copley's work has been highlighted by Live Science, which featured it in their list of the most interesting articles, further emphasizing its relevance and importance in the field of deep sea exploration and knowledge.

name: ASK AN OCEAN EXPLORER
description: Ask an Ocean Explorer is a book written by Jon Copley in 2019. It contains 25 chapters, each answering a question commonly asked about the deep sea [Source: Live Science, 2023-09-28]

name: SENSORY ECOLOGY
description: Sensory ecology is a science field that studies how animals perceive their environment and respond to it, including how they avoid being seen by predators. This area has seen a lot of interesting papers over the past five years, as mentioned by Jon Copley in an interview with Live Science [2023-09-28]

name: JON COPLEY
description: Jon Copley is an explorer and scientist who has expertise in deep sea research. He was interviewed by Live Science in 2023, where he discussed various aspects of deep sea knowledge and concerns [2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA MINING
description: Deep sea mining is an activity that has attracted a lot of attention recently. It involves extracting minerals and resources from the deep ocean floor. Jon Copley mentioned in an interview that deep sea mining has made people care more about the deep ocean, but he also noted that research does not support some of the more exaggerated claims about its impacts [2023-09-28]

name: HYDROTHERMAL VENTS
description: Hydrothermal vents, remarkable geological features located in the deep ocean, serve as unique habitats where superheated water and minerals are discharged from the Earth's crust. These vents are notably fragile ecosystems, a fact highlighted by Jon Copley in a discussion on the impacts of deep sea mining on September 28, 2023. They are home to over 400 distinct animal species that are exclusive to this environment, unable to be found in any other type of habitat. As noted by Live Science in their coverage on September 28, 2023, hydrothermal vents support entire populations of animal species through the process of chemosynthesis, a biological process that allows organisms to produce energy without sunlight, making these vents crucial for the survival of these deep-sea creatures.

name: CHEMOSYNTHESIS
description: Chemosynthesis is a process where life is powered by a form of chemical energy instead of sunlight with photosynthesis. It was once thought to be impossible to sustain whole populations of animal species until the discovery of hydrothermal vents and similar habitats [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA VENTS
description: Deep sea vents glow very faintly, too faint for the human eye to see, but bright enough that microbes can use it as an energy source. This expands our notion of what's possible in the cosmos, as life doesn't necessarily have to be close to a bright star to sustain [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-09-28]

name: DEEP SEA CREATURES
description: Deep sea creatures have evolved extreme strategies to cope with their environment, including unique adaptations to thrive in the absence of sunlight [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-09-28]

name: LIVE SCIENCE: THE MOST INTERESTING ARTICLES
description: Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles is a news source that published an article about the deep ocean and its life forms on 2023-09-28 [Live Science: The Most Interesting Articles, 2023-09-28]

name: EYLON LEVY
description: Eylon Levy, aged 32, is a government spokesperson for the State of Israel, working at the National Public Diplomacy Directorate in the Prime Minister's Office. He has gained massive exposure worldwide for his articulate and quick-witted responses in interviews, particularly in the context of the recent events since October 7, 2023. [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: STATE OF ISRAEL
description: Since October 7, 2023, the State of Israel has been embroiled in a conflict, as confirmed by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and government spokesperson Eylon Levy. The country, known for its resilience, found itself under attack by hostile forces that infiltrated its territory, prompting a swift response to clear these forces and restore security and peace to its communities. The State of Israel, facing what Netanyahu describes as a war, has been dealing with a harsh reality forced upon it, as Levy echoes, emphasizing the ongoing atrocities that the nation has been combating. Despite these challenges, the State of Israel remains committed to its objective of ensuring the safety and tranquility of its citizens.

name: MARK REGEV
description: Mark Regev is the former Israeli ambassador to the UK, who inspired Eylon Levy to dream of becoming a spokesperson for the State of Israel. [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: NATIONAL PUBLIC DIPLOMACY DIRECTORATE
description: The National Public Diplomacy Directorate is a government agency in the Prime Minister's Office where Eylon Levy works as a spokesperson to the international media. [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: PRIME MINISTER'S OFFICE
description: The Prime Minister's Office is the central government agency in Israel, where Eylon Levy serves as a spokesperson. [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: KAY BURLEY

name: UK SKY NEWS
description: UK Sky News is a media outlet where Kay Burley works as a presenter. [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: REPORTERS AND PHOTOGRAPHERS IN GAZA
description: Reporters and photographers in Gaza, who are part of the system and operate under the control of Hamas, are not free to present the full truth [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: LEVY
description: Levy, a person born and raised in England, is an active figure in the Israeli public sphere. Known for his role as a spokesperson for the government, Levy has raised eyebrows by also participating in protests against the government's judicial reform. He is deeply committed to advocating for Israel, often engaging in debates and acting as a public diplomat to clarify and defend the country's position against misconceptions. On November 17, 2023, Levy was spotted outside a synagogue with Hand, looking at posters of Israeli kidnap victims, demonstrating his concern for the safety and well-being of the Israeli community. Levy believes that the strength of Israeli society is its inclusivity and that the unity forged after the protests is crucial for the nation's resilience and success. His dual role as a government spokesperson and a protest participant highlights the complex dynamics of Israeli politics and society, as reported by FOX News - Lifestyle and Globes, Israel business news on December 3, 2023.

name: THE ECONOMIST
description: The Economist is a publication that Levy used to read while growing up, showing his interest in news and current affairs [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: THE STATE OF ISRAEL
description: The State of Israel is a country that Levy has a strong awareness of its importance and historical role in the history of the Jewish people [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: ANTI-SEMITISM
description: Anti-Semitism is a social issue that Levy was exposed to during debates and every time there was a round of fighting, he found himself defending Israel's position [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: GEORGE GALLOWAY
description: George Galloway, a British MP, is known as a notorious Israel hater, who walked out of a debate with Levy when he found out Levy was Israeli [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: UNIVERSITY OF OXFORD
description: The University of Oxford is where Levy was an undergraduate and conducted a debate with George Galloway [Globes English | Israel Business Arena, 2023-12-03]

name: GOVERNMENT'S JUDICIAL REFORM
description: The government's judicial reform is a law that has sparked protests in Israel. The details of the reform are not provided in the text, but it is clear that it has caused significant controversy and division among the Israeli population. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on December 3, 2023]

name: PROTESTS
description: Protests against the government's judicial reform have taken place in Israel. These protests have been significant enough to draw the attention of the public and have been attended by various individuals, including the entity in question. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on December 3, 2023]

description: Israeli society is a group that has come to its senses after the traumas of the protests against the government's judicial reform. Levy, a spokesperson for the government, argues that the strength of Israeli society lies in its ability to work for everyone and that the unity that has emerged after the traumas of the protests is essential for winning the war. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on December 3, 2023]

description: Dizengoff Square is a place in Israel where Levy witnessed significant shoving and shouting during the protests against the government's judicial reform. [Globes, Israel business news - en.globes.co.il - on December 3, 2023]

name: BING
description: Bing, a search engine product developed and managed by Duane Forrester during his tenure at Microsoft, has been represented by Forrester as a company. Often positioned as the underdog to Google's online search dominance, Bing has recently overhauled its layout to be more graphic and interactive, incorporating generative AI explanations from its chatbot to enhance user experience. This innovative feature allows users to ask follow-up questions in searches, although it is not yet fully developed. In product searches, Bing is noted for sometimes offering more expensive options. The quality of Bing's search results is significantly influenced by the work of SEOs, contributing to its evolving role in the digital search landscape.

name: KENT WALKER
description: Kent Walker is the president of global affairs at Google. He argues that Google's search product is the favorite of users, browsers, and device makers because it is the best in the business. He also points out that users tend to put Google back as the default search engine when faced with a situation where it is not the default [The Age, 2023-10-22]

name: YAHOO!
description: Yahoo! was made the default search engine on Firefox by Mozilla, but it was not preferred by most users who changed it back to Google [The Age, 2023-10-22]

name: MEGAN GRAY
description: Megan Gray is a lawyer and privacy advocate who wrote an opinion article for Wired alleging that Google manipulates search queries for ad revenue

name: GOOGLE SEARCH
description: Google Search is a search engine that uses meaning matching systems to understand the intent behind search queries, helping users find relevant results even when they make spelling mistakes or use synonyms. It also employs machine learning to rank results and considers user information like location and web history to refine search outcomes. Google's software constantly crawls the web and updates its central index, which is over 100 million gigabytes in size. In 2023, it deals with a data volume of 120 ZB per year, compared to 9 ZB in 2013. Google denies using monetisation practices to push users towards more monetisable subjects. [The Age, 2023-10-22]

name: MEGAN GREY
description: Megan Grey, a prominent critic in the technology sector, argues that Google intentionally employs semantic keyword matching to decrease the precision of search results. This strategy, according to Grey, serves to expand the range of content that is displayed, thereby increasing the number of auctions for Google's advertisements. Her assertions were featured in an article published by The Age on October 22, 2023. Despite the repetition of the description, it is clear that Megan Grey's critique centers on Google's search algorithms and their impact on ad auctions.

name: SEARCH QUALITY RATERS
description: Google works with independent search quality raters to gauge the effectiveness of its search processes. In 2022, Google ran almost 900,000 quality tests with these raters. [The Age, 2023-10-22]

name: SEMANTIC KEYWORD MATCHING
description: Semantic keyword matching is a technology used by Google to match search queries with a wider range of content, potentially making searches less precise [The Age, 2023-10-22]

name: WALMART+
description: Walmart+, a membership program provided by Walmart, grants its members exclusive privileges, including early access to the Cyber Monday sale. Specifically, members are given the opportunity to start shopping three hours before the general public, with the special early entry time set at 4 p.m. ET. This information was reported by Mashable on 2023-11-25, highlighting the benefits of joining Walmart+ for those interested in taking advantage of Cyber Monday deals.

name: 55-INCH QLED TV
description: This 55-inch QLED TV was already affordable at full price and is now seeing an extra $50 discount, pushing it below $350. Thanks to its extra layer of quantum dots, you'll be able to appreciate rich colors and deep blacks even during the day. [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: HP LAPTOP
description: This HP laptop is a business 2-in-1 with an Intel Core i5 processor, capable of handling day-to-day work and after-work streaming and surfing. While supplies last, you can get this device for under $500. [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: AIRPODS PRO (2ND GENERATION)
description: The second-gen AirPods Pro with a Lightning port are a stellar buy at only $169 — it's their lowest price to date. These wireless earbuds from fall 2022 "sound wonderful and have almost uncanny active noise cancelation," said Mashable senior editor Stan Schroeder, and they last for up to six hours on a single charge. [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: ONN. TABLET
description: The ONN. TABLET, as described by Mashable on November 25, 2023, is a budget-friendly device priced under $30, making it an attractive option for those seeking a super basic tablet. Although it may not encompass all the advanced features of an iPad, it serves well for fundamental entertainment purposes such as watching videos and reading. This tablet is ideal for individuals who prioritize affordability and essential functionality over high-end capabilities.

name: APPLE AIRPODS PRO (2ND GENERATION)
description: Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation) are headphones with active noise cancelation, lasting up to six hours on a single charge [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: STAN SCHROEDER
description: Stan Schroeder is a senior editor at Mashable who provided information about the Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation) [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: APPLE WATCH SE (2ND GENERATION)
description: Apple's latest entry-level wearable is lighter, faster, and features health tools like heart rate notifications, Emergency SOS, Cycle Tracking, and Fall and Crash Detection [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: DIABLO IV
description: Diablo IV is a game included for free with the Xbox Series X bundle [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: JBL FLIP 6 CHARGE
description: JBL Flip 6 Charge is a portable Bluetooth speaker, decently loud for its compact size, IPX7-rated for waterproofing, and capable of charging other devices via USB [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: DYSON V15 DETECT
description: The Dyson V15 Detect, introduced and highlighted by Mashable on 2023-11-25, is a high-end cordless stick vacuum designed to enhance cleaning efficiency and precision. This model features a sophisticated LCD screen that provides real-time information and a built-in laser, which serves as a unique innovation by Dyson. The laser's purpose is to highlight and illuminate minute particles such as crumbs, pet hairs, and dust on various floor surfaces, ensuring that no debris goes unnoticed during the cleaning process. Additionally, the Dyson V15 Detect incorporates HEPA filtration, making it an ideal choice for households concerned about air quality and allergens. The Absolute variant of the V15 Detect boasts a luxurious gold finish and comes equipped with an extra dusting/crevice tool, further expanding its versatility and utility in tackling different cleaning tasks.

name: SHARK 2023 MATRIX VACUUM
description: Shark's 2023 Matrix vacuum is a robot vacuum that maps your home, vacuums, and mops rooms, offering a thorough cleaning with Matrix mode and a crosshatch cleaning pattern for vacuuming and multi-angle floor scrubbing for mopping

name: VITAMIX EXPLORIAN MODEL
description: The Vitamix Explorian model is a powerful blender with a 64-ounce capacity, three program settings for Smoothies, Hot Soup, and Frozen Desserts, and a low-profile container that fits under most kitchen countertops

name: SOLO STOVE RANGER 2.0
description: The Solo Stove Ranger 2.0 is a compact, virtually smokeless fire pit designed for portability and convenience. Crafted from lightweight stainless steel, it features a removable ashtray for easy cleaning and maintenance. The product comes with a dedicated carrying case, facilitating effortless transport, and a stand that ensures safe usage on various surfaces, including decks and grass. As of November 25, 2023, the bundle is available for purchase at $264.99 on the Solo Stove brand's official website, while Walmart offers the same at a slightly more competitive price.

name: TRACTIVE
description: Tractive is a dog tracking device that allows pet parents to track their dog's live location within a companion app. It enables setting up a virtual fence and notifies when the pet steps out of or enters the safe area. The device has some limitations, such as a mediocre battery life and occasional live tracking glitches, but it is a solid choice for those on a budget. It is available for $29.99 at Walmart for Black Friday, saving $20. [Mashable, 2023-11-25]

name: KEVIN DURANT
description: Kevin Durant, a transcendent superstar in the NBA, currently serves as a forward for the Phoenix Suns. Initially drafted by the Seattle SuperSonics with the No.2 pick in 2007, Durant has since amassed an impressive 27,393 points in the regular season and 4,878 points in the playoffs, securing his place as the 11th and 7th highest scorer in NBA history, respectively. Despite his remarkable skills and talent, Durant has not been immune to controversy and has faced a fair share of disrespect from the media and fans. Notably, he was part of the Oklahoma City Thunder team that lost to the record-breaking 73-9 Golden State Warriors in the 2016 playoffs. In a surprising turn of events, Durant joined the Warriors during the 2016 offseason, a move that significantly impacted his public image and the dynamics of the league.

name: BALDUR'S GATE 3
description: Baldur's Gate 3 is a video game where players can choose from 12 classes and 46 subclasses, which mostly determine how their character will fight in the game. The game offers opportunities for creative problem solving and combat. [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: CLASS

name: SUBCLASS
description: Subclass is a gameplay element in Baldur's Gate 3 that adds depth to the character's abilities and fighting style. There are 46 subclasses across the 12 classes. [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: ABILITY SCORE
description: Ability Score is a gameplay element in Baldur's Gate 3 that affects skills used to interact with the game world. The game assigns Ability Scores automatically, but they can be tweaked in the character creator. [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: WISDOM

name: ORIGIN CHARACTER
description: In Baldur's Gate 3, Origin Character is an option that allows players to choose one of the NPCs from their party and play as them. This option limits the player to that character's predetermined story. [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: CUSTOM CHARACTER
description: Custom Character is an option in Baldur's Gate 3 that allows players to create their own character with a chosen race and background. This option offers more freedom to experience the entire story of the game. [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: FIGHTER
description: Fighter is a class in Baldur’s Gate 3 that is considered the best melee class for beginners, as it is straightforward and does not require managing spells or Ki Points [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: RANGER

name: CHAMPION
description: Champion is a subclass of the Fighter class in Baldur’s Gate 3, recommended for beginners as it keeps the gameplay simple with a better chance to deal a Critical Hit [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: HUNTER
description: Hunter is a subclass of the Ranger class in Baldur’s Gate 3, recommended for beginners as it allows specialization of melee abilities [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: CLERIC

name: WIZARD
description: In Baldur's Gate 3, a role-playing game, the Wizard is recognized as the archetypical caster class, characterized by an Intelligence-based primary ability. This class boasts the most extensive collection of spells and spell slots, making them exceptionally potent in magic damage. The Evocation subclass is deemed the best for Wizards, enabling them to manipulate their environment through the powerful use of alchemy and magic. For optimal gameplay, one should consult the Wizard build guide to understand the rationale behind the subclass choice and to discover the recommended skills and feats to enhance the character's capabilities. Wizards are particularly adept at dialogue-heavy encounters outside of combat, but due to their lack of armor, they should be strategically positioned away from melee combat to ensure their survival and maximize their magical prowess.

name: SORCERER
description: "SORCERER is a character class in the role-playing game Baldur's Gate 3, introduced on 2023-12-18 by Polygon. SORCERERs derive their magic from within, showcasing a flexible and varied spell repertoire that sets them apart from other classes. Their primary Ability is Charisma, making them particularly adept at social interactions and dialogue-heavy encounters outside of combat. However, SORCERERs do not possess any armor, necessitating a strategic approach to keep them away from melee combat to ensure their safety and maximize their magical potential."

name: BARDIC INSPIRATION
description: Bardic Inspiration is a Bard ability in Baldur’s Gate 3 that boosts the rolls of allies and can make enemies weaker [Polygon, 2023-12-18]

name: EVOCATION
description: Evocation, hailed as the premier subclass for a Wizard in the captivating role-playing game Baldur's Gate 3, is renowned for its specialization in alchemy and the manipulation of the environment. This subclass empowers the wizard to harness the arcane energies to alter the world around them, making it a strategic choice for players seeking to dominate the battlefield with elemental forces and clever environmental manipulation. As of the latest analysis on 2023-12-18 by Polygon, Evocation stands out as the go-to option for those who wish to explore the depths of magical power and creativity in Baldur's Gate 3.

name: PATRICK KANE
description: Patrick Kane, a professional ice hockey player renowned for his skills as a winger, is currently a free agent in the NHL, actively seeking a team for the 2023-24 season. With an impressive career that includes three Stanley Cup championships, Kane was notably traded from the Chicago Blackhawks to the New York Rangers in the recent past. However, his stint with the Rangers was cut short as the team faced elimination in the first round of the playoffs. Adding to his challenges, Kane underwent hip surgery during the summer, which has necessitated a period of rehabilitation since the beginning of the new season. Despite these setbacks, Kane's passion for the game remains undiminished, and he has expressed a strong desire to play for the Dallas Stars. Known for his chemistry with teammates Artemi Panarin and Alex DeBrincat, there are speculations that Kane could potentially reunite with them in Dallas, a move that would likely bolster the team's offensive capabilities. As of November 27, 2023, the sporting world eagerly awaits the announcement of Patrick Kane's next team, with Dallas Stars being a frontrunner in the race to secure his talents.

name: BUFFALO SABRES
description: The Buffalo Sabres, a professional ice hockey team based in Buffalo, New York, are considered a potential and advantageous landing spot for Patrick Kane, a notable hockey player. As a Buffalo native, Kane's return to his hometown adds a significant narrative to the potential signing. The Sabres, with their ample salary cap space, are well-positioned to make a competitive offer. The team is in need of bolstering their offensive capabilities and power play effectiveness, areas where Kane's skills could make a substantial impact, as reported by Sporting News on November 27, 2023.

name: LIAM PARO
description: Liam Paro, a 27-year-old Australian super lightweight boxer, has faced significant challenges in 2023, including an unknown facial fracture and an Achilles tendon issue, which led to a stall in his career and caused him to miss crucial fights, notably a world title shot against Regis Prograis. Despite these setbacks, Paro is now back in full health and is scheduled to face Montana Love on December 9, 2023 (Dec. 10 in Australia) in San Francisco, on the undercard of the WBC super lightweight title bout between Haney and Prograis. Paro, who was previously ranked number one in the division with the WBO but is now 11th due to his inactivity, is confident that a strong performance against Love can propel him back to the front of the queue for a championship shot. He plans to fight three times in 2024 to make up for having only had one round in the past two years, that being a first-round knockout over Brock Jarvis in October 2022. Paro has also sparred with WBC lightweight champion Shakur Stevenson, commenting on a leaked sparring video from 2019, which he refers to as "schoolyard bullsh*t," but acknowledges the free exposure. Despite the leaked video, Paro maintains respect for Stevenson and his camp, stating he would still work with Stevenson again if required. As Paro prepares for his return to the ring, he is determined to prove that he is better than Love in every aspect and to reignite his career trajectory.

name: SHAKUR STEVENSON
description: Shakur Stevenson, the WBC lightweight champion, recently made headlines for his record-breaking, albeit cautious, performance against Edwin De Los Santos, where he landed the fewest punches over a 12-round contest. Despite this, Stevenson showcased his aggressive and active boxing skills in a sparring clip with Liam Paro that was circulated last week. The clip, which Stevenson shared with Bill Haney, the father of former undisputed 135-pound champ Devin Haney, demonstrated Stevenson's dominance over Paro, a stark contrast to his approach in the De Los Santos fight. Paro, in response to the clip, addressed it ahead of his return fight, highlighting the competitive nature of the boxing community.

name: BILL HANEY

name: STARDUW VALLEY
description: Stardew Valley is a modern-classic farming simulation game inspired by the Harvest Moon series, where players can work together to plant and harvest crops or engage in various activities like fishing or mining. Local co-op is available for two players, with up to four players supported through online multiplayer. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: UNTITLED GOOSE GAME
description: Untitled Goose Game is a game known for its treacherous honking and causing communal chaos, adding to the fun of local multiplayer. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: ESCAPE ACADEMY
description: Escape Academy is a game that has recently been included in Polygon's recommendations update, as of 2023-10-20. This game offers a local multiplayer mode designed for two players, providing an engaging and interactive experience for those interested in cooperative or competitive gameplay within the same physical space.

name: PORTAL
description: Portal is a game included in the Switch remaster, where players explore and solve puzzles using a portal gun, with the number of portals that can be placed doubled in local co-op mode. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: PORTAL 2
description: Portal 2 is a game included in the Switch remaster, offering puzzle-solving gameplay and physics experimentation, which is more enjoyable with a friend in local co-op. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: GOOD JOB!
description: Good Job! is a game where players take on the role of a CEO in a large corporation, helping employees stay on task through a series of tasks and challenges. It shares similarities with Untitled Goose Game and is played in local co-op. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: CAPTAIN TOAD: TREASURE TRACKER
description: Captain Toad: Treasure Tracker is a Wii U game ported to the Nintendo Switch, featuring local co-op gameplay where players control Captain Toad and Toadette to explore and solve puzzles in a series of bite-size courses. [Source: Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: RABBIDS
description: Rabbids is a video game featuring evil characters that can be played in local co-op mode, with specific challenges designed for cooperative play[Polygon: 2023-10-20]

name: CRYPT OF THE NECRODANCER
description: Crypt of the Necrodancer is a dungeon crawler and rhythm game with sweet tunes that can be played in local co-op by up to two players, making the experience more fun even though it doesn’t necessarily make the game easier[Polygon: 2023-10-20]

name: DIABLO 3
description: Diablo 3 is an action RPG that has become a comforting grind game for local multiplayer, especially on the Nintendo Switch, and is still a great choice more than a decade after its release[Polygon: 2023-10-20]

name: RAYMAN LEGENDS
description: "Rayman Legends, a captivating installment in the renowned series celebrated for its platforming and hijinks, is a video game that offers an engaging local co-op gameplay experience. As reported by Polygon on 2023-10-20, the game boasts delightful levels, time trials, and collection elements, providing players with a variety of challenges and innovative gameplay mechanics that keep them entertained and immersed in the vibrant world of Rayman."

name: ROCKET LEAGUE
description: Rocket League is a game that combines racing and soccer, played with rocket-powered vehicles, as described by Polygon on 2023-10-20[]

name: TOWERFALL ASCENSION
description: Towerfall Ascension is a 2D arena game where players fight each other with arrows and agile movements, featuring different multiplayer variants to keep the game fresh, as reported by Polygon on 2023-10-20[]

name: OVERCOOKED! ALL YOU CAN EAT
description: Overcooked! All You Can Eat is a definitive remaster that bundles Overcooked and Overcooked 2, featuring gameplay where players prepare orders for customers while facing challenges like cooking in a hot air balloon or crossing a busy street, according to Polygon on 2023-10-20[]

name: SUPER MARIO 3D WORLD + BOWSER'S FURY
description: Super Mario 3D World + Bowser's Fury is a game that offers a modern 3D world with classic Super Mario gameplay, allowing players to choose characters like Mario, Luigi, Peach, or Toad, each with slightly different perks, as described by Polygon on 2023-10-20[]

name: MARIO PARTY
description: Mario Party is a family-friendly party game in a board game-style format, where players pick their favorite Nintendo character and compete in minigames, including a baseball-bat-swinging rhythm game, rowboat race, and snow catching, as reported by Polygon on 2023-10-20[]

name: WII SPORTS
description: Wii Sports is a legacy game that introduced various sports minigames, including baseball, rowboat race, snow catching, and more. Its soundtrack is also memorable. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: MARIO KART
description: Mario Kart is a 20-year series of multiplayer kart racing games. The most recent edition, released in 2017, still reigns supreme in kart racing and gets new courses, such as Mario Kart 7’s Rainbow Road. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: SCRAMBLE
description: Scramble is a multiplayer game where players operate a spaceship hurtling through outer space, each controlling one of the ship’s eight total control panels. It requires teamwork and communication. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: PAPER-BASED GAME
description: A paper-based game is a multiplayer game where each player is a piece of paper and can cut shapes out of one another to accomplish tasks, such as creating a specific shape or working together to shoot a ball into a hoop or fill up a basin with water. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: NINTENDO'S FIGHT-TO-THE-DEATH BRAWLER
description: Nintendo's fight-to-the-death brawler is a multiplayer game stocked with favorite characters, allowing up to eight players to compete and be the last one standing. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: TMNT: SHREDDER’S REVENGE
description: TMNT: Shredder’s Revenge is a multiplayer beat-’em-up brawler for TMNT fans, featuring the four Turtles — Leonardo, Michelangelo, Donatello, and Raphael — along with April O’Neil, Master Splinter, and Casey Jones. [Polygon, 2023-10-20]

name: BIG TEN CHAMPIONSHIP
description: The Big Ten Championship is a sports event that the Michigan Wolverines have won in the last two years. [Sporting News, 2023-11-25]

name: CFP SEMIFINALS
description: The CFP Semifinals is a sports event that the Michigan Wolverines have lost in the last two years. [Sporting News, 2023-11-25]

name: ABDEL-FATTAH EL-SISI
description: Abdel-Fattah El-Sisi is the President of Egypt, who is preparing for elections in less than two months

name: REFUGEES
description: Refugees are people fleeing the violence in Gaza, potentially seeking temporary housing in Egypt

name: SINAI PENINSULA
description: The Sinai Peninsula is a region in Egypt where Israel has suggested refugees could be temporarily housed in tent camps

name: MIRETTE MABROUK
description: Mirette Mabrouk is the director of the Egypt program at the Washington-based Middle East Institute, providing insights on Egypt's policy regarding Palestinian displacement

name: INTERNATIONAL MONETARY FUND
description: The International Monetary Fund is an organization that Egypt reached a deal with in December 2023, and is currently in talks to boost the rescue program to over $5 billion

name: WORLD BANK
description: The World Bank is an organization that was involved in annual meetings in Morocco where economists, bankers, and investors discussed Egypt's economic situation

name: RICCARDO FABIANI
description: Riccardo Fabiani, an expert on regional conflicts and stability, serves as the project director for North Africa with Crisis Group. In this capacity, he offers valuable insights on the dynamics and potential shifts in the region, including the possibility of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) adjusting its requirements for Egypt, which could have significant implications for the country's economic and political landscape. Riccardo's deep understanding of North Africa's complex issues makes him a key resource for analyzing and predicting developments in the area.

name: CRISIS GROUP
description: Crisis Group is an organization that provides analysis and policy recommendations on conflicts and crises around the world

name: EL-SISI
description: El-Sisi is the President of Egypt who has been actively involved in diplomatic efforts and has hosted world leaders in a "Summit for Peace" in Cairo

name: ROBERT SATLOFF
description: Robert Satloff is the executive director at The Washington Institute for Near East Policy, an expert on Middle East security and politics

name: WASHINGTON INSTITUTE FOR NEAR EAST POLICY
description: The Washington Institute for Near East Policy is a think tank that provides analysis and policy recommendations on Middle East security and politics

name: VLADIMIR PUTIN
description: Vladimir Putin is the President of Russia who invaded Ukraine in 2022, leading to increased attention on Egypt as a regional gas producer

name: SYRIA
description: Syria is a country in the Middle East that has experienced a civil war, leading to a large number of refugees in Egypt

name: SUDAN
description: Sudan is a country in Africa that has experienced political instability and conflict, leading to a large number of refugees in Egypt

name: YEMEN
description: Yemen is a country in the Middle East that has experienced a civil war and humanitarian crisis, leading to a large number of refugees in Egypt

name: LIBYA
description: Libya is a country in North Africa that has experienced political instability and conflict, leading to a large number of refugees in Egypt

name: OLAF SCHOLZ
description: Olaf Scholz is the Chancellor of Germany who praised German-Egyptian unity in working to prevent a Middle East "conflagration"

name: XI JINPING
description: Xi Jinping is the President of China who met with Egyptian Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouly in Beijing

name: FABIANI
description: Fabiani is a person who is part of a group and has provided commentary on Egypt's current situation [Fortune, 2023-10-22]

name: GROUP
description: Group is an organization that includes Fabiani, who has commented on Egypt's role in international affairs [Fortune, 2023-10-22]

name: EU LAW
description: EU law, specifically the European Court of Justice's (CJEU) ruling in 2020, has an anomaly that could result in European artists losing up to 40% of their income from terrestrial radio broadcasts and public performances of their music [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: US-BASED ARTISTS
description: US-based artists will be able to collect performance royalties from their recordings being played on the radio in the EU, due to the anomaly in EU law [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: EU ARTISTS
description: EU artists will continue to get nothing from their recordings being played in the US, leading to a potential loss of up to 40% of their income from terrestrial radio broadcasts and public performances [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: IMPALA
description: IMPALA, a prominent organization representing independent music companies across Europe, serves as the trade association for European indie labels. This entity, deeply involved in the music industry, is part of a coalition of groups that have issued a significant warning. According to a statement highlighted by Music Business Worldwide on November 29, 2023, IMPALA and its allies are concerned about potential revenue losses for European artists and labels if the existing EU law isn't amended. The warning underscores the critical role IMPALA plays in advocating for legal frameworks that support the financial sustainability of the European music sector.

name: ADAMI
description: ADAMI, recognized as the French collective management organization dedicated to safeguarding performers' rights, is deeply involved in a significant advocacy effort. In alignment with other concerned groups, ADAMI has signed a joint statement, highlighting the urgent need for a revision in EU law. The organization warns that without such changes, European artists and labels could face substantial revenue losses, a critical issue that has gained attention as of November 29, 2023, according to Music Business Worldwide. ADAMI's active role in this coalition underscores its commitment to protecting and enhancing the rights and financial interests of performers within the European Union.

name: WIPO PERFORMANCES AND PHONOGRAMS TREATY
description: The WIPO Performances and Phonograms Treaty of 1996 includes the reciprocity principle, which has been affected by the anomaly in EU law [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: EUROPEAN COURT OF JUSTICE (CJEU)
description: The European Court of Justice (CJEU) ruled in 2020 that the reciprocity principle no longer applies to EU member states, even if it exists in copyright treaties and national laws [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: RENTAL/LENDING DIRECTIVE
description: The European Union’s Rental/Lending Directive of 2006 doesn’t allow EU member states to withhold payments to nationals of non-EU countries, contributing to the anomaly in EU law [Music Business Worldwide, 2023-11-29]

name: RECIPROCITY PRINCIPLE
description: The reciprocity principle is a legal concept that ensures countries extend the same rights to each other's citizens or companies. In the context of the music industry, it refers to the fair distribution of revenue between performers and producers from different countries.[]

name: DUTCH MUSICIANS’ UNION NTB/KUNSTENBOND
description: The Dutch musicians’ union Ntb/Kunstenbond is a trade union representing musicians in the Netherlands. According to its chairman, Will Maas, the union is observing a significant decrease in revenue for Dutch and European performers and producers due to the application of the reciprocity principle.[]

name: WILL MAAS
description: Will Maas is the chairman of the Dutch musicians’ union Ntb/Kunstenbond. He expressed concerns about the revenue drop for Dutch and European performers and producers due to the application of the reciprocity principle.[]

name: SWEDISH MUSICIANS’ UNION MUSIKERFÖRBUNDET
description: The Swedish musicians’ union Musikerförbundet is a trade union representing musicians in Sweden. It is one of the groups that signed the statement warning about the potential revenue loss for European artists and labels if EU law isn’t changed.[]

name: BELGIAN COLLECTIVE MANAGEMENT SOCIETY PLAYRIGHT
description: The Belgian collective management society PlayRight is an organization that signed the statement warning about the potential revenue loss for European artists and labels if EU law isn’t changed.[]

name: SWEDISH ARTISTS’ AND MUSICIANS’ INTEREST ORGANISATION (SAMI)
description: The Swedish Artists’ and Musicians’ Interest Organisation (SAMI) is an organization that signed the statement warning about the potential revenue loss for European artists and labels if EU law isn’t changed.[]

name: SWEDISH UNION OF PROFESSIONAL MUSICIANS (SYMF)
description: The Swedish Union of Professional Musicians (SYMF) is a trade union representing professional musicians in Sweden. It is one of the groups that signed the statement warning about the potential revenue loss for European artists and labels if EU law isn’t changed.[]

name: UNISONO, THE GERMAN FEDERATION OF MUSICIANS
description: Unisono, the German Federation of Musicians, is a trade union representing musicians in Germany. It is one of the groups that signed the statement warning about the potential revenue loss for European artists and labels if EU law isn’t changed.[]

name: US CONGRESS
description: The US Congress is the legislative branch of the United States government. In 1971, it extended copyright protections to sound recordings, but those protections did not include a public performance right. In 1995, it passed the Digital Performance Right in Sound Recordings Act, which included performance rights but was limited to digital audio transmissions.[]

name: DIGITAL PERFORMANCE RIGHT IN SOUND RECORDINGS ACT
description: The Digital Performance Right in Sound Recordings Act is a US law passed in 1995 that granted performance rights for sound recordings, but only for performances made by means of a digital audio transmission, excluding terrestrial radio.[]

name: ALLIGATOR
description: A 10-foot alligator was used as a gimmick at a party for digital marketers in South Florida [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: DIGITAL MARKETERS
description: Digital marketers are professionals who specialize in online marketing strategies, including search engine optimization (SEO), and were the target of a party where a 10-foot alligator was used as a gimmick [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: SEARCH ENGINE OPTIMIZATION (SEO)
description: Search Engine Optimization (SEO) is a strategic technique employed by digital marketers to enhance the visibility of websites in search engine results, aiming to improve their ranking and thereby increase organic traffic. This practice has evolved into a business model that capitalizes on Google's perceived objectivity to attract users and present them with advertisements. However, SEO businesses faced a significant challenge in 2011 when Google implemented its Panda update, which negatively affected many of these enterprises, sparking criticism and controversy within the industry. Despite this setback, SEO remains a crucial aspect of digital marketing, continuously adapting to search engine algorithms to optimize online content for better search performance.

name: SEO PROFESSIONALS
description: SEO professionals are the people who engage in the mysterious art of search engine optimization, or SEO, and are blamed by some for ruining the internet by exploiting users' dumbest impulses for traffic and profit [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: CADE LEE
description: Cade Lee, a seasoned SEO expert with over a decade of experience in the field, has a complex and candid perspective on the nature of business and making money. Despite his past as an ex-convict with a history of securities fraud, Lee now runs a construction company and has worked across diverse industries, including the Marines and mortgage sales. Known for his tattoos that cover his body, Lee is not one to shy away from controversy, having publicly discussed violating Google's guidelines. He critiques the common arrogance among SEO professionals, referring to the practice as "modern-day pirate shit" in an interview with The Verge on November 1, 2023. Lee also acknowledges Google's aspiration for a wholesome internet, recognizing that while this ideal would be perfect in a world without money and greed, it is challenging to maintain in today's business landscape. Despite his skepticism, Lee prefers to conduct business in a minimally harmful way, reflecting a nuanced view of commerce and ethics.

name: MISSY WARD
description: Missy Ward, a blonde woman with a significant history in the technology and marketing industry, is renowned for her early involvement in SEO, starting her career in 1998. Her entrepreneurial journey culminated in the successful sale of her company for a staggering $40 million, a testament to her expertise and strategic acumen in the digital marketing space. In a memorable event covered by The Verge on November 1, 2023, Missy attended an alligator-themed party, a gathering of digital marketers, dressed in an orange bandage dress. The dress, purchased from Amazon, was so tight that it restricted her movement, adding an element of daring and perhaps a touch of discomfort to her appearance. Notably, Missy had not tried on the dress until the day of the event, a spontaneous decision that contributed to the evening's unique atmosphere.

name: ALLIGATOR PARTY
description: The alligator party is an event where digital marketers gather, and it was advertised with a 10-foot alligator, but the actual alligator was only five and a half feet long [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: DARON BABIN
description: Daron Babin, often referred to as a "modern-day pirate shit" guy, is an SEO expert who began his career in 1994, predating the existence of Google. He was part of a community that discussed strategies for outsmarting search engine algorithms and recounted his successful manipulation of SEO using fake domain names, a practice that was legal but not condoned by the dominant search engine of the time. Despite these tactics, Babin faced no consequences. He took Darren's advice to pivot into consulting, initially charging $2,000 a day, and as his career flourished, he raised his rates to $5,000 a day. Babin predicts that AI will have a significant impact on SEO in the future, potentially degrading Google's search results as they become saturated with AI-generated content tailored to appease the algorithms. This information is sourced from The Verge on November 1, 2023.

name: DARREN BLATT
description: Darren Blatt, also known as "D-Money," is the host of the alligator party and has been friends with Daron Babin for decades. They both managed to milk the early online cash cows: porn, pills, and gambling [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: DARREN
description: Darren is an individual who, along with Daron, managed to exploit the early online cash cows: porn, pills, and gambling, and later advised Daron to become a SEO consultant [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: PFIZER
description: Pfizer is a pharmaceutical company that was mentioned in the context of being outranked by Darren and Daron's efforts in the SEO domain [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: JAIRO BASTILLA
description: Jairo Bastilla is a tall, charming individual who describes himself as "a nerd" and specializes in email campaigns, which he calls "deliverability," using core knowledge of SEO that remains relevant for various online marketing strategies [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: CANNABIS AND PSYCHEDELICS
description: Cannabis and psychedelics are industries that Daron Babin mostly invests in nowadays, as SEO became too complicated for not enough money [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: LARS MAPSTEAD
description: Lars Mapstead is an individual who was once considered a god in the SEO space and is now preparing to run for president in 2024 as a Libertarian in Northern California. He spent his early years in a Volkswagen van and became a tinkerer and autodidact, first hearing about the World Wide Web in 1993 while working for a company selling computer motherboards [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: WORLD WIDE WEB
description: The World Wide Web, as Lars Mapstead first encountered in 1993 while working for a company involved in the sales of computer motherboards, is a revolutionary technology that he immediately recognized as a powerful tool for the freedom of information and collaboration. This pivotal moment, as highlighted by The Verge on November 1, 2023, underscores the significance of the World Wide Web in enabling the widespread dissemination of knowledge and fostering a global community interconnected through shared interests and information. Mapstead's association of the Web with the liberation of data and enhancement of collective efforts reflects its profound impact on various sectors, including technology and entertainment, by breaking down barriers to access and participation.

name: VOLKSWAGEN
description: Volkswagen is a car manufacturer that produced the van in which Mapstead's hippie parents traveled along the Pacific coast with their children, goats, chickens, and without electricity.[]

name: PACIFIC COAST
description: The Pacific coast is a geographic location where Mapstead's parents traveled in a Volkswagen van before settling in Big Sur.[]

name: MAPSTEAD
description:
Mapstead, a self-taught individual with a unique upbringing, emerged from a nomadic childhood spent in a Volkswagen van along the Pacific coast, before his hippie parents found a permanent home in Big Sur. This background fostered a spirit of innovation and resourcefulness, leading Mapstead to develop a keen interest in technology. He honed his skills in building websites and creating chat rooms, which became a hub for global connections. In the early days of the internet, Mapstead capitalized on the opportunity to monetize his websites by placing banner ads, a move that initially brought in $2,000 a month but soon escalated to a monthly income of $25,000-$30,000 as he mastered the art of search engine optimization (SEO).

As the digital landscape evolved, Mapstead adapted to Google's algorithm changes, demonstrating his resilience and adaptability in the face of technological shifts. However, his methods were not always in line with the guidelines set by major platforms. He was involved in spamming Facebook with car-related content, directing traffic to banner ads, a strategy that proved profitable but was later disrupted by Google's algorithm updates. These changes, which Mapstead perceived as detrimental to his business model, forced him to reassess and refine his approach to online marketing. Despite the challenges, Mapstead's journey from a tinkerer to a tech-savvy entrepreneur showcases his ability to navigate the complexities of the internet and leverage its potential for financial gain. [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: WEBCRAWLER
description: WebCrawler is an early search directory that Mapstead learned how to submit his site to be listed in.[]

name: INFOSEEK
description: Infoseek is an early search directory that Mapstead learned how to submit his site to be listed in.[]

name: LYCOS
description: Lycos is an early search directory that Mapstead learned how to submit his site to be listed in.[]

name: NEW YORK COMPANY
description: A company in New York offered Mapstead $2,000 a month to put banner ads on one of his websites, which changed his approach to website building and search engine optimization.[]

name: ITALIAN PROFESSOR
description: An Italian professor published a journal article about Search Engines Persuasion in 1997, highlighting the problem of finding the right information on the World Wide Web and the degradation of search engine performance due to companies trying to make their customer web pages as visible as possible.[]

name: ADULTFRIENDFINDER
description: AdultFriendFinder is a once-ubiquitous hookup site that Mapstead helped start. The site was sold in 2007 for $500 million [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: KENT
description: Kent is an SEO consultant who has worked in the industry and has an outsider's perspective, often criticizing that 80 percent of SEOs are scammers [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: SEO INDUSTRY
description: The SEO industry is known for optimizing websites to improve their search engine rankings, but it has a reputation problem due to the prevalence of scammers [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: BRUCE CLAY
description: Bruce Clay is often credited with coining the phrase "search engine optimization" and is referred to as "the father of SEO." He runs an agency that hires only experienced SEOs [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: JOHN HEARD
description: John Heard is a longtime SEO based in Kansas who explains that even a talented SEO might need a year of work to make a difference in a site's ranking [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: BARRY
description: Barry is a person who defends the SEO industry, stating that while there are scammers, it's easier to call oneself an SEO than to claim a title in a more regulated profession like medicine [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: DUANE FORRESTER
description: Duane Forrester is a chipper, charismatic man who worked at Microsoft from 2007 until 2015, helping to launch and manage Bing, and has also worked as an SEO, giving him a holistic understanding of the industry [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE
description: The Department of Defense is a government agency that Duane Forrester compares his experience in the SEO industry to, likening it to an aerospace engineer who spent a few years at the Department of Defense and now is much better at winning military contracts [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: FORRESTER
description: Forrester, a seasoned figure in the SEO industry, has built a notable career through keynote presentations and adept networking, often enjoying the finer aspects of life with multiple Michelin-starred meals during travels for events. Having once represented Bing, he played a pivotal role in enhancing the search engine's results by closely engaging with SEO professionals. In a move mirroring Matt Cutts from Google, Forrester ceased drinking at conferences to uphold a professional demeanor and gather valuable insights into SEO strategies. Additionally, he has provided critical analysis on the dynamics between Google and SEOs, offering perspectives on the personalities of those who succeeded Matt Cutts at Google and highlighting the distinct approach to public relations employed by Danny Sullivan, which he perceives as differing from Cutts'.

name: CLAY
description: Clay, described as the father of SEO, has a close relationship with Forrester and has compared him to a cruise director on the SS SEO [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: MICHELIN-STARRED MEALS
description: Michelin-starred meals are high-end dining experiences that Forrester has had numerous times during his time in the SEO industry [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: MATT CUTTS
description: Matt Cutts, a significant figure in the technology industry, is recognized for his role as an engineer at Google where he contributed to the development and led the web spam team. His tenure at Google, spanning until 2016, saw him become a celebrity among Search Engine Optimizers (SEOs), a status attributed to his efforts in maintaining communication with them and understanding their methodologies. Despite his efforts to stay neutral, Cutts faced intense backlash, including death threats and hate mail, as a result of Google's algorithm updates that significantly affected SEO businesses. His departure from Google is viewed by many SEOs as a pivotal moment in the evolution of the internet, symbolizing the shift from Google's early idealistic phase to its current position as a dominant force in the tech landscape. Cutts stepped back from his active role in 2014 before officially leaving the company in 2016.

name: ASTON MARTIN
description: An Aston Martin is a luxury vehicle that was used by one of the SEOs as a conversation starter with potential clients at a conference [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: PANDA UPDATE
description: The Panda update is a significant algorithm change released by Google in 2011 that aimed to improve search quality by penalizing websites with low-quality content [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: SEARCH ENGINE LAND
description: Search Engine Land is an industry publication where Schwartz works. It was started by Danny Sullivan in the 2000s and covers topics related to search engine optimization and search engine marketing [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: JOHN SULLIVAN
description: John Sullivan is a Google employee who is defensive about the company's era under his leadership, arguing that Google has been transparent and that search results have improved, not deteriorated [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: LILY RAY
description: Lily Ray is an SEO expert who helped clarify the changes in Google's search results, attributing the differences to Google's response to disinformation and the evolving algorithm[The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: RAY
description: Ray, a prominent figure in the SEO industry and a thought leader, has evolved her strategies over the past decade, moving away from the manipulative tactics that were prevalent between 2003 and 2011. She has changed her last name to align more closely with her grandmother's uncle, the renowned artist Man Ray, enhancing her personal branding. Ray lived frugally overseas in locations such as Bali and Chiang Mai, where she employed SEO techniques that are now considered guideline-violating. However, she has since abandoned these practices, opting to create high-quality websites that adhere to Google's rules, with the intention of contributing positively to the internet. Ray has noticed a significant shift in the industry, particularly with the rise of AI-generated content being used to exploit Google's algorithms, causing frustration for users. She has conducted extensive research on how certain sites have performed under Google's updated guidelines and confirms that the search results do indeed feel different today compared to five or six years ago. Despite the challenges, Ray is committed to maintaining a high moral standard in her business practices, even as she observes the tension in the industry between what Google advises and what people are doing and getting away with.

name: E-E-A-T
description: E-E-A-T stands for experience, expertise, authoritativeness, and trustworthiness, which are factors Google's algorithm now pays more attention to, especially for sites offering legal, financial, or health advice [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: URBAN DICTIONARY
description: Urban Dictionary is a website that has seen a decrease in its ranking under Google's new E-E-A-T guidelines [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: WESTERN MEDICINE
description: Western medicine is a system of medical practice that has been critiqued for its limitations, especially in the context of health and wellness information on the internet [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: BLACK HAT SEO
description: BLACK HAT SEO, as defined by The Verge on 2023-11-01, encompasses a set of search engine optimization (SEO) strategies and techniques that deliberately contravene the established guidelines set by search engines. These tactics are primarily employed to artificially boost a website's ranking in search engine results pages, often at the expense of the user experience and the integrity of the search engine's algorithms. Examples of black hat SEO practices include keyword stuffing, cloaking, and link schemes, all of which aim to deceive search engines rather than provide genuine value to users. Engaging in black hat SEO can result in penalties from search engines, including reduced visibility or complete removal from search results, thus it is generally discouraged in favor of ethical, white hat SEO methods that adhere to search engine policies and focus on long-term success.

name: WHITE HAT SEO
description: White hat SEO refers to search engine optimization tactics that are approved by search engines and focus on improving website quality and relevance. [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: SPAM
description: In the context of search engine optimization (SEO) and digital marketing, SPAM is a term coined by Sullivan to denote strategies that contravene Google's terms of service. These practices typically involve the creation of manipulative or irrelevant content, which is designed to artificially boost search engine rankings. Sullivan posits that such rule-breaking SEO tactics should not be conflated with legitimate SEO methods but should be categorized as SPAM, as they are detrimental to the integrity and functionality of search engines. This perspective was highlighted in an article by The Verge on November 1, 2023, where the nuances of SPAM and its impact on search engine algorithms were discussed. Essentially, SPAM is characterized by activities that search engines actively discourage and penalize, aiming to maintain a fair and high-quality search experience for users.

name: CUTTS
description: Cutts, a former Google employee, claims that during his time at the company, search quality always came before financial goals. However, he believes that the public underestimates how Google shapes what they see, likening search engines to newspaper-like entities making editorial decisions. He also suggests that Google doesn't want the public to think too hard about how search works because it could encourage regulators and make people realize the significant financial value involved [The Verge, 2023-11-01]

name: THE PEOPLE WHO RUINED THE INTERNET
description: "The people who ruined the internet" is an article published by The Verge on 2023-11-01, discussing the negative impacts of certain internet practices, including SEO

name: U.S. SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (SEC)
description: The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), a government regulatory body, has taken significant actions in the aftermath of the FTX collapse. In response to the financial scandal that led to the downfall of the major cryptocurrency exchange, the SEC has imposed civil penalties on key figures associated with FTX and its related entities. These penalties extend to Gary Wang and Caroline Ellison, who played pivotal roles within the organization, as well as the mastermind behind the collapse, Sam Bankman-Fried, and his companies, FTX and Alameda Research. The SEC's actions are part of a broader effort to enforce securities laws and protect investors in the volatile and complex world of digital assets.

This includes Gary Wang and Caroline Ellison, as well as Sam Bankman-Fried, the founder of FTX, and his companies, FTX and Alameda Research. These penalties are part of the CFTC's efforts to enforce laws and regulations in the realm of commodity trading and futures markets, ensuring fair practices and protecting investors from fraudulent activities. The actions taken by the CFTC highlight the agency's role in overseeing and regulating the complex world of financial derivatives, particularly in the context of the rapidly evolving cryptocurrency sector. [TechCrunch, 2023-10-01]
