name: DEFT
description: DEFT, a startup co-founded by Alex Gunnarson and Zach Hudson in 2019, is revolutionizing the e-commerce search experience by constructing a robust search engine that prioritizes user-centric interactions and purchasing solutions. The company, which has been garnering attention and praise from investors for its product enhancements and AI-driven search capabilities, recently secured $1.8 million in seed funding from a consortium of venture capital firms including Hustle Fund, Frontier VC, Vitalize, Long Ecommerce Ventures, 43 Ventures, and angel investors. DEFT is set to reach 50,000 monthly active users by the end of the year, with tens of thousands of searches being conducted weekly. The startup is currently concentrating on optimizing search results for furniture and home decor, utilizing its proprietary scraping technology to compile a comprehensive database of products. To further enhance user experience, DEFT is exploring two paid tiers that offer advanced search customization and a personal shopping service, all while maintaining an ad-free environment and generating revenue through affiliate commissions and subscriptions.

name: JORDAN POYER
description: Jordan Poyer, a versatile and accomplished safety for the Buffalo Bills in the NFL, has been with the team for six seasons, during which he has achieved notable milestones such as 500 or more tackles, 20 or more interceptions, and 10 or more sacks. He is not only a Bills captain but also an Ed Block Courage Award winner, a Pro Bowl safety, and an All-Pro. Despite his successful career and loving family, Poyer experienced a sense of unhappiness and anxiety, leading him to seek therapy and eventually try ayahuasca. This transformative experience, which he first discovered in 2023, has profoundly impacted his life, relationships, and perspective on success and failure. It helped him let go of resentment towards his biological father, Louis Dunbar, and gain a deeper understanding of himself. Poyer is considering a career in football commentary after retirement and is fascinated by the stars, believing in epistemic humility and the idea that knowledge is limited and filtered by personal experiences. He even heard a handpan for the first time in Costa Rica, which he now plays frequently, creating music that the old Jordan Poyer never could have. In March, he plans to return to Resonance for another ayahuasca retreat and is working on a documentary about his experiences with the substance. Despite being the second-leading tackler on his team, Poyer feels he hasn't made as many big plays as he would like, but his purpose remains clear: to be a bright light for everyone he touches and connects with.

name: AYAHUASCA
description: Ayahuasca, a psychedelic drug derived from the leaves of the Psychotria viridis shrub and the stalks of the Banisteriopsis caapi vine, has a rich history dating back over a thousand years as a central component in traditional Amazonian shamanic practices and ceremonies. This psychoactive brew is known for inducing a dreamlike state, altered consciousness, mystical experiences, and euphoria, serving as a tool for spiritual and healing purposes among indigenous tribes. Jordan Poyer, an individual whose life has been significantly transformed by Ayahuasca, credits this substance for providing him with a new perspective on life, football, and his relationships, particularly aiding him in addressing his ego and self-understanding. As a result of these profound experiences, Poyer has become more appreciative of his family and is embarking on a journey to explore the mysteries of his existence further, planning to work on a documentary about Ayahuasca and its impact on his life and approach to alcohol.

name: POYER
description: Poyer, a former NFL player known for his consensus All-American college career and steady progress in his early professional years, despite grappling with alcoholism, has experienced a significant transformation in his life. His drinking spiraled out of control, leading to quick six-pack binges of IPAs in mere minutes, and frequent blackouts that put a strain on his marriage to Rachel Bush, an Instagram model. Their relationship, however, was characterized by a strong, almost magnetic connection, which helped them through the tough times. After the birth of their daughter, Aliyah, Poyer signed with the Buffalo Bills, relocating to Buffalo. It was here that he sought help, attending Alcoholics Anonymous meetings, and successfully overcame his drinking problem. Despite achieving a stellar career and having a loving family, Poyer felt a void in his life as recently as last year. In pursuit of personal growth, he took an unconventional step, intrigued by the spiritual and healing properties of ayahuasca, which he learned about through social media and podcasts. Instead of a traditional guys trip, Poyer embarked on a journey to explore this substance, marking a new chapter in his quest for fulfillment and self-discovery.

description: Alcoholics Anonymous is an organization that Poyer went to for help with his alcoholism. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: PSYCHOTHERAPIST
description: In 2018, Jordan Poyer saw a therapist for anxiety once a week, but found the experience unfulfilling. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: RESONANCE
description: Resonance, a retreat center nestled on a hilltop in Costa Rica, offers a breathtaking view of the Pacific coast and the Monteverde cloud forest. Known for hosting unique and transformative retreats, Resonance has become a destination for individuals seeking to experience ayahuasca, a traditional South American brew used for spiritual and medicinal purposes. Jordan Poyer, a notable individual, discovered Resonance as the perfect location for his "guys trip" to partake in ayahuasca ceremonies. Impressed by his initial experience, Poyer plans to return to Resonance in March for another retreat, further emphasizing the center's reputation as a hub for ayahuasca-related activities. As an organization, Resonance is dedicated to providing a safe and supportive environment for participants to explore their inner selves and connect with nature.

name: COSTA RICA
description: Costa Rica is the location of Resonance, a retreat center where Poyer went to experience ayahuasca. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: MONTEVERDE
description: Monteverde is a cloud forest in Costa Rica that is part of the landscape where Resonance, the retreat center Poyer visited, is situated. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: SHAMAN
description: A shaman is a person who presented each participant, including Poyer, with a cup of ayahuasca brew during the ceremony. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: LES FRAZIER
description: Les Frazier is a former defensive coordinator for the Buffalo Bills and now an analyst for NFL Network. He praised Jordan Poyer for enabling his defense to be the best it can by lifting others through versatility, sacrifice, toughness, and communication. [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: LOUIS DUNBAR
description: Louis Dunbar is Jordan Poyer's biological father. He has done multiple stints in prison for violent crimes. He called Jordan for the first time when he was 12 and revealed he was his father. Jordan has not seen him since [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: EGO
description: Ego is a powerful force in professional athletes. It helps them ascend and often hastens their downfalls. Jordan Poyer believes his responses to successes and failures in previous seasons were too ego-driven [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: CRYSTAL BOWLS
description: Crystal bowls are musical instruments made of quartz crystal. Jordan Poyer, Taylor Rapp, and Will Greenberg play crystal bowls at Bills headquarters on Fridays this season. The different tones can enhance chakras within a person and help them heal [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: TAYLOR RAPP
description: Taylor Rapp is a fellow safety on the Buffalo Bills team. He plays crystal bowls with Jordan Poyer and Will Greenberg at Bills headquarters on Fridays this season [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: WILL GREENBERG
description: Will Greenberg is an assistant strength coach for the Buffalo Bills. He plays crystal bowls with Jordan Poyer and Taylor Rapp at Bills headquarters on Fridays this season [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: RACHEL POYER
description: Rachel Poyer is Jordan Poyer's wife. She has no interest in taking ayahuasca but is grateful her husband discovered it [The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: THE BILLS
description: The Bills is the football team Jordan Poyer plays for, and they have an out in his contract after this season. [Source: The New York Times, 2023-12-15]

name: HANDPAN
description: A handpan is a steel musical instrument that generates sound through vibrations. Sound healers and meditators often play the handpan. Jordan Poyer heard one for the first time in Costa Rica and was drawn to it, now he plays it frequently. [Source: The New York Times, 2023-12-15]
